('aftTribalBond',	'ancEwok',	'Tribal Bond',	'Ewoks fight better as a pack. When you use the Aid action to help an ally’s Attack Roll or Skill Check, and you roll a Critical Failure, you get a Failure instead (you don''t penalize them). If you roll a Success, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus (instead of +1).',	NULL,	'Ewoks fight better as a pack.',	'0',	1,	'Ewok, Auditory, Emotion',	NULL),
('aftDeadfallExpert',	'ancEwok',	'Deadfall Expert',	'You are a master of gravity-based warfare. You become trained in Crafting and gain the Snare Crafting feat. You can craft simple snares (like log traps or tripwires) using raw natural materials (wood/vines) at no cost, though these "free" snares only last for 24 hours.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaSnareCrafting", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}]}}',	'You are a master of gravity-based warfare.',	'0',	5,	'Ewok',	NULL),
('aftTheWolfsHour',	'ancShistavanen',	'The Wolf''s Hour',	'You refuse to die until the hunt is finished. You are not knocked unconscious. Instead, you remain conscious with 0 Hit Points and gain the Wounded 1 condition (or increase your Wounded value by 1). For 1 minute, you cannot fall unconscious due to hit point loss, though taking damage still increases your Dying value. If you are still at 0 Hit Points when the minute ends, you fall unconscious and start dying as normal. While in this state, you gain a +10-foot status bonus to Speed and a +2 status bonus to attack rolls.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">The Wolf''s Hour</h3>
