  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are reduced to 0 Hit Points but not immediately killed.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You refuse to die until the hunt is finished. You are not knocked unconscious. Instead, you remain conscious with 0 Hit Points and gain the Wounded 1 condition (or increase your Wounded value by 1). For 1 minute, you cannot fall unconscious due to hit point loss, though taking damage still increases your Dying value. If you are still at 0 Hit Points when the minute ends, you fall unconscious and start dying as normal. While in this state, you gain a +10-foot status bonus to Speed and a +2 status bonus to attack rolls."
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actThe WolfsHour", "name": "The Wolf''s Hour", "traits": "Shistavanen", "trigger": "You are reduced to 0 Hit Points but not immediately killed.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You refuse to die until the hunt is finished. You are not knocked unconscious. Instead, you remain conscious with 0 Hit Points and gain the Wounded 1 condition (or increase your Wounded value by 1). For 1 minute, you cannot fall unconscious due to hit point loss, though taking damage still increases your Dying value. If you are still at 0 Hit Points when the minute ends, you fall unconscious and start dying as normal. While in this state, you gain a +10-foot status bonus to Speed and a +2 status bonus to attack rolls.\""}]}}',	'You refuse to die until the hunt is finished.',	'0',	17,	'Shistavanen',	NULL),
('aftCuriousScavenger',	'ancEwok',	'Curious Scavenger',	'You have an eye for shiny things. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Perception checks to Search for hidden objects. Additionally, you can use the Crafting skill to Recall Knowledge about technology, even if you are untrained, by poking, smelling, and tasting it (though you might not understand the theory, you understand the function).',	'{"perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Curious Scavenger", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Search for hidden objects.", "target": "all"}]}}',	'You have an eye for shiny things..',	'0',	1,	'Ewok',	NULL),
('aftTechBreaker',	'ancEwok',	'Tech-Breaker',	'You know that the "magic" of the sky-people is fragile. When you attack an object with the Tech trait (like a droid, a vehicle, or a generator) or a creature with the Construct trait, you ignore the first 5 points of Hardness. If you score a Critical Hit against such a target, it must succeed at a Fortitude save (DC = your Class DC) or become Broken.',	NULL,	'You know that the "magic" of the sky-people is fragile.',	'0',	5,	'Ewok',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftTreeDweller',	'ancEwok',	'Tree-Dweller',	'You were born in the canopy. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Athletics checks to Climb. If you roll a Success on a Climb check, you get a Critical Success instead. You are not off-guard while climbing.',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Tree-Dweller", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Climb.", "target": "sklAthletics"}]}}',	'You were born in the canopy.',	'0',	1,	'Ewok',	NULL),
('aftGunganWeaponFamiliarity',	'ancGungan',	'Gungan Weapon Familiarity',	'You are trained in the weapons of the Otoh Gunga Guard. You have familiarity with weapons with the Gungan trait including the cesta and electropole. For the purpose of proficiency, you treat any of these that are martial weapons as simple weapons and any that are advanced weapons as martial weapons.

At 5th level, whenever you get a critical hit with one of these weapons, you get its critical specialization effect.',	'{"attack": [{"weapon_familiarity": ["Gungan"]}]}',	'You are trained in the weapons of the Otoh Gunga Guard.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftPhotographicMemory',	'ancDuros',	'Photographic Memory',	'You can vividly recall anything you have seen or read in the last week. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Recall Knowledge checks if you have access to a datapad or library to cross-reference your memory.',	NULL,	'You can vividly recall anything you have seen or read in the last week.',	'0',	5,	'Duros',	NULL),
('aftGamorreanWeaponFamiliarity',	'ancGamorrean',	'Gamorrean Weapon Familiarity',	'You were trained in the clan traditions of the arg’garok (great axe). You have familiarity with weapons with the Gamorrean trait including the Arg''garok and Gamorrean Cleaver. For the purpose of proficiency, you treat any of these that are martial weapons as simple weapons and any that are advanced weapons as martial weapons.

At 5th level, whenever you get a critical hit with one of these weapons, you get its critical specialization effect.',	'{"attack": [{"weapon_familiarity": ["Gamorrean"]}]}',	'You were trained in the clan traditions of the arg’garok (great axe).',	'0',	1,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftGuerrillaMaster',	'ancEwok',	'Guerrilla Master',	'You strike from nowhere and vanish. If you start your turn Hidden or Undetected, make a Strike. If the attack hits, you remain Hidden after the attack (you do not become Observed). You can continue to make attacks; you only become Observed if you move or miss an attack.',	'{"feat": [{"id": "aftForestCamouflage", "type": "ancestry"}]}',	'You strike from nowhere and vanish.',	'0',	17,	'Ewok',	NULL),
('aftThickHide',	'ancGamorrean',	'Thick Hide',	'Your skin is green, leathery, and tough as armor. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC while unarmored. If you are wearing Light or Medium armor, you instead reduce the Check Penalty of that armor by 1.',	'{"armor": [{"grant": [{"id": "natToughHide", "name": "Gamorrean Hide", "ac_bonus": 1, "category": "Unarmored"}]}], "defense": [{"medium": {"check_penalty_mod": 1}}, {"light": {"check_penalty_mod": 1}}]}',	'Your skin is green, leathery, and tough as armor.',	'0',	1,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftPigHeaded',	'ancGamorrean',	'Pig-Headed',	'Gamorreans are notoriously difficult to influence once they have made up their minds. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Will saves against Mental effects. If an effect would force you to act against your orders or betray your allies (like Charm or Command), the bonus increases to +2.',	NULL,	'Gamorreans are notoriously difficult to influence once they have made up their minds.',	'0',	1,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftMuscularMenace',	'ancGamorrean',	'Muscular Menace',	'You don''t need words to be scary; you just need to flex. You can use Strength instead of Charisma for Intimidation checks to Demoralize or Coerce. You gain the Intimidating Glare skill feat.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaIntimidatingGlare", "type": "skill"}]}}',	'You don''t need words to be scary; you just need to flex.',	'0',	1,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftMercenarysInstinct',	'ancGamorrean',	'Mercenary''s Instinct',	'You have spent your life guarding Hutt palaces and crime lords. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Perception checks to Sense Motive or to detect Hidden creatures, provided you are currently standing guard at a specific post or doorway.',	NULL,	'You have spent your life guarding Hutt palaces and crime lords.',	'0',	1,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftEndorsRevenge',	'ancEwok',	'Endor’s Revenge',	'You are a whirlwind of destruction against technology. Your attacks ignore ALL Hardness of objects with the Tech trait. When you critically hit a creature wearing technological armor or a droid, the target is Slowed 1 (as systems fail) and takes ongoing Bleed damage (or electricity damage for droids) equal to 1d10.',	NULL,	'You are a whirlwind of destruction against technology.',	'0',	17,	'Ewok',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftTechBreaker", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftPersistentConfidence',	'ancHuman',	'Persistent Confidence',	'You always believe in yourself. You can use Confident Actualization once per hour, rather than once per day.',	NULL,	'You always believe in yourself.',	'0',	17,	'Human',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaConfidentActualization", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftSpiritOfTheTrees',	'ancEwok',	'Spirit of the Trees',	'The forest protects its own.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
