  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The forest protects its own. Reroll the saving throw with a +2 circumstance bonus. You must use the second result.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSpiritOfTheTrees", "name": "Spirit of the Trees", "traits": "Ewok, Fortune", "trigger": "You fail a Reflex saving throw or any saving throw against a Tech effect.", "frequency": "Once per hour.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "The forest protects its own. Reroll the saving throw with a +2 circumstance bonus. You must use the second result."}]}}',	'The forest protects its own.',	'0',	13,	'Ewok, Fortune',	NULL),
('aftTongueLash',	'ancGungan',	'Tongue Lash',	'You use your tongue to trip or harass foes. You can attempt to Disarm or Trip a target within 10 feet. You use your Athletics modifier for this check. On a Critical Failure, you do not fall prone or drop your weapon; instead, you bite your tongue and are Dazzled for 1 round.',	NULL,	'You use your tongue to trip or harass foes.',	'0',	5,	'Gungan',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftPrehensileTongue", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftPatientMarksman',	'ancTusken',	'Patient Marksman',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Patient Marksman</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tusken Raider</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a loaded ranged weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You stabilize your breathing and take the time to perfectly line up your shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to the attack roll, and you ignore the target''s concealed condition.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPatientMarksman", "name": "Patient Marksman", "traits": "Tusken Raider", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You stabilize your breathing and take the time to perfectly line up your shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to the attack roll, and you ignore the target''s concealed condition.", "requirements": "You are wielding a loaded ranged weapon."}]}}',	'You stabilize your breathing and take the time to perfectly line up your shot. Make a ranged weapon Strike.',	'0',	9,	'Tusken Raider',	NULL),
('aftHydroDynamic',	'ancGungan',	'Hydro-Dynamic',	'You were born in the underwater cities. You gain a Swim Speed of 25 feet. You can hold your breath for 10 minutes before risking drowning. While in water, you do not take the usual penalties for using bludgeoning or slashing melee weapons.',	NULL,	'You were born in the underwater cities.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftPrehensileTongue',	'ancGungan',	'Prehensile Tongue',	'Your long, sticky tongue is a third hand. You can use an Interact action to pick up a light object (Bulk L) within 10 feet and bring it to your hand. You cannot use your tongue to wield weapons, activate items, or perform fine manipulation (like typing), but you can use it to steal unprotected objects (like a keycard on a belt) using Thievery.',	NULL,	'Your long, sticky tongue is a third hand.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftEnergyShieldExpert',	'ancGungan',	'Energy Shield Expert',	'You are trained in the use of the personal energy buckler (cessa). When you Raise a Shield, if that shield has the Tech trait or is made of energy, you gain resistance 5 to Energy damage (Fire, Cold, Electricity, Sonic, Plasma) until the start of your next turn.',	NULL,	'You are trained in the use of the personal energy buckler (cessa).',	'0',	5,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftClumsyDodge',	'ancGungan',	'Clumsy Dodge',	'Your movements are flailing and unpredictable, confusing targeting computers. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against reactions.',	NULL,	'Your movements are flailing and unpredictable, confusing targeting computers.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftMarshWader',	'ancGungan',	'Marsh-Wader',	'You are used to moving through thick swamp muck. You ignore Difficult Terrain caused by water, mud, bog, or deep vegetation.',	NULL,	'You are used to moving through thick swamp muck.',	'0',	5,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftRubberBones',	'ancGungan',	'Rubber Bones',	'Your skeleton is made of flexible cartilage, not hard bone. You gain resistance to Falling Damage equal to your Level. Additionally, you can Squeeze through tight spaces as if you were one size smaller, and you do not take the -5 penalty to Speed while Squeezing.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Falling", "amount": "{level}", "source": "Rubber Bones (Ancestry Feat)"}]}}',	'Your skeleton is made of flexible cartilage, not hard bone.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan',	NULL),
('aftTooStupidToDie',	'ancGamorrean',	'Too Stupid to Die',	'You simply don''t register that you are dead yet.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Too Stupid to Die</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 17</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Gamorrean</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You would be reduced to 0 Hit Points.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You simply don''t register that you are dead yet. You remain at 1 Hit Point. You immediately gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level + your Constitution modifier. You are Confused (berserk) for 1 round, attacking the nearest creature (friend or foe), after which you regain your senses.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTooStupidToDie", "name": "Too Stupid to Die", "traits": "Gamorrean", "trigger": "You would be reduced to 0 Hit Points.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You simply don''t register that you are dead yet. You remain at 1 Hit Point. You immediately gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level + your Constitution modifier. You are Confused (berserk) for 1 round, attacking the nearest creature (friend or foe), after which you regain your senses."}]}}',	'You simply don''t register that you are dead yet.',	'0',	17,	'Gamorrean',	NULL),
('aftBombadBravado',	'ancGungan',	'"Bombad" Bravado',	'You are either incredibly brave or too foolish to know when to run. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Will saves against Fear. If you roll a Success on a save against Fear, you get a Critical Success instead.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "\"Bombad\" Bravado", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against Fear.", "target": "will"}]}]}',	'You are either incredibly brave or too foolish to know when to run.',	'0',	1,	'Gungan, Emotion, Mental',	NULL),
('aftWideAngleVision',	'ancIthorian',	'Wide-Angle Vision',	'Your eyes are located on the extreme sides of your T-shaped head. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Perception checks to Seek or Sense Motive.',	NULL,	'Your eyes are located on the extreme sides of your T-shaped head.',	'0',	1,	'Ithorian',	NULL),
('aftFierceStoryteller',	'ancTusken',	'Fierce Storyteller',	'During a 10-minute rest, you can recount the legendary battles of your ancestors to invigorate your allies. Up to five allies who can hear you (they do not need to understand your language, as the cadence and tone convey the meaning) gain temporary Hit Points equal to your level. These temporary Hit Points last for 1 hour or until depleted.',	NULL,	'During a 10-minute rest, you can recount the legendary battles of your ancestors to invigorate your allies.',	'0',	9,	'Tusken Raider, Auditory, Emotion, Mental',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftOralHistorian", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftIronWillOfIthor',	'ancIthorian',	'Iron Will of Ithor',	'Your devotion to peace is a fortress. You gain Resolve (Success on Will saves becomes Critical Success). If your class already grants Resolve (or you gain it later), you instead gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Will saves against Mental effects.',	NULL,	'Your devotion to peace is a fortress.',	'0',	9,	'Ithorian',	NULL),
('aftMotherJunglesDisciple',	'ancIthorian',	'Mother Jungle’s Disciple',	'You have studied the agricultural and spiritual traditions of Ithor. You become trained in Nature and Gardening Lore. If you were already trained in Nature, you become trained in a skill of your choice. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Nature checks to identify plants or cure natural poisons.',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklLoreGardening", "rank": "Trained"}]}}',	'You have studied the agricultural and spiritual traditions of Ithor.',	'0',	1,	'Ithorian',	NULL),
('aftStereoProjection',	'ancIthorian',	'Stereo Projection',	'With two mouths and four throats, you can produce sounds that are impossible for other species to replicate or ignore. You are trained in the Performance skill and gain the Virtuosic Performer skill feat (Singing or Oratory). Additionally, you can throw your voice to originate from any point within 30 feet of you.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaVirtuosicPerformer", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}]}}',	'With two mouths and four throats, you can produce sounds that are impossible for other species to replicate or ignore.',	'0',	1,	'Ithorian, Auditory',	NULL),
('aftGentleGiant',	'ancIthorian',	'Gentle Giant',	'You are reluctant to kill, but skilled at stopping violence. You do not take the standard -2 penalty when making Nonlethal Attacks with weapons that do not have the Nonlethal trait. When you make a Nonlethal attack, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to damage.',	NULL,	'You are reluctant to kill, but skilled at stopping violence.',	'0',	1,	'Ithorian',	NULL),
('aftShockingConduction',	'ancGungan',	'Shocking Conduction',	'You know how to modulate the power output of electropoles and energy weapons to cause cascading system failures.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shocking Conduction</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
