  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Mon Calamari</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Auditory</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Visual</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per round.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You point out a specific enemy within 60 feet. Until the start of your next turn, the first time any ally hits that enemy with a Strike, the ally deals additional 1d6 Precision damage.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDesignateTarget", "name": "Designate Target", "traits": "Mon Calamari, Auditory, Visual", "frequency": "Once per round.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You point out a specific enemy within 60 feet. Until the start of your next turn, the first time any ally hits that enemy with a Strike, the ally deals additional 1d6 Precision damage."}]}}',	'You coordinate fire to exploit enemy weaknesses.',	'0',	9,	'Mon Calamari, Auditory, Visual',	'[{"skill": [{"id": ["sklDiplomacy", "sklIntimidation"], "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftMatterDecomposition',	'ancUgnaught',	'Matter Decomposition',	'Your attacks dismantle matter at a molecular level. Your melee Strikes ignore all Hardness of objects and vehicles. When you hit a living creature wearing armor (or with natural armor), you apply a -2 status penalty to their AC until the start of your next turn (shredding their protection).',	NULL,	'Your attacks dismantle matter at a molecular level.',	'0',	17,	'Ugnaught',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftDroidDisassembler", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftNaturalAmbition',	'ancHuman',	'Natural Ambition',	'You were raised to be ambitious and always reach for the stars, leading you to progress quickly in your chosen field. You gain a 1st-level class feat for your class. You must meet the prerequisites, but you can select the feat later in the character creation process in order to determine which prerequisites you meet.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''natural_ambition_feat'')", "type": "class"}]}, "inputs": {"name": "natural_ambition_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Class Feat", "filter": {"level": 1}}}',	'You were raised to be ambitious and always reach for the stars, leading you to progress quickly in your chosen field.',	'0',	1,	'Human',	NULL),
('aftUnionSteward',	'ancUgnaught',	'Union Steward',	'You organize your party like a work crew, ensuring maximum efficiency. When you use the Aid action to help an ally''s Skill Check, you grant a +2 circumstance bonus on a Success (instead of +1) and a +4 bonus on a Critical Success (instead of +3).',	NULL,	'You organize your party like a work crew, ensuring maximum efficiency.',	'0',	9,	'Ugnaught',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftGruffNegotiator", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftUnstoppableLabor',	'ancUgnaught',	'Unstoppable Labor',	'The job isn''t done until the job is done. You ignore Difficult Terrain caused by rubble, debris, or machinery. Additionally, if you start your turn Slowed, you reduce the Slowed value by 1 immediately (allowing you to act normally if you were Slowed 1).',	NULL,	'The job isn''t done until the job is done.',	'0',	13,	'Ugnaught',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftIndenturedStamina", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftEarnedRetirement',	'ancUgnaught',	'Earned Retirement',	'You have worked too hard to die before spending your credits.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Earned Retirement</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 17</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Ugnaught</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You would be reduced to 0 Hit Points but not instantly killed.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You remain at 1 Hit Point. You gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level x 2. You immediately take a Step action.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actEarnedRetirement", "name": "Earned Retirement", "traits": "Ugnaught, Fortune", "trigger": "You would be reduced to 0 Hit Points but not instantly killed.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You remain at 1 Hit Point. You gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level x 2. You immediately take a Step action."}]}}',	'You have worked too hard to die before spending your credits.',	'0',	17,	'Ugnaught, Fortune',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftIndenturedStamina", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftIntimidatingRoar',	'ancWookiee',	'Intimidating Roar',	'You can project a vocalization that taps into the primal fear of lesser species. You are trained in Intimidation and gain the Intimidating Glare skill feat, but you do so by roaring rather than staring. When you Demoralize a creature, you do not take a penalty if the creature does not understand your language.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaIntimidatingGlare", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}]}}',	'You can project a vocalization that taps into the primal fear of lesser species.',	'0',	1,	'Wookiee, Auditory, Emotion',	NULL),
('aftShatteringStrike',	'ancSavrip',	'Shattering Strike',	'Your fists hit with the force of a starship''s breaching pod. Your unarmed melee attacks ignore up to 5 Hardness of objects. Furthermore, when you critically hit a creature wearing physical armor, you dent or buckle their plating, applying a -1 circumstance penalty to their AC until the armor is Repaired.',	NULL,	'Your fists hit with the force of a starship''s breaching pod.',	'0',	13,	'Mantellian Savrip',	NULL),
('aftHonorBound',	'ancWookiee',	'Honor Bound',	'You take the concept of the Life Debt seriously; protecting your chosen charge gives you strength. During your daily preparations, you can designate one ally as your "Charge." When you are adjacent to your Charge, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Will saves. If your Charge is reduced to 0 HP, you gain Temporary HP equal to your Level.',	NULL,	'You take the concept of the Life Debt seriously; protecting your chosen charge gives you strength.',	'0',	1,	'Wookiee, Emotion',	NULL),
('aftHardHat',	'ancUgnaught',	'Hard Hat',	'Your skull is thick, and you likely wear protective headgear. You gain resistance to Critical Hits. When an enemy scores a Critical Hit against you with a physical weapon, the extra damage from the critical (the amount doubled) is reduced by an amount equal to your level.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Critical Hits (Physical)", "amount": "{level}", "source": "Hard Hat (Ancestry Feat)"}]}}',	'Your skull is thick, and you likely wear protective headgear.',	'0',	9,	'Ugnaught',	NULL),
('aftTenaciousVitality',	'ancWookiee',	'Tenacious Vitality',	'It is incredibly difficult to put a Wookiee down for good. You gain the Diehard general feat. Additionally, when you roll a Success on a Recovery Check (to stabilize while dying), you get a Critical Success instead (waking up with 1 HP).',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaDiehard", "type": "general"}]}}',	'It is incredibly difficult to put a Wookiee down for good.',	'0',	13,	'Wookiee',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftShadowlandsSurvivor", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftBowcasterBallistics',	'ancWookiee',	'Bowcaster Ballistics',	'You know how to brace the heavy magnetic accelerator of a bowcaster to maximize impact. When you hit a target with a Bowcaster within 30 feet, you deal an additional +2 damage per die. On a Critical Hit, the target is pushed back 5 feet (in addition to normal critical effects).',	NULL,	'You know how to brace the heavy magnetic accelerator of a bowcaster to maximize impact.',	'0',	5,	'Wookiee',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftWookieeWeaponFamiliarity", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftCrushingGrip',	'ancWookiee',	'Crushing Grip',	'Your hand strength allows you to crush durasteel pipe like paper. You gain the Titan Wrestler skill feat. When you successfully Grapple a creature, you deal Bludgeoning damage equal to your Strength modifier to them automatically.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaTitanWrestler", "type": "skill"}]}}',	'Your hand strength allows you to crush durasteel pipe like paper.',	'0',	5,	'Wookiee',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('ancLetTheWookieeWin',	'ancWookiee',	'"Let the Wookiee Win"',	'People generally find it wiser to agree with you than to risk having their arms pulled out of their sockets. You can use Intimidation instead of Diplomacy to Make an Impression. If you succeed, the target is not Frightened; they are simply agreeable because they wish to avoid conflict. If you Critical Fail, they realize you are bluffing or become hostile.',	NULL,	'People generally find it wiser to agree with you than to risk having their arms pulled out of their sockets.',	'0',	5,	'Wookiee, Mental',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftWoodSmithsIngenuity',	'ancWookiee',	'Wood-Smith''s Ingenuity',	'You practice the ancient Kashyyyk art of fusing technology with nature (wood-tech). You can use Nature instead of Crafting to Repair items, provided you have access to natural materials (wood, sap, resin). When you craft or repair a wooden item (like a Bowcaster stock or Ryyk blade handle), the item gains +5 Hardness and +5 HP.',	NULL,	'You practice the ancient Kashyyyk art of fusing technology with nature (wood-tech).',	'0',	9,	'Wookiee',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftWallBreaker',	'ancWookiee',	'Wall-Breaker',	'Barriers are just things you haven''t smashed yet. Your melee Strikes deal double damage to objects and structures. When you attempt to Force Open a door or container, you treat a Success as a Critical Success.',	NULL,	'Barriers are just things you haven''t smashed yet.',	'0',	13,	'Wookiee',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftCrushingGrip", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftColossusOfOrdMantell',	'ancSavrip',	'Colossus of Ord Mantell',	'Your hide has scarred and thickened over countless battles, rendering you a walking juggernaut. You gain resistance to physical damage (bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing) equal to half your level. This resistance does not apply to damage dealt by weapons with the Force Power trait or environmental hazards like extreme heat.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Bludgeoning", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Colossus of Ord Mantell (Ancestry Feat)"}, {"type": "Piercing", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Colossus of Ord Mantell (Ancestry Feat)"}, {"type": "Slashing", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Colossus of Ord Mantell (Ancestry Feat)"}]}}',	'Your hide has scarred and thickened over countless battles, rendering you a walking juggernaut.',	'0',	17,	'Mantellian Savrip',	NULL),
('aftWookieeWarCry',	'ancWookiee',	'Wookiee War-Cry',	'Your roar is no longer just scary; it is a physical force of morale. When you use Defiant Roar, in addition to Frightening enemies, all Allies within 30 feet gain Temporary HP equal to your Level + your Charisma modifier. These temporary HP last for 1 minute.',	NULL,	'Your roar is no longer just scary; it is a physical force of morale.',	'0',	17,	'Wookiee, Auditory, Emotion, Mental',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftDefiantRoar", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftCrownOfHorns',	'ancZabrak',	'Crown of Horns',	'Your vestigial cranial horns are hardened and sharp, allowing you to use your head as a weapon in a clinch. You gain a Horn unarmed attack that deals 1d6 Piercing damage. It has the Finesse and Unarmed traits. Because you are using your head, you can make this attack even if your hands are full or you are Bound',	'{"weapon": [{"id": "natZabrakHorns", "bulk": null, "name": "Zabrak Horns", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Finesse", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d6", "damagetype": "P", "description": "Your vestigial cranial horns are hardened and sharp, allowing you to use your head as a weapon in a clinch. You gain a Horn unarmed attack that deals 1d6 Piercing damage. It has the Finesse and Unarmed traits. Because you are using your head, you can make this attack even if your hands are full or you are Bound"}]}',	'Your vestigial cranial horns are hardened and sharp, allowing you to use your head as a weapon in a clinch.',	'0',	1,	'Zabrak',	NULL),
('aftPainToPower',	'ancZabrak',	'Pain to Power',	'You channel physical pain into immediate aggression.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Pain to Power</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 5</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Zabrak</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Emotion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You take damage from a hostile source.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Attack Rolls until the end of your next turn. If the damage you took was a Critical Hit, this bonus increases to +2.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPainToPower", "name": "Pain to Power", "traits": "Zabrak, Emotion, Mental", "trigger": "You take damage from a hostile source.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Attack Rolls until the end of your next turn. If the damage you took was a Critical Hit, this bonus increases to +2."}]}}',	'You channel physical pain into immediate aggression.',	'0',	5,	'Zabrak, Emotion, Mental',	NULL),
('aftIronWillOfIridonia',	'ancZabrak',	'Iron Will of Iridonia',	'Your mind is as hard as the iron of your homeworld. You gain the Resolve class feature (Success on Will saves becomes Critical Success). If you already have Resolve (or a feature with the same effect), you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Will saves against Fear.',	'{"feature": ["cftResolve"]}',	'Your mind is as hard as the iron of your homeworld.',	'0',	5,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancStoicDetermination", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftTwoHeartedStamina',	'ancZabrak',	'Two-Hearted Stamina',	'Your binary cardiovascular system pumps oxygen more efficiently than most species, allowing you to exert yourself for longer. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Athletics checks to Swim, Climb, or Force Open doors. Additionally, you treat the Fatigued condition as one stage lower for the purpose of exploration activities (you can hustle longer before tiring).',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Two-Hearted Stamina", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Swim, Climb, or Force Open doors.", "target": "sklAthletics"}]}}',	'Your binary cardiovascular system pumps oxygen more efficiently than most species, allowing you to exert yourself for longer.',	'0',	1,	'Zabrak',	NULL),
('aftStoicDetermination',	'ancZabrak',	'Stoic Determination',	'Zabrak culture teaches that pain is merely a signal that can be ignored. When you fail a Will save against a Pain or Emotion effect, you can choose to take 1d4 Mental damage to reroll the save. You must use the second result.',	NULL,	'Zabrak culture teaches that pain is merely a signal that can be ignored.',	'0',	1,	'Zabrak, Mental',	NULL),
('aftRapidCoagulation',	'ancZabrak',	'Rapid Coagulation',	'Your blood clots almost instantly, and your second heart picks up the slack if the first is stressed. The DC of flat checks to remove Persistent Bleed Damage is reduced from 15 to 10 (or 10 to 5 if you received assistance).  Additionally, if you make a DC 16 flat check whenever you lose the Dying condition, your Wounded value doesn''t increase.',	NULL,	'Your blood clots almost instantly, and your second heart picks up the slack if the first is stressed.',	'0',	5,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancTwoHeartedStamina", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftIridonianSurvivor',	'ancZabrak',	'Iridonian Survivor',	'You were raised in the harsh, acidic winds of Iridonia (or a colony with similar conditions). You gain resistance to Acid damage equal to half your level (minimum 1). You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Survival checks.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Acid", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Iridonian Survivor (Ancestry Feat)"}]}}',	'You were raised in the harsh, acidic winds of Iridonia (or a colony with similar conditions).',	'0',	1,	'Zabrak',	NULL),
('aftTerrifyingVisage',	'ancZabrak',	'Terrifying Visage',	'You use your tattoos and horns to project a demonic aura.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Terrifying Visage</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 9</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Zabrak</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Visual</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Emotion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per minute.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Attempt an Intimidation check to Demoralize all enemies within 30 feet. You do not take a penalty for not sharing a language.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTerrifyingVisage", "name": "Terrifying Visage", "traits": "Zabrak, Visual, Emotion, Mental", "frequency": "Once per minute.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Attempt an Intimidation check to Demoralize all enemies within 30 feet. You do not take a penalty for not sharing a language."}]}}',	'You use your tattoos and horns to project a demonic aura.',	'0',	9,	'Zabrak, Visual, Emotion, Mental',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftBinaryOverdrive',	'ancZabrak',	'Binary Overdrive',	'Your cardiovascular system is redundant for a reason. When your body is pushed to its limit, your second heart begins to beat out of sync with the first, flooding your system with oxygen and adrenaline to ensure survival through violence. While you have fewer than half your maximum Hit Points, you gain a +10 foot status bonus to Speed and a +2 status bonus to damage rolls.',	NULL,	'Your cardiovascular system is redundant for a reason. When your body is pushed to its limit, your second heart begins to beat out of sync with the first, flooding your system with oxygen and adrenaline to ensure survival through violence.',	'0',	13,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancPainToPower", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftIndomitablePhysiology',	'ancZabrak',	'Indomitable Physiology',	'Your body purges toxins with terrifying efficiency. You are immune to Diseases. You gain a +4 circumstance bonus to Fortitude saves against Poisons.',	NULL,	'Your body purges toxins with terrifying efficiency.',	'0',	13,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancRapidCoagulation", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftBoomaBombardier',	'ancGungan',	'Booma Bombardier',	'You are an expert with energy balls (Boomas) and grenades. You can draw a Grenade or thrown weapon with the Splash trait as a free action, provided you immediately throw it. When you throw a grenade, the Splash radius increases by 5 feet.',	'{"attack": [{"group": [{"grenade": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}, {"trait": [{"Splash": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}',	'You are an expert with energy balls (Boomas) and grenades.',	'0',	5,	'Gungan',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "aftGunganWeaponFamiliarity", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftDisciplineOverPain',	'ancZabrak',	'Discipline Over Pain',	'You can force your body to function perfectly even when broken. You ignore the Enfeebled and Clumsy conditions if their value is 1. If their value is 2 or higher, you reduce the penalty by 1.',	NULL,	'You can force your body to function perfectly even when broken.',	'0',	9,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancStoicDetermination", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftCoreWorldEducation',	'ancHuman',	'Core World Education',	'You were raised on a planet like Coruscant, Corellia, or Alderaan, where high-level technology and bureaucracy are part of daily life. You become Trained in Computers and Bureaucracy Lore. You also gain the Experienced Professional skill feat.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaExperiencedProfessional", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklLoreBureaucracy", "rank": "Trained"}]}}',	'You were raised on a planet like Coruscant, Corellia, or Alderaan, where high-level technology and bureaucracy are part of daily life.',	'0',	1,	'Human',	NULL),
('aftWarlordOfIridonia',	'ancZabrak',	'Warlord of Iridonia',	'You are a master of the brutal martial culture of your people. You are permanently Quickened. You can only use the extra action to Strike or Step. Additionally, your Crown of Horns attack deals 1d10 damage and gains the Deadly d12 trait.',	'{"weapon": [{"id": "natZabrakHorns", "bulk": null, "name": "Zabrak Horns", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Agile, Deadly d12, Finesse", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d10", "damagetype": "P", "description": "Your vestigial cranial horns are hardened and sharp, allowing you to use your head as a weapon in a clinch. You gain a Horn unarmed attack that deals 1d6 Piercing damage. It has the Finesse and Unarmed traits. Because you are using your head, you can make this attack even if your hands are full or you are Bound<br><br>You have integrated your horns into your flowing combat forms. Your Horn attack gains the Agile trait. Additionally, when you critically hit with your horns, the target takes 1d4 persistent Bleed damage as the horns tear flesh.<br><br>Additionally, your Crown of Horns attack deals 1d10 damage and gains the Deadly d12 trait."}]}',	'You are a master of the brutal martial culture of your people.',	'0',	17,	'Zabrak',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "ancTerrifyingVisage", "type": "ancestry"}]}]'),
('aftMultitalented',	'ancHuman',	'Multitalented',	'You''ve learned to split your focus between multiple classes with ease. You gain a 2nd-level multiclass dedication feat (for more about multiclass archetypes, see Archetypes), even if you normally couldn''t take another dedication feat until you take more feats from your current archetype.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Dedication Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Multiclass"], "max_level": 2}}]}',	'You''ve learned to split your focus between multiple classes with ease.',	'0',	9,	'Human',	NULL),
('aftCircuitBreaker',	'ancAnzellan',	'Circuit Breaker',	'You know exactly where to stick a hydrospanner to cause the most problems. When you damage a creature with the Construct or Tech trait, or an object with the Tech trait, you ignore the first 5 points of Hardness or resistance.',	NULL,	'You know exactly where to stick a hydrospanner to cause the most problems.',	'0',	5,	'Anzellan',	'[{"skill": [{"id": ["sklComputers", "sklCrafting"], "rank": "Trained"}]}]'),
('aftTooStubbornToDie',	'ancHuman',	'Too Stubborn to Die',	'You return from the brink of death, hauling yourself back to consciousness through exhaustion and pain. 

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Too Stubborn to Die</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 17</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Human</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You would die.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You return from the brink of death, hauling yourself back to consciousness through exhaustion and pain. If you have the dying or unconscious conditions, you lose the dying and unconscious conditions. If you''re at 0 Hit Points, you have 1 Hit Point. Increase the value of your wounded and doomed conditions by 1. You can use this reaction while unconscious.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTooStubbornToDie", "name": "Too Stubborn to Die", "traits": "Human, Fortune", "trigger": "You would die.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You return from the brink of death, hauling yourself back to consciousness through exhaustion and pain. If you have the dying or unconscious conditions, you lose the dying and unconscious conditions. If you''re at 0 Hit Points, you have 1 Hit Point. Increase the value of your wounded and doomed conditions by 1. You can use this reaction while unconscious."}]}}',	'You return from the brink of death, hauling yourself back to consciousness through exhaustion and pain. ',	'0',	17,	'Human',	NULL),
('aftStubbornPersistence',	'ancHuman',	'Stubborn Persistence',	'Humans are renowned for their ability to persist through the most grueling of trials that would leave others ready to drop. When you would become fatigued, attempt a DC 17 flat check. On a success, you aren''t fatigued. If the fatigued condition has an underlying cause that you don''t address, such as lack of rest, you must attempt the check again at an interval determined by the GM until you fail the flat check or address the underlying cause.',	NULL,	'Humans are renowned for their ability to persist through the most grueling of trials that would leave others ready to drop.',	'0',	13,	'Human',	NULL),
('aftShadowlandsSurvivor',	'ancWookiee',	'Shadowlands Survivor',	'You have braved the lower levels of the Kashyyyk forests, where the flora is carnivorous and the fauna is huge. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Survival checks. You gain resistance to Poison damage equal to half your level (minimum 1).',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Poison", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Shadowlands Survivor (Ancestry Feat)"}]}}',	'You have braved the lower levels of the Kashyyyk forests, where the flora is carnivorous and the fauna is huge.',	'0',	1,	'Wookiee',	NULL),
('aftOneInAMillion',	'ancHuman',	'One in a Million',	'The probability of surviving this scenario is approximately 3,720 to 1. You like those odds.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">One in a Million</h3>
