    <span class="trait-tag">Focused</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>An enemy damages an ally within 15 feet of you.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You project a telekinetic cushion or physically intercept the blow. The damage the ally takes is reduced by 2 + your Level. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your next Attack roll against the triggering enemy before the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>

<h3 id="lightsaber-discipline">Lightsaber Discipline</h3>
<p>You are a student of the seven forms. In addition to the form feat granted by your Guardian Cause, any lightsaber you wield gains the <strong>Parry</strong> trait. (This allows you to spend an Action to gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC until the start of your next turn).</p>
<h3 id="guardian-cause">Guardian Cause</h3>
<p>You must dedicate your blade to a specific philosophy of protection. Choose a <strong>Guardian Cause</strong>. This cause grants you a passive benefit while <strong>Focused</strong> and the basic feat representing one of the seven lightsaber forms at 1st level.</p>
<h3 id="guardian-feats">Guardian Feats</h3>
<p>At 1st level and every even-numbered level, you gain a guardian class feat.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-skill-feats-span-span-level-2-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Skill Feats</span><span>Level 2</span></div></h3>
<p>At 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill feat.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-bravery-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Bravery</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>You face the impossible without flinching. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to Master. When you roll a success on a Will save against a Fear effect, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-jedi-weapon-expertise-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Jedi Weapon Expertise</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You have trained until the lightsaber is an extension of your will. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, martial weapons, lightsabers, and unarmed attacks increase to expert. You gain access to the critical specialization effects of lightsabers.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-battlefield-intuitive-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Battlefield Intuitive</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to Master. In addition, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Perception checks for Initiative.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-armor-expertise-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Armor Expertise</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You have learned to move in armor as if it were a second skin. Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as unarmored defense, increase to expert. You gain the armor specialization effects of medium and heavy armor.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you&#39;re an expert. This damage increases to 3 if you&#39;re a master, and 4 if you&#39;re legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-tough-as-nails-span-span-level-9-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Tough As Nails</span><span>Level 9</span></div></h3>
<p>Your body is tempered by combat. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to Master. When you roll a success on a Fortitude save, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-armor-mastery-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Armor Mastery</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>Your skill with armor improves. Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as unarmored defense, increase to master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-vigilance-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Vigilance</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>Your reflexes are honed by precognition. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to Expert. When you roll a success on a Reflex save, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-jedi-weapon-mastery-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Jedi Weapon Mastery</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, martial weapons, lightsabers, and unarmed attacks increase to master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-greater-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Greater Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your damage from weapon specialization increases to 4 with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you&#39;re an expert, 6 if you&#39;re a master, and 8 if you&#39;re legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-guardian-expertise-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Guardian Expertise</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency rank for your guardian class DC increases to expert.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-unshakable-juggernaut-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Unshakable Juggernaut</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your body is a fortress of the Force. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to Legendary. When you roll a critical failure on a Fortitude save, you get a failure instead. When you fail a Fortitude save against an effect that deals damage, you halve the damage you take.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-legendary-armor-span-span-level-17-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Legendary Armor</span><span>Level 17</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency ranks for light, medium, and heavy armor, as well as unarmored defense, increase to legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-master-guardian-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Master Guardian</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency rank for your guardian class DC increases to master.</p>
',	'Guardian',	10,	'You are the shield of the Order and the hammer of justice. While Consulars seek to understand the Force, you seek to embody it through physical perfection and martial discipline. You stand on the front lines, deflecting blaster fire, crushing droids, and engaging Sith Lords in single combat. Your mastery of the lightsaber is unrivaled, and your very presence on the battlefield inspires hope in your allies and terror in your enemies.',	'{"1": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "class"]}, "feature": ["clfGuardianInitialProficiencies", "clfBattleFocus", "clfIntercede", "clfLightsaberDiscipline", "clfWaysOfTheForce"], "attribute": {"key_attribute": "STR"}}, "2": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "3": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feeature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "4": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "5": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfJediWeaponExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "6": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "7": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfArmorExpertise", "clfBattlefieldIntuitive", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfWeaponSpecialization"]}, "8": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "9": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfToughAsNails"]}, "10": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "11": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfArmorMastery", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfVigilance"]}, "12": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "13": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfJediWeaponMastery"]}, "14": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "15": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfGreaterWeaponSpecialization", "clfGuardianExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary", "clfUnshakableJuggernaut"]}, "16": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "17": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfLegendaryArmor", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "18": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "19": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfMasterGuardian", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "20": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}}'),
('clsSentinel',	'Sentinel',	'<p>You are the watcher in the shadows, the investigator of mysteries, and the pragmatic hand of the Order. While Guardians train for war and Consulars study the mysteries of the cosmos, you study <em>reality</em>. You are a master of skills—slicing computers, piloting starships, and moving unseen. In combat, you do not rely on brute strength or overwhelming power; you rely on precognition. You see the future of the fight, allowing you to strike with perfect precision or avoid a losing engagement entirely.</p>
<p><strong>Key Attribute: Wisdom</strong></p>
<p>At 1st level, your class gives you an attribute boost to Wisdom.</p>
<p><strong>Hit Points: 8 plus your Constitution modifier</strong></p>
<p>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at 1st level and every level thereafter.</p>
<h3 id="key-terms">Key Terms</h3>
<p>You&#39;ll see the following key terms in many sentinel class features.</p>
<p><strong>Force Premonition:</strong> Your core combat mechanic. You roll your attack <em>before</em> you decide to strike, allowing you to use your Wisdom modifier for the attack.<br><strong>Sentinel&#39;s Strike:</strong> Precision damage dealt when you execute a plan based on your premonition.<br><strong>Force Expertise:</strong> Your ability to substitute your connection to the Force for mundane aptitude in skills.</p>
<h3 id="roleplaying-the-sentinel">Roleplaying the Sentinel</h3>
<p><strong>During Combat Encounters…</strong></p>
<p>You observe the flow of battle before committing to a strike. If you foresee a successful hit, you strike with lethal precision. If you foresee a failure, you pivot instantly—using your skills to hack terminals, disable droids, or distract enemies to support your allies.</p>
<p><strong>During Social Encounters…</strong></p>
<p>You are the listener and the observer. You notice the lies in a politician&#39;s voice or the hidden weapon in a bounty hunter&#39;s holster. You use the Force to guide your intuition and persuasion.</p>
<p><strong>While Exploring…</strong></p>
<p>You are the scout and the technician. You bypass security systems, slice computers, and move unseen ahead of the party.</p>
<p><strong>In Downtime…</strong></p>
<p>You gather information, craft lightsabers and gadgets, or investigate disturbances in the Force that others might overlook.</p>
<hr>
<h3 id="initial-proficiencies">Initial Proficiencies</h3>
<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>
<p><strong>Perception</strong></p>
<p>Expert in Perception</p>
<p><strong>Saving Throws</strong></p>
<p>Trained in Fortitude<br>Expert in Reflex<br>Expert in Will</p>
<p><strong>Skills</strong></p>
<p>Trained in The Force<br>Trained in one skill determined by your <strong>Sentinel Path</strong><br>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to <strong>6</strong> plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<p><strong>Attacks</strong></p>
<p>Trained in simple weapons<br>Trained in martial weapons<br>Trained in lightsabers<br>Trained in unarmed attacks</p>
<p><strong>Defenses</strong></p>
<p>Trained in light armor<br>Trained in unarmored defense</p>
<p><strong>Class DC</strong></p>
<p>Trained in sentinel class DC</p>
<hr>
<h3 id="class-features">Class Features</h3>
<p>You gain these abilities as a Sentinel. Abilities gained at higher levels list the levels at which you gain them next to the features&#39; names.</p>
