  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per round</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You focus on a creature you can see. Roll a d20. This is your Premonition Roll. If you make a Strike against the chosen creature later this round, you must use the result of your Premonition Roll for your attack roll (instead of rolling a new d20). If you Strike the chosen creature using your Premonition Roll, you can use your Wisdom modifier for the attack roll instead of Strength or Dexterity.<br><br>
If your Premonition Roll is low (a likely miss), you are not forced to attack. You can choose to use your remaining actions to move, use a Force Power, or perform a Skill action, knowing that an attack would have failed.
  </div>
</div>

<h3 id="sentinel-s-strike">Sentinel&#39;s Strike</h3>
<p>When you act on your visions, you strike vital points. When you make a Strike against a creature that you used <strong>Force Premonition</strong> on this round, and you use the substitution to use Wisdom for the attack, you deal an extra <strong>1d6 precision damage</strong>.</p>
<p>This damage increases by 1d6 at 5th, 9th, 13th, and 17th levels.</p>
<h3 id="force-expertise">Force Expertise</h3>
<p>You let the Force guide your actions in non-combat situations. At 1st level, choose two skills. You can use your <strong>Wisdom modifier</strong> instead of the normal attribute modifier for checks with these skills.</p>
<h3 id="sentinel-path">Sentinel Path</h3>
<p>At 1st level, you choose the path that defines your service to the Order. Choose a <strong>Sentinel Path</strong> (Subclass). This path grants you a <strong>Path Skill</strong> (which becomes a Trained skill), a special benefit to your <strong>Force Premonition</strong>, and a <strong>Path Feat</strong> at 1st level.</p>
<h3 id="sentinel-feats">Sentinel Feats</h3>
<p>At 1st level and every even-numbered level, you gain a sentinel class feat.</p>
<h3 id="skillful-force">Skillful Force</h3>
<p>Your mastery of skills accelerates. You gain a skill feat at every level, starting from level 1. You gain a skill increase at 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, which you can use to increase your proficiency rank to expert in a skill in which you&#39;re already trained.</p>
<p>At 7th level, you can use skill increases to become a master in a skill in which you&#39;re already an expert, and at 15th level, you can use them to become legendary in a skill in which you&#39;re already a master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-expertise-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Weapon Expertise</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You have trained until the lightsaber is an extension of your will. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, martial weapons, lightsabers, and unarmed attacks increase to expert. You gain access to the critical specialization effects of lightsabers.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-vigilance-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Vigilance</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>Your foresight warns you of danger. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to Master. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Perception checks for Initiative.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you&#39;re an expert. This damage increases to 3 if you&#39;re a master, and 4 if you&#39;re legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-great-fortitude-span-span-level-9-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Great Fortitude</span><span>Level 9</span></div></h3>
<p>Your physique is incredibly hardy. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to Expert.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-resolve-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Resolve</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>You have steeled your mind with incredible discipline. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to Master. When you roll a success on a Will save, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-perception-mastery-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Perception Mastery</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to Legendary. You can detect Invisible creatures as if they were Hidden.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-expertise-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Expertise</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>You have learned to move in armor as if it were a second skin. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to expert. You gain the armor specialization effects of light armor.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-evasion-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Evasion</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>You&#39;ve learned to move quickly to avoid explosions and other area effects. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to Master. When you roll a success on a Reflex save, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-greater-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Greater Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your damage from weapon specialization increases to 4 with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you&#39;re an expert, 6 if you&#39;re a master, and 8 if you&#39;re legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-master-techniques-span-span-level-17-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Master Techniques</span><span>Level 17</span></div></h3>
<p>Your proficiency rank for your sentinel class DC increases to master. When you successfully Hit a target using <strong>Force Premonition</strong>, you can apply a Debilitation. The target must succeed at a Fortitude save against your Class DC or become <strong>Enfeebled 1</strong>, <strong>Clumsy 1</strong>, or <strong>Slowed 1</strong> (your choice) until the end of your next turn.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-mastery-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Mastery</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>Your skill with armor improves. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to master.</p>
',	'Sentinel',	8,	'You are the watcher in the shadows, the investigator of mysteries, and the pragmatic hand of the Order. While Guardians train for war and Consulars study the mysteries of the cosmos, you study _reality_. You are a master of skills—slicing computers, piloting starships, and moving unseen. In combat, you do not rely on brute strength or overwhelming power; you rely on precognition. You see the future of the fight, allowing you to strike with perfect precision or avoid a losing engagement entirely.',	'{"1": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSentinelInitialProficiencies", "clfForceExpertise", "clfForcePremonition", "clfSentinelsStrike", "clfWaysOfTheForce"], "attribute": {"key_attribute": "WIS"}}, "2": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "3": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "4": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "5": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfJediWeaponExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "6": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "7": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfVigilance", "clfWeaponSpecialization"]}, "8": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "9": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfFortitudeExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "10": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "11": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfResolve", "clfPerceptionMastery"]}, "12": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "13": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfLightArmorExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "14": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "15": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfEvasion", "clfGreaterWeaponSpecialization", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "16": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "17": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfMasterTechniques", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "18": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "19": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfLightArmorMastery", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "20": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}}'),
('clsEnvoy',	'Envoy',	'<p>You&#39;re a master influencer. You make your way in the universe with a charming smile, quick wit, and keen sense of self-preservation. You&#39;re a leader who motivates your teammates, pushes them past their limits, and helps them through tough spots. You excel at getting others to do what you want, but you&#39;re always ready to face trouble head-on when things take a turn for the worse. You might be a con artist, diplomat, performer, or military officer—or you might take on whatever role the situation demands.</p>
<p><strong>Key Attribute:</strong>  <strong>Charisma</strong><br>At 1st level, your class gives you an attribute boost to Charisma.</p>
<p><strong>Hit Points: 8 plus your Constitution modifier</strong><br>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at 1st level and every level thereafter.</p>
<h3 id="key-terms">Key Terms</h3>
<p>You&#39;ll see the following terms in envoy class features.<br><strong>Directive:</strong>  Actions with this trait are special orders that provide benefits for your allies if they follow them. Your allies must be able to sense you to benefit from your directives. This action has the auditory or visual trait depending on how you inspire your allies.<br><strong>Flourish:</strong>  Actions with this trait are special techniques that require too much exertion for you to perform frequently. You can use only 1 action with the flourish trait per turn.</p>
<h2 id="roleplaying-the-envoy">Roleplaying the Envoy</h2>
<h3 id="during-combat-encounters-">During Combat Encounters…</h3>
<p>You issue directives to your allies, granting benefits and letting you take the lead. Your words and deeds bolster your allies or harry your foes, and your cunning can get you and your team out of danger.</p>
<h3 id="during-social-encounters-">During Social Encounters…</h3>
<p>You&#39;re often the face for your team, whether you use diplomacy, lies, threats, or whatever words it takes to get your way.</p>
<h3 id="while-exploring-">While Exploring…</h3>
<p>You adapt to situations and excel at motivating your team to overcome obstacles.</p>
<h3 id="in-downtime-">In Downtime…</h3>
<p>You look for new opportunities to make a name for yourself, work your way up through the ranks of an organization, or establish an enterprise of your own.</p>
<h3 id="you-might-">You Might…</h3>
<ul>
<li>Aspire to lead a business or military organization, or captain a starship.</li>
<li>Have friends—and enemies—in unexpected places.</li>
<li>Look for opportunities to talk your way out of fights.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="others-probably-">Others Probably…</h3>
<ul>
<li>Like you, or at least respect you.</li>
<li>Ask for your help navigating complex social situations.</li>
<li>Assume you like being in charge.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="initial-proficiencies">Initial Proficiencies</h2>
<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>
<h3 id="perception">Perception</h3>
<p>Trained in Perception</p>
<h3 id="saving-throws">Saving Throws</h3>
<p>Trained in Fortitude<br>
Expert in Reflex<br>
Expert in Will</p>
<h3 id="skills">Skills</h3>
<p>Trained in one of the following skills of your choice: Deception, Diplomacy, Intimidation<br>
Trained in one skill based on your leadership style<br>
Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 6 plus your Intelligence modifier  </p>
<h3 id="attacks">Attacks</h3>
<p>Trained in simple weapons<br>Trained in martial weapons<br>Trained in unarmed attacks</p>
<h3 id="defenses">Defenses</h3>
<p>Trained in light armor<br>Trained in unarmored defense</p>
<h3 id="class-dc">Class DC</h3>
<p>Trained in envoy class DC</p>
