  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
     You batter a target with compressed air or debris. Make an attack roll against the target using The Force. This attack deals 1d8 Bludgeoning damage. This damage increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level. If you spend 2 actions, add your Wisdom modifier to the damage.</div>
</div>

<h3 id="consular-mandate">Consular Mandate</h3>
<p>The Jedi and Sith have many philosophies regarding the application of power. Choose a <strong>Consular Mandate</strong>. Your mandate determines your initial bonus feat and grants you a passive benefit while you are Connected.</p>
<h3 id="consular-feats">Consular Feats</h3>
<p>At 1st level and every even-numbered level, you gain a consular class feat. Many of these feats grant Force Powers; if a feat has the <strong>Connected</strong> trait, you must be in the Connected state to use it.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-skill-feats-span-span-level-2-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Skill Feats</span><span>Level 2</span></div></h3>
<p>At 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill feat. Skill feats can be found in Chapter 5 and have the skill trait. You must be trained or better in the corresponding skill to select a skill feat.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-iron-will-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Iron Will</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>Your training allows you to shrug off mental influence. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to Legendary. When you roll a critical success on a Will save, you treat the result as one degree of success better.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-general-feats-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>General Feats</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>At 3rd level and every 4 levels thereafter, you gain a general feat. General feats are listed in Chapter 5.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-skill-increases-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Skill Increases</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>At 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill increase. You can use this increase either to increase your proficiency rank to trained in one skill you&#39;re untrained in, or to increase your proficiency rank in one skill in which you&#39;re already trained to expert.</p>
<p>At 7th level, you can use skill increases to increase your proficiency rank to master in a skill in which you&#39;re already an expert, and at 15th level, you can use them to increase your proficiency rank to legendary in a skill in which you&#39;re already a master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-legendary-alertness-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Legendary Alertness</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You remain alert to threats around you. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to Legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-consular-weapon-expertise-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Consular Weapon Expertise</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You have dedicated yourself to the art of the lightsaber as a meditative practice. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, lightsabers, and unarmed attacks increase to expert. You gain access to the critical specialization effects of lightsabers.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-ancestry-feats-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Ancestry Feats</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>In addition to the initial ancestry feat you started with, you gain an ancestry feat at 5th level and every 4 levels thereafter. The list of ancestry feats available to you can be found in your ancestry&#39;s entry.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-expertise-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Expertise</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You have learned to trust in the Force to guide your movements, making you harder to hit. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to expert. You gain the armor specialization effects of light armor.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-consular-expertise-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Consular Expertise</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>Your command of the Force deepens. Your proficiency rank for your consular class DC increases to expert.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you&#39;re an expert. This damage increases to 3 if you&#39;re a master, and 4 if you&#39;re legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-serenity-span-span-level-9-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Serenity</span><span>Level 9</span></div></h3>
<p>Your calm mind is a fortress. If you start your turn Confused, Controlled, or Frightened, you can reduce the value of the condition by 1 and can attempt a new save against the effect immediately as a free action.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-vigilance-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Vigilance</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>Your reflexes are honed by precognition. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to Expert. When you roll a success on a Reflex save, you get a critical success instead.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-mastery-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Mastery</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>Your skill with defense improves. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-master-of-the-force-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Master of the Force</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>Your connection to the Force is potent. Your proficiency rank for your consular class DC increases to master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-consular-weapon-mastery-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Consular Weapon Mastery</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Through skill and dedication, you have mastered the lightsaber. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, lightsabers, and unarmed attacks increase to master.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-legendary-consular-span-span-level-17-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Legendary Consular</span><span>Level 17</span></div></h3>
<p>Your command over the Force is unrivaled. Your proficiency rank for your consular class DC increases to legendary.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-one-with-the-force-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>One with the Force</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>Your body is merely a vessel for the Force. You gain resistance to all damage equal to your Wisdom modifier. Additionally, once per day, if you would be reduced to 0 Hit Points, you can instead remain at 1 Hit Point and immediately enter the Connected state (even if it isn&#39;t your turn).</p>
',	'Consular',	8,	'You are a conduit for the cosmic energy known as the Force. While others rely on blasters or brute strength, you rely on the power of your mind and the depth of your connection to the galaxy. You control the battlefield through telekinesis, revitalize your allies with healing energy, or dominate the wills of your enemies. Though you carry a lightsaber, your true weapon is the Force itself.',	'{"1": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "class"]}, "power": {"grant": [{"id": "powTelekineticImpact", "name": "Telekinetic Impact", "level": 1, "range": "30 feet", "target": "1 creature", "traits": "Force Power, Attack, Connected", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You batter a target with compressed air or debris. Make an attack roll against the target using The Force. This attack deals 1d8 Bludgeoning damage. This damage increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level. If you spend 2 actions, add your Wisdom modifier to the damage."}], "power_slot": [{"count": 2, "level": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfConsularInitialProficiencies", "clfForceConnection"], "attribute": {"key_attribute": "WIS"}}, "2": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "3": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfIronWill", "clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "4": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "5": {"feat": {"feat_slot": "ancestry"}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfLegendaryAlertness", "clfSkillIncreaseExpert", "clfConsularWeaponExpertise"]}, "6": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "7": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfConsularExpertise", "clfLightArmorExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfWeaponSpecialization"]}, "8": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "9": {"feat": {"feat_slot": "ancestry"}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfSerenity", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "10": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "11": {"feat": ["general"], "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfVigilance"]}, "12": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "13": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfLightArmorMastery", "clfMasterOfTheForce", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "14": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "15": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfConsularWeaponMastery", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "16": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "17": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfLegendaryConsular", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "18": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}, "19": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}, "feature": ["clfOneWithTheForce", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "20": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}}}'),
('clsSoldier',	'Soldier',	'<p>You&#39;re a master of area weapons, heavy armor, and soaking damage. You fight in the thick of the battle and unleash devastating salvos against your foes as you take withering fire in return. By laying down a barrage of suppressing fire with powerful weapons, you set your allies up to fulfill their respective roles while encouraging enemies to focus on you.</p>
<p><strong>Key Attribute:</strong>  <strong>Constitution</strong><br>At 1st level, your class gives you an attribute boost to Constitution.</p>
<p><strong>Hit Points: 10 plus your Constitution modifier</strong><br>You increase your maximum number of HP by this number at 1st level and every level thereafter.</p>
<h3 id="key-terms">Key Terms</h3>
<p>You&#39;ll see the following key terms in many soldier class features.<br><strong>Area Fire:</strong>  This is a special action usually made with weapons that have the area trait. This type of action is used to launch weapons that affect a wide area, such as a burst, cone, or line.<br><strong>Auto-Fire:</strong>  This is a special action usually made with weapons that have the automatic trait. This type of action is used to fire weapons in rapid succession, affecting all foes in a wide cone.<br><strong>Suppressed:</strong>  Suppressed is a condition often applied by the soldier when using area and automatic weapons against targets. Creatures a soldier suppresses might receive additional conditions and other negative effects using feats with the suppressed trait; a soldier can only apply one such feat each time they use an action that confers the suppressed trait.</p>
<h2 id="roleplaying-the-soldier">Roleplaying the Soldier</h2>
<h3 id="during-combat-encounters-">During Combat Encounters…</h3>
<p>You set yourself up on the battlefield to rain down fire with heavy weapons. You defy damage and keep your comrades safe from foes as they target you.</p>
<h3 id="during-social-encounters-">During Social Encounters…</h3>
<p>You might stand back and let others do the talking, using your menacing presence to remind others not to mess with your allies. Sometimes you might surprise others with an insightful take.</p>
<h3 id="while-exploring-">While Exploring…</h3>
<p>You’re at the front of the group. You position yourself so you can unload a magazine into any ambush that might pop up while body blocking for your allies.</p>
<h3 id="in-downtime-">In Downtime…</h3>
<p>You might join a military, perform physical labor, or take mercenary jobs when you need credits. You likely spend time training at a gym or tinkering with your weapons and shopping for new ammunition and upgrades.</p>
<h3 id="you-might-">You Might…</h3>
<ul>
<li>Use your heavy weapons to demand enemy attention in combat, enjoying the challenge of battle while soaking attacks for your allies.</li>
<li>Rush forward, knowing that your bulk and endurance will see you through.</li>
</ul>
<h3 id="others-probably-">Others Probably…</h3>
<ul>
<li>Rely on you to lead the charge and take incoming fire.</li>
<li>Assume there&#39;s not much of a personality or intellect under all that armor.</li>
<li>Appreciate your menacing presence at the negotiating table.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="initial-proficiencies">Initial Proficiencies</h2>
<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>
<h3 id="perception">Perception</h3>
<p>Trained in Perception</p>
<h3 id="saving-throws">Saving Throws</h3>
<p>Expert in Fortitude
Trained in Reflex
Expert in Will</p>
<h3 id="skills">Skills</h3>
<p>Trained in Intimidation<br>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 3 plus your Intelligence modifier</p>
<h3 id="attacks">Attacks</h3>
<p>Trained in simple weapons<br>Trained in martial weapons<br>Trained in unarmed attacks</p>
<h3 id="defenses">Defenses</h3>
<p>Trained in all armor<br>Trained in unarmored defense</p>
<h3 id="class-dc">Class DC</h3>
<p>Trained in soldier class DC</p>
