  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    <p>You spend time reverse-engineering and compiling a new Modification to permanently add to your Modification Library. This requires spending a specific amount of time and credits on specialized compilers, decryption keys, or hardware components, and attempting a <strong>Crafting</strong> check against a standard DC corresponding to the Modification&#39;s level.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Level 1 Modification:</strong> Requires 1 hour and costs <strong>20 credits</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Level 7 Modification:</strong> Requires 4 hours and costs <strong>360 credits</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Level 15 Modification:</strong> Requires 8 hours and costs <strong>6,500 credits</strong>.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> You successfully compile the Modification and add it to your Modification Library. Your brilliant optimization means you only spend half the required credits.<br><strong>Success</strong> You successfully compile the Modification, spend the required credits, and add it to your Modification Library.<br><strong>Failure</strong> You can&#39;t fully integrate the schematic with your rig&#39;s architecture. You don&#39;t spend the credits, but you can&#39;t try to learn this specific Modification again until you gain a level.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> You catastrophically corrupt the data or fry the necessary hardware components during the attempt. You waste half the required credits and can&#39;t try to learn this specific Modification again until you gain a level.</p>
  </div>
</div></p>

<h3 id="engineering-disciplines">Engineering Disciplines</h3>
<p>At 1st level, you choose an Engineering Discipline that defines your technical methodology, your role within a squad, and the specific way you push your hardware to the breaking point. This choice grants you specific proficiencies, a core feature, and unique synergies with your Custom Rig and the Overclock trait.</p>

<h3 id="overclock">Overclock</h3>
<p>You know how to bypass safety limiters to achieve incredible results. Every Modification you prepare has an Overclock effect. When you use a Modification, you can choose to Overclock it. You apply the Overclock effect listed in the Modification''s description, altering the baseline action. Immediately after resolving an Overclocked action, you must attempt a DC 15 flat check.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Success</strong> You stabilize the power surge. You suffer no ill effects.</li>
<li><strong>Failure</strong> You lose the ability to Overclock for 10 minutes. Your prepared Modifications still work in their standard mode.</li>
<li><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The specific Modification you used is disabled (including its Standby benefit) and completely unusable until you spend 10 minutes repairing it. You also lose the ability to Overclock for 10 minutes.</li>
</ul>

<h3 id="tech-specialist-feats">Tech Specialist Feats</h3>
<p>At 1st level and every even-numbered level, you gain a tech specialist class feat.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-skill-feats-span-span-level-2-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Skill Feats</span><span>Level 2</span></div></h3>
<p>At 2nd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill feat. You must be trained or better in the corresponding skill to select a skill feat.</p>
<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-skill-increases-span-span-level-2-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Skill Increases</span><span>Level 2</span></div></h3>
<p>At 2nd level and every level thereafter, you gain a skill increase. You can use this increase to either become trained in one skill you''re untrained in or to become an expert in one skill in which you''re already trained.</p>
<p>At 7th level, you can use skill increases to become a master in a skill in which you''re already an expert, and at 15th level, you can use them to become legendary in a skill in which you''re already a master.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-general-feats-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>General Feats</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>At 3rd level and every 4 levels thereafter, you gain a general feat.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-tech-savvy-span-span-level-3-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Tech Savvy</span><span>Level 3</span></div></h3>
<p>You possess a deep understanding of technological hazards and structural weaknesses. You gain a +1 status bonus to your Reflex and Fortitude saves against traps and environmental hazards, and a +1 status bonus to AC against attacks made by technological hazards.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-ancestry-feats-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Ancestry Feats</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>In addition to the initial ancestry feat you started with, you gain an ancestry feat at 5th level and every 4 levels thereafter.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-perception-expertise-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Perception Expertise</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You have a keen eye for details and always manage to remain alert to threats around you. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to expert.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-expertise-span-span-level-5-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Simple Weapon Expertise</span><span>Level 5</span></div></h3>
<p>You''ve learned a few tricks with your weapons. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons and unarmed attacks increase to expert.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-emergency-reroute-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Emergency Reroute</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You can rapidly shunt power to save your Rig from a catastrophic failure. You gain the Emergency Reroute reaction. </p>
<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Emergency Reroute</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger </strong><span>You fail or critically fail the flat check for an Overclock action.</span></div>
    <div><strong>Frequency </strong><span>Once per day.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You ground the electrical surge through your own body. You take electricity damage equal to your level, but you upgrade the result of the triggering flat check by one degree of success (from a critical failure to a failure, or a failure to a success).
  </div>
</div>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-tech-specialist-expertise-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Tech Specialist Expertise</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>Your hands-on experience has improved your engineering skills. Your proficiency rank for your tech specialist class DC increases to expert.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-7-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 7</span></div></h3>
<p>You''ve learned how to inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you''re an expert. This damage increases to 3 damage if you''re a master, and 4 damage if you''re legendary.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-fortitude-expertise-span-span-level-9-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Fortitude Expertise</span><span>Level 9</span></div></h3>
<p>Your physical resilience to industrial accidents and toxic fumes pays off. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to expert.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-perception-mastery-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Perception Mastery</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>Through your adventures, you&#39;ve developed keen awareness and attention to detail. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to master.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-reflex-mastery-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Reflex Mastery</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>You&#39;ve learned to move quickly to avoid explosions, dragon&#39;s breath, and worse. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Reflex save, you get a critical success instead.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-reliable-overclock-span-span-level-11-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Reliable Overclock</span><span>Level 11</span></div></h3>
<p>You have refined your hardware to handle heavier loads. The flat check DC for your Overclock actions is reduced from 15 to 13.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-expertise-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Expertise</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>You''ve learned how to dodge while wearing light or no armor. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to expert.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-weapon-mastery-span-span-level-13-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Simple Weapon Mastery</span><span>Level 13</span></div></h3>
<p>You know your weapons like you know yourself. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons and unarmed attacks increase to master.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-greater-weapon-specialization-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Greater Weapon Specialization</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your damage from weapon specialization increases to 4 with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you''re an expert, 6 if you''re a master, and 8 if you''re legendary.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-tech-specialist-mastery-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Master Tech Specialist</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>Your mastery of technology is unparalleled. Your proficiency rank for your tech specialist class DC increases to master.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-resolve-span-span-level-15-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Resolve</span><span>Level 15</span></div></h3>
<p>You&#39;ve strengthened your mind with an inner reservoir of determination. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Will save, you get a critical success instead.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-incredible-senses-span-span-level-17-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Incredible Senses</span><span>Level 17</span></div></h3>
<p>You notice things that are almost impossible for an ordinary person to detect. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to legendary.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-flawless-overclock-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Flawless Overclock</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>You have perfectly calibrated your Custom Rig. The flat check DC for your Overclock actions is reduced from 13 to 10.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-light-armor-mastery-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Light Armor Mastery</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>Your skill with light armor improves, increasing your ability to dodge blows. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to master.</p>

<h3 id="-div-style-display-flex-justify-content-space-between-span-unfettered-processing-span-span-level-19-span-div-"><div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span>Unfettered Processing</span><span>Level 19</span></div></h3>
<p>Your mind and your Rig process information at a staggering rate. You gain the following action.</p>
<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Unfettered Processing</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span><span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger </strong><span>You roll a skill check for Computers, Crafting, or any Engineering Lore skill in which you have legendary proficiency.</span></div>
    <div><strong>Frequency </strong><span>Once per day per skill.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You can reroll the triggering skill check and use the better result.
  </div>
</div>',	'Tech Specialist',	8,	'You''re a master of machines, code, and jury-rigged miracles. While others rely on ancient religions or brute military force, you know that the true power in the galaxy lies in the hands of those who build, repair, and control its technology. You might be a brilliant slicer infiltrating corporate mainframes, a gritty mechanic keeping a scrap-heap freighter flying, or a combat engineer turning battlefield debris into deadly weapons. You understand the hidden language of circuitry, and you aren''t afraid to push your hardware past its safe operating limits to achieve the impossible.',	'{"1": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry", "class"]}, "feature": ["clfCustomRig", "clfModificationLibrary", "clfOverclock", "clfTechSpecialistInitialProficiencies"], "attribute": {"key_attribute": "INT"}}, "2": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "3": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "4": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "5": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfPerceptionExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseExpert", "clfSimpleWeaponExpertise"]}, "6": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseExpert"]}, "7": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfEmergencyReroute", "clfFortitudeExpertise", "clfTechSpecialistExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster", "clfWeaponSpecialization"]}, "8": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "9": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfFortitudeExpertise", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "10": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "11": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfPerceptionMastery", "clfReflexMastery", "clfReliableOverclock", "clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "12": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "13": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfLightArmorExpertise", "clfSkillincreaseMaster", "clfSimpleWeaponMastery"]}, "14": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseMaster"]}, "15": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfGreaterWeaponSpecialization", "clfResolve", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary", "clfMasterTechSpecialist"]}, "16": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "17": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["ancestry"]}, "feature": ["clfIncredibleSenses", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "18": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}, "19": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["general"]}, "feature": ["clfFlawlessOverclock", "clfLightArmorMaster", "clfPredictiveEvasion", "clfSkillIncreaseLegendary", "clfUnfetteredProcessing"]}, "20": {"feat": {"feat_slot": ["class", "skill"]}, "feature": ["clfSkillIncreaseLegendary"]}}');

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "ClassFeat";
CREATE TABLE "public"."ClassFeat" (
    "ClassFeatID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Description" text NOT NULL,
    "Prerequisites" jsonb,
    "Summary" character varying NOT NULL,
    "ClassID" character varying,
    "Features" jsonb,
    "Traits" character varying,
    "Level" smallint NOT NULL,
    "Repeatable" boolean DEFAULT false NOT NULL,
    "ArchetypeID" character varying,
    CONSTRAINT "ClassFeat_ClassFeatID" PRIMARY KEY ("ClassFeatID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."ClassFeat"."ClassFeatID" IS 'Unique Class Feat ID';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."ClassFeat"."Name" IS 'Class Feat Name';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."ClassFeat"."Description" IS 'Class Feat deescription text';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."ClassFeat"."Prerequisites" IS 'JSON list of prerequsite classes and levels';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."ClassFeat"."Summary" IS 'Class Feat short summary';

INSERT INTO "ClassFeat" ("ClassFeatID", "Name", "Description", "Prerequisites", "Summary", "ClassID", "Features", "Traits", "Level", "Repeatable", "ArchetypeID") VALUES
('cftKillSteal',	'Kill Steal',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Kill Steal</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>An ally ends their turn after hitting a creature two or more times or critically hitting a creature.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You fire a quick shot at a foe your ally is focusing their attacks on. You Aim at the creature your triggering ally hit and then make a ranged Strike against that creature.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You fire a quick shot at a foe your ally is focusing their attacks on.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKillSteal", "name": "Kill Steal", "traits": "Operative", "trigger": "An ally ends their turn after hitting a creature two or more times or critically hitting a creature.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You fire a quick shot at a foe your ally is focusing their attacks on. You Aim at the creature your triggering ally hit and then make a ranged Strike against that creature.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSuppressingFire',	'Suppressing Fire',	'You gain the suppressing fire class feature.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSoldierDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the suppressing fire class feature.',	NULL,	'{"feature": ["clfSuppressingFire"]}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcSoldier'),
('cftAdvancedDroidUpgradeA',	'Advanced Droid Upgrade',	'You heavily modify your droid for specialized field operations. Your droid companion''s proficiency rank for unarmed attacks and unarmored defense increases to master. Its Dexterity modifier increases by 2 and its Strength and Constitution modifiers increase by 1.

The droid''s integrated tools are upgraded to Advanced-grade, granting a +2 item bonus to the relevant skill checks.

Choose one of the following hardware specializations for your droid:

<strong>Infiltrator-Spec</strong> Your droid is optimized for stealth and evasion. Its proficiency rank in Stealth increases to expert, and its Speed increases by 10 feet. It gains an active optical camouflage system, allowing it to use the Hide action even if it does not have cover or concealment.

<strong>Escort-Spec</strong> Your droid is optimized to protect you in firefights. Its unarmed attacks deal 3 additional damage. It gains a miniaturized deflector shield generator. When you roll Initiative, the droid grants Temporary Hit Points equal to its level to itself and one ally in its space or an adjacent square (usually you).',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftUpgradedDroidChassis", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You heavily modify your droid for specialized field operations.',	NULL,	'{"minion": {"apply_template": "mature", "template_choice": {"key": "companion_type", "label": "Companion Type", "options": ["escort", "infiltrator"]}}}',	'Archetype',	8,	'0',	'arcDroidCompanion'),
('cftCompanionsCry',	'Companion''s Cry',	'You can urge your companion to do its utmost. You can spend 2 actions to Command an Animal instead of 1 when commanding your animal companion. If you do, your animal companion uses an additional action.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You can urge your companion to do its utmost.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftMobileAim',	'Mobile Aim',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Mobile Aim</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You’re rarely still, and you’ve learned to reliably hit your targets even while moving. You Stride and then Aim with a gun you’re wielding.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You’re rarely still, and you’ve learned to reliably hit your targets even while moving.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMobileAim", "name": "Mobile Aim", "traits": "Operative, Traversal", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You’re rarely still, and you’ve learned to reliably hit your targets even while moving. You Stride and then Aim with a gun you’re wielding."}]}}',	'Operative, Traversal',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBrutalBarrage',	'Brutal Barrage',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Brutal Barrage</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You prepare the perfect shot, able to tear through those closest to the impact point. If your next action is to Area Fire, Auto-Fire, or Whirling Swipe, add two additional weapon damage dice to targets who are adjacent to the center point of impact or within the first 10 feet of a cone or line.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You prepare the perfect shot, able to tear through those closest to the impact point.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBrutalBarrage", "name": "Brutal Barrage", "traits": "Soldier, Flourish", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You prepare the perfect shot, able to tear through those closest to the impact point. If your next action is to Area Fire, Auto-Fire, or Whirling Swipe, add two additional weapon damage dice to targets who are adjacent to the center point of impact or within the first 10 feet of a cone or line.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon."}]}}',	'Flourish, Soldier',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOverwhelmingAssault',	'Overwhelming Assault',	'You overwhelm the defenses of suppressed foes. Your multiple attack penalty for attacks against suppressed targets is –4 (–3 with an agile weapon) on your second attack of the turn instead of –5, and –8 (–7 with an agile weapon) on your third and subsequent attacks of the turn instead of –10.',	NULL,	'You overwhelm the defenses of suppressed foes.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftYouCanDoIt',	'You Can Do It',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">You Can Do It!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You motivate an ally within 60 feet to lead by example. As a free action, that ally can immediately perform the lead by example actions of your last action, gaining any benefits and using any abilities that would normally be used as if you used two-actions to issue the direction. Use your Charisma modifier instead of your ally’s when determining any relevant benefits, such as the status bonus to damage for Get ''Em!
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You motivate an ally within 60 feet to lead by example.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actYouCanDoIt", "name": "You Can Do It!", "traits": "Envoy, Flourish, Mental", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You motivate an ally within 60 feet to lead by example. As a free action, that ally can immediately perform the lead by example actions of your last action, gaining any benefits and using any abilities that would normally be used as if you used two-actions to issue the direction. Use your Charisma modifier instead of your ally’s when determining any relevant benefits, such as the status bonus to damage for Get ''Em!", "requirements": "Your last action was a 1-action directive."}]}}',	'Envoy, Flourish, Mental',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCloakingField',	'Cloaking Field',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Cloaking Field</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You bend light and background vibrations around yourself, either through expertise or a bit of technological ingenuity, allowing you to avoid detection. You become invisible for 10 minutes. This makes you undetected to all creatures, though creatures can attempt to find you, making you hidden instead. If you use a hostile action, the effect ends after that hostile action is completed. While your Cloaking Field is active, security cameras, sentries, and other surveillance don''t detect you unless they possess special senses that normally see through invisibility.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You bend light and background vibrations around yourself, either through expertise or a bit of technological ingenuity, allowing you to avoid detection.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCloakingField", "name": "Cloaking Field", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You bend light and background vibrations around yourself, either through expertise or a bit of technological ingenuity, allowing you to avoid detection. You become invisible for 10 minutes. This makes you undetected to all creatures, though creatures can attempt to find you, making you hidden instead. If you use a hostile action, the effect ends after that hostile action is completed. While your Cloaking Field is active, security cameras, sentries, and other surveillance don''t detect you unless they possess special senses that normally see through invisibility."}]}}',	'Operative',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftPeek',	'Peek',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Peek</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You shoot and then duck out of the way to avoid retaliation and errant gunfire. Make a ranged Strike, then Take Cover.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You shoot and then duck out of the way to avoid retaliation and errant gunfire.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPeek", "name": "Peek", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You shoot and then duck out of the way to avoid retaliation and errant gunfire. Make a ranged Strike, then Take Cover."}]}}',	'Operative',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSmoothDiversions',	'Smooth Diversions',	'You''re practiced in the art of diverting attention quickly and subtly. When you succeed at an attempt to Create a Diversion, you can immediately Sneak or Step as a free action.

Additionally, creatures only become aware you were trying to trick them if you critically fail to Create a Diversion. Otherwise the creature assumes that your diversion was part of your regular bravado.',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	'You''re practiced in the art of diverting attention quickly and subtly.',	'clsEnvoy',	NULL,	'Envoy',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAmmoHoarder',	'Ammo Hoarder',	'By using direct and methodical burst fire, you conserve your ammunition without compromising your destructive potential. Your Auto-Fire has an expend equal to the number of targets in the area, rather than the number of targets in the area × 2',	NULL,	'By using direct and methodical burst fire, you conserve your ammunition without compromising your destructive potential.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftHastyReconfiguration',	'Hasty Reconfiguration',	'You maintain modular, hot-swappable components on your custom rig. You can perform a Hot-Swap to exchange one of your actively installed Modifications for another Modification from your library by spending 1 minute of uninterrupted interaction, rather than the standard 10 minutes.',	NULL,	'You maintain modular, hot-swappable components on your custom rig.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAnchoringImpacts',	'Anchoring Impacts',	'Your suppressing attacks pin foes in place, preventing them from moving at more than a crawling pace. When you suppress a target with one of your attacks, increase the speed penalty to a –20-foot status penalty for the duration of the suppressed condition. If the effect that imparted the suppressed condition was a critical hit, or the target critically fails its save and becomes suppressed, then the target also becomes stunned 1.',	NULL,	'Your suppressing attacks pin foes in place, preventing them from moving at more than a crawling pace.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier, Suppressed',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBulletDance',	'Bullet Dance',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Bullet Dance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You dance across the battlefield while dispatching enemies with precision and grace. Stride up to twice. You can make up to three ranged Strikes during this movement. Each ranged Strike you make must target a different creature within your f irst range increment (calculated from the point at which you took your attack at that target). Each attack counts toward your multiple attack penalty but doesn’t increase your penalty until you’ve made all your attacks.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You dance across the battlefield while dispatching enemies with precision and grace.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBulletDance", "name": "Bullet Dance", "traits": "Operative, Flourish, Traversal", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You dance across the battlefield while dispatching enemies with precision and grace. Stride up to twice. You can make up to three ranged Strikes during this movement. Each ranged Strike you make must target a different creature within your f irst range increment (calculated from the point at which you took your attack at that target). Each attack counts toward your multiple attack penalty but doesn’t increase your penalty until you’ve made all your attacks.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative, Flourish, Traversal',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftHammerTheNail',	'Hammer the Nail',	'You adjust the angle of your barrage to maximize the ammunition''s impact on creatures'' bodies. Increase the distance creatures are pushed by your Shoving Shot to 5 feet on a success, 10 feet on a failure, and 20 feet on a critical failure. In addition, on a critical failure, the target is also knocked prone.',	'[{"feat": {"id": "cftShovingShot", "type": "class"}}]',	'You adjust the angle of your barrage to maximize the ammunition''s impact on creatures'' bodies.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftGuardiansResolve',	'Guardian''s Resolve',	'You steel your mind. Reduce the Frightened value you would take by 1.',	NULL,	'You steel your mind.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actGuardiansResolve", "name": "Guardian''s Resolve", "traits": "Guardian, Emotion, Mental", "trigger": "You would be affected by the Frightened condition.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You steel your mind. Reduce the Frightened value you would take by 1."}]}}',	'Guardian, Emotion, Mental',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShotOnTheRun',	'Shot on the Run',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shot on the Run</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    By preparing your weapon while on the move, you ready yourself to fire a salvo as soon as you’re in position. Stride up to your Speed, and then Area Fire or Auto-Fire.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'By preparing your weapon while on the move, you ready yourself to fire a salvo as soon as you’re in position.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShotOnTheRun", "name": "Shot on the Run", "traits": "Soldier, Traversal", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "By preparing your weapon while on the move, you ready yourself to fire a salvo as soon as you’re in position. Stride up to your Speed, and then Area Fire or Auto-Fire.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon."}]}}',	'Soldier, Traversal',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCutEmDeep',	'Cut ‘Em Deep',	'Your insults and threats almost always hit the mark. When you roll a failure on a Demoralize action, you get a success instead. You can still critically fail.

When you successfully Demoralize the target of your Get ''Em!, the target doesn''t become immune to your further attempts to Demoralize them.',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	'Your insults and threats almost always hit the mark.',	'clsEnvoy',	NULL,	'Envoy',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftRunCowards',	'Run, Cowards!',	'You use your weapon to help corral panicked enemies. An enemy who critically fails a save against your Area Fire or Auto-Fire is fleeing for 1 round.',	NULL,	'You use your weapon to help corral panicked enemies.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAdvancedConduit',	'Advanced Conduit',	'You gain one Consular class feat. For the purpose of meeting its prerequisites, your Consular level is equal to half your character''s level.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once. Each time you select it, you gain another Consular class feat.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBasicConduit", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain one Consular class feat.',	NULL,	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class_feat"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Consular Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Consular"], "max_level": "{slot_level // 2}"}}]}',	'Archetype',	6,	'1',	'arcConsular'),
('cftDance',	'Dance!',	'You compel enemies to avoid your attacks by aiming at their legs, wings, or other forms of movement to make them easier to outmaneuver. When you suppress a target with one of your attacks, it also becomes off-guard until the start of its turn.

In addition, when Auto-Firing in a cone that affects only a single target, that target takes a –1 circumstance penalty to Reflex saves against the Auto-Fire attack.',	NULL,	'You compel enemies to avoid your attacks by aiming at their legs, wings, or other forms of movement to make them easier to outmaneuver.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier, Suppressed',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCountermeasureProtocols',	'Countermeasure Protocols',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Countermeasure Protocols</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are targeted by a ranged Strike, and the attacker''s roll is a critical success.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your rig''s automated threat-detection instantly deploys micro-chaff, localized smoke, or a magnetic flare. You immediately become concealed against the triggering attack. The attacker must roll a DC 11 flat check; if they fail the flat check, the attack misses entirely.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your rig''s automated threat-detection instantly deploys micro-chaff, localized smoke, or a magnetic flare.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCountermeasureProtocols", "name": "Countermeasure Protocols", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "trigger": "You are targeted by a ranged Strike, and the attacker''s roll is a critical success.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Your rig''s automated threat-detection instantly deploys micro-chaff, localized smoke, or a magnetic flare. You immediately become concealed against the triggering attack. The attacker must roll a DC 11 flat check; if they fail the flat check, the attack misses entirely."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOverkill',	'Overkill',	'Sometimes there’s no better way to assure success than to pin a hapless enemy with concentrated firepower. When you suppress a creature with Area Fire or Auto-Fire and only one creature was in the area of your attack, or when you use Concentrated Shot, the target takes 1d10 persistent bleed damage. If you critically hit it with your primary target Strike, this increases to 2d10 persistent bleed damage.',	NULL,	'Sometimes there’s no better way to assure success than to pin a hapless enemy with concentrated firepower.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier, Suppressed',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSoldiersTraining',	'Soldier''s Training',	'Constant drills and combat experience leave you with reflexes capable of making snap decisions. Choose one soldier class feat you have that grants a reaction. At the start of your turn, you gain an additional reaction that you can only use for the selected class feat or an action granted by the selected class feat.

You can change the reaction selected for this feat when you make your daily preparations as long as the new feat meets the requirements.',	NULL,	'Constant drills and combat experience leave you with reflexes capable of making snap decisions.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDamaritoshsGrip',	'Mythosaur''s Grip',	'You have become a legendary warrior on par with the ancient crusaders of Mandalore and need not choose between the destructive power of your heavy blaster and the brutal tradition of your melee weapons. You can wield two-handed weapons in one hand.',	NULL,	'You have become a legendary warrior on par with the ancient crusaders of Mandalore and need not choose between the destructive power of your heavy blaster and the brutal tradition of your melee weapons.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBulletTyphoon',	'Bullet Typhoon',	'Your destructive power has become second nature as enemies stand in awe of your overwhelming firepower. You can use the Area Fire or Auto-Fire attacks as a single action. However, you can never make more than two such attacks in the same round.',	NULL,	'Your destructive power has become second nature as enemies stand in awe of your overwhelming firepower.',	'clsSoldier',	NULL,	'Soldier',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftPrimaryTarget',	'Primary Target',	'You gain the primary target class feature.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSoldierDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the primary target class feature.',	NULL,	'{"feature": ["clfPrimaryTarget"]}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcSoldier'),
('cftTwinShooter',	'Twin Shooter',	'You''re especially dangerous while brandishing twin guns. As long as you''re wielding two simple guns, both guns gain the agile trait.',	'[{"feat": {"id": "cftTwinDraw", "type": "class"}}]',	'You''re especially dangerous while brandishing twin guns.',	'clsOperative',	NULL,	'Operative',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSidestep',	'Sidestep',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Sidestep</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>The attack roll for a Strike targeting you fails.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You deftly step out of the way of an attack, letting the blow continue to the creature next to you. You redirect the attack to a creature of your choice that''s adjacent to you and within range or reach of the triggering attack. The attacker rerolls the Strike''s attack roll against the new target.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You deftly step out of the way of an attack, letting the blow continue to the creature next to you.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSidestep", "name": "Sidestep", "traits": "Envoy", "trigger": "The attack roll for a Strike targeting you fails.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You deftly step out of the way of an attack, letting the blow continue to the creature next to you. You redirect the attack to a creature of your choice that''s adjacent to you and within range or reach of the triggering attack. The attacker rerolls the Strike''s attack roll against the new target."}]}}',	'Envoy',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftStopThemInTheirTracks',	'Stop Them In Their Tracks',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Stop Them In Their Tracks</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    With a deadly authority, you order your target to halt in their tracks, drop their weapons, and surrender. You attempt to Demoralize your mark. This check doesn''t take the –4 circumstance penalty if the target doesn''t share a language with you. On a critical success, your mark is also immobilized for 1 round.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'With a deadly authority, you order your target to halt in their tracks, drop their weapons, and surrender.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actStopThemInTheirTracks", "name": "Stop Them In Their Tracks", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "With a deadly authority, you order your target to halt in their tracks, drop their weapons, and surrender. You attempt to Demoralize your mark. This check doesn''t take the –4 circumstance penalty if the target doesn''t share a language with you. On a critical success, your mark is also immobilized for 1 round."}]}}',	'Operative',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftElusiveTarget',	'Elusive Target',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Elusive Target</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
