    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You succeed at a Will save against a mental effect from a creature.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You reflect the psychic energy back at the attacker. The attacker takes Mental damage equal to your Level. If you Critically Succeeded on the save, the attacker is also Stupefied 1.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You reflect the psychic energy back at the attacker.',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powMentalRebound", "name": "Mental Rebound", "level": 8, "traits": "Consular, Force Power, Mental", "trigger": "You succeed at a Will save against a mental effect from a creature.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You reflect the psychic energy back at the attacker. The attacker takes Mental damage equal to your Level. If you Critically Succeeded on the save, the attacker is also Stupefied 1."}]}}',	'Consular, Force Power, Mental',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDeepReserves',	'Deep Reserves',	'You recover from exertion faster than others. Once per day when you lose your Connected state due to Overexertion, you are not fatigued or penalized. Additionally, the action cost to Open Connection is reduced to a Free Action if you start your turn Unconnected but have rolled Initiative in the last round.',	NULL,	'You recover from exertion faster than others.',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSupremeConnection',	'Supreme Connection',	'Your focus is absolute. You can use Open Connection as a Free Action at the start of your turn. Additionally, you no longer lose your Connected state when you fall Unconscious (though you still cannot act).',	NULL,	'Your focus is absolute.',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftProjectedWill',	'Projected Will',	'You fold space to act through another. Choose an ally or an unattended object within 60 feet. The next Force Power you use this turn originates from that creature or object''s space for the purpose of determining Line of Sight, Range, and Cover. You must still have Line of Effect to the chosen origin point.',	NULL,	'You fold space to act through another.',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular, Concetrate, Connected',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftEffortlessSustain',	'Effortless Sustain',	'Sustaining a Force Power no longer costs an action. You can Sustain one power per round as a Free Action. (Sustaining a second power still costs an action or the Dual Focus feat).',	NULL,	'Sustaining a Force Power no longer costs an action.',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMasterNegotiator',	'Master Negotiator',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Master Negotiator</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You can use Diplomacy to Make an Impression as a single action (instead of 1 minute) and without the penalty for rushing. If you are Connected, you can target up to 3 creatures at once.<br><br>Your words carry the weight of the Force. When you use Diplomacy or Intimidation to influence a creature, the creature is always treated as having a lower degree of success by one step.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": "subMandateOfTheSage"}]',	'You can use Diplomacy to Make an Impression as a single action (instead of 1 minute) and without the penalty for rushing.',	'clsConsular',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMasterNegotiator", "name": "Master Negotiator", "traits": "Consular, Mental", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You can use Diplomacy to Make an Impression as a single action (instead of 1 minute) and without the penalty for rushing. If you are Connected, you can target up to 3 creatures at once.<br><br>Your words carry the weight of the Force. When you use Diplomacy or Intimidation to influence a creature, the creature is always treated as having a lower degree of success by one step."}]}}',	'Consular, Mental',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBulletHell',	'Bullet Hell',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Bullet Hell</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an automatic or area (cone) weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You fire your weapon in sustained bursts to unleash a consistent deluge of firepower that tears apart the terrain to become treacherous. Make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack with your weapon. Until the start of your next turn, any creature that moves through the area you attacked takes 1d4 damage of the same type as the weapon fired per square traversed, with a basic Reflex save at the end of each move action it takes through the area. On a failure, a creature becomes suppressed until the start of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You fire your weapon in sustained bursts to unleash a consistent deluge of firepower that tears apart the terrain to become treacherous.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBulletHell", "name": "Bullet Hell", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You fire your weapon in sustained bursts to unleash a consistent deluge of firepower that tears apart the terrain to become treacherous. Make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack with your weapon. Until the start of your next turn, any creature that moves through the area you attacked takes 1d4 damage of the same type as the weapon fired per square traversed, with a basic Reflex save at the end of each move action it takes through the area. On a failure, a creature becomes suppressed until the start of your next turn.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an automatic or area (cone) weapon."}]}}',	'Soldier',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftScramblerProtocol',	'Scrambler Protocol',	'You maintain a suite of aggressive, disruptive pop-ups and localized frequency jammers. You gain the Digital Diversion skill feat, even if you don''t meet the prerequisites. When you use Digital Diversion, you can target a creature up to 30 feet away instead of only an adjacent target. Additionally, you can use the Computers skill instead of Deception to Feint, or instead of Intimidation to Demoralize, against targets within 30 feet that are carrying, wearing, or wielding a tech item, or that have the construct trait.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subSlicer"}]}]',	'You maintain a suite of aggressive, disruptive pop-ups and localized frequency jammers.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaDigitalDiversion", "type": "skill"}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAvatarOfTheForce',	'Avatar of the Force',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Avatar of the Force</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 20</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Polymorph</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Duration</strong>
      <span>1 minute</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You transcend your physical form, becoming a being of pure light (or shadow). You gain the following benefits:
    <br><br>
    - You gain resistance 20 to all damage.
    <br>
    - You gain a Fly speed of 60 feet.
    <br>
    - All Force Powers you use cost 1 fewer action to cast (minimum 1).
    <br>
    - You cannot lose your Connected state, even if you use Overexertion abilities.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You transcend your physical form, becoming a being of pure light (or shadow).',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powAvatarOfTheForce", "name": "Avatar of the Force", "level": 20, "traits": "Consular, Force Power, Polymorph", "duration": "1 minute", "frequency": "Once per day", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You transcend your physical form, becoming a being of pure light (or shadow). You gain the following benefits:\n\n- You gain Resistance 20 to all damage.\n- You gain a Fly speed of 60 feet.\n- All Force Powers you use cost 1 fewer action to cast (minimum 1).\n- You cannot lose your Connected state, even if you use Overexertion abilities."}]}}',	'Consular, Force Power, Polymorph',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftNaturesPrecision',	'Nature''s Precision',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion with an agile or finesse unarmed attack

Your companions pick at an enemy''s weak points. When your companion strikes a off-guard creature with an agile or finesse unarmed attack, it deals an additional 1d4 precision damage (2d4 if the animal companion is specialized). If the companion already deals precision damage, combine the precision damage.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your companions pick at an enemy''s weak points.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftOneWithTheUniverse',	'One with the Universe',	'You are constantly aware of the flow of the Force. You are permanently under the effects of True Seeing. You can communicate telepathically with any creature within 100 feet.',	NULL,	'You are constantly aware of the flow of the Force.',	'clsConsular',	'{"sense": {"True Seeing": "100 feet"}}',	'Consular, Sense',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShatterpoint',	'Shatterpoint',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shatterpoint</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Connected</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You sense the fracture point in reality. The next Force Power you use ignores all Resistance and Hardness. If the target has Immunity to the damage type, treat it as Resistance 20 instead.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You sense the fracture point in reality.',	'clsConsular',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShatterpoint", "name": "Shatterpoint", "traits": "Consular, Connected", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You sense the fracture point in reality. The next Force Power you use ignores all Resistance and Hardness. If the target has Immunity to the damage type, treat it as Resistance 20 instead."}]}}',	'Consular, Connected',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftArmoredFortress',	'Armored Fortress',	'You have conditioned your body to bear the weight of durasteel. You ignore the Speed penalty from wearing Medium or Heavy armor.',	NULL,	'You have conditioned your body to bear the weight of durasteel.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"defense": [{"medium": {"reduce_speed_penalty": "all"}}, {"heavy": {"reduce_speed_penalty": "all"}}]}',	'Guardian',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftArmorPiercingOverdrive',	'Armor-Piercing Overdrive',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Armor-Piercing Overdrive</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions] or [three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You rapidly recalibrate your weapon''s energy output or payload density to punch through heavy plating. Make a ranged Strike, ignoring an amount of the target''s physical resistance equal to your level. If you use three actions instead, you can Overclock the attack using your Suppressive Overdrive ability, making an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack also ignoring the same amount of resistance.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subArmstech"}]}]',	'You rapidly recalibrate your weapon''s energy output or payload density to punch through heavy plating.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actArmorPiercingOverdrive", "name": "Armor-Piercing Overdrive", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "action_cost": "[two-actions] or [three-actions]", "description": "You rapidly recalibrate your weapon''s energy output or payload density to punch through heavy plating. Make a ranged Strike, ignoring an amount of the target''s physical resistance equal to your level. If you use three actions instead, you can Overclock the attack using your Suppressive Overdrive ability, making an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack also ignoring the same amount of resistance."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftJuryRiggersKnack',	'Jury-Rigger''s Knack',	'You are intimately familiar with keeping broken gear functional under pressure. You gain the Quick Repair skill feat. Additionally, your custom rig functions as a commercial repair toolkit, meaning you can repair items even if your hands are empty and your physical tools are missing.',	NULL,	'You are intimately familiar with keeping broken gear functional under pressure.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaQuickRepair", "type": "skill"}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTenaciousEndurance',	'Tenacious Endurance',	'You encourage your companion to refuse to yield, against even the mightiest of foes. When one of your animal companions is reduced to 0 Hit Points, if it isn''t wounded, it can remain standing with 1 Hit Point and become wounded 1.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You encourage your companion to refuse to yield, against even the mightiest of foes.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype, Emotion, Mental',	6,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftOperativeResiliency',	'Operative Resiliency',	'You gain 3 additional Hit Points for each operative archetype class feat you have. As you continue selecting operative archetype class feats, you continue to gain additional Hit Points in this way.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftOperativeDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain 3 additional Hit Points for each operative archetype class feat you have.',	NULL,	'{"defense": {"hp_per_archetype_feat": {"hp": 3, "archetype_id": "arcOperative"}}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcOperative'),
('cftVectorReflector',	'Vector Reflector',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Vector Reflector</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>A suppressed creature damages you with a Strike.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your armor absorbs some of the kinetic energy of your opponent''s attack. You gain resistance equal to half your level against the triggering damage (or equal to your level if you have the armor storm fighting style). If the triggering creature is within reach, attempt an Athletics check to Shove it.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your armor absorbs some of the kinetic energy of your opponent''s attack.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actVectorReflector", "name": "Vector Reflector", "traits": "Soldier", "trigger": "A suppressed creature damages you with a Strike.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Your armor absorbs some of the kinetic energy of your opponent''s attack. You gain resistance equal to half your level against the triggering damage (or equal to your level if you have the armor storm fighting style). If the triggering creature is within reach, attempt an Athletics check to Shove it."}]}}',	'Soldier',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSharpshooter',	'Sharpshooter',	'Your ranged Strikes against the target of your Aim using the required ranged weapon deal an additional 1d4 precision damage until the end of your turn. This damage increases to 2d4 at 6th level.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftOperativeDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your ranged Strikes against the target of your Aim using the required ranged weapon deal an additional 1d4 precision damage until the end of your turn.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcOperative'),
('cftRicochetShot',	'Ricochet Shot',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Ricochet Shot</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a ranged weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your predictive ballistics calculate the exact angle needed to bounce a shot off the environment. Make a ranged Strike against a target within your weapon''s first range increment. As long as there is a solid surface within 15 feet of the target for your shot to bounce off of, this attack ignores standard cover and greater cover, and the target cannot use the Take Cover action to gain a circumstance bonus to AC against this attack.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subArmstech"}]}]',	'Your predictive ballistics calculate the exact angle needed to bounce a shot off the environment.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRicochetShot", "name": "Ricochet Shot", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "Your predictive ballistics calculate the exact angle needed to bounce a shot off the environment. Make a ranged Strike against a target within your weapon''s first range increment. As long as there is a solid surface within 15 feet of the target for your shot to bounce off of, this attack ignores standard cover and greater cover, and the target cannot use the Take Cover action to gain a circumstance bonus to AC against this attack.", "requirements": "You are wielding a ranged weapon."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDirtyRetort',	'Dirty Retort',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Dirty Retort</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>A creature misses you with a melee Strike.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You turn the tables on your attacker, using underhanded tactics to temporarily hinder it, such as throwing dirt in its eyes, shining a light in its face, pulling its coat over its head, or otherwise being a meddlesome nuisance. The triggering creature becomes your choice of clumsy 1 or enfeebled 1 until the end of its next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You turn the tables on your attacker, using underhanded tactics to temporarily hinder it, such as throwing dirt in its eyes, shining a light in its face, pulling its coat over its head, or otherwise being a meddlesome nuisance.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDirtyRetort", "name": "Dirty Retort", "traits": "Envoy", "trigger": "A creature misses you with a melee Strike.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You turn the tables on your attacker, using underhanded tactics to temporarily hinder it, such as throwing dirt in its eyes, shining a light in its face, pulling its coat over its head, or otherwise being a meddlesome nuisance. The triggering creature becomes your choice of clumsy 1 or enfeebled 1 until the end of its next turn."}]}}',	'Envoy',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftLineEmUp',	'Line ''Em Up',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Line ''Em Up</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You fire a single trick shot that passes through multiple foes. Make a ranged Strike with your gun against a target within your first range increment. Apply this attack against all creatures in a straight line between you and your target. This attack ignores any lesser cover the targets would provide one another. Roll damage only once, and apply it to each creature you hit. Line ’Em Up counts as two attacks for your multiple attack penalty
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You fire a single trick shot that passes through multiple foes.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLineEmUp", "name": "Line ''Em Up", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You fire a single trick shot that passes through multiple foes. Make a ranged Strike with your gun against a target within your first range increment. Apply this attack against all creatures in a straight line between you and your target. This attack ignores any lesser cover the targets would provide one another. Roll damage only once, and apply it to each creature you hit. Line ’Em Up counts as two attacks for your multiple attack penalty", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftForceJump',	'Force Jump',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Force Jump</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
