('cftCustomFirmwareA',	'Custom Firmware',	'You have written bespoke operating protocols for your droid, pushing its hardware far beyond factory specifications.

Your droid''s proficiency rank in one saving throw or skill of your choice increases to legendary. Two of its attributes of your choice increase by 1.

Integrated Paragon Tools: The droid''s integrated tools are upgraded to Paragon-grade, granting a +3 item bonus to the relevant skill checks.

Your droid gains one Firmware Protocol of your choice:

Medic Protocol: If your droid has the Stim Dispenser feat, it can now use the Dispense Stim action as a Reaction when an adjacent ally takes damage.

Targeting Protocol: When your droid uses its Support Benefit, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack rolls against the designated target until the end of your turn.

Slicer Protocol: The droid''s processing speed is vastly improved. When you command your droid to use the Slicer Uplink feat to perform a Computers or Thievery check, it only takes 1 action instead of the usual 2 actions required for those skill actions.

Special: You can select this feat up to three times. Each time, your droid gains a new Firmware Protocol and the attribute/proficiency increases.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftAdvancedDroidUpgrade", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have written bespoke operating protocols for your droid, pushing its hardware far beyond factory specifications.',	NULL,	'{"need": "fix"}',	'Archetype',	14,	'1',	'arcDroidCompanion'),
('cftDoublePremonition',	'Double Premonition',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Double Premonition</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Level 10</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span><span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You scan multiple futures. Choose two different creatures. Roll a separate Force Premonition die for each of them. You can attack either one (or both, if you have actions) using their respective rolls. If you attack one, the premonition for the other fades at the end of the turn.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You scan multiple futures.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powDoublePremonition", "name": "Double Premonition", "traits": "Sentinel, Force Power", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You scan multiple futures. Choose two different creatures. Roll a separate Force Premonition die for each of them. You can attack either one (or both, if you have actions) using their respective rolls. If you attack one, the premonition for the other fades at the end of the turn."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Force Power',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTelekineticHaul',	'Telekinetic Haul',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Telekinetic Haul</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
