    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per round.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You channel the residual energy into your blade. Your next Lightsaber Strike deals an additional 1d6 Force damage.  At level 16, the additional damage increases to 2d6.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subCauseOfTheWarden"}]}]',	'You channel the residual energy into your blade.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForceInfusion", "name": "Force Infusion", "traits": "Guardian", "trigger": "You use a Force Power.", "frequency": "Once per round.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You channel the residual energy into your blade. Your next Lightsaber Strike deals an additional 1d6 Force damage.  At level 16, the additional damage increases to 2d6."}]}}',	'Guardian',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftHybridTechnique',	'Hybrid Technique',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Hybrid Technique</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You can combine methods into a deadly new hybrid technique. Choose two soldier feats that take 2 actions to use, require you to wield an area or automatic weapon, and cause you to make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack as part of its effects. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire once and then apply the additional effects and benefits of both selected feats to the attack.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You can combine methods into a deadly new hybrid technique.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHybridTechnique", "name": "Hybrid Technique", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You can combine methods into a deadly new hybrid technique. Choose two soldier feats that take 2 actions to use, require you to wield an area or automatic weapon, and cause you to make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack as part of its effects. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire once and then apply the additional effects and benefits of both selected feats to the attack.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon"}]}}',	'Soldier',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftVolatileAdaptation',	'Volatile Adaptation',	'When you use your Jury-Rigged Adapter to change the damage type of a Modification, the jury-rigged energy is highly unstable. The Modification deals 1 splash damage of the new energy type to the target and all creatures within 5 feet of the target. This splash damage increases to 2 at 10th level and 3 at 15th level.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subScrapper"}]}]',	'When you use your Jury-Rigged Adapter to change the damage type of a Modification, the jury-rigged energy is highly unstable.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCollateralWitness',	'Collateral Witness',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Collateral Witness</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You reduce your primary target to 0 Hit Points using Auto-Fire.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    With a subtle gesture of your weapon and a stare, you remind a survivor of your onslaught that there''s more where that came from. Demoralize a single creature that was in the area of your Auto-Fire; you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to this check. If you have legendary proficiency in Intimidation, or if you have the action hero fighting style and the target of Collateral Witness is the enemy closest to you, you can use this as a free action with the same trigger.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'With a subtle gesture of your weapon and a stare, you remind a survivor of your onslaught that there''s more where that came from.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCollateralWitness", "name": "Collateral Witness", "traits": "Soldier", "trigger": "You reduce your primary target to 0 Hit Points using Auto-Fire.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "With a subtle gesture of your weapon and a stare, you remind a survivor of your onslaught that there''s more where that came from. Demoralize a single creature that was in the area of your Auto-Fire; you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to this check. If you have legendary proficiency in Intimidation, or if you have the action hero fighting style and the target of Collateral Witness is the enemy closest to you, you can use this as a free action with the same trigger."}]}}',	'Soldier',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftRepositioningTether',	'Repositioning Tether',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Repositioning Tether</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You successfully hit an enemy with a touch-range technological effect (such as an installed Modification) or a melee attack using a tech weapon.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per round.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You instantly fire your tether to disengage. You immediately Step. This movement does not trigger Reactive Strikes.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You instantly fire your tether to disengage.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRepositioningTether", "name": "Repositioning Tether", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "trigger": "You successfully hit an enemy with a touch-range technological effect (such as an installed Modification) or a melee attack using a tech weapon.", "frequency": "Once per round.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You instantly fire your tether to disengage. You immediately Step. This movement does not trigger Reactive Strikes."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftArmorPiercingOrdnance',	'Armor-Piercing Ordnance',	'You have fundamentally redesigned your weapon telemetry to shear through heavy armor plating and energy shielding. Whenever you deal physical or energy damage with a ranged weapon interfaced to your custom rig, you ignore an amount of the target''s Hardness or Resistance equal to half your level.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subArmstech"}]}]',	'You have fundamentally redesigned your weapon telemetry to shear through heavy armor plating and energy shielding.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTacticalCycle',	'Tactical Cycle',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Tactical Cycle</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a ranged weapon that requires reloading or a technological item that requires clearing to function.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You treat weapon maintenance as an afterthought to your tactical movement. You Stride, Step, or Sneak, and then immediately Interact to reload your weapon or clear a misfire.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You treat weapon maintenance as an afterthought to your tactical movement.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTacticalCycle", "name": "Tactical Cycle", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You treat weapon maintenance as an afterthought to your tactical movement. You Stride, Step, or Sneak, and then immediately Interact to reload your weapon or clear a misfire.", "requirements": "You are wielding a ranged weapon that requires reloading or a technological item that requires clearing to function."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftPrecognitiveDodge',	'Precognitive Dodge',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Precognitive Dodge</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Misfortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are hit by an attack from a creature you used Force Premonition on this round.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You saw it coming. The attacker must reroll the attack roll and take the lower result.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You saw it coming.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPrecognitiveDodge", "name": "Precognitive Dodge", "traits": "Sentinel, Misfortune", "trigger": "You are hit by an attack from a creature you used Force Premonition on this round.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You saw it coming. The attacker must reroll the attack roll and take the lower result."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Misfortune',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDiagnosticPing',	'Diagnostic Ping',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Diagnostic Ping</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Concentrate</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You flood the immediate area with a rapid, multi-spectrum sensor sweep. You can immediately Seek in a 30-foot emanation around you. Any hidden or undetected creatures that you successfully locate become observed to you, and you can instantly point them out to all allies within 30 feet as part of this action.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You flood the immediate area with a rapid, multi-spectrum sensor sweep.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDiagnosticPing", "name": "Diagnostic Ping", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Concentrate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You flood the immediate area with a rapid, multi-spectrum sensor sweep. You can immediately Seek in a 30-foot emanation around you. Any hidden or undetected creatures that you successfully locate become observed to you, and you can instantly point them out to all allies within 30 feet as part of this action."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Concentrate',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCustomFirmware',	'Custom Firmware',	'You have written bespoke operating protocols for your droid, pushing its hardware far beyond factory specifications.

Your droid''s proficiency rank in one saving throw or skill of your choice increases to legendary. Two of its attributes of your choice increase by 1.

Integrated Paragon Tools: The droid''s integrated tools are upgraded to Paragon-grade, granting a +3 item bonus to the relevant skill checks.

Your droid gains one Firmware Protocol of your choice:

Medic Protocol: If your droid has the Stim Dispenser feat, it can now use the Dispense Stim action as a Reaction when an adjacent ally takes damage.

Targeting Protocol: When your droid uses its Support Benefit, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack rolls against the designated target until the end of your turn.

Slicer Protocol: The droid''s processing speed is vastly improved. When you command your droid to use the Slicer Uplink feat to perform a Computers or Thievery check, it only takes 1 action instead of the usual 2 actions required for those skill actions.

Special: You can select this feat up to three times. Each time, your droid gains a new Firmware Protocol and the attribute/proficiency increases.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subDroidwright"}]}]',	'You have written bespoke operating protocols for your droid, pushing its hardware far beyond factory specifications.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"need": "fix"}',	'Tech Specialist',	14,	'1',	NULL),
('cftMenacingLaughter',	'Menacing Laughter',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Menacing Laughter</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Auditory</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your laughter (or other vocalization) remains audible over the din of your weapons fire. Attempt an Intimidation check to Demoralize each creature within 30 feet who''s suppressed.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your laughter (or other vocalization) remains audible over the din of your weapons fire.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMenacingLaughter", "name": "Menacing Laughter", "traits": "Soldier, Auditory", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your laughter (or other vocalization) remains audible over the din of your weapons fire. Attempt an Intimidation check to Demoralize each creature within 30 feet who''s suppressed."}]}}',	'Auditory, Soldier',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTacticalIgnition',	'Tactical Ignition',	'<strong>Requirements</strong> You are wearing a jetpack that is active or you are wearing jump jets ready to use.

You use your jetpack''s thrusters for precise, evasive bursts rather than just sustained flight. You can use the Step action to move 5 feet using your fly speed, allowing you to Step vertically or over difficult or hazardous terrain without triggering reactions. Additionally, when you take the Fly action, the first 10 feet of your movement do not trigger reactions.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMandalorianDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You use your jetpack''s thrusters for precise, evasive bursts rather than just sustained flight.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcMandalorian'),
('cftShovingShot',	'Shoving Shot',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shoving Shot</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You use the blast of your weapon to push back your adversaries. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire. Your primary target must attempt a Fortitude save against your class DC.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target is pushed back 10 feet. If using an area (burst) weapon, the target is pushed away from the burst''s center point.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong>As failure, but the target is pushed 15 feet.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You use the blast of your weapon to push back your adversaries.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShovingShot", "name": "Shoving Shot", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You use the blast of your weapon to push back your adversaries. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire. Your primary target must attempt a Fortitude save against your class DC.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target is pushed back 10 feet. If using an area (burst) weapon, the target is pushed away from the burst''s center point.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong>As failure, but the target is pushed 15 feet.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon"}]}}',	'Soldier',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShieldingAura',	'Shielding Aura',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shielding Aura</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 6</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Guardian</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Focused</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You project a shimmering field of energy. For 1 minute, you and all allies adjacent to you gain Resistance 2 to Energy damage (Fire, Electricity, Cold, Plasma). This resistance increases to 4 at Level 10, and 6 at Level 14.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You project a shimmering field of energy.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powShieldingAura", "name": "Shielding Aura", "level": 6, "traits": "Guardian, Focused, Force Power", "action_cost": ["two-actions"], "description": "You project a shimmering field of energy. For 1 minute, you and all allies adjacent to you gain Resistance 2 to Energy damage (Fire, Electricity, Cold, Plasma). This resistance increases to 4 at Level 10, and 6 at Level 14."}]}}',	'Guardian, Focused, Force Power, Force',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftKineticDampeners',	'Kinetic Dampeners',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Kinetic Dampeners</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You fall at least 10 feet or are subjected to forced movement.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You trigger a burst of micro-thrusters or localized repulsor fields to arrest your momentum. You take no falling damage and land on your feet, or you reduce the distance of the forced movement by up to 10 feet.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You trigger a burst of micro-thrusters or localized repulsor fields to arrest your momentum.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKineticDampeners", "name": "Kinetic Dampeners", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "trigger": "You fall at least 10 feet or are subjected to forced movement.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You trigger a burst of micro-thrusters or localized repulsor fields to arrest your momentum. You take no falling damage and land on your feet, or you reduce the distance of the forced movement by up to 10 feet."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCovertApproach',	'Covert Approach',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Covert Approach</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You use the environment and timing to mask your movement. You Stride up to your Speed. If you end this movement in cover or concealment, you can immediately attempt a Stealth check to Hide.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	'You use the environment and timing to mask your movement.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCovertApproach", "name": "Covert Approach", "traits": "Sentinel", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You use the environment and timing to mask your movement. You Stride up to your Speed. If you end this movement in cover or concealment, you can immediately attempt a Stealth check to Hide."}]}}',	'Sentinel',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftUpgradedDroidChassis',	'Upgraded Droid Chassis',	'You have installed superior servos, reinforced plating, and expanded memory banks into your companion. Your droid companion''s proficiency rank for unarmed attacks and unarmored defense increases to expert. Its attributes for Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, and Wisdom each increase by 1. Its unarmed attacks deal two dice of damage instead of one.<br><br>Integrated Tactical Tools: Your droid is outfitted with specialized internal compartments and retractable instruments. It counts as a set of Tactical-grade tools (granting a +1 item bonus to the relevant skill checks) for a skill of your choice, such as Computers, Thievery, or Crafting. You can reconfigure its internal arrays to function as tools for a different applicable skill with 10 minutes of work.<br><br>Independent Action: Even if you don''t use the Command an Animal action, your droid companion can still use 1 action on your turn to Stride or Strike.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subDroidwright"}]}]',	'You have installed superior servos, reinforced plating, and expanded memory banks into your companion.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"minion": {"apply_template": "upgraded"}}',	'Tech Specialist',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftIntegratedVambraces',	'Integrated Vambraces',	'Your vambraces are masterpieces of Mandalorian engineering, seamlessly wired into your armor''s targeting suite and firing mechanisms. When wearing a weapon with the Mandalorian and free-hand traits, you can Strike with it even if you are wielding another weapon or holding an item in that hand.

Furthermore, integrated servos and automated feeding mechanisms allow you to bypass standard loading limitations. You can Interact to reload these weapons even if you do not have a free hand.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMandalorianWeaponFamiliarity", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your vambraces are masterpieces of Mandalorian engineering, seamlessly wired into your armor''s targeting suite and firing mechanisms.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcMandalorian'),
('cftOverchargedMunitions',	'Overcharged Munitions',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Overcharged Munitions</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You rapidly route raw, unstable energy from your custom rig directly into your weapon''s firing chamber or striking surface. Your next Strike before the end of your turn deals an additional 1d6 damage. You choose the damage type, but it must match the damage type of a Modification you currently have actively installed in your custom rig.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You rapidly route raw, unstable energy from your custom rig directly into your weapon''s firing chamber or striking surface.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOverchargedMunitions", "name": "Overcharged Munitions", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You rapidly route raw, unstable energy from your custom rig directly into your weapon''s firing chamber or striking surface. Your next Strike before the end of your turn deals an additional 1d6 damage. You choose the damage type, but it must match the damage type of a Modification you currently have actively installed in your custom rig."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftChainedImpact',	'Chained Impact',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Chained Impact</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 10</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Connected</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Overexertion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Range</strong>
      <span>60 feet</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Target</strong>
      <span>1 creature</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You unleash an erratic bolt of pure force. Make an attack roll using The Force.
    <br><br>
    This attack deals 6d6 Force damage. On success, the bolt then arcs to a second target within 15 feet and then to a third target within 15 feet of the second if the second attack hits.  These additional attacks count towards and are subject to penalties for multiple attacks as normal, and their damage reduces by 2d6 for each attack.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subMandateOfConflict"}]}]',	'You unleash an erratic bolt of pure force.',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powChainedImpact", "name": "Chained Impact", "level": 10, "range": "60 feet", "target": "1 creature", "traits": "Consular, Force Power, Connected, Overexertion, Mental", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You unleash an erratic bolt of pure force. Make an attack roll using The Force.\n\nThis attack deals 6d6 Force damage. On success, the bolt then arcs to a second target within 15 feet and then to a third target within 15 feet of the second if the second attack hits.  These additional attacks count towards and are subject to penalties for multiple attacks as normal, and their damage reduces by 2d6 for each attack. "}]}}',	'Consular, Force Power, Connected, Overexertion, Offense, Attack',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBulletFever',	'Bullet Fever',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Bullet Fever</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You take damage that would reduce you to 0 Hit Points.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>once per hour</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You fly into a frenzy instead of accepting defeat. Instead of being knocked out, you''re reduced to 1 Hit Point, gain a number of temporary Hit Points equal to your half you level for 1 minute, increase your wounded value by 1, and enter a frenzy that lasts for 1 minute. You can''t voluntarily end your frenzy. While in a frenzy caused by Bullet Fever, you''re affected as follows.<br><br>-   You automatically apply precision damage to all targets as though you were Aiming.<br>-   You take a –1 circumstance penalty to AC.<br>-   You take a –1 circumstance penalty to Will saves.<br>-   You can''t take actions that don''t have the attack or move traits except to Reload] your weapons.<br><br>When Bullet Fever ends, you lose any remaining temporary Hit Points from Bullet Fever.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You fly into a frenzy instead of accepting defeat.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBulletFever", "name": "Bullet Fever", "traits": "Operative", "trigger": "You take damage that would reduce you to 0 Hit Points.", "frequency": "once per hour", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You fly into a frenzy instead of accepting defeat. Instead of being knocked out, you''re reduced to 1 Hit Point, gain a number of temporary Hit Points equal to your half you level for 1 minute, increase your wounded value by 1, and enter a frenzy that lasts for 1 minute. You can''t voluntarily end your frenzy. While in a frenzy caused by Bullet Fever, you''re affected as follows.\n\n-   You automatically apply precision damage to all targets as though you were Aiming.\n-   You take a –1 circumstance penalty to AC.\n-   You take a –1 circumstance penalty to Will saves.\n-   You can''t take actions that don''t have the attack or move traits except to Reload] your weapons.\n\nWhen Bullet Fever ends, you lose any remaining temporary Hit Points from Bullet Fever."}]}}',	'Operative',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTelekineticDisarm',	'Telekinetic Disarm',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Telekinetic Disarm</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
