      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You regain consciousness after being unconscious.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Even when you''re downed, you get right back into the thick of things once recovered. You Stand and Interact to draw a weapon or grab an unattended weapon.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Even when you''re downed, you get right back into the thick of things once recovered.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actIllBeBack", "name": "I''ll Be Back", "traits": "Soldier", "trigger": "You regain consciousness after being unconscious.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "Even when you''re downed, you get right back into the thick of things once recovered. You Stand and Interact to draw a weapon or grab an unattended weapon."}]}}',	'Soldier',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShadowClone',	'Shadow Clone',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shadow Clone</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Level 6</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span><span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span><span class="trait-tag">Illusion</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You create a static Force illusion of yourself in your current square, then become Invisible and Stride up to half your speed. The invisibility ends at the end of your turn or if you attack. The clone lasts until the start of your next turn or until touched.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subPathOfTheShadow"}]}]',	'You create a static Force illusion of yourself.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powShadowClone", "name": "Shadow Clone", "traits": "Sentinel, Force Power, Illusion", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You create a static Force illusion of yourself in your current square, then become Invisible and Stride up to half your speed. The invisibility ends at the end of your turn or if you attack. The clone lasts until the start of your next turn or until touched."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Force Power',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftKillShot',	'Kill Shot',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Kill Shot</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions] or [three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You take careful aim at your mark and shoot to kill. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If this attack is a success (but not a critical success), you deal maximum damage. Calculate this damage as if every die you would roll has a maximum result. On a critical success, roll the result normally, but if the double damage would be less than the result of a maximum damage on a normal success, use the maximum damage on the success instead.<br><br>If you spent 3 actions and your attack was a critical success, then you deal maximum damage and double the damage of that result as normal.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You take careful aim at your mark and shoot to kill.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKillShot", "name": "Kill Shot", "traits": "Operative, Flourish", "action_cost": "[two-actions] or [three-actions]", "description": "You take careful aim at your mark and shoot to kill. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If this attack is a success (but not a critical success), you deal maximum damage. Calculate this damage as if every die you would roll has a maximum result. On a critical success, roll the result normally, but if the double damage would be less than the result of a maximum damage on a normal success, use the maximum damage on the success instead.\n\nIf you spent 3 actions and your attack was a critical success, then you deal maximum damage and double the damage of that result as normal.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative, Flourish',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTacticalHUDIntegration',	'Tactical HUD Integration',	'You constantly broadcast threat telemetry to your squad''s comms and visors. As long as you are conscious and have your custom rig, allies within 30 feet of you do not treat enemies as concealed if you have a clear line of sight to that enemy and it is not concealed from you. Additionally, allies within this aura gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against attacks made by enemies you have successfully identified using the Recall Knowledge action during this encounter.',	NULL,	'You constantly broadcast threat telemetry to your squad''s comms and visors.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftWidenArea',	'Widen Area',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Widen Area</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You set up your area weapon to affect more targets. If the next action you use is to Area Fire or Auto-Fire in a burst, cone, or line, or if you use Whirling Swipe, you increase the area of that attack. Add 5 feet to the radius of a burst that normally has a radius of at least 10 feet (a burst with a smaller radius isn’t affected). Add 5 feet to the length of a cone or line that’s normally 15 feet or smaller, and add 10 feet to the length of a larger cone or line.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You set up your area weapon to affect more targets.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actWidenArea", "name": "Widen Area", "traits": "Soldier, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You set up your area weapon to affect more targets. If the next action you use is to Area Fire or Auto-Fire in a burst, cone, or line, or if you use Whirling Swipe, you increase the area of that attack. Add 5 feet to the radius of a burst that normally has a radius of at least 10 feet (a burst with a smaller radius isn’t affected). Add 5 feet to the length of a cone or line that’s normally 15 feet or smaller, and add 10 feet to the length of a larger cone or line.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon"}]}}',	'Manipulate, Soldier',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftRunHot',	'Run Hot',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Run Hot</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding an area weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You hold down the trigger and push your weapons to their absolute limits with a ceaseless barrage of firepower. Area Fire twice with the required weapon, ignoring the unwieldy trait of your weapon. Creatures in the area of the second Area Fire attack gain a +2 circumstance bonus to their save.<br><br>After you use this action, your weapon must cool off and can''t be used until after your next turn or until you take any amount of cold damage.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You hold down the trigger and push your weapons to their absolute limits with a ceaseless barrage of firepower.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRunHot", "name": "Run Hot", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You hold down the trigger and push your weapons to their absolute limits with a ceaseless barrage of firepower. Area Fire twice with the required weapon, ignoring the unwieldy trait of your weapon. Creatures in the area of the second Area Fire attack gain a +2 circumstance bonus to their save.\n\nAfter you use this action, your weapon must cool off and can''t be used until after your next turn or until you take any amount of cold damage.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area weapon."}]}}',	'Soldier',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBurstOfStrength',	'Burst Of Strength',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Burst of Strength</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You fail an Athletics check to Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, or Trip.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
