    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You skillfully line up your shot to hinder your foe. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If the Strike hits, the creature becomes off-guard until the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You skillfully line up your shot to hinder your foe.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHamperingShot", "name": "Hampering Shot", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You skillfully line up your shot to hinder your foe. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If the Strike hits, the creature becomes off-guard until the end of your next turn.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSkirmishStrike',	'Skirmish Strike',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Skirmish Strike</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You attack as you move, staying mobile as you fight and keeping your enemies on their toes. Either Step and then Strike, or Strike and then Step.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You attack as you move, staying mobile as you fight and keeping your enemies on their toes.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSkirmishStrike", "name": "Skirmish Strike", "traits": "Operative, Flourish", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You attack as you move, staying mobile as you fight and keeping your enemies on their toes. Either Step and then Strike, or Strike and then Step."}]}}',	'Operative, Flourish',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMagneticSingularity',	'Magnetic Singularity',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Magnetic Singularity</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You overcharge a localized gravity-inverter, creating a terrifying vortex of crushing debris. You deal 8d6 plus your level bludgeoning damage in a 30-foot burst within 60 feet. Creatures in the area must attempt a Fortitude save against your Tech Specialist Class DC.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature braces itself and is unaffected.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage and is pulled 10 feet toward the center of the burst.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage, is pulled 20 feet toward the center of the burst, and is knocked prone.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage, is pulled to the nearest unoccupied space adjacent to the center of the burst, and is immobilized until it Escapes (DC equal to your class DC).
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subScrapper"}]}]',	'You overcharge a localized gravity-inverter, creating a terrifying vortex of crushing debris.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMagneticSingularity", "name": "Magnetic Singularity", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You overcharge a localized gravity-inverter, creating a terrifying vortex of crushing debris. You deal 8d6 plus your level bludgeoning damage in a 30-foot burst within 60 feet. Creatures in the area must attempt a Fortitude save against your Tech Specialist Class DC.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature braces itself and is unaffected.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The creature takes half damage and is pulled 10 feet toward the center of the burst.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes full damage, is pulled 20 feet toward the center of the burst, and is knocked prone.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage, is pulled to the nearest unoccupied space adjacent to the center of the burst, and is immobilized until it Escapes (DC equal to your class DC)."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftFollowUpFire',	'Follow-Up Fire',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Follow-Up Fire</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>once per round</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding two guns, and your last action was a ranged Strike that missed.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    When at first you don’t succeed, shoot again. Make a second ranged Strike using the weapon you’re wielding that you didn’t f ire with. This Strike doesn’t count the multiple attack penalty from the prior attack but does count toward future multiple attack penalties.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'When at first you don’t succeed, shoot again.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFollowUpFire", "name": "Follow-Up Fire", "traits": "Operative, Flourish", "frequency": "once per round", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "When at first you don’t succeed, shoot again. Make a second ranged Strike using the weapon you’re wielding that you didn’t f ire with. This Strike doesn’t count the multiple attack penalty from the prior attack but does count toward future multiple attack penalties.", "requirements": "You’re wielding two guns, and your last action was a ranged Strike that missed."}]}}',	'Operative, Flourish',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTwinDraw',	'Twin Draw',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
