    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You upload a completely dominating rootkit into an enemy''s primary CPU. Target one creature with the construct trait or a hazard with the tech trait within 30 feet. Attempt a Computers check against the target''s Will DC or the hazard''s Disable DC.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You temporarily rewrite the target''s IFF protocols. The target is controlled by you on its next turn, though it cannot use reactions. At the end of its turn, the rootkit burns out, and the target is temporarily immune to Override Command for 24 hours.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target''s systems heavily lag as they fight the rootkit. A target creature is stunned 1. A target hazard loses all actions for its next turn. The target is temporarily immune for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold. No effect.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop violently overloads your rig. You are stunned 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subSlicer"}]}]',	'You upload a completely dominating rootkit into an enemy''s primary CPU.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOverrideCommand", "name": "Override Command", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Incapacitation, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You upload a completely dominating rootkit into an enemy''s primary CPU. Target one creature with the construct trait or a hazard with the tech trait within 30 feet. Attempt a Computers check against the target''s Will DC or the hazard''s Disable DC.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You temporarily rewrite the target''s IFF protocols. The target is controlled by you on its next turn, though it cannot use reactions. At the end of its turn, the rootkit burns out, and the target is temporarily immune to Override Command for 24 hours.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target''s systems heavily lag as they fight the rootkit. A target creature is stunned 1. A target hazard loses all actions for its next turn. The target is temporarily immune for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold. No effect.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop violently overloads your rig. You are stunned 1."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Incapacitation, Manipulate',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftWhirlingSwipe',	'Whirling Swipe',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Whirling Swipe</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a two-handed melee weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You swipe your weapon in a wide swing to create a deadly arc. Your weapon gains the area (burst 5 feet) and unwieldy traits until the end of the turn. If your weapon has reach, the burst radius becomes the reach of your weapon. Area Fire with the required weapon, centering the burst on a corner of a square you occupy. You’re excluded from the burst. If you’re using a weapon with the backswing or sweep trait, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the save DC of the attack. If you have the primary target class feature, the primary target Strike you make is a melee Strike, rather than a ranged Strike.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You swipe your weapon in a wide swing to create a deadly arc.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actWhirlingSwipe", "name": "Whirling Swipe", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You swipe your weapon in a wide swing to create a deadly arc. Your weapon gains the area (burst 5 feet) and unwieldy traits until the end of the turn. If your weapon has reach, the burst radius becomes the reach of your weapon. Area Fire with the required weapon, centering the burst on a corner of a square you occupy. You’re excluded from the burst. If you’re using a weapon with the backswing or sweep trait, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the save DC of the attack. If you have the primary target class feature, the primary target Strike you make is a melee Strike, rather than a ranged Strike.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a two-handed melee weapon."}]}}',	'Soldier',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSituationalAwareness',	'Situational Awareness',	'<div class="power-card-display">
