('cftHardReset',	'Hard Reset',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Hard Reset</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are currently unable to Overclock due to failing an Overclock flat check.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You violently cycle your custom rig''s power supply, physically bypassing blown safety limiters and venting trapped heat. Attempt a Crafting or Computers check against your Tech Specialist class DC.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The lockout ends, and you immediately regain the ability to Overclock your modifications.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The lockout remains.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The lockout remains, and you take electricity damage equal to your level as your rig violently surges.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You violently cycle your custom rig''s power supply to immediately recover from an Overclock lockout.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHardReset", "name": "Hard Reset", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You violently cycle your custom rig''s power supply, physically bypassing blown safety limiters and venting trapped heat. Attempt a Crafting or Computers check against your Tech Specialist class DC.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The lockout ends, and you immediately regain the ability to Overclock your modifications.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The lockout remains.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The lockout remains, and you take electricity damage equal to your level as your rig violently surges.", "requirements": "You are currently unable to Overclock due to failing an Overclock flat check."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftParallelProcessing',	'Parallel Processing',	'Your custom rig is now capable of flawlessly bifurcating its active routines without losing processing power. Whenever you activate a Modification that normally targets a single creature, you can target a second creature. The second target must be within the Modification''s range and within 30 feet of the first target. The Modification affects both targets, though any variable choices made for the Modification (such as damage type) must be the same for both.',	NULL,	'Your custom rig is now capable of flawlessly bifurcating its active routines without losing processing power.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftLeadThePack',	'Lead the Pack',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> you have multiple animal companions

You can have up to two animal companions active at once. However, when you do, it’s slightly more difficult to Command them. If you don’t Command either of your companions, one of the two (your choice) can still use 1 action on your turn to Stride or Strike, per Mature Beastmaster Companion, but not both. When you Command an Animal, either choose one of the companions to take 2 actions, as normal, or else each companion can take 1 action to Stride or Strike. Either way, you can’t Command an Animal to make either companion act again until your next turn.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMatureBeastmasterCompanion", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You can have up to two animal companions active at once.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	16,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftAerialAce',	'Aerial Ace',	'<div class="power-card-display">
