  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your opponents can run, but they can’t hide! You spray your weapon in the general direction of an unseen enemy, revealing its location. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire. If the primary target is concealed, you don’t need to attempt a flat check to target it, and if it’s hidden, the DC of the flat check to target it is 5. When you suppress a concealed creature with this attack, the debris around it helps reveal its current position, and no flat check is needed to target it; If it’s hidden, the DC of the flat check to target it becomes 5, and the creature can’t become undetected. This benefit lasts as long as the creature remains suppressed.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your opponents can run, but they can’t hide! You spray your weapon in the general direction of an unseen enemy, revealing its location.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLightEmUp", "name": "Light ''Em Up", "traits": "Soldier, Suppressed", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "Your opponents can run, but they can’t hide! You spray your weapon in the general direction of an unseen enemy, revealing its location. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire. If the primary target is concealed, you don’t need to attempt a flat check to target it, and if it’s hidden, the DC of the flat check to target it is 5. When you suppress a concealed creature with this attack, the debris around it helps reveal its current position, and no flat check is needed to target it; If it’s hidden, the DC of the flat check to target it becomes 5, and the creature can’t become undetected. This benefit lasts as long as the creature remains suppressed.", "requirements": "You’re wielding an area or automatic weapon"}]}}',	'Soldier, Suppressed',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftIndomitable',	'Indomitable',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Indomitable</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Guardian</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You fail a Saving Throw.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>once per hour</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You refuse to yield to the effect. Reroll the saving throw and take the better result.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You refuse to yield to the effect.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actIndomitable", "name": "Indomitable", "traits": "Guardian, Fortune", "trigger": "You fail a Saving Throw.", "frequency": "once per hour", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You refuse to yield to the effect. Reroll the saving throw and take the better result."}]}}',	'Guardian, Fortune',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTacticalAssessment',	'Tactical Assessment',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Tactical Assessment</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Guardian</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You analyze the enemy''s stance. Make a Recall Knowledge check against an enemy. If you succeed, you and all allies gain a +1 circumstance bonus to attack rolls against that enemy until the start of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subCauseOfTheWarden"}]}]',	'You analyze the enemy''s stance.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTacticalAssessment", "name": "Tactical Assessment", "traits": "Guardian", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You analyze the enemy''s stance. Make a Recall Knowledge check against an enemy. If you succeed, you and all allies gain a +1 circumstance bonus to attack rolls against that enemy until the start of your next turn."}]}}',	'Guardian',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShieldedCore',	'Shielded Core',	'You have replaced your companion''s standard power plant with an experimental, self-sustaining micro-core. Your droid companion gains Resistance 10 to all energy damage (acid, cold, electricity, fire, force, and sonic). Additionally, if your droid companion is destroyed, the core enters a rapid self-repair cycle; it automatically revives after 1 minute with Hit Points equal to three times your level, without requiring you to spend downtime repairing it.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subDroidwright"}]}]',	'You have replaced your companion''s standard power plant with an experimental, self-sustaining micro-core.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCascadingOverload',	'Cascading Overload',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Cascading Overload</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Ion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You broadcast a localized spike of malicious code paired with a physical surge of raw voltage. Target one creature or hazard within 30 feet that has the tech trait. Attempt a Computers check against the creature''s Fortitude DC, or the hazard''s Disable DC. Regardless of the result, the target is temporarily immune to your Cascading Overload for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The surge is catastrophic. The target takes 4d6 plus your level electricity damage and is stunned 1. If the target is a hazard, its routines lag heavily; it is completely suppressed for 1 round, and this critical success counts as one successful Computers check toward permanently disabling the hazard.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target takes 4d6 plus your level electricity damage. If the target is a hazard, it loses its reaction until the start of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold or its grounding plating absorbs the surge. It takes no damage.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop surges back into your custom rig. You take electricity damage equal to your level.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subSlicer"}]}]',	'You broadcast a localized spike of malicious code paired with a physical surge of raw voltage.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCascadingOverload", "name": "Cascading Overload", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Ion, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You broadcast a localized spike of malicious code paired with a physical surge of raw voltage. Target one creature or hazard within 30 feet that has the tech trait. Attempt a Computers check against the creature''s Fortitude DC, or the hazard''s Disable DC. Regardless of the result, the target is temporarily immune to your Cascading Overload for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The surge is catastrophic. The target takes 4d6 plus your level electricity damage and is stunned 1. If the target is a hazard, its routines lag heavily; it is completely suppressed for 1 round, and this critical success counts as one successful Computers check toward permanently disabling the hazard.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target takes 4d6 plus your level electricity damage. If the target is a hazard, it loses its reaction until the start of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold or its grounding plating absorbs the surge. It takes no damage.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop surges back into your custom rig. You take electricity damage equal to your level."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Ion, Manipulate',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftLoadBearingHero',	'Load-Bearing Hero',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Load-Bearing Hero</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You and one adjacent ally attempt a Reflex or Fortitude save against the same effect.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Whether holding up a crumbling ceiling or jumping into a fireball, you interpose yourself between your ally and incoming danger. The result of your save becomes one degree worse, but the result of your ally’s save becomes one degree higher.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Whether holding up a crumbling ceiling or jumping into a fireball, you interpose yourself between your ally and incoming danger.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLoadBearingHero", "name": "Load-Bearing Hero", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Whether holding up a crumbling ceiling or jumping into a fireball, you interpose yourself between your ally and incoming danger. The result of your save becomes one degree worse, but the result of your ally’s save becomes one degree higher.", "requirements": "You and one adjacent ally attempt a Reflex or Fortitude save against the same effect."}]}}',	'Soldier',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCoveringFire',	'Covering Fire',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Covering Fire</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You make a well placed shot or unleash a hail of fire to cover your allies. Make a ranged Strike against a target and select one ally within range of the same attack. If your Strike hits your target, you deal no damage, but the targeted creature becomes suppressed and takes a –2 circumstance penalty on attacks made against your ally until the end of your next turn.<br><br>You can use Covering Fire as a 2-action activity to Area Fire or Auto-Fire instead of making a ranged Strike, affecting targets that fail their save.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You make a well placed shot or unleash a hail of fire to cover your allies.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCoveringFire", "name": "Covering Fire", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You make a well placed shot or unleash a hail of fire to cover your allies. Make a ranged Strike against a target and select one ally within range of the same attack. If your Strike hits your target, you deal no damage, but the targeted creature becomes suppressed and takes a –2 circumstance penalty on attacks made against your ally until the end of your next turn.\n\nYou can use Covering Fire as a 2-action activity to Area Fire or Auto-Fire instead of making a ranged Strike, affecting targets that fail their save."}]}}',	'Soldier',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMasterGuardian',	'Master Guardian',	'Your mastery of combat and the Force is absolute. Your proficiency rank for your Guardian class DC increases to master.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftExpertGuardian", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your mastery of combat and the Force is absolute. ',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Guardian Class DC", "rank": "Master", "attribute": "STR"}]}',	'Archetype',	18,	'0',	'arcGuardian'),
('cftAdvancedLeadership',	'Advanced Leadership',	'You gain one envoy feat. For the purpose of meeting its prerequisites, your envoy level is equal to half your character level.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBasicLeadership", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain one envoy feat.',	NULL,	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class_feat"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Envoy Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Envoy"], "max_level": "{slot_level // 2}"}}]}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcEnvoy'),
('cftForceGuidance',	'Force Guidance',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Force Guidance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>An ally within 30 feet misses an attack roll.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You nudge their arm with the Force or shout a correction. The ally rerolls the attack roll and must use the new result.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You nudge their arm with the Force or shout a correction.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForceGuidance", "name": "Force Guidance", "traits": "Sentinel, Fortune", "trigger": "An ally within 30 feet misses an attack roll.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You nudge their arm with the Force or shout a correction. The ally rerolls the attack roll and must use the new result."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Fortune',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDoublePrey',	'Double Prey',	'You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down. When you use the Hunt Prey action, you can pick two creatures as your prey.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBountyHunterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You can focus on two foes at once, hunting both of them down.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	14,	'0',	'arcBountyHunter'),
('cftScoutDedication',	'Scout Dedication',	'You are a highly skilled scout, capable of guiding your allies, detecting imminent threats, and avoiding the attention of dangerous enemies. You can perform the Scout exploration activity at the same time as the Avoid Notice exploration activity. The bonus to initiative you grant when you Scout is +2 instead of +1.',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	'You are a highly skilled scout, capable of guiding your allies, detecting imminent threats, and avoiding the attention of dangerous enemies.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype, Dedication',	2,	'0',	'arcScout'),
('cftDontYouDieOnMe',	'Don''t You Die on Me!',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Don''t You Die on Me!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Emotion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You encourage your ally to hang on and keep going, despite life-threatening wounds or other serious injuries that might take them out. Select an adjacent dying ally. Reduce the target''s dying value by 1. If this would reduce their dying value to 0, they lose the dying condition, don''t increase their wounded condition, and remain unconscious. The targeted ally then becomes temporarily immune to Don''t You Die on Me for 1 hour.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You encourage your ally to hang on and keep going, despite life-threatening wounds or other serious injuries that might take them out.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDontYouDieOnMe", "name": "Don''t You Die on Me!", "traits": "Envoy, Emotion, Mental", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You encourage your ally to hang on and keep going, despite life-threatening wounds or other serious injuries that might take them out. Select an adjacent dying ally. Reduce the target''s dying value by 1. If this would reduce their dying value to 0, they lose the dying condition, don''t increase their wounded condition, and remain unconscious. The targeted ally then becomes temporarily immune to Don''t You Die on Me for 1 hour."}]}}',	'Emotion, Envoy, Mental',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftForseenFailure',	'Forseen Failure',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Forseen Failure</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You use Force Premonition and roll a natural 9 or lower on the d20.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The vision of failure allows you to pivot instantly. You are Quickened for this turn. You can use the extra action to Step, Recall Knowledge, Parry, or Raise a Shield (or use Predictive Defense if you have it).
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'The vision of failure allows you to pivot instantly.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForseenFailure", "name": "Forseen Failure", "traits": "Sentinel", "trigger": "You use Force Premonition and roll a natural 9 or lower on the d20.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "The vision of failure allows you to pivot instantly. You are Quickened for this turn. You can use the extra action to Step, Recall Knowledge, Parry, or Raise a Shield (or use Predictive Defense if you have it)."}]}}',	'Sentinel',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDynamicShielding',	'Dynamic Shielding',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Dynamic Shielding</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You temporarily overclock your custom rig''s environmental protections to project a localized, hard-light kinetic barrier or magnetic repulsion field. You immediately Take Cover, gaining the benefits of standard cover (a +2 circumstance bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and Stealth checks to Hide) even if you are out in the open and not adjacent to a physical object that would normally provide cover. This projected cover lasts until the start of your next turn, or until you move from your current space, whichever comes first.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You temporarily overclock your custom rig''s environmental protections to project a localized, hard-light kinetic barrier or magnetic repulsion field.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDynamicShielding", "name": "Dynamic Shielding", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You temporarily overclock your custom rig''s environmental protections to project a localized, hard-light kinetic barrier or magnetic repulsion field. You immediately Take Cover, gaining the benefits of standard cover (a +2 circumstance bonus to AC, Reflex saves, and Stealth checks to Hide) even if you are out in the open and not adjacent to a physical object that would normally provide cover. This projected cover lasts until the start of your next turn, or until you move from your current space, whichever comes first."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftReallyGetEm',	'Really Get ''Em!',	'You gain the Lead by Example benefit for your Get ’Em! directive, except you and your allies get a +2 status bonus to damage on both the initial and subsequent Strikes.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftEnvoyDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the Lead by Example benefit for your Get ’Em! directive, except you and your allies get a +2 status bonus to damage on both the initial and subsequent Strikes.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	8,	'0',	'arcEnvoy'),
('cftBasicInsight',	'Basic Insight',	'You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level Sentinel class feat of your choice.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSentinelDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level Sentinel class feat of your choice.',	NULL,	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class_feat"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Sentinel Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Sentinel"], "max_level": 2}}]}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cft360NoScope',	'360 No Scope',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">360 No Scope</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You fire a trick shot as part of a daredevil maneuver. You Parkour. You can Aim and then make a ranged Strike with the gun you''re wielding during this movement, including when you''re falling.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": {"id": "cftParkour", "type": "class"}}]',	'You fire a trick shot as part of a daredevil maneuver.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "act360NoScope", "name": "360 No Scope", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You fire a trick shot as part of a daredevil maneuver. You Parkour. You can Aim and then make a ranged Strike with the gun you''re wielding during this movement, including when you''re falling.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftIntensifyForce',	'Intensify Force',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Intensify Force</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Concentrate</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Connected</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You pour your entire will into a single technique. If the next action you use is a Force Power that requires a Saving Throw, the DC of that save increases by 1 (or by 2 if the power has the Overexertion trait).
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You pour your entire will into a single technique.',	'clsConsular',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actIntensifyForce", "name": "Intensify Force", "traits": "Consular, Concentrate, Connected", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You pour your entire will into a single technique. If the next action you use is a Force Power that requires a Saving Throw, the DC of that save increases by 1 (or by 2 if the power has the Overexertion trait)."}]}}',	'Consular, Connected, Concentrate',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftFishInABarrel',	'Fish in a Barrel',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Fish in a Barrel</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    As the old saying goes: hitting easy targets is like shooting fish in a barrel. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against a prone or immobilized creature not benefiting from cover. Treat a success as a critical success. If you roll a critical success, the creature is off-guard and suppressed until the beginning of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'As the old saying goes: hitting easy targets is like shooting fish in a barrel.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFishInABarrel", "name": "Fish in a Barrel", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "As the old saying goes: hitting easy targets is like shooting fish in a barrel. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against a prone or immobilized creature not benefiting from cover. Treat a success as a critical success. If you roll a critical success, the creature is off-guard and suppressed until the beginning of your next turn."}]}}',	'Operative',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftExpandedSchematics',	'Expanded Schematics',	'You spend your downtime obsessively scraping the holonet for new tech blueprints. You add two additional Modifications to your Modification Library.<br><br></strong>Special</strong> You can take this feat multiple times; each time you do, you add two Modifications to your Library of any level you can install.',	NULL,	'You spend your downtime obsessively scraping the holonet for new tech blueprints.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	1,	'1',	NULL),
('cftLeadersConfidence',	'Leader''s Confidence',	'You gain the leader''s confidence class feature (see Envoy).',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftEnvoyDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the leader''s confidence class feature.',	NULL,	'{"feature": ["clfLeadersConfidence"]}',	'Archetype',	12,	'0',	'arcEnvoy'),
('cftSentinelsStrike',	'Sentinel''s Strike',	'When you act on your visions, you strike vital points. When you make a Strike against a creature that you used Force Premonition on this round, and you use the substitution to use Wisdom for the attack, you deal an extra 1d6 precision damage. Unlike the standard Sentinel class feature, this precision damage does not automatically increase at higher levels.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSentinelsPremonition", "type": "class"}]}]',	'When you act on your visions, you strike vital points.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftScrapPlating',	'Scrap Plating',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Scrap Plating</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You rapidly magnetize nearby debris or engage micro-deflectors to absorb an incoming blow. You gain temporary Hit Points equal to your Intelligence modifier plus half your level. These temporary Hit Points last for 1 minute. You cannot use Scrap Plating again for 10 minutes.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subScrapper"}]}]',	'You rapidly magnetize nearby debris or engage micro-deflectors to absorb an incoming blow.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actScrapPlating", "name": "Scrap Plating", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You rapidly magnetize nearby debris or engage micro-deflectors to absorb an incoming blow. You gain temporary Hit Points equal to your Intelligence modifier plus half your level. These temporary Hit Points last for 1 minute. You cannot use Scrap Plating again for 10 minutes."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCalculatedSplash',	'Calculated Splash',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Calculated Splash</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are holding a grenade, explosive, or splash weapon.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You calculate the perfect trajectory. You throw the item. It gains the effects of your Force Premonition (using Wisdom to hit). If you hit, you can choose to exclude one creature in the splash radius from taking damage, or increase the splash damage by an amount equal to your Wisdom modifier.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": ["subPathOfTheArtisan", "subPathOfTheCorsair"]}]}]',	'You calculate the perfect trajectory.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCalculatedSplash", "name": "Calculated Splash", "traits": "Sentinel", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You calculate the perfect trajectory. You throw the item. It gains the effects of your Force Premonition (using Wisdom to hit). If you hit, you can choose to exclude one creature in the splash radius from taking damage, or increase the splash damage by an amount equal to your Wisdom modifier.", "requirements": "You are holding a grenade, explosive, or splash weapon."}]}}',	'Sentinel',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMasterPlan',	'Master Plan',	'During your daily preparations, you can review stratagems with up to five allies. Later, you can quickly advise each of these allies on your schemes using the reaction below.

You gain the New Plan reaction.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">New Plan</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Linguistic</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>An ally you reviewed stratagems with is about to attempt an attack roll or skill check</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The ally rolls the triggering check twice and takes the better of the two results. That ally then becomes temporarily immune to your New Plan until your next daily preparations.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'During your daily preparations, you can review stratagems with up to five allies.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actNewPlan", "name": "New Plan", "traits": "Envoy, Fortune, Linguistic", "trigger": "An ally you reviewed stratagems with is about to attempt an attack roll or skill check", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "The ally rolls the triggering check twice and takes the better of the two results. That ally then becomes temporarily immune to your New Plan until your next daily preparations."}]}}',	'Envoy',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftGetInThere',	'Get in There!',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Get in There!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Directive</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You urge your allies to hustle into the fight or to get out of the way. Until the beginning of your next turn, you and your allies within 100 feet who can sense you gain a +5-foot status bonus to Speed. As your envoy level increases, increase the bonus by an additional 5 feet at 7th level, 12th level, and 17th level.<br><br><strong>Lead by Example</strong> If you used two actions, Step or Stride. Each of your allies within 100 feet who can sense you can immediately Step or Stride up to half their Speed (rounded down to the nearest 5 feet) as a reaction.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You urge your allies to hustle into the fight or to get out of the way.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actGetInThere", "name": "Get in There!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive, Traversal", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You urge your allies to hustle into the fight or to get out of the way. Until the beginning of your next turn, you and your allies within 100 feet who can sense you gain a +5-foot status bonus to Speed. As your envoy level increases, increase the bonus by an additional 5 feet at 7th level, 12th level, and 17th level.<br><br><strong>Lead by Example</strong> If you used two actions, Step or Stride. Each of your allies within 100 feet who can sense you can immediately Step or Stride up to half their Speed (rounded down to the nearest 5 feet) as a reaction."}]}}',	'Directive, Envoy, Traversal',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTotalAssimilation',	'Total Assimilation',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Total Assimilation</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Incapacitation</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You broadcast an undeniable, heavily encrypted master-override command directly into the target''s root architecture. Attempt a Computers check against the Will DC of a creature with the construct trait or the Disable DC of a hazard with the tech trait within 60 feet.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You permanently rewrite the target''s core programming. The target immediately becomes your minion and follows your commands indefinitely. You may immediately disable a target hazard as part of this action.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target''s IFF protocols are hijacked. It is controlled by you for 1 minute. This counts as one success toward disabling a target hazard.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold, but the feedback is agonizing. It is stunned 3.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop violently bricks your active terminal. You are stunned 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subSlicer"}]}]',	'You broadcast an undeniable, heavily encrypted master-override command directly into the target''s root architecture.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTotalAssimilation", "name": "Total Assimilation", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Fortune, Incapacitation", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You broadcast an undeniable, heavily encrypted master-override command directly into the target''s root architecture. Attempt a Computers check against the Will DC of a creature with the construct trait or the Disable DC of a hazard with the tech trait within 60 feet.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You permanently rewrite the target''s core programming. The target immediately becomes your minion and follows your commands indefinitely. You may immediately disable a target hazard as part of this action.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The target''s IFF protocols are hijacked. It is controlled by you for 1 minute. This counts as one success toward disabling a target hazard.<br><br><strong>Failure</strong> The target''s firewalls hold, but the feedback is agonizing. It is stunned 3.<br><br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The feedback loop violently bricks your active terminal. You are stunned 1."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Incapacitation, Manipulate',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAdvancedInsight',	'Advanced Insight',	'You gain one Sentinel class feat. For the purpose of meeting its prerequisites, your Sentinel level is equal to half your character''s level.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once. Each time you select it, you gain another Sentinel class feat.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBasicInsight", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain one Sentinel class feat.',	NULL,	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class_feat"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Sentinel Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Sentinel"], "max_level": "{slot_level // 2}"}}]}',	'Archetype',	6,	'1',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftRangedDefibrillation',	'Ranged Defibrillation',	'You upgrade your medical nanites to act as localized, ballistic defibrillators. You can perform the Administer First Aid action on targets up to 30 feet away. Additionally, if you successfully use Administer First Aid to stabilize a dying creature, that creature also regains 1 Hit Point, though their wounded condition still increases as normal.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subBioTech"}]}]',	'You upgrade your medical nanites to act as localized, ballistic defibrillators.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftFanTheHammer',	'Fan the Hammer',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Fan the Hammer</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>Your last action this turn was an Area Fire or Auto-Fire.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You hold down the trigger and continue blasting. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire, ignoring your weapon’s unwieldy trait. You don’t designate a primary target with this attack, and creatures you damage with this attack don’t gain the suppressed condition.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You hold down the trigger and continue blasting.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFanTheHammer", "name": "Fan the Hammer", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You hold down the trigger and continue blasting. You Area Fire or Auto-Fire, ignoring your weapon’s unwieldy trait. You don’t designate a primary target with this attack, and creatures you damage with this attack don’t gain the suppressed condition.", "requirements": "Your last action this turn was an Area Fire or Auto-Fire."}]}}',	'Soldier',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftQuickDeploy',	'Quick Deploy',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Quick Deploy</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You have heavily modified your rig''s harnesses and holsters for maximum efficiency. You Interact to draw a weapon or a technological item, then immediately Strike with that weapon or activate that item (provided the item''s activation costs exactly 1 action).
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You have heavily modified your rig''s harnesses and holsters for maximum efficiency.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actQuickDeploy", "name": "Quick Deploy", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You have heavily modified your rig''s harnesses and holsters for maximum efficiency. You Interact to draw a weapon or a technological item, then immediately Strike with that weapon or activate that item (provided the item''s activation costs exactly 1 action)."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftForceNegotiator',	'Force Negotiator',	'You can sense the emotional currents in a conversation. You can use your Wisdom modifier instead of Charisma for Diplomacy checks. If you spend 1 minute conversing with a creature, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Perception DC against their Deception attempts.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subPathOfTheWatchman"}]}]',	'You can sense the emotional currents in a conversation.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Force Negotiator", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to DC against Deception after 1 minute of conversation.", "target": "all"}]}}',	'Sentinel',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftForceShield',	'Force Shield',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Force Shield</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Level 2</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Guardian</span><span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You create a barrier of Force energy around yourself. You gain temporary Hit Points equal to 1d10 + your Wisdom modifier. These temporary HP last for 1 minute.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"is": "subCauseOfTheStalwart"}]}]',	'You raise a barrier of pure force.',	'clsGuardian',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powForceShield", "name": "Force Shield", "level": 2, "traits": "Guardian, Force Power", "action_cost": ["one-action"], "description": "You raise a barrier of pure force.. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC until the start of your next turn. This counts as Raising a Shield that you can use for the Shield Block reaction. The shield has Hardness equal to 2 + your Level and dissipates after blocking.\n\nAfter you''ve blocked using this shield, you cannot use this action again for 1 minute."}]}}',	'Guardian, Force Power',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDuelistsPride',	'Duelist''s Pride',	'Your defense is impenetrable, and your counters are instant. While in Makashi Stance, you gain an extra Reaction at the start of each of your turns that can only be used for Contentious Riposte.

<strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> Your superiority is absolute. Against your Dueling Target, your attacks ignore all circumstance conuses to AC (such as from Shields, Parrying, or Cover). Additionally, if your Dueling Target misses you with a melee attack, they become Off-Guard to you until the end of your next turn.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSurgicalPrecision", "type": "form"}]}]',	'Your defense is impenetrable, and your counters are instant.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Form',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDisarmingPresence',	'Disarming Presence',	'Your connection to the Force projects an aura of calm (or dread). While Connected, hostile creatures within 10 feet of you take a –1 circumstance penalty to Attack Rolls made against you.',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": ["subMandateOfTheSage", "subMandateOfVisions"]}]}]',	'Your connection to the Force projects an aura of calm (or dread).',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular, Connected Mental, Emotion',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftLazariteInfusion',	'Lazarite Infusion',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Lazarite Infusion</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Healing</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You inject an ally with a miracle-tier cocktail of experimental, self-replicating regenerative nanites. Target an ally within your reach. They immediately regain all of their Hit Points, their wounded condition is reduced to 0, and they are instantly cured of all non-magical poisons and diseases. If the target has died within the last minute, they are immediately restored to life with full Hit Points and no negative conditions, bypassing the need for a Medicine check entirely.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subBioTech"}]}]',	'You inject an ally with a miracle-tier cocktail of experimental, self-replicating regenerative nanites.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLazariteInfusion", "name": "Lazarite Infusion", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You inject an ally with a miracle-tier cocktail of experimental, self-replicating regenerative nanites. Target an ally within your reach. They immediately regain all of their Hit Points, their wounded condition is reduced to 0, and they are instantly cured of all non-magical poisons and diseases. If the target has died within the last minute, they are immediately restored to life with full Hit Points and no negative conditions, bypassing the need for a Medicine check entirely."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftIncredibleBeastmasterCompanion',	'Incredible Beastmaster Companion',	'Your mature animal companions continue to grow and develop. Each of them becomes a nimble or savage animal companion, gaining additional capabilities determined by the type of companion. You choose nimble or savage individually for each companion, including any companion that becomes mature after you take this feat.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMatureBeastmasterCompanion", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your mature animal companions continue to grow and develop.',	NULL,	'{"minion": {"apply_template": "mature", "template_choice": {"key": "companion_type", "label": "Companion Type", "options": ["nimble", "savage"]}}}',	'Archetype',	8,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftShellShower',	'Shell Shower',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shell Shower</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>once per round</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Whether you got tired of getting hit in the face or slipping on bullet casings in the middle of a fight, you’ve learned how to redirect your weapon’s spent ammunition or terrain warping vented energy while firing off a barrage. After you make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack with a weapon, make any number of squares adjacent to you difficult terrain. If a square was already difficult terrain, it instead becomes greater difficult terrain. Any difficult or greater difficult terrain created by this action remains in place until cleared.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Whether you got tired of getting hit in the face or slipping on bullet casings in the middle of a fight, you’ve learned how to redirect your weapon’s spent ammunition or terrain warping vented energy while firing off a barrage.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShellShower", "name": "Shell Shower", "traits": "Soldier", "frequency": "once per round", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "Whether you got tired of getting hit in the face or slipping on bullet casings in the middle of a fight, you’ve learned how to redirect your weapon’s spent ammunition or terrain warping vented energy while firing off a barrage. After you make an Area Fire or Auto-Fire attack with a weapon, make any number of squares adjacent to you difficult terrain. If a square was already difficult terrain, it instead becomes greater difficult terrain. Any difficult or greater difficult terrain created by this action remains in place until cleared."}]}}',	'Soldier',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftForceInterrogation',	'Force Interrogation',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Force Interrogation</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You force the truth from a mind. Attempt a Perception check against the Will DC of an adjacent creature.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You learn one surface thought or fact from the target, and they are Stunned 1.<br><strong>Success</strong> You sense their general emotional state and intent (Hostile, Fearful, Deceptive).
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": ["subPathOfTheJusticar", "subPathOfTheWatchman"]}]}]',	'You force the truth from a mind.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForceInterrogation", "name": "Force Interrogation", "traits": "Sentinel, Mental", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You force the truth from a mind. Attempt a Perception check against the Will DC of an adjacent creature.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> You learn one surface thought or fact from the target, and they are Stunned 1.<br><strong>Success</strong> You sense their general emotional state and intent (Hostile, Fearful, Deceptive)."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Mental',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftReactiveDeflectors',	'Reactive Deflectors',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Reactive Deflectors</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are targeted by an attack, but the attack roll has not yet been made.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You rapidly flare your rig''s micro-shields or magnetize your armor plating. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Armor Class against the triggering attack.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You rapidly flare your rig''s micro-shields or magnetize your armor plating.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actReactiveDeflectors", "name": "Reactive Deflectors", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "trigger": "You are targeted by an attack, but the attack roll has not yet been made.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You rapidly flare your rig''s micro-shields or magnetize your armor plating. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Armor Class against the triggering attack."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftRedundantSubroutines',	'Redundant Subroutines',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Redundant Subroutines</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You fail or critically fail your Overclock flat check.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You maintain a parallel processing environment to catch catastrophic logic errors before they fry your hardware. You immediately reroll the flat check and must use the second result, even if it is worse.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You maintain a parallel processing environment to catch catastrophic logic errors before they fry your hardware.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRedundantSubroutines", "name": "Redundant Subroutines", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Fortune", "trigger": "You fail or critically fail your Overclock flat check.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You maintain a parallel processing environment to catch catastrophic logic errors before they fry your hardware. You immediately reroll the flat check and must use the second result, even if it is worse."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Fortune',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftExpertSentinel',	'Expert Sentinel',	'Your foresight warns you of danger and grants you superior tactical control. Your proficiency rank for your Sentinel class DC increases to expert.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSentinelDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your foresight warns you of danger and grants you superior tactical control.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Sentinel Class DC", "rank": "Expert", "attribute": "WIS"}]}',	'Archetype',	12,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftBeastmasterDedication',	'Beastmaster Dedication',	'You gain the service of a young animal companion that travels with you and obeys your commands. Contrary to the usual rules for animal companions, this feat can grant you a second animal companion. If you ever have more than one animal companion, you gain the Call Companion action.',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	'You gain the service of a young animal companion that travels with you and obeys your commands.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCallCompanion", "name": "Call Companion", "traits": "Exploration", "action_cost": null, "description": "You spend 1 minute calling for a different animal companion, switching your active companion for another of your animal companions."}]}, "minion": {"companion_slot": [{"count": 1, "label": "Animal Companion", "trait_filter": "Animal"}]}}',	'Archetype, Dedication',	2,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftMuzzleFlash',	'Muzzle Flash',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Muzzle Flash</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You’re wielding a gun.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your attack distracts your foe. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If the Strike hits, the creature becomes dazzled until the end of your next turn if it''s within your first range increment.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your attack distracts your foe.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMuzzleFlash", "name": "Muzzle Flash", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "Your attack distracts your foe. You Aim and then make a ranged Strike against your mark. If the Strike hits, the creature becomes dazzled until the end of your next turn if it''s within your first range increment.", "requirements": "You’re wielding a gun."}]}}',	'Operative',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBasicConsularTelekinesis',	'Basic Consular Telekinesis',	'You gain the Telekinetic Impact Force Power. You have learned to project raw kinetic energy even without achieving a deep meditative focus. You can use the 1-action version of this power even if you are not in the Connected state. You must be in the Connected state to use the 2-action version of this power or to heighten it.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftConsularDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the Telekinetic Impact Force Power.',	NULL,	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powTelekineticImpact", "name": "Telekinetic Impact", "level": 1, "range": "30 feet", "target": "1 creature", "traits": "Force Power, Attack, Connected", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You batter a target with compressed air or debris. Make an attack roll against the target using The Force. This attack deals 1d8 Bludgeoning damage. This damage increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level. If you spend 2 actions, add your Wisdom modifier to the damage."}]}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcConsular'),
('cftUpgradedDroidChassisA',	'Upgraded Droid Chassis',	'You have installed superior servos, reinforced plating, and expanded memory banks into your companion.

Your droid companion''s proficiency rank for unarmed attacks and unarmored defense increases to expert. Its attributes for Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, and Wisdom each increase by 1. Its unarmed attacks deal two dice of damage instead of one.

Your droid is outfitted with specialized internal compartments and retractable instruments. It counts as a set of Tactical-grade tools (granting a +1 item bonus to the relevant skill checks) for a skill of your choice, such as Computers, Thievery, or Crafting. You can reconfigure its internal arrays to function as tools for a different applicable skill with 10 minutes of work.

Even if you don''t use the Command an Animal action, your droid companion can still use 1 action on your turn to Stride or Strike.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftDroidCompanionDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have installed superior servos, reinforced plating, and expanded memory banks into your companion.',	NULL,	'{"minion": {"apply_template": "upgraded"}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcDroidCompanion'),
('cftTechSpecialistDedication',	'Tech Specialist Dedication',	'You assemble a basic Custom Rig to assist your primary skill set. Your Custom Rig weighs 1 Bulk and functions as a commercial repair toolkit. You become trained in Crafting; for each of these skills in which you were already trained, you become trained in a skill of your choice. You become trained in tech specialist class DC. You calculate your tech specialist class DC using Intelligence.
You also compile a basic Modification Library containing two Level 1 Modifications of your choice. You can keep exactly one Modification actively installed in your Custom Rig at a time, granting you its permanent Standby benefit and the ability to activate it (but not Overclock it). You can swap your installed Modification during your daily preparations, or by spending 10 minutes to perform a Hot-Swap.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained two other feats from the Tech Specialist archetype.',	'[{"attribute": [{"int": 2}]}]',	'You assemble a basic Custom Rig to assist your primary skill set.',	NULL,	'{"1": {"modification": {"library_slot": {"count": 2}}}, "dc": [{"name": "Tech Specialist Class DC", "rank": "Trained", "attribute": "INT"}], "item": {"grant": [{"id": "idCustomRig", "bulk": 1, "name": "Custom Rig", "level": 0, "traits": "Toolkit", "equipped": true, "features": {"reduce_bulk": 999}, "quantity": 1, "item_type": "item", "is_container": true, "trait_filter": ["Toolkit"], "contained_item_ids": [], "always_process_contents": true}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLearnAModification", "name": "Learn a Modification", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Downtime", "description": "<p>You spend time reverse-engineering and compiling a new Modification to permanently add to your Modification Library. This requires spending a specific amount of time and credits on specialized        compilers, decryption keys, or hardware components, and attempting a <strong>Crafting</strong> check against a standard DC corresponding to the Modification&#39;s level.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Level 1 Modification:</strong> Requires 1 hour and costs <strong>20 credits</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Level 7 Modification:</strong>Requires 4 hours and costs <strong>360 credits</strong>.</p></li><li><p><strong>Level 15 Modification:</strong> Requires 8 hours and costs <strong>6,500 credits</strong>.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> You successfully compile the Modification and add it to your Modification Library. Your brilliant optimization means you only spend half the required credits.<br><strong>Success</strong> You successfully compile the Modification, spend the required credits, and add it to your Modification Library.<br><strong>Failure</strong> You can&#39;t fully integrate the schematic with your rig&#39;s architecture. You don&#39;t spend the credits, but you can&#39;t try to learn this specific Modification again until you gain a level.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> You catastrophically corrupt the data or fry the necessary hardware components during the attempt. You waste half the required credits and can&#39;t try to learn this specific Modification again until you gain a level.</p>", "requirements": "You have access to a physical schematic, an encrypted data shard, or an allied Tech Specialist who knows the Modification you want to learn."}]}, "modification": {"mod_slot": {"count": 1}}}',	'Archetype, Dedication, Multiclass',	2,	'0',	'arcTechSpecialist'),
('cftBasicConduit',	'Basic Conduit',	'You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level Consular class feat of your choice.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftConsularDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain a 1st- or 2nd-level Consular class feat of your choice.',	NULL,	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "class_feat"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "class_feat", "label": "Consular Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["Consular"], "max_level": 2}}]}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcConsular'),
('cftAdditionalCompanion',	'Additional Companion',	'Another animal joins you in your travels. It is a young animal companion that has the minion trait. See Beastmaster Animal Companions for rules on how having multiple animal companions works.

<strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once, gaining an additional animal companion each time, to a maximum of four total companions from all sources.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Another animal joins you in your travels.',	NULL,	'{"minion": {"companion_slot": [{"count": 1, "label": "Additional Companion", "trait_filter": "Animal"}]}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'1',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftOffensiveDefense',	'Offensive Defense',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Offensive Defense</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You have a force field upgrade in your armor or are holding a tech shield.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You overcharge a shield to create a concussive blast that repulses nearby foes. You Area Fire using your force field or shield, dealing 2d10 bludgeoning damage in a 5-foot radius burst centered on one corner of a square you occupy. This attack has the tracking +1 trait and is in the shield weapon group. A creature that fails its save is pushed back 5 feet. If you have the primary target class feature, the primary target Strike uses your force field or shield.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> If you''re using a force field or shield that''s superior or better, the tracking trait increases to +2, or +3 if ultimate or better. Likewise, if it''s elite or better, the damage increases to 3d10, or 4d10 if paragon.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You overcharge a shield to create a concussive blast that repulses nearby foes.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOffensiveDefense", "name": "Offensive Defense", "traits": "Soldier", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "    You overcharge a shield to create a concussive blast that repulses nearby foes. You Area Fire using your force field or shield, dealing 2d10 bludgeoning damage in a 5-foot radius burst centered on one corner of a square you occupy. This attack has the tracking +1 trait and is in the shield weapon group. A creature that fails its save is pushed back 5 feet. If you have the primary target class feature, the primary target Strike uses your force field or shield.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> If you''re using a force field or shield that''s superior or better, the tracking trait increases to +2, or +3 if ultimate or better. Likewise, if it''s elite or better, the damage increases to 3d10, or 4d10 if paragon.", "requirements": "You have a force field upgrade in your armor or are holding a tech shield."}]}}',	'Soldier',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTelekineticThrow',	'Telekinetic Throw',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Telekinetic Throw</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 1</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a melee weapon of the Lightsaber weapon group or with the Finesse trait.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You use the Force to guide your weapon through the air and pull it back. Make a Ranged Strike with the weapon against a target within 30 feet. This attack uses your normal melee attack bonuses and modifiers. After the attack, the weapon returns to your hand. If you use Force Premonition before this attack and the target is within 30 feet, you can use your Wisdom modifier for the attack roll and add your Sentinel''s Strike damage.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You use the Force to guide your weapon through the air and pull it back.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powTelekineticThrow", "name": "Telekinetic Throw", "traits": "Sentinel, Force Power", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You use the Force to guide your weapon through the air and pull it back. Make a Ranged Strike with the weapon against a target within 30 feet. This attack uses your normal melee attack bonuses and modifiers. After the attack, the weapon returns to your hand. If you use Force Premonition before this attack and the target is within 30 feet, you can use your Wisdom modifier for the attack roll and add your Sentinel''s Strike damage.", "requirements": "You are wielding a melee weapon of the Lightsaber weapon group or with the Finesse trait."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Force Power',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftExpertTechSpecialist',	'Expert Tech Specialist',	'You have extensively refined your rig''s targeting algorithms and brute-force processing speeds. Your proficiency rank for your Tech Specialist class DC increases to expert.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftTechSpecialistDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have extensively refined your rig''s targeting algorithms and brute-force processing speeds.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Tech Specialist Class DC", "rank": "Expert", "attribute": "INT"}]}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcTechSpecialist'),
('cftMasterSentinel',	'Master Sentinel',	'Your precognitive abilities and mastery of reality reach their pinnacle. Your proficiency rank for your Sentinel class DC increases to master.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftExpertSentinel", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your precognitive abilities and mastery of reality reach their pinnacle.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Sentinel Class DC", "rank": "Master", "attribute": "WIS"}]}',	'Archetype',	18,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftScoutsSpeed',	'Scout''s Speed',	'You move faster, especially when traveling, allowing you to scout out ahead and report back without slowing your allies. You gain a +10-foot status bonus to your Speed. When calculating your travel speed, this increases to a +20-foot status bonus.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftScoutDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You move faster, especially when traveling, allowing you to scout out ahead and report back without slowing your allies.',	NULL,	'{"speed": {"bonus": [{"base": "10"}]}}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcScout'),
('cftHurry',	'Hurry',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Hurry</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You urge an ally to pick up the pace and contribute more to the events happening around them. One ally within 30 feet who can sense you becomes quickened for 1 round. They can use the extra action to Interact, Step, or Stride. The target is then temporarily immune to Hurry for the next 10 minutes.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You urge an ally to pick up the pace and contribute more to the events happening around them.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHurry", "name": "Hurry", "traits": "Envoy, Mental, Traversal", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You urge an ally to pick up the pace and contribute more to the events happening around them. One ally within 30 feet who can sense you becomes quickened for 1 round. They can use the extra action to Interact, Step, or Stride. The target is then temporarily immune to Hurry for the next 10 minutes."}]}}',	'Envoy, Mental, Traversal',	6,	'0',	NULL),
('cftAnimalEmpathy',	'Animal Empathy',	'You have a connection to the creatures of the natural world that allows you to communicate with them on a rudimentary level. You can use Diplomacy to Make an Impression on animals and to make very simple Requests of them. In most cases, wild animals will give you time to make your case.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have a connection to the creatures of the natural world that allows you to communicate with them on a rudimentary level.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftMakashiStance',	'Form II: Makashi',	'The dueling form. Elegant, precise, and specifically designed for single combat. It relies on footwork, feints, and punishing the mistakes of the opponent.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Makashi Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber in one hand with your other hand free.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You adopt a duelist''s profile. You designate one visible enemy as your Dueling Target. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against melee attacks from that target. You can change your Dueling Target as a single action (or as a Free Action if the target drops to 0 HP).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can use Feint against your Dueling Target as a Free Action once per round.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The dueling form. Elegant, precise, and specifically designed for single combat. It relies on footwork, feints, and punishing the mistakes of the opponent.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMakashiStance", "name": "Makashi Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You adopt a duelist''s profile. You designate one visible enemy as your Dueling Target. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against melee attacks from that target. You can change your Dueling Target as a single action (or as a Free Action if the target drops to 0 HP).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can use Feint against your Dueling Target as a Free Action once per round.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber in one hand with your other hand free."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOpportuneRetort',	'Opportune Retort',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Opportune Retort</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>A creature critically fails on a melee attack roll against you.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You take advantage of the opening in your foe’s defenses. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You take advantage of the opening in your foe’s defenses.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOpportuneRetort", "name": "Opportune Retort", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You take advantage of the opening in your foe’s defenses. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature.", "requirements": "A creature critically fails on a melee attack roll against you."}]}}',	'Operative',	10,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMasterTechSpecialist',	'Master Tech Specialist',	'Your hardware and software are operating at absolute peak efficiency, leaving almost no room for enemies to evade your tech. Your proficiency rank for your Tech Specialist class DC increases to master.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftExpertTechSpecialist", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your hardware and software are operating at absolute peak efficiency, leaving almost no room for enemies to evade your tech.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Tech Specialist Class DC", "rank": "Master", "attribute": "INT"}]}',	'Archetype',	18,	'0',	'arcTechSpecialist'),
('cftForceFlight',	'Force Flight',	'While Connected, you gain a permanent Fly Speed equal to your Speed. You do not need to spend actions to maintain it.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftForceLevitation", "type": "class"}]}]',	'While Connected, you gain a permanent Fly Speed equal to your Speed. You do not need to spend actions to maintain it.',	'clsConsular',	NULL,	'Consular, Connected',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftConsularConnection',	'Consular Connection',	'You have learned to fully center yourself and allow the Force to flow through you freely. You gain the Open Connection action, allowing you to enter the Connected state. You can now utilize Force Powers and abilities that possess the Connected trait.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftConsularDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have learned to fully center yourself and allow the Force to flow through you freely.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOpenConnection", "name": "Open Connection", "traits": "Concentrate, Force Power, Stance", "frequency": "Once per round", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You center yourself, allowing the Force to flow through you freely. You enter the Connected state. While Connected, you can use abilities with the Connected trait. While Connected, you can use the Telekinetic Impact action. If you fall unconscious, the connection ends. You cannot use Open Connection if you are fatigued."}]}}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcConsular'),
('cftAlterFate',	'Alter Fate',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Alter Fate</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 18</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Misfortune</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>A creature within 60 feet rolls an attack roll, saving throw, or skill check.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per 10 minutes</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You saw the result before it happened and nudged reality to change the outcome. The target must reroll the check.br<><br>If the target is an ally, then they take the better of the two results. If the target is an enemym then they take the worse of the two results.<br><br>You can use this reaction after seeing the result of the die roll, but before the GM declares the final outcome.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You saw the result before it happened and nudged reality to change the outcome.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powAlterFate", "name": "Alter Fate", "level": 18, "traits": "Sentinel, Force Power, Fortune, Misfortune", "trigger": "A creature within 60 feet rolls an attack roll, saving throw, or skill check.", "frequency": "Once per 10 minutes", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You saw the result before it happened and nudged reality to change the outcome. The target must reroll the check.br<><br>If the target is an ally, then they take the better of the two results. If the target is an enemym then they take the worse of the two results.<br><br>You can use this reaction after seeing the result of the die roll, but before the GM declares the final outcome."}]}}',	'Sentinel',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOverwhelmingShot',	'Overwhelming Shot',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Overwhelming Shot</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You pierce through your foe''s resistance with a well-timed shot. You Aim and then make a Strike against your mark. Select one of the following damage types: acid, bludgeoning, cold, electricity, fire, mental, piercing, poison, slashing, or sonic damage. Your shot ignores an amount of the target''s resistance to the selected damage type equal to your level. If the creature has a weakness to the selected damage type, increase that weakness by an amount equal to half your level. A creature''s immunities are unaffected.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You pierce through your foe''s resistance with a well-timed shot.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOverwhelmingShot", "name": "Overwhelming Shot", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You pierce through your foe''s resistance with a well-timed shot. You Aim and then make a Strike against your mark. Select one of the following damage types: acid, bludgeoning, cold, electricity, fire, mental, piercing, poison, slashing, or sonic damage. Your shot ignores an amount of the target''s resistance to the selected damage type equal to your level. If the creature has a weakness to the selected damage type, increase that weakness by an amount equal to half your level. A creature''s immunities are unaffected."}]}}',	'Operative',	12,	'0',	NULL),
('cftCamouflage',	'Camouflage',	'You alter your appearance to blend in to the wilderness. In natural terrain, you can Hide and Sneak even without cover or being concealed.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftScoutDedication", "type": "class"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	'You alter your appearance to blend in to the wilderness.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	12,	'0',	'arcScout'),
('cftSlicerUplink',	'Slicer Uplink',	'You have hardwired a direct command uplink to your droid''s slicing tools. When your droid companion is adjacent to a terminal, control panel, or technological lock, you can command it to slice the system. You can perform Computers and Thievery skill actions through your droid companion, using your own skill modifiers and proficiency ranks. Your droid must have the appropriate physical tools to attempt the check.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftDroidCompanionDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have hardwired a direct command uplink to your droid''s slicing tools.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcDroidCompanion'),
('cftInfinitePower',	'Infinite Power',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Infinite Power</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Consular</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Connected</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Overexertion</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You use a Force Power that deals damage or restores HP.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You channel the full might of the Cosmic Force. Do not roll dice for damage or healing; instead, treat every die as having rolled its maximum possible value.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You channel the full might of the Cosmic Force.',	'clsConsular',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actInfinitePower", "name": "Infinite Power", "traits": "Consular, Connected, Overexertion", "trigger": "You use a Force Power that deals damage or restores HP.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You channel the full might of the Cosmic Force. Do not roll dice for damage or healing; instead, treat every die as having rolled its maximum possible value."}]}}',	'Consular, Connected, Overexertion',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBestialProtection',	'Bestial Protection',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion that’s Large or larger

Your companion''s mere presence is enough to rattle creatures that fall under its shadow. When a creature adjacent to your animal companion that''s smaller than it targets you with an attack, that creature becomes frightened 1.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your companion''s mere presence is enough to rattle creatures that fall under its shadow.',	NULL,	NULL,	'Archetype, Emotion, Fear, Mental',	6,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftDangerAwareness',	'Danger Awareness',	'You have an intuitive sense that alerts you to danger and allows you to discern the presence of hidden threats. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Perception checks to find traps and hidden, undetected, and unnoticed creatures; to AC against attacks made by traps and hidden, undetected, and unnoticed creatures; and to saves against traps. Even if you aren’t Searching, you get a check to find traps that normally require you to be Searching. You still need to meet any other requirements to find the trap. If your initiative result is tied with an opponent, you always go first.',	NULL,	'You have an intuitive sense that alerts you to danger and allows you to discern the presence of hidden threats.',	'clsOperative',	'{"ac": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Danger Awareness", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against attacks made by traps and hidden, undetected, and unnoticed creatures.", "target": "ac"}]}, "perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Danger Awareness", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to find traps and hidden, undetected, and unnoticed creatures.", "target": "all"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Danger Awareness", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against traps.", "target": "reflex"}]}]}',	'Operative',	2,	'0',	NULL),
('cftStimDispenser',	'Stim Dispenser',	'Your droid is equipped with a small fabrication matrix or storage cylinder for bacta stims. Your droid companion gains the Dispense Stim action.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftDroidCompanionDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your droid is equipped with a small fabrication matrix or storage cylinder for bacta stims.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDispenseStim", "name": "Dispense Stim", "traits": "Archetype", "frequency": "A number of times per day equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum 1).", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The droid injects a potent dose of bacta into the ally. The ally regains 1d8 Hit Points. This healing increases by 1d8 for every 2 levels you have beyond 4th.", "requirements": "The droid is adjacent to a living ally or sharing a living ally''s space."}]}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcDroidCompanion'),
('cftSizeUp',	'Size Up',	'You spend 1 minute observing a specific individual, 10 minutes researching a specific individual on the infosphere, or 1 hour networking and gathering information. This subject is your asset. If you assess your asset via observation, you don''t need to know their identity, but if you assess your asset via research or networking, you must know their identity, which requires at least two relevant pieces of information about them. Examples of relevant information could include their name, their place of origin, their current residence, the name of their parent or significant other, their employer, or their organizational affiliation. The GM determines what constitutes relevant information for this purpose, based on the asset you''ve selected.

You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Deception, Diplomacy, Intimidation, and Perception checks against or in relation to your asset, and a +1 circumstance bonus to attempts to Recall Knowledge about your asset.

You gain the benefits of the 2-action Get ''Em! when using 1-action Get ''Em! on an asset.

You can maintain a number of assets equal to your Charisma modifier. If you Size Up other assets after that, your new asset replaces a previous one.',	NULL,	'You spend 1 minute observing a specific individual, 10 minutes researching a specific individual on the infosphere, or 1 hour networking and gathering information.',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Size Up", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus regarding your asset.", "target": "sklDeception"}, {"name": "Size Up", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus regarding your asset.", "target": "sklDiplomacy"}, {"name": "Size Up", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus regarding your asset.", "target": "sklIntimidation"}, {"name": "Size Up", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Recall Knowledge about your asset.", "target": "all"}]}, "perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Size Up", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus regarding your asset.", "target": "all"}]}}',	'Concentrate, Envoy, Exploration',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftResuscitate',	'Resuscitate',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Resuscitate</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Healing</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are holding a medkit, or you are wearing one and have a hand free.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You resuscitate the dead. Attempt a DC 40 Medicine check to revive a dead creature who has been dead for no more than 3 rounds and whose body is mostly intact. If you succeed, the target returns to life with 1 Hit Point, and still with any long-term debilitations of the old body. If the target had the wounded condition, its value increases by 1; otherwise the target gains the wounded 1 condition. Even revived, death leaves the target temporarily debilitated, making it clumsy 2, drained 2, and enfeebled 2 for 1 week; these conditions can''t be removed or reduced by any means until the week has passed. Whether you succeed or fail, the target is temporarily immune to Resuscitate for 1 day.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMedicDedication", "type": "class"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	'You resuscitate the dead.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actResuscitate", "name": "Resuscitate", "traits": "Archetype, Healing, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You resuscitate the dead. Attempt a DC 40 Medicine check to revive a dead creature who has been dead for no more than 3 rounds and whose body is mostly intact. If you succeed, the target returns to life with the effects of raise dead, except it still has the wounded condition it had before dying, increased by 1 (or wounded 1 if it wasn’t wounded before dying). Whether you succeed or fail, the target is temporarily immune to Resuscitate for 1 day.", "requirements": "You are holding a medkit, or you are wearing one and have a hand free."}]}}',	'Archetype, Healing, Manipulate',	16,	'0',	'arcMedic'),
('cftPackMovement',	'Pack Movement',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Pack Movement</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You and your companion move to take down a common enemy. You and your animal companion both Stride. If both of you end your movement within reach of the same creature, you and your animal companion each make a melee Strike against the creature. You can use Pack Movement to Burrow, Climb, Fly, or Swim instead of Stride if both you and your animal companion have the corresponding movement type.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You and your companion move to take down a common enemy.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPackMovement", "name": "Pack Movement", "traits": "Archetype, Flourish", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You and your companion move to take down a common enemy. You and your animal companion both Stride. If both of you end your movement within reach of the same creature, you and your animal companion each make a melee Strike against the creature. You can use Pack Movement to Burrow, Climb, Fly, or Swim instead of Stride if both you and your animal companion have the corresponding movement type."}]}}',	'Archetype, Flourish',	8,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftSwiftGuardian',	'Swift Guardian',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Swift Guardian</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Concentrate</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You roll initative.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    When danger appears, you quickly send away your active companion and call in a different animal ally. You use Call Companion. The new animal companion typically arrives in the same location as the one that departed, though the GM might adjust this depending on the circumstances and Speeds of the animals. If you have Lead the Pack, you can swap one of your two active companions for an inactive companion.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'When danger appears, you quickly send away your active companion and call in a different animal ally. ',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSwiftGuardian", "name": "Swift Guardian", "traits": "Archetype, Concentrate", "trigger": "You roll initative.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "When danger appears, you quickly send away your active companion and call in a different animal ally. You use Call Companion. The new animal companion typically arrives in the same location as the one that departed, though the GM might adjust this depending on the circumstances and Speeds of the animals. If you have Lead the Pack, you can swap one of your two active companions for an inactive companion."}]}}',	'Archetype, Concentrate',	6,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftExpertConsular',	'Expert Consular',	'Your connection to the Force deepens, making your powers much harder to resist. Your proficiency rank for your Consular class DC increases to expert.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftConsularDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your connection to the Force deepens, making your powers much harder to resist.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Consular Class DC", "rank": "Expert", "attribute": "WIS"}]}',	'Archetype',	12,	'0',	'arcConsular'),
('cftMasterConsular',	'Master Consular',	'Your mastery over the Force rivals that of the Jedi High Council. Your proficiency rank for your Consular class DC increases to master.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftExpertConsular", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your mastery over the Force rivals that of the Jedi High Council.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Consular Class DC", "rank": "Master", "attribute": "WIS"}]}',	'Archetype',	18,	'0',	'arcConsular'),
('cftSystemOverclock',	'System Overclock',	'You learn how to bypass safety limiters and push your hardware to its absolute maximum yield. You gain the ability to use the Overclock activation for any Modification you currently have installed in your Custom Rig.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftTechSpecialistDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You learn how to bypass safety limiters and push your hardware to its absolute maximum yield.',	NULL,	'{"feature": ["clfOverclock"]}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcTechSpecialist'),
('cftParkour',	'Parkour',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Parkour</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You dash forward, unhindered by obstacles or walls. Stride and Long Jump or High Jump (in any order). You must start your movement on a horizontal surface. During this movement, you can ignore difficult terrain and run up vertical surfaces, like walls, at your full Speed. If you end the Stride off the ground, you fall after taking your next action or when your turn ends, whichever comes first (though you can Grab an Edge, if applicable).
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You dash forward, unhindered by obstacles or walls.',	'clsOperative',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actParkour", "name": "Parkour", "traits": "Operative, Flourish", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You dash forward, unhindered by obstacles or walls. Stride and Long Jump or High Jump (in any order). You must start your movement on a horizontal surface. During this movement, you can ignore difficult terrain and run up vertical surfaces, like walls, at your full Speed. If you end the Stride off the ground, you fall after taking your next action or when your turn ends, whichever comes first (though you can Grab an Edge, if applicable)."}]}}',	'Operative, Flourish',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOverwatch',	'Overwatch',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Overwatch</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Soldier</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>A suppressed creature within your weapon''s first range increment makes a ranged attack or leaves a square during a move action it''s using.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You concentrate fire on a specific target operating within your weapon’s threat range. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature, ignoring the unwieldy trait of weapons you wield for this Strike. On a critical hit, if the triggering action was a move action, you disrupt that action.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You concentrate fire on a specific target operating within your weapon’s threat range.',	'clsSoldier',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOverwatch", "name": "Overwatch", "traits": "Soldier", "trigger": "A suppressed creature within your weapon''s first range increment makes a ranged attack or leaves a square during a move action it''s using.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You concentrate fire on a specific target operating within your weapon’s threat range. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature, ignoring the unwieldy trait of weapons you wield for this Strike. On a critical hit, if the triggering action was a move action, you disrupt that action."}]}}',	'Soldier',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftRunningKick',	'Running Kick',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion with a foot, hoof, or talon unarmed attack

Your companion weaves in and out of combat, swiftly attacking before getting to a better position. Your companions with a qualifying unarmed attack learn the Running Kick activity.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Running Kick</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    This companion Strides up to twice its Speed and makes a hoof, foot, or talon Strike at any point during the movement. This movement doesn''t provoke reactions from a creature damaged by the Strike.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your companion weaves in and out of combat, swiftly attacking before getting to a better position.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRunningKick", "name": "Running Kick", "traits": "Archetype", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "This companion Strides up to twice its Speed and makes a hoof, foot, or talon Strike at any point during the movement. This movement doesn''t provoke reactions from a creature damaged by the Strike."}]}}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftMedicDedication',	'Medic Dedication',	'You become an expert in Medicine. When you succeed with Battle Medicine or Treat Wounds, the target gains a circumstance bonus to the number of Hit Points they regain equal to 5 HP at DC 20, 10 HP at DC 30, or 15 HP at DC 40.

Once per day, you can use Battle Medicine on a creature that’s temporarily immune due to having already been treated with Battle Medicine. If you’re a master in Medicine, you can do so once per hour.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaBattleMedicine", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	'You become an expert in Medicine.',	NULL,	'{"skill": {"upgrade": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "to": "Expert"}]}}',	'Archetype, Dedication',	2,	'0',	'arcMedic'),
('cftQuickDraw',	'Quick Draw',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Quick Draw</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You draw your weapon and attack with the same fluid motion. You Interact to draw a weapon, then Strike with that weapon.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> If you are a Path of the Artisan Sentinel, you can use this feat to Interact to draw a tool or device and then Activate it (if the activation is 1 action) or use it for a Skill Action (like Combat Slicing).
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You draw your weapon and attack with the same fluid motion.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actQuickDraw", "name": "Quick Draw", "traits": "Sentinel", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You draw your weapon and attack with the same fluid motion. You Interact to draw a weapon, then Strike with that weapon.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> If you are a Path of the Artisan Sentinel, you can use this feat to Interact to draw a tool or device and then Activate it (if the activation is 1 action) or use it for a Skill Action (like Combat Slicing)."}]}}',	'Sentinel',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftPosse',	'Posse',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Posse</h3>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Exploration</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You have designated prey with Hunt Prey.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    By spending 1 minute giving guidance to help hunt down your prey, you instruct up to five willing creatures to assist you. They gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Seek your prey, to Track your prey, and to Gather Information about your prey. You and the creatures assisting you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to initiative rolls when entering combat with your prey. These benefits lasts until you designate a new prey or your prey dies, whichever comes first. An individual creature assisting you loses this benefit if they’re out of your presence for too long to benefit from your instructions. This is usually 1 hour, but is determined by the GM.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBountyHunterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'By spending 1 minute giving guidance to help hunt down your prey, you instruct up to five willing creatures to assist you.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPosse", "name": "Posse", "traits": "Archetype, Exploration", "description": "By spending 1 minute giving guidance to help hunt down your prey, you instruct up to five willing creatures to assist you. They gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Seek your prey, to Track your prey, and to Gather Information about your prey. You and the creatures assisting you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to initiative rolls when entering combat with your prey. These benefits lasts until you designate a new prey or your prey dies, whichever comes first. An individual creature assisting you loses this benefit if they’re out of your presence for too long to benefit from your instructions. This is usually 1 hour, but is determined by the GM.", "requirements": "You have designated prey with Hunt Prey."}]}}',	'Archetype, Exploration',	4,	'0',	'arcBountyHunter'),
('cftPackTakedown',	'Pack Takedown',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Pack Takedown</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You have two active companions.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The pack is strongest when it acts as one, and like a group of hungry wolves, you work together to bring down a single target. If you and both of your active companions threaten the same creature, each of you makes a melee Strike against it. The creature is off-guard against all of these attacks. If more than one attack hits, combine the damage from all successful Strikes, and apply resistances and weaknesses only once.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftLeadThePack", "type": "class"}]}]',	'The pack is strongest when it acts as one, and like a group of hungry wolves, you work together to bring down a single target.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPackTakedown", "name": "Pack Takedown", "traits": "Archetype, Flourish", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "The pack is strongest when it acts as one, and like a group of hungry wolves, you work together to bring down a single target. If you and both of your active companions threaten the same creature, each of you makes a melee Strike against it. The creature is off-guard against all of these attacks. If more than one attack hits, combine the damage from all successful Strikes, and apply resistances and weaknesses only once.", "requirements": "You have two active companions."}]}}',	'Archetype, Flourish',	20,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftSabotage',	'Sabotage',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Sabotage</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Sentinel</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You introduce a fault. Attempt a Computers or Crafting check against the Reflex DC of a weapon or mechanical device within reach (or within 30 feet if you have a datajack).<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The item is damaged. If it is a weapon, attacks made with it take a –2 penalty. If it is a device, it malfunctions (GM discretion). This lasts for 1 minute or until the holder spends an Interact action to fix it.<br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The weapon jams or the device shuts down. It cannot be used until fixed.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subPathOfTheArtisan"}]}]',	'You introduce a fault.',	'clsSentinel',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSabotage", "name": "Sabotage", "traits": "Sentinel, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You introduce a fault. Attempt a Computers or Crafting check against the Reflex DC of a weapon or mechanical device within reach (or within 30 feet if you have a datajack).<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The item is damaged. If it is a weapon, attacks made with it take a –2 penalty. If it is a device, it malfunctions (GM discretion). This lasts for 1 minute or until the holder spends an Interact action to fix it.<br><strong>Critical Success</strong> The weapon jams or the device shuts down. It cannot be used until fixed."}]}}',	'Sentinel, Manipulation',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftOpportunisticGrapple',	'Opportunistic Grapple',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
