</div>',	NULL,	'You flood the area with brute-force processing and localized sensor-blinding telemetry.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSystemOverride", "name": "System Override", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate, Misfortune", "trigger": "You activate a Modification that requires targets to attempt a saving throw.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You flood the area with brute-force processing and localized sensor-blinding telemetry. All targets in the Modification''s area must roll their saving throw twice and use the worse result."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftFailSafeProtocols',	'Fail-Safe Protocols',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Fail-Safe Protocols</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Misfortune</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You roll a critical failure on a Fortitude or Reflex saving throw.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your rig instantly detects the catastrophic systemic failure and forcibly injects a stimulant, locks your armor servos, or overloads a micro-shield to absorb the brunt of the impact. You treat the result of your saving throw as a failure instead of a critical failure.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'Your rig instantly detects the catastrophic systemic failure and forcibly injects a stimulant, locks your armor servos, or overloads a micro-shield to absorb the brunt of the impact.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFailSafeProtocols", "name": "Fail-Safe Protocols", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Fortune", "trigger": "You roll a critical failure on a Fortitude or Reflex saving throw.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Your rig instantly detects the catastrophic systemic failure and forcibly injects a stimulant, locks your armor servos, or overloads a micro-shield to absorb the brunt of the impact. You treat the result of your saving throw as a failure instead of a critical failure."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Fortune',	16,	'0',	NULL),
('cftTechnologicalApotheosis',	'Technological Apotheosis',	'You and your hardware operate in perfect, seamless synchronization, bypassing biological reaction limits entirely. You are permanently quickened. You can use this extra action only to Stride, Step, Interact, or activate a Modification. (If you already have the Wetware Overclock feat, you can immediately retrain it).',	NULL,	'You and your hardware operate in perfect, seamless synchronization, bypassing biological reaction limits entirely.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftZeroDayExploit',	'Zero-Day Exploit',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Zero-Day Exploit</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fortune</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are about to roll a Computers, Crafting, or Thievery check.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You apply an unpatchable, god-tier bypass to the system you are interacting with. You do not roll the skill check; instead, you automatically treat the result of the check as a critical success.
  </div>
</div>',	NULL,	'You apply an unpatchable, god-tier bypass to the system you are interacting with.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actZeroDayExploit", "name": "Zero-Day Exploit", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Fortune", "trigger": "You are about to roll a Computers, Crafting, or Thievery check.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You apply an unpatchable, god-tier bypass to the system you are interacting with. You do not roll the skill check; instead, you automatically treat the result of the check as a critical success."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Fortune',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftExterminatorProtocol',	'Exterminator Protocol',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Exterminator Protocol</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a ranged technological weapon interfaced to your custom rig.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You unleash your weapon''s absolute maximum yield, temporarily disabling all heat sinks and safety limiters. Make a separate ranged Strike against any number of enemy targets within your weapon''s first range increment. These attacks do not count toward your multiple attack penalty until all of the attacks have been resolved. After the protocol is complete, your weapon overheats; it cannot be fired again until you spend three Interact actions to manually flush the thermal core.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subArmstech"}]}]',	'You unleash your weapon''s absolute maximum yield, temporarily disabling all heat sinks and safety limiters.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actExterminatorProtocol", "name": "Exterminator Protocol", "traits": "Tech Specialist", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You unleash your weapon''s absolute maximum yield, temporarily disabling all heat sinks and safety limiters. Make a separate ranged Strike against any number of enemy targets within your weapon''s first range increment. These attacks do not count toward your multiple attack penalty until all of the attacks have been resolved. After the protocol is complete, your weapon overheats; it cannot be fired again until you spend three Interact actions to manually flush the thermal core.", "requirements": "You are wielding a ranged technological weapon interfaced to your custom rig."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist',	20,	'0',	NULL),
('cftPanaceaNanites',	'Panacea Nanites',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Panacea Nanites</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Tech Specialist</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Healing</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Frequency</strong>
      <span>Once per day.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You rapidly vent your entire reserve of master-grade medical nanites into the air filtration or ambient atmosphere. All willing allies within a 30-foot emanation regain Hit Points equal to 10d8 plus your level. Additionally, the nanites automatically attempt a counteract check against every disease, poison, and persistent bleed effect currently affecting those allies, using your Medicine modifier for the counteract check.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"subclass": [{"id": "subBioTech"}]}]',	'You rapidly vent your entire reserve of master-grade medical nanites into the air filtration or ambient atmosphere.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPanaceaNanites", "name": "Panacea Nanites", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You rapidly vent your entire reserve of master-grade medical nanites into the air filtration or ambient atmosphere. All willing allies within a 30-foot emanation regain Hit Points equal to 10d8 plus your level. Additionally, the nanites automatically attempt a counteract check against every disease, poison, and persistent bleed effect currently affecting those allies, using your Medicine modifier for the counteract check."}]}}',	'Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate',	18,	'0',	NULL),
('cftMandalorianDedication',	'Mandalorian Dedication',	'You walk the path of the Mandalore. Honing your body and mind to match the unforgiving metal of your armor, you carry the weight of your culture''s legendary martial history into every battle. You become trained in Mandalorian Lore and your choice of Intimidation or Survival. If you are already trained in both skills, you become trained in another skill of your choice.<br><br>Additionally, you expand your armor training to accommodate traditional beskar''gam. You become trained in light armor. If you already have training in light armor, you gain training in medium armor. If you already have training in both, you gain training in heavy armor. If you are at least 13th level, you become an expert in any armor type this feat grants you, and you become a master at 19th level.<br><strong>Special</strong> You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained at least two other feats from this archetype.',	'[{"attribute": [{"str": 2}, {"dex": 2}]}]',	'You walk the path of the Mandalore.',	NULL,	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklLoreMandalorian", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "choice(''mando_dedication'')", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "mando_dedication", "type": "skill", "label": "Intimidation or Survival", "filter": {"id": ["sklIntimidation", "sklSurvival"]}}], "armor_progression": {"sequence": ["light", "medium", "heavy"], "base_rank": "Trained", "level_upgrades": [{"rank": "Expert", "min_level": 13}, {"rank": "Master", "min_level": 19}]}}',	'Archetype, Dedication',	2,	'0',	'arcMandalorian'),
('cftShiiChoStance',	'Form I: Shii-Cho',	'The oldest form, Shii-Cho is direct, sweeping, and relentless. It excels at managing multiple opponents and overwhelming defenses through pure kinetic energy.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shii-Cho Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You enter the foundational stance of the Jedi. While in this stance, your attacks with a lightsaber gain the Sweep trait (gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack roll if you have already attacked a different target this turn).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> When you make a Strike against a creature you have not yet attacked this turn, you ignore the multiple attack penalty for that specific strike.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The oldest form, Shii-Cho is direct, sweeping, and relentless. It excels at managing multiple opponents and overwhelming defenses through pure kinetic energy.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShiiChoStance", "name": "Shii-Cho Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You enter the foundational stance of the Jedi. While in this stance, your attacks with a lightsaber gain the Sweep trait (gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your attack roll if you have already attacked a different target this turn).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> When you make a Strike against a creature you have not yet attacked this turn, you ignore the multiple attack penalty for that specific strike.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSentinelDedication',	'Sentinel Dedication',	'You have learned to study reality and rely on precognition to guide your strikes like a Sentinel. You become trained in The Force and one additional skill of your choice. If you are already trained in The Force, you instead become trained in a skill of your choice.

You become trained in simple weapons and lightsabers, as well as the sentinel class DC.

Special: You cannot select another dedication feat until you have gained at least two other feats from the Sentinel archetype.',	'[{"attribute": [{"wis": 2}]}]',	'You have learned to study reality and rely on precognition to guide your strikes like a Sentinel.',	NULL,	'{"dc": [{"name": "Sentinel Class DC", "rank": "Trained", "attribute": "WIS"}], "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}], "skill_increase": [{"max": "Trained", "count": 1}]}, "attack": [{"simple": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}',	'Archetype, Dedication, Multiclass',	2,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftSpecializedBeastmasterCompanion',	'Specialized Beastmaster Companion',	'Your nimble and savage animal companions become cunning enough to become specialized. Each companion gains one specialization of your choice. Choose the specialization separately for each companion, including any companion that becomes specialized after you take this feat.

<strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once. Each time, add a different specialization to each of your nimble and savage companions. Your nimble and savage companions can have up to three specializations each.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftIncredibleBeastmasterCompanion", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your nimble and savage animal companions become cunning enough to become specialized.',	NULL,	'{"minion": {"specialization_choice": {"key": "spec", "label": "Companion Specialization", "options": {"bully": {"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert", "conditional_max": "Master"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert", "conditional_max": "Master"}], "attribute": {"cha": 3, "str": 1}}, "racer": {"attribute": {"con": 1}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Legendary"}}], "speed_choice": {"key": "racer_speed", "label": "Speed Bonus Type", "amount": 10, "options": ["base", "swim", "fly"]}}, "tracker": {"skill": [{"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert", "conditional_max": "Master"}], "attribute": {"wis": 1}, "ability_flags": ["track_at_full_speed"]}, "wrecker": {"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Master"}], "attribute": {"str": 1}, "ability_flags": ["ignore_half_hardness"]}, "ambusher": {"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Expert", "conditional_max": "Master"}], "attribute": {"dex": 1}, "proficiency": "Expert", "ability_flags": ["can_sneak_when_observed"], "proficiency_conditional_max": "Master"}, "daredevil": {"skill": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Master"}], "attribute": {"dex": 1}, "proficiency": "Expert", "ability_flags": ["deny_advantage"]}}}}}',	'Archetype',	14,	'1',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftJuyoVaapadStance',	'Form VII: Juyo/Vaapad',	'The forbidden form. It channels the user''s inner darkness (or enjoyment of the fight) into a conduit of pure destruction. It is high-risk, high-reward.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Juyo/Vaapad Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    ou open yourself to the chaos of battle. While in this stance, you take a –1 penalty to AC, but you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Attack Rolls.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The bonus to Attack Rolls increases to +2.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The forbidden form. It channels the user''s inner darkness (or enjoyment of the fight) into a conduit of pure destruction. It is high-risk, high-reward.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actJuyoVaapadStance", "name": "Juyo/Vaapad Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "ou open yourself to the chaos of battle. While in this stance, you take a –1 penalty to AC, but you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Attack Rolls.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The bonus to Attack Rolls increases to +2.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftNimanStance',	'Form VI: Niman',	'The diplomat''s form. It has no specific strengths or weaknesses but focuses on integrating Force Powers seamlessly into lightsaber combat. It is the favorite of Consulars.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Niman Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You adopt a balanced guard that bridges the gap between martial and mystical. While in this stance, if you make a successful Strike with a lightsaber, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the DC (or attack roll using The Force) of the next [Force Power] you use before the end of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The synergy flows both ways. If you use a Force Power, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your next lightsaber Strike before the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The diplomat''s form. It has no specific strengths or weaknesses but focuses on integrating Force Powers seamlessly into lightsaber combat. It is the favorite of Consulars.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actNimanStance", "name": "Niman Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You adopt a balanced guard that bridges the gap between martial and mystical. While in this stance, if you make a successful Strike with a lightsaber, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the DC (or attack roll using The Force) of the next [Force Power] you use before the end of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The synergy flows both ways. If you use a Force Power, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your next lightsaber Strike before the end of your next turn.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftShienDjemSoStance',	'Form V: Shien/Djem So',	'The counter-attack form. Divided into Shien (blaster deflection) and Djem So (lightsaber dueling), it focuses on turning an opponent''s strength against them with brute force.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Shien/Djem So Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You hold your blade ready to snap back. While in this stance, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to damage rolls with two-handed Lightsaber strikes.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> When an enemy hits you with a melee attack, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your next Attack Roll against them. When an enemy hits you with a ranged attack, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against subsequent ranged attacks from that enemy for 1 round.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The counter-attack form. Divided into Shien (blaster deflection) and Djem So (lightsaber dueling), it focuses on turning an opponent''s strength against them with brute force.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShienDjemSoStance", "name": "Shien/Djem So Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You hold your blade ready to snap back. While in this stance, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to damage rolls with two-handed Lightsaber strikes.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> When an enemy hits you with a melee attack, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your next Attack Roll against them. When an enemy hits you with a ranged attack, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against subsequent ranged attacks from that enemy for 1 round.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSoresuStance',	'Form III: Soresu',	'The ultimate defensive form. Created to counter blasters, it creates a tight defensive sphere that creates an "eye of the storm" for the Jedi and their allies.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Soresu Stance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Stance</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wielding a lightsaber.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You pull your lightsaber close to your body to minimize exposure. While in this stance, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against Ranged Attacks, but your Speed is reduced by 10 feet.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The AC bonus applies to Melee Attacks as well.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"attack": [{"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}]}]',	'The ultimate defensive form. Created to counter blasters, it creates a tight defensive sphere that creates an "eye of the storm" for the Jedi and their allies.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSoresuStance", "name": "Soresu Stance", "traits": "Form, Stance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You pull your lightsaber close to your body to minimize exposure. While in this stance, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against Ranged Attacks, but your Speed is reduced by 10 feet.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The AC bonus applies to Melee Attacks as well.", "requirements": "You are wielding a lightsaber."}]}}',	'Form, Stance',	1,	'0',	NULL),
('cftHawkBatSwoop',	'Hawk-Bat Swoop',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Hawk-Bat Swoop</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Move</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Ataru Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You launch yourself into the air and strike from above. You launch yourself into the air and strike from above. You Leap (or High Jump/Long Jump without a check). At any point during the jump, you can make a melee Strike. If you hit, you deal an additional die of weapon damage.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If the Strike hits, you can immediately make a second Strike against the same target at a -5 penalty.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftAtaruStance", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You launch yourself into the air and strike from above.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHawkBatSwoop", "name": "Hawk-Bat Swoop", "traits": "Form, Move", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You launch yourself into the air and strike from above. You launch yourself into the air and strike from above. You Leap (or High Jump/Long Jump without a check). At any point during the jump, you can make a melee Strike. If you hit, you deal an additional die of weapon damage.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If the Strike hits, you can immediately make a second Strike against the same target at a -5 penalty.", "requirements": "You are in Ataru Stance."}]}}',	'Form, Move',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftViciousRend',	'Vicious Rend',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion with a claw, fist, pincer, or talon unarmed attack

Your companion sinks its claws and rips. Your companions with a qualifying unarmed attack learn the Vicious Rend activity.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Vicious Rend</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Make two claw, fist, pincer, or talon Strikes against the same target, applying the multiple attack penalty as normal. If both Strikes hit, the target takes an additional 1d6 persistent bleed damage. This damage increases to 2d6 if your companion is specialized.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Your companion sinks its claws and rips.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actViciousRend", "name": "Vicious Rend", "traits": "Archetype", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "Make two claw, fist, pincer, or talon Strikes against the same target, applying the multiple attack penalty as normal. If both Strikes hit, the target takes an additional 1d6 persistent bleed damage. This damage increases to 2d6 if your companion is specialized."}]}}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftSinkingJaws',	'Sinking Jaws',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion with a jaws or fangs unarmed attack

Like how a constrictor wraps itself around its next meal, your companion tightens its teeth around its constrained prey to squeeze the life out of it. Your companions with a qualifying unarmed attack learn the Sinking Jaws activity.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Sinking Jaws</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>

  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>This companion has a creature grabbed or restrained with its jaws or fangs.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    This companion''s grabbed or restrained foe takes piercing damage equal to the companion''s level plus Strength modifier.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Like how a constrictor wraps itself around its next meal, your companion tightens its teeth around its constrained prey to squeeze the life out of it.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSinkingJaws", "name": "Sinking Jaws", "traits": "Archetype", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "This companion''s grabbed or restrained foe takes piercing damage equal to the companion''s level plus Strength modifier.", "requirements": "This companion has a creature grabbed or restrained with its jaws or fangs."}]}}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftFerociousCharge',	'Ferocious Charge',	'<strong>Prerequisites</strong> animal companion with an antlers, head, or horn unarmed attack

You''ve taught your companions to charge directly at an enemy. Your companions with a qualifying unarmed Strike learn the Ferocious Charge activity.



<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Ferocious Charge</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">

  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The companion Strides up to twice its Speed in a straight line and makes an antlers, head, or horn Strike. If it moved at least 20 feet, it deals an additional 1d8 damage. This damage increases to 2d8 if your companion is specialized. The companion can use Ferocious Charge while Burrowing, Climbing, Flying, or Swimming instead of Striding if it has the corresponding movement type.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeastmasterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You''ve taught your companions to charge directly at an enemy.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFerociousCharge", "name": "Ferocious Charge", "traits": "Archetype", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "The companion Strides up to twice its Speed in a straight line and makes an antlers, head, or horn Strike. If it moved at least 20 feet, it deals an additional 1d8 damage. This damage increases to 2d8 if your companion is specialized. The companion can use Ferocious Charge while Burrowing, Climbing, Flying, or Swimming instead of Striding if it has the corresponding movement type."}]}}',	'Archetype',	10,	'0',	'arcBeastmaster'),
('cftExpandedMemoryArchitecture',	'Expanded Memory Architecture',	'You have fundamentally upgraded your custom rig''s storage drives and heuristic processing limits. You can install one additional Modification from your Modification Library during your daily preparations. Additionally, if you have the Brute-Force Execution or Hot-Swappable Memory feats, their frequency improves from "Once per day" to "Twice per day."',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftModularExpansion", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You have fundamentally upgraded your custom rig''s storage drives and heuristic processing limits.',	'clsTechSpecialist',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftBeskarRetaliation',	'Beskar Retaliation',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Beskar Retaliation</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You use Beskar Deflection to reduce the damage of a ranged attack made by a creature within 100 feet of you.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You masterfully angle your beskar''gam to ricochet the incoming fire back at its source. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature using your highest ranged attack modifier. This Strike does not require a wielded weapon and does not apply any weapon item bonuses to the attack roll.<br><br>On a hit, you deal damage of the same type as the triggering attack equal to the amount of damage your Beskar Deflection just prevented. On a critical hit, you deal double that amount. This Strike does not count toward your multiple attack penalty, and your multiple attack penalty does not apply to it.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBeskarDeflection", "type": "class"}]}]',	'ou masterfully angle your beskar''gam to ricochet the incoming fire back at its source.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBeskarRetaliation", "name": "Beskar Retaliation", "traits": "Archetype", "trigger": "You use Beskar Deflection to reduce the damage of a ranged attack made by a creature within 100 feet of you.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You masterfully angle your beskar''gam to ricochet the incoming fire back at its source. Make a ranged Strike against the triggering creature using your highest ranged attack modifier. This Strike does not require a wielded weapon and does not apply any weapon item bonuses to the attack roll.<br><br>On a hit, you deal damage of the same type as the triggering attack equal to the amount of damage your Beskar Deflection just prevented. On a critical hit, you deal double that amount. This Strike does not count toward your multiple attack penalty, and your multiple attack penalty does not apply to it."}]}}',	'Archetype',	8,	'0',	'arcMandalorian'),
('cftKeepPace',	'Keep Pace',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Keep Pace</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>Your prey is within reach and attempts to move away from you.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Once you are upon your prey, they can’t escape. Stride up to your Speed, following the foe and keeping it in reach throughout its movement until it stops moving or you’ve moved your full Speed. You can use Keep Pace to Burrow, Climb, Fly, or Swim instead of Stride if you have the corresponding movement type.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftBountyHunterDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'Once you are upon your prey, they can’t escape.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKeepPace", "name": "Keep Pace", "traits": "Archetype", "trigger": "Your prey is within reach and attempts to move away from you.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Once you are upon your prey, they can’t escape. Stride up to your Speed, following the foe and keeping it in reach throughout its movement until it stops moving or you’ve moved your full Speed. You can use Keep Pace to Burrow, Climb, Fly, or Swim instead of Stride if you have the corresponding movement type."}]}}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcBountyHunter'),
('cftBarrierOfBlades',	'Barrier of Blades',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Barrier of Blades</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You are hit by a melee or ranged attack.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Shien / Djem So Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You meet force with force. Roll your lightsaber damage.  You reduce the damage of the incoming attack by the damage rolled.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If the attack was a melee attack, you can immediately make a Strike against the attacker using the damage rolled above as the attack''s damage. Your multiple attack penalty applies as normal to this attack.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftFallingAvalanche", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You meet force with force.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBarrierOfBlades", "name": "Barrier of Blades", "traits": "Form", "trigger": "You are hit by a melee or ranged attack.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You meet force with force. Roll your lightsaber damage.  You reduce the damage of the incoming attack by the damage rolled.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If the attack was a melee attack, you can immediately make a Strike against the attacker using the damage rolled above as the attack''s damage. Your multiple attack penalty applies as normal to this attack.", "requirements": "You are in Shien / Djem So Stance."}]}}',	'Form',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftSaberSwarm',	'Saber Swarm',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Saber Swarm</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Ataru Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You unleash a blur of rapid strikes. Make two melee Strikes against a single target. The multiple attack penalty applies normally, but if both hit, combine their damage for the purpose of overcoming Resistance.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The second attack does not count towards your multiple attack penalty.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftHawkBatSwoop", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You unleash a blur of rapid strikes.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSaberSwarm", "name": "Saber Swarm", "traits": "Form, Flourish", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You unleash a blur of rapid strikes. Make two melee Strikes against a single target. The multiple attack penalty applies normally, but if both hit, combine their damage for the purpose of overcoming Resistance.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The second attack does not count towards your multiple attack penalty.", "requirements": "You are in Ataru Stance."}]}}',	'Form, Flourish',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftVornskrsFerocity',	'Vornskr''s Ferocity',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Vornskr''s Ferocity</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You critically hit a creature.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Juyo Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Your bloodlust surges. You gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The target of your critical hit is Frightened 1. If they are already Frightened, their Frightened condition icreases by 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftJuyoVaapadStance", "type": "form"}]}]',	'Your bloodlust surges.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actVornskrsFerocity", "name": "Vornskr''s Ferocity", "traits": "Form", "trigger": "You critically hit a creature.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "Your bloodlust surges. You gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> The target of your critical hit is Frightened 1. If they are already Frightened, their Frightened condition icreases by 1.", "requirements": "You are in Juyo Stance."}]}}',	'Form',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftContentiousRiposte',	'Contentious Riposte',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Contentious Riposte</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>Your Dueling Target critically fails a melee Strike against you.</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Makashi Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You exploit their over-extension. You make a melee Strike against the triggering creature.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can trigger this Reaction on a regular Failure (miss), not just a Critical Failure.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMakashiStance", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You exploit their over-extension.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actContentiousRiposte", "name": "Contentious Riposte", "traits": "Form", "trigger": "Your Dueling Target critically fails a melee Strike against you.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You exploit their over-extension. You make a melee Strike against the triggering creature.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can trigger this Reaction on a regular Failure (miss), not just a Critical Failure.", "requirements": "You are in Makashi Stance."}]}}',	'Form',	4,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDeathWatchAssault',	'Death Watch Assault',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Death Watch Assault</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are wearing a jetpack and have a fly speed.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You throw yourself into the fray from above. You Fly twice. If you end your movement within reach of at least one enemy, you can make a melee Strike against that enemy. If you moved a total of at least 20 feet during these Fly actions, the target is off-guard against this Strike.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMandalorianDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You throw yourself into the fray from above.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDeathWatchAssault", "name": "Death Watch Assault", "traits": "Archetype", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You throw yourself into the fray from above. You Fly twice. If you end your movement within reach of at least one enemy, you can make a melee Strike against that enemy. If you moved a total of at least 20 feet during these Fly actions, the target is off-guard against this Strike.", "requirements": "You are wearing a jetpack and have a fly speed."}]}}',	'Archetype',	6,	'0',	'arcMandalorian'),
('cftDoctorsVisitation',	'Doctor''s Visitation',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Doctor''s Visitation</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You move to provide immediate care to those who need it. You Stride, then use Battle Medicine or Treat Poison. You can spend 2 actions for Doctor’s Visitation to instead Stride and then use either Administer First Aid or Treat Condition (if you have that feat).
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMedicDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You move to provide immediate care to those who need it.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDoctorsVisitation", "name": "Doctor''s Visitation", "traits": "Archetype, Flourish", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You move to provide immediate care to those who need it. You Stride, then use Battle Medicine or Treat Poison. You can spend 2 actions for Doctor’s Visitation to instead Stride and then use either Administer First Aid or Treat Condition (if you have that feat)."}]}}',	'Archetype, Flourish',	4,	'0',	'arcMedic'),
('cftFleetingShadow',	'Fleeting Shadow',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Fleeting Shadow</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You''re able to quickly disappear and then move about without drawing the attention of your enemies. You Hide, then Sneak twice.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftScoutDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You''re able to quickly disappear and then move about without drawing the attention of your enemies.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFleetingShadow", "name": "Fleeting Shadow", "traits": "Archetype, Flourish", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You''re able to quickly disappear and then move about without drawing the attention of your enemies. You Hide, then Sneak twice."}]}}',	'Archetype, Flourish',	6,	'0',	'arcScout'),
('cftIntegratedMastery',	'Integrated Mastery',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Integrated Mastery</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 14</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Niman Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You blend the lightsaber and the Force effortlessly. You Cast a Force Power with an action cost of no more than 2 and simultaneously make a melee Strike.  Both of these count towards your multiple attack penalty, but neither suffers from it.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can convert all of the damage from the Strike to Force damage.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftPushingSlash", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You blend the lightsaber and the Force effortlessly.',	NULL,	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powIntegratedMastery", "name": "Integrated Mastery", "traits": "Form, Force Power", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You blend the lightsaber and the Force effortlessly. You Cast a Force Power with an action cost of no more than 2 and simultaneously make a melee Strike.  Both of these count towards your multiple attack penalty, but neither suffers from it.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> You can convert all of the damage from the Strike to Force damage.", "requirements": "You are in Niman Stance."}]}}',	'Form',	14,	'0',	NULL),
('cftDisarmingBlast',	'Disarming Blast',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Disarming Blast</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Shii-Cho Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You strike with the intent to shatter weaponry. Make a Strike against an opponent. If you hit, you also attempt a Disarm check against them using the same attack roll result (adding any item bonuses from your weapon).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> On a Critical Hit with the Strike, the Disarm effect is automatically a Critical Success (dropping the weapon).
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSarlaccSweep", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You strike with the intent to shatter weaponry.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDisarmingBlast", "name": "Disarming Blast", "traits": "Form", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You strike with the intent to shatter weaponry. Make a Strike against an opponent. If you hit, you also attempt a Disarm check against them using the same attack roll result (adding any item bonuses from your weapon).<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> On a Critical Hit with the Strike, the Disarm effect is automatically a Critical Success (dropping the weapon).", "requirements": "You are in Shii-Cho Stance."}]}}',	'Form',	8,	'0',	NULL),
('cftScoutsPounce',	'Scout''s Pounce',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Scout''s Pounce</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Flourish</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are hidden from or undetected by all of your opponents, and you aren''t within 10 feet of any enemy.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You leap from the shadows to strike at your foes. Stride up to your Speed, then Strike twice. If you were hidden or unnoticed by the target of these Strikes, the target is off-guard against both attacks. Your multiple attack penalty applies normally for both attacks.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftScoutDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You leap from the shadows to strike at your foes.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actScoutsPounce", "name": "Scout''s Pounce", "traits": "Archetype, Flourish", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You leap from the shadows to strike at your foes. Stride up to your Speed, then Strike twice. If you were hidden or unnoticed by the target of these Strikes, the target is off-guard against both attacks. Your multiple attack penalty applies normally for both attacks.", "requirements": "You are hidden from or undetected by all of your opponents, and you aren''t within 10 feet of any enemy."}]}}',	'Archetype, Flourish',	10,	'0',	'arcScout'),
('cftSentinelsPremonition',	'Sentinel''s Premonition',	'You gain the Force Premonition action. However, your foresight is less sustained than a fully trained Sentinel''s. For you, Force Premonition has a frequency of once per minute. If you Strike the chosen creature using your Premonition Roll and the attack is a critical hit or reduces the target to 0 Hit Points, you ignore this frequency limitation and can use Force Premonition again without waiting a minute.',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftSentinelDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	'You gain the Force Premonition action.',	NULL,	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powForcePremonition", "name": "Force Premonition", "level": 1, "traits": "Concentrate, Force Power, Fortune", "frequency": "Once per round", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You focus on a creature you can see. Roll a d20. This is your Premonition Roll. If you make a Strike against the chosen creature later this round, you must use the result of your Premonition Roll for your attack roll (instead of rolling a new d20). If you Strike the chosen creature using your Premonition Roll, you can use your Wisdom modifier for the attack roll instead of Strength or Dexterity.<br><br>If your Premonition Roll is low (a likely miss), you are not forced to attack. You can choose to use your remaining actions to move, use a Force Power, or perform a Skill action, knowing that an attack would have failed."}]}}',	'Archetype',	4,	'0',	'arcSentinel'),
('cftSarlaccSweep',	'Sarlacc Sweep',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Sarlacc Sweep</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Form</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are in Shii-Cho Stance.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You lash out in a wide arc. Make a single melee Strike with your Lightsaber and compare the attack roll to the AC of all enemies within your reach. Roll damage once and apply it to each creature you hit. This counts as two attacks for your Multiple Attack Penalty.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If you hit at least two enemies, you gain Temporary HP equal to your Strength modifier.
  </div>
</div>',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftShiiChoStance", "type": "form"}]}]',	'You lash out in a wide arc.',	NULL,	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSarlaccSweep", "name": "Sarlacc Sweep", "traits": "Form", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You lash out in a wide arc. Make a single melee Strike with your Lightsaber and compare the attack roll to the AC of all enemies within your reach. Roll damage once and apply it to each creature you hit. This counts as two attacks for your Multiple Attack Penalty.<br><br><strong>Guardian Mastery</strong> If you hit at least two enemies, you gain Temporary HP equal to your Strength modifier.", "requirements": "You are in Shii-Cho Stance."}]}}',	'Form, Flourish',	4,	'0',	NULL);

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Feat";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Feat" (
    "FeatID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Description" text NOT NULL,
    "Traits" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Prerequisites" jsonb,
    "Level" smallint NOT NULL,
    "Summary" character varying,
    "Repeatable" boolean DEFAULT false NOT NULL,
    "Features" jsonb,
    "ArchetypeID" character varying,
    CONSTRAINT "Feat_FeatID" PRIMARY KEY ("FeatID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."FeatID" IS 'Unique Feat ID';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Name" IS 'Feat Name';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Description" IS 'Feat description text';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Traits" IS 'Feat traits';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Prerequisites" IS 'Feat prerequisites';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Level" IS 'Feat level';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Summary" IS 'Feat short summary';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Feat"."Repeatable" IS 'Allow feat to be taken multiple times?';

INSERT INTO "Feat" ("FeatID", "Name", "Description", "Traits", "Prerequisites", "Level", "Summary", "Repeatable", "Features", "ArchetypeID") VALUES
('feaBreathControl',	'Breath Control',	'You can breathe even in hazardous or sparse air. You can hold your breath for 25 times as long as usual before suffocating. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against inhaled threats, such as inhaled poisons, and if you roll a success on such a saving throw, you get a critical success instead.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You can breathe even in hazardous or sparse air.',	'0',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Breath Control", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against inhaled threats.", "target": "all"}]}]}',	NULL),
('feaBargainHunter',	'Bargain Hunter',	'You can Earn Income using Diplomacy, spending your days hunting for bargains and reselling at a profit. You can also spend time specifically seeking a great bargain on an item; this works as if you were using Earn Income with Diplomacy, except instead of gaining money, you purchase the item at a discount equal to the money you would have gained, gaining the item for free if your earned income equals or exceeds its cost. Finally, if you select Bargain Hunter during character creation at 1st level, you start play with an additional 20 credits.
Traits',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can Earn Income using Diplomacy, spending your days hunting for bargains and reselling at a profit.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCrowdSurfing',	'Crowd Surfing',	'You move through crowds without slowing down. You can move at full Speed in crowds. Treat areas truly packed with people as difficult terrain instead of greater difficult terrain.',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You move through crowds without slowing down.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDiehard',	'Diehard',	'It takes more to kill you than most. You die from the dying condition at dying 5, rather than dying 4.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'It takes more to kill you than most.',	'0',	'{"attribute": {"dying_track": {"max": 5}}}',	NULL),
('feaCharmingLiar',	'Charming Liar',	'Your charm allows you to win over those you lie to. When you get a critical success using the Lie action, the target''s attitude toward you improves by one step, as though you''d succeeded at using Diplomacy to Make an Impression. This works only once per conversation, and if you critically succeed against multiple targets using the same result, you choose one creature''s attitude to improve. You must be lying to impart seemingly important information, inflate your status, or ingratiate yourself, which trivial or irrelevant lies can''t achieve.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your charm allows you to win over those you lie to.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaUrbanSurvivalist',	'Urban Survivalist',	'You can use Survival in place of Society to Subsist in cities, space stations, and other settlements. You can also use Survival instead of Perception to notice hazards in these environments; if you find a hazard in this way, you can also use Survival instead of Thievery to Disable the Device.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can use Survival in place of Society to Subsist in cities, space stations, and other settlements. ',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaArmorProficiency',	'Armor Proficiency',	'You become trained in light armor. If you already were trained in light armor, you gain training in medium armor. If you were trained in both, you become trained in heavy armor. If you are at least 13th level, you become an expert in this armor type.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once. Each time, you become trained in the next type of armor, as detailed above.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You become trained in light armor.',	'1',	'{"armor_progression": {"sequence": ["light", "medium", "heavy"], "base_rank": "Trained", "level_upgrades": [{"rank": "Expert", "min_level": 13}]}}',	NULL),
('feaCatFall',	'Cat Fall',	'Your catlike aerial acrobatics allow you to cushion your falls. Treat falls as 10 feet shorter. If you''re an expert in Acrobatics, treat falls as 25 feet shorter and 50 feet if you''re a master. If you''re legendary in Acrobatics, you always land on your feet and don''t take damage, regardless of the distance of the fall.',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your catlike aerial acrobatics allow you to cushion your falls.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDubiousKnowledge',	'Dubious Knowledge',	'You’re a treasure trove of information, but not all of it comes from reputable sources. When you fail (but don’t critically fail) a Recall Knowledge check using any skill, you learn the correct answer and an erroneous answer, but you don’t have any way to differentiate which is which. This can occur as knowing something is significant, but not whether it’s good or bad.',	'General, Skill',	NULL,	1,	'You’re a treasure trove of information, but not all of it comes from reputable sources.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaBlendIn',	'Blend In',	'You know how to blend in and become a forgettable face in the crowd. While in a crowd of at least 10 other creatures, you can roll a Society check in place of a Stealth check when using the Avoid Notice exploration activity to see if enemies notice you. While in a settlement, you can use Society in place of Deception when Impersonating a non-specific individual.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You know how to blend in and become a forgettable face in the crowd.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCannyAcumen',	'Canny Acumen',	'Your avoidance or observation is beyond the ken of most in your profession. Choose Fortitude saves, Reflex saves, Will saves, or Perception. You become an expert in your choice. At 17th level, you become a master in your choice.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'Your avoidance or observation is beyond the ken of most in your profession.',	'0',	'{"saving_throw": {"select": {"rank": "Expert", "automatic_upgrade": {"17": "Master"}}}}',	NULL),
('feaCombatClimber',	'Combat Climber',	'Your techniques allow you to fight as you climb. You''re not off-guard while Climbing and can Climb with a hand occupied. You must still use another hand and both legs to Climb.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your techniques allow you to fight as you climb.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaForceSensitive',	'Force Sensitive',	'You can sense and manipulate the Force.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	NULL,	1,	'You have developed a connection with the Force and the ability to interact with it at a basic level.',	'0',	'{"power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 2, "level": 1}]}}',	NULL),
('feaExpressDriver',	'Express Driver',	'You know how to get there fast. When calculating your travel Speed for the day while piloting a vehicle, you can attempt a Piloting check to increase your vehicle''s travel Speed for long-term overland or aerial travel. The DC is determined by the GM but is typically based on the vehicle''s piloting DC or a difficulty based on the environment, whichever is harder. On a success, double your vehicle''s travel Speed for the day. This has no effect on your vehicle''s movement in encounters or on starships traveling through hyperspace.',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You know how to get there fast.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaIncredibleInitiative',	'Incredible Initiative',	'You react more quickly than others can. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to initiative rolls.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You react more quickly than others can.',	'0',	'{"perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Incredible Initiative", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to initiative.", "target": "all"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaFaceInTheCrowd',	'Face in the Crowd',	'You know how to get lost in a crowd. You can use cover from crowds to Hide and Sneak, gaining a +2 circumstance bonus to your Stealth checks when in a crowd of at least 10 creatures and a +4 circumstance bonus to your Stealth checks when in a crowd of at least 100 creatures. Hidden creatures don''t count as members of a crowd. If you''re a master in Deception you only need 5 creatures to get these bonuses.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You know how to get lost in a crowd.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Face in the Crowd", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus when in a crowd of at least 10 creatures; +4 when in a crowd of at least 100.", "target": "sklStealth"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaFeatherStep',	'Feather Step',	'You step carefully and quickly. You can Step into difficult terrain.',	'General',	'[{"attribute": [{"dex": 2}]}]',	1,	'You step carefully and quickly.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaHologramSkeptic',	'Hologram Skeptic',	'You easily spot the tiny glitches and imperfections in holograms. Even if you aren''t Searching, you always attempt a check to disbelieve holograms and effects with the illusion and tech traits that normally require you to Search or Interact with them.',	'General, Skill, Computers',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You easily spot the tiny glitches and imperfections in holograms. Even if you aren''t Searching, you always attempt a check to disbelieve holograms and effects with the illusion and tech traits that normally require you to Search or Interact with them.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDigitalAmbassador',	'Digital Ambassador',	'As long as you’re using a comm unit, datapad, or computer to communicate, when you attempt to use a skill action with the linguistic trait on a creature that doesn’t understand the language you’re using, roll a DC 15 flat check. On a success, the effect works as if the creature understood the language you’re using. If you’re Legendary in Society, the DC is 10.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'As long as you’re using a comm unit, datapad, or computer to communicate, when you attempt to use a skill action with the linguistic trait on a creature that doesn’t understand the language you’re using, roll a DC 15 flat check.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaExperiencedProfessional',	'Experienced Professional',	'You carefully safeguard your professional endeavors to prevent disaster. When you use Lore to Earn Income, if you roll a critical failure, you instead get a failure. If you''re an expert in Lore, you gain twice as much income from a failed check to Earn Income, unless it was originally a critical failure.',	'General, Skill, Lore',	NULL,	1,	'You carefully safeguard your professional endeavors to prevent disaster.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaExperiencedTracker',	'Experienced Tracker',	'Tracking is second nature to you, and when necessary you can follow a trail without pause. You can Track while moving at full Speed by taking a –5 penalty to your Survival check. If you''re a master in Survival, you don''t take the –5 penalty. If you''re legendary in Survival, you no longer need to roll a new Survival check every hour when tracking, though you still need to roll whenever there are significant changes in the trail.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Tracking is second nature to you, and when necessary you can follow a trail without pause.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaExperiencedSmuggler',	'Experienced Smuggler',	'You often smuggle things past the authorities. When the GM rolls your Stealth check to see if a passive observer notices a small item you’ve concealed, the GM uses the number rolled or 10—whichever is higher—as the result of your die roll, adding it to your Stealth modifier to determine your Stealth check result. If you’re a master in Stealth, the GM uses the number rolled or 15, and if you’re legendary in Stealth, you automatically succeed at hiding a small concealed item from passive observers. This provides no benefits when a creature attempts a Perception check while actively searching you for hidden items.',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You often smuggle things past the authorities.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaConcealingLegerdemain',	'Concealing Legerdemain',	'Rather than hide an object somewhere the inspectors won''t search, you''re skilled at keeping the object on the move so it''s never where they look. When you Conceal an Object of light Bulk or less, you can use Thievery instead of Stealth for your checks and for the DC of an active searcher''s Perception check. You roll the check only once, but you must continue to use actions to Conceal an Object throughout the process.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Rather than hide an object somewhere the inspectors won''t search, you''re skilled at keeping the object on the move so it''s never where they look.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFleet',	'Fleet',	'You move more quickly on foot. Your Speed increases by 5 feet.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You move more quickly on foot.',	'0',	'{"speed": {"bonus": [{"base": "5"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaScareToDeath',	'Scare to Death',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Scare to Death</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 15</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Intimidation</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Emotion</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Fear</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You can frighten foes so much, they might die. Attempt an Intimidation check against the Will DC of a living creature within 30 feet of you that you sense or observe and who can sense or observe you. If the target can''t hear you or doesn''t understand the language you are speaking, you take a –4 circumstance penalty. The creature is temporarily immune for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> The target must attempt a Fortitude save against your Intimidation DC. On a critical failure, it dies. On any other result, it becomes frightened 2 and is fleeing for 1 round. The critical failure effect has the death trait.<br><b>Success</b> The target becomes frightened 2.<br><b>Failure</b> The target becomes frightened 1.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> The target is unaffected.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Intimidation, Emotion, Fear',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can frighten foes so much, they might die.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actScareToDeath", "name": "Scare to Death", "traits": "General, Skill, Intimidation, Emotion, Fear", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You can frighten foes so much, they might die. Attempt an Intimidation check against the Will DC of a living creature within 30 feet of you that you sense or observe and who can sense or observe you. If the target can''t hear you or doesn''t understand the language you are speaking, you take a –4 circumstance penalty. The creature is temporarily immune for 1 minute.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> The target must attempt a Fortitude save against your Intimidation DC. On a critical failure, it dies. On any other result, it becomes frightened 2 and is fleeing for 1 round. The critical failure effect has the death trait.<br><b>Success</b> The target becomes frightened 2.<br><b>Failure</b> The target becomes frightened 1.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> The target is unaffected."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaRide',	'Ride',	'When you Command an Animal you''re mounted on to take a move action (such as Stride), you automatically succeed instead of needing to attempt a check. Any animal you''re mounted on acts on your turn, like a minion. If you Mount an animal in the middle of an encounter, it skips its next turn and then acts on your next turn. See the minion trait for more information on minions.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'When you Command an Animal you''re mounted on to take a move action (such as Stride), you automatically succeed instead of needing to attempt a check.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickInstall',	'Quick Install',	'You take only 1 minute to Install an Upgrade. If you''re legendary in Crafting, you can Install an Upgrade as a 3-action activity.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You take only 1 minute to Install an Upgrade.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaGroupImpression',	'Group Impression',	'When you Make an Impression, you can compare your Diplomacy check result to the Will DCs of up to 10 targets you conversed with, with no penalty. The number of targets increases to 20 if you''re an expert, 50 if you''re a master, and 100 if you''re legendary.',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'When you Make an Impression, you can compare your Diplomacy check result to the Will DCs of up to 10 targets you conversed with, with no penalty.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaGroupCoercion',	'Group Coercion',	'You can strong-arm people effectively, even when you don''t have them isolated. When you Coerce, you can compare your Intimidation check result to the Will DCs of up to five targets instead of one.

It''s possible to get a different degree of success for each target. The number of targets you can Coerce in a single action increases to 10 if you''re an expert, 25 if you''re a master, and 50 if you''re legendary.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can strong-arm people effectively, even when you don''t have them isolated.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaIntimidatingGlare',	'Intimidating Glare',	'You can Demoralize with a mere glare. When you do, Demoralize loses the auditory trait and gains the visual trait, and you don''t take a penalty if the creature doesn''t understand your language.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can Demoralize with a mere glare.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFascinatingPerformance',	'Fascinating Performance',	'When you Perform, compare your result to the Will DC of one observer. If you succeed, the target is fascinated by you for 1 round. If the observer is in a situation that demands immediate attention, such as combat, you must critically succeed to fascinate it and the Perform action gains the incapacitation trait. You must choose which creature you''re trying to fascinate before you roll your check, and the target is then temporarily immune for 1 hour.

If you''re an expert in Performance, you can fascinate up to four observers; if you''re a master, you can fascinate up to 10 observers; and if you''re legendary, you can fascinate any number of observers at the same time.',	'General, Skill, Performance',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'When you Perform, compare your result to the Will DC of one observer. If you succeed, the target is fascinated by you for 1 round.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaManagementMaterial',	'Management Material',	'Anyone who speaks with you about a job, workplace, or office skill set assumes you''re a professional in that setting unless you intentionally present yourself differently. You can use Society to Make an Impression on a professional or to Impersonate a type of professional or a specific individual professional. If you use the normally required skills in those situations, you receive a +1 circumstance bonus to the check instead.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Anyone who speaks with you about a job, workplace, or office skill set assumes you''re a professional in that setting unless you intentionally present yourself differently.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPickpocket',	'Pickpocket',	'You can Steal or Palm an Object that''s closely guarded, such as in a pocket, without taking the –5 penalty. You can''t steal objects that would be extremely noticeable or time consuming to remove (like worn shoes or armor or actively wielded objects). If you''re a master in Thievery, you can attempt to Steal from a creature in combat or otherwise on guard. When doing so, Stealing requires 2 actions instead of 1, and you take a –5 penalty.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can Steal or Palm an Object that''s closely guarded, such as in a pocket, without taking the –5 penalty. ',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaUnusualTreatment',	'Unusual Treatment',	'Your medical training extends to less obvious conditions. When you succeed against a DC 20 check to Treat Wounds, you can also reduce the value of one clumsy, enfeebled, or stupefied condition on the patient by 1. If you''re able to treat more than one creature at once, choose only one to gain this benefit. A creature can benefit from Unusual Treatment only once per day.

If the condition results from an affliction, the affliction isn''t cured, though the condition is reduced as long as the affliction remains at that stage.

If you are a master in Medicine, add the drained condition to the list of conditions you can remove if you succeed at a DC 30 check. If you are legendary in Medicine, you reduce the chosen condition by 2 instead of by 1.',	'General, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'Your medical training extends to less obvious conditions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaSeasoned',	'Seasoned',	'You''ve mastered the preparation of many types of food and drink. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to checks to Craft food and drink, including serums if you have Serum Crafting. If you are a master in one of the prerequisite skills, this bonus increases to +2.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklLoreWarfare", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You''ve mastered the preparation of many types of food and drink.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Seasoned", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus Craft food and drink; +2 if you are Master.", "target": "all"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaBarricade',	'Barricade',	'You hastily create a barricade using nearby items, junk, or debris. The barricade provides lesser cover for you and one other ally, though you can Take Cover to increase this benefit to standard cover. The barricade is flimsy and falls apart at the end of your next turn.',	'General, Manipulate',	NULL,	1,	'You hastily create a barricade using nearby items, junk, or debris.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBarricade", "name": "Barricade", "traits": "General, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You hastily create a barricade using nearby items, junk, or debris. The barricade provides lesser cover for you and one other ally, though you can Take Cover to increase this benefit to standard cover. The barricade is flimsy and falls apart at the end of your next turn."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaSurveyWildlife',	'Survey Wildlife',	'You can spend 10 minutes assessing the area around you for signs of creatures. Attempt a Survival check against a DC determined by the GM based on how obvious the signs are. On a success, you can attempt a Recall Knowledge check with a –2 penalty to learn more about the creatures just from these signs. If you''re a master in Survival, you don''t take the penalty.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can spend 10 minutes assessing the area around you for signs of creatures.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTerrainStalker',	'Terrain Stalker',	'Select one type of difficult terrain from the following list: rubble, snow, or underbrush. While undetected by all non-allies in that type of terrain, you can Sneak without attempting a Stealth check as long as you move no more than 5 feet and do not pass within 10 feet of an enemy during your movement.

During exploration, this also allows you to automatically approach within 15 feet of other creatures while Avoiding their Notice, as long as they aren''t actively Searching or on guard.

<b>Special</b> You can select this feat multiple times. Each time, choose a different type of terrain.',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Select one type of difficult terrain from the following list: rubble, snow, or underbrush.',	'1',	'{"inputs": [{"name": "Terrain", "options": ["Rubble", "Snow", "Underbrush"]}]}',	NULL),
('feaSignLanguage',	'Sign Language',	'You learn the sign languages associated with the languages you know, allowing you to sign and understand signs. Sign languages typically require both hands to convey more complex concepts, and they are visual rather than auditory.

Sign language is difficult to understand during combat due to the level of attention needed, unlike basic gestures like pointing at a foe to suggest a target. Sign language is hard to use in areas of low visibility, just like speech is difficult in a noisy environment.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You learn the sign languages associated with the languages you know, allowing you to sign and understand signs.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaWeaponProficiency',	'Weapon Proficiency',	'You become trained in all martial weapons. If you were already trained in all martial weapons, you become trained in one advanced weapon of your choice. If you are at least 11th level, you also become an expert in these weapons.<br><br><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat more than once. Each time you do, you become trained in an advanced weapon.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You become trained in all martial weapons.',	'1',	'{"weapon_progression": {"base_rank": "Trained", "level_upgrades": [{"rank": "Expert", "min_level": 11}]}}',	NULL),
('feaSubtleTheft',	'Subtle Theft',	'When you successfully Steal something, observers (creatures other than the creature you stole from) take a –2 circumstance penalty to their Perception DCs to detect your theft. Additionally, if you first Create a Diversion using Deception, taking a single Palm an Object or Steal action doesn''t end your undetected condition.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'When you successfully Steal something, observers (creatures other than the creature you stole from) take a –2 circumstance penalty to their Perception DCs to detect your theft.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaSkillTraining',	'Skill Training',	'You become trained in the skill of your choice.

<b>Special</b> You can select this feat multiple times, choosing a new skill to become trained in each time.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"attribute": [{"int": 1}]}]',	1,	'You become trained in the skill of your choice.',	'1',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''trained_skill'')", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "trained_skill", "type": "skill"}]}',	NULL),
('feaToughness',	'Toughness',	'Your body can withstand more punishment than most before succumbing. Increase your maximum Hit Points by your level. You reduce the DC of recovery checks by 1.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'Your body can withstand more punishment than most before succumbing.',	'0',	'{"defense": {"hp": "{level}"}}',	NULL),
('feaUntrainedImprovisation',	'Untrained Improvisation',	'You''ve learned how to handle situations when you''re out of your depth. Your proficiency bonus to untrained skill checks is equal to your level –2. This improves to your level –1 at 5th level and your full level at 7th level. This doesn''t allow you to use the skill''s trained actions.',	'General',	NULL,	3,	'You''ve learned how to handle situations when you''re out of your depth.',	'0',	'{"5": {"untrained_bonus": {"skills": "{level - 1}"}}, "7": {"untrained_bonus": {"skills": "{level}"}}, "untrained_bonus": {"skills": "{level - 2}"}}',	NULL),
('feaNaturalMedicine',	'Natural Medicine',	'You can apply natural cures to heal your allies. You can use Nature instead of Medicine to Treat Wounds, including higher Nature proficiency letting you attempt more difficult checks. It doesn’t replace Medicine for uses of the skill other than Treat Wounds or for feat prerequisites.

If you’re in the wilderness, you might have easier access to fresh ingredients, allowing you to gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your check to Treat Wounds using Nature, subject to the GM’s determination.',	'General, Skill, Nature',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can apply natural cures to heal your allies.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Natural Medicine", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to your check to Treat Wounds in wilderness.", "target": "sklNature"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaGracefulDescent',	'Graceful Descent',	'You use the Force to slow your falls. You treat falls as 10 feet shorter. If you are a Master in The Force, you treat falls as 25 feet shorter. If you are Legendary, you treat falls as 50 feet shorter. If you take no damage from a fall, you land on your feet and do not fall Prone.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You use the Force to slow your falls.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDeadlift',	'Deadlift',	'For 1 minute, you can carry 4 more Bulk than normal before becoming encumbered. The amount you can carry increases to 6 at expert, 8 at master, and 10 at legendary. When the benefits of this feat end, you become fatigued for 10 minutes.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'For 1 minute, you can carry 4 more Bulk than normal before becoming encumbered.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTitanWrestler',	'Titan Wrestler',	'You can attempt to Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, or Trip creatures up to two sizes larger than you, or up to three sizes larger than you if you''re legendary in Athletics.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can attempt to Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, or Trip creatures up to two sizes larger than you, or up to three sizes larger than you if you''re legendary in Athletics.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCombatRepair',	'Combat Repair',	'Battle Medicine for Droids',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Battle Medicine for Droids',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCombatRepair", "name": "Combat Repair", "traits": "General, Crafting, Healing, Manipulate, Skill", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You can restore Droids to working order, even in combat. Attempt a Crafting check with the same DC as for Treat Wounds and restore the corresponding amount of HP; this doesn''t remove the wounded condition. As with Treat Wounds, you can attempt checks against higher DCs if you have the minimum proficiency rank. The target is then immune to your Combat Repair for 1 day. This does not make them immune to, or otherwise count as, Treat Wounds.", "requirements": "You’re holding or wearing a repair kit."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaWithoutATrace',	'Without a Trace',	'You''re an expert at destroying or removing incriminating evidence from a crime scene. When using the Cover Tracks exploration activity, anyone tracking you must succeed at a Perception check against your Deception, Stealth, or Underworld Lore DC (whichever is highest). If you spent 10 minutes cleaning up a crime scene, anyone investigating the scene must succeed at a Perception check against your Deception, Stealth, or Underworld Lore DC (whichever is highest) to uncover any hidden evidence.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"skill": [{"id": ["sklDiplomacy", "sklStealth", "sklLoreUnderworld"], "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You''re an expert at destroying or removing incriminating evidence from a crime scene.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFastRecovery',	'Fast Recovery',	'Your body quickly bounces back from afflictions. You regain twice as many Hit Points from resting. Each time you succeed at a Fortitude save against an ongoing disease or poison, you reduce its stage by 2, or by 1 against a virulent disease or poison. Each critical success you achieve against an ongoing disease or poison reduces its stage by 3, or by 2 against a virulent disease or poison. In addition, you reduce the severity of your drained condition by 2 when you rest for a night instead of by 1.',	'General',	'[{"attribute": [{"con": 2}]}]',	1,	'Your body quickly bounces back from afflictions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDigitalDiversion',	'Digital Diversion',	'Whether it''s a sudden comm unit ping or a warning alarm on an equipment display, you can Create a Diversion by using Computers instead of Deception on an adjacent target carrying, wearing, or wielding a tech item.',	'General, Skill, Computers',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Whether it''s a sudden comm unit ping or a warning alarm on an equipment display, you can Create a Diversion by using Computers instead of Deception on an adjacent target carrying, wearing, or wielding a tech item.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPhishingExpertise',	'Phishing Expertise',	'You''re skilled at running digital fraud schemes. You can Create a Forgery using Computers instead of Society. Digital forgeries are compared against your Computers DC. Using information gained from a successful forgery usually requires additional checks, including Deception and Society, and casting too wide a net runs the risk of a potential victim figuring out your ruse and turning you in to the authorities.',	'General, Skill, Computers',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You''re skilled at running digital fraud schemes.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCourtlyGraces',	'Courtly Graces',	'You were raised among the nobility or have learned proper etiquette and bearing, allowing you to present yourself as a noble and play games of influence and politics. Unless you are intentionally presenting yourself differently, anyone who speaks with you will assume you are a noble or closely associated with the nobility (such as a prominent servant). You can use Society to Make an Impression on a noble, as well as with Impersonate to pretend to be a type of noble or a specific individual noble. If you use the normal skills in those situations, you receive a +1 circumstance bonus to the check instead.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You were raised among the nobility or have learned proper etiquette and bearing, allowing you to present yourself as a noble and play games of influence and politics.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaImpressivePerformance',	'Impressive Performance',	'Your performances inspire admiration and win you fans. You can Make an Impression using Performance instead of Diplomacy. If you spend at least 10 minutes performing in front of an audience, you can Make an Impression targeting up to 10 members of the audience who were there for the whole performance, without taking the normal penalty. The number of targets increases to 20 for a 1-hour performance and 50 for a 2-hour performance.',	'General, Skill, Performance',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your performances inspire admiration and win you fans.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDisturbanceInTheForce',	'Disturbance in the Force',	'You have a passive "radar" for danger. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Initiative rolls. Additionally, the GM should secretly roll a check for you when you are about to walk into a trap or ambush (even if you aren''t searching); on a success, you get a vague feeling of "wrongness" or "danger."',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You have a passive "radar" for danger.',	'0',	'{"perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Disturbance in the Force", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to initiative rolls.", "target": "all"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaLieToMe',	'Lie to Me',	'You can use Deception to weave traps to trip up anyone trying to deceive you. If you can engage in conversation with someone trying to Lie to you, use your Deception DC if it is higher than your Perception DC to determine whether they succeed. This doesn''t apply if you don''t have a back-and-forth dialogue, such as when someone attempts to Lie during a long speech.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can use Deception to weave traps to trip up anyone trying to deceive you.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPlantRumor',	'Plant Rumor',	'You intercede in a conversation to subtly damage another''s reputation and make their argument less compelling. The creature targeted by the triggering check gains a +2 circumstance bonus to its Will DC for that check.',	'Auditory, General, Linguistic, Mental, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You intercede in a conversation to subtly damage another''s reputation and make their argument less compelling.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPlantRumor", "name": "Plant Rumor", "traits": "General, Auditory, Linguistic, Mental, Skill, Society", "trigger": "You perceive a creature attempting a check using Deception, Diplomacy, or Intimidation against another creature''s Will DC.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You intercede in a conversation to subtly damage another''s reputation and make their argument less compelling. The creature targeted by the triggering check gains a +2 circumstance bonus to its Will DC for that check."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaMultilingual',	'Multilingual',	'<p>You easily pick up new languages. You learn two new languages. You learn an additional language if you are or become a master in Society and again if you are or become legendary.</p>
<p><strong>Special</strong> You can select this feat multiple times. Each time, you learn additional languages.</p>
',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You easily pick up new languages.',	'1',	'{"extra_languages": 2}',	NULL),
('feaJustKidding',	'Just Kidding!',	'You attempt to play off a social misstep as a joke. Attempt a Performance check against the same DC as your ally''s check. If you succeed, your ally treats their critical failure as a failure.',	'Auditory, Emotion, Fortune, General, Linguistic, Skill, Performance',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You attempt to play off a social misstep as a joke.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actJustKidding", "name": "Just Kidding!", "traits": "General, Auditory, Emotion, Fortune, Linguistic, Skill, Performance", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You attempt to play off a social misstep as a joke. Attempt a Performance check against the same DC as your ally''s check. If you succeed, your ally treats their critical failure as a failure."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaReadLips',	'Read Lips',	'You can read lips of others nearby who you can clearly see. The language read must be one that you know. When you''re at your leisure, you can do this automatically. In encounter mode or when attempting a more difficult feat of lipreading, you''re fascinated and off-guard during each round in which you focus on lip movements, and you must succeed at a Society check (DC determined by the GM) to successfully read someone''s lips.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can read lips of others nearby who you can clearly see.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCombatHack',	'Combat Hack',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Combat Hack</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 2</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Attack</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You are holding or wearing a hacking toolkit and have a free hand.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Attempt a Computers check to Hack an adjacent creature, hazard, or item with the tech trait. The DC is equal to the creature, item, or hazard''s Fortitude DC, or the Fortitude DC of the creature attending the object. If the target is an unattended object, the GM sets the DC for the check based on the item''s level. The target is temporarily immune to your attempts to Combat Hack it for 10 minutes.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> The target becomes glitching 2.<br><b>Success</b> The target becomes glitching 1.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> If the target has the glitching condition, reduce the value of its glitching condition by 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Computers, Attack, Manipulate',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'Attempt a Computers check to Hack an adjacent creature, hazard, or item with the tech trait.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCombatHack", "name": "Combat Hack", "traits": "General, Skill, Attack, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Attempt a Computers check to Hack an adjacent creature, hazard, or item with the tech trait. The DC is equal to the creature, item, or hazard''s Fortitude DC, or the Fortitude DC of the creature attending the object. If the target is an unattended object, the GM sets the DC for the check based on the item''s level. The target is temporarily immune to your attempts to Combat Hack it for 10 minutes.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> The target becomes glitching 2.<br><b>Success</b> The target becomes glitching 1.<br><b>Critical Failure</b> If the target has the glitching condition, reduce the value of its glitching condition by 1.", "requirements": "You are holding or wearing a hacking toolkit and have a free hand."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaPercussiveMaintenance',	'Percussive Maintenance',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Percussive Maintenance</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 2</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Crafting</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Attack</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You''re holding a tech item that has the glitching condition.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You try to repair an item by smashing it against a hard surface. Attempt a DC 10 flat check.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> Reduce the glitching condition by 2.<br><b>Success</b> Reduce the glitching condition by 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Crafting, Attack',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You try to repair an item by smashing it against a hard surface.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPercussiveMaintenance", "name": "Percussive Maintenance", "traits": "General, Skill, Crafting, Attack", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You try to repair an item by smashing it against a hard surface. Attempt a DC 10 flat check.<br><br><b>Critical Success</b> Reduce the glitching condition by 2.<br><b>Success</b> Reduce the glitching condition by 1.", "requirements": "You''re holding a tech item that has the glitching condition."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaCommunalCrafting',	'Communal Crafting',	'You can have other PCs help you Craft an item, under your direction. A helper PC rolls a check with a skill in which they''re trained. The skill must be Crafting or another skill relevant to the item, as determined by the GM. For example, a PC might use Religion to help you Craft an item with the divine trait or Warfare Lore to help you Craft a weapon. Your roll still determines whether you successfully create the item. Any helper''s roll contributes toward reducing the cost of raw materials using the numbers from Earn Income; this uses the ally PC''s proficiency rank in the skill and their level – 1 for their level.

Helping PCs must accompany you throughout the Craft activity (preventing them from pursuing other downtime activities) or the benefit is lost. The GM might determine that only a certain number of PCs can help depending on the circumstances.

Communal Crafting also allows you to take the role of a helper when someone else is crafting, provided they accept your help.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You can have other PCs help you Craft an item, under your direction.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTakeTheWheel',	'Take the Wheel',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Take the Wheel</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 3</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Piloting</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You Board and Take Control of an adjacent vehicle.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	3,	'You Board and Take Control of an adjacent vehicle.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTakeTheWheel", "name": "Take the Wheel", "traits": "General, Skill, Piloting", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You Board and Take Control of an adjacent vehicle."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaArmorAssist',	'Armor Assist',	'You are practiced in helping yourself and others don heavy gear. You can attempt an Athletics or Warfare Lore check with a DC determined by the GM (usually DC 15 for common armor, DC 20 for uncommon armor, and DC 25 for rare armor) to halve the time you take to don armor. You can halve an ally''s time to don armor by working with them to don the armor and succeeding at an Athletics or Warfare Lore check against the same DC.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"skill": [{"id": ["sklAthletics", "sklLoreWarfare"], "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You are practiced in helping yourself and others don heavy gear.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaAdditionalLore',	'Additional Lore',	'Your knowledge has expanded to encompass a new field. Choose a Lore skill subcategory. You become trained in it. At 3rd, 7th, and 15th levels, you gain an additional skill increase you can apply only to the chosen Lore subcategory.
Special You can select this feat more than once. Each time you must select a new subcategory of Lore, and you gain the additional skill increases to that subcategory for the listed levels.',	'General, Skill',	NULL,	1,	'Your knowledge has expanded to encompass a new field.',	'1',	'{"3": {"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''additional_lore_skill'')", "rank": "Expert"}]}}, "7": {"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''additional_lore_skill'')", "rank": "Master"}]}}, "15": {"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''additional_lore_skill'')", "rank": "Legendary"}]}}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''additional_lore_skill'')", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "additional_lore_skill", "type": "skill", "label": "Additional Lore Skill", "lore_filter": "untrained"}]}',	NULL),
('feaQuickRepair',	'Quick Repair',	'For you, the Repair activity loses the exploration trait and takes 1 minute instead of 10 minutes. If you''re a master in Crafting, it takes 3 actions. If you''re legendary, it takes 1 action.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'For you, the Repair activity loses the exploration trait and takes 1 minute instead of 10 minutes.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaShieldBlock',	'Shield Block',	'You snap your shield in place to ward off a blow. Your shield prevents you from taking an amount of damage up to the shield’s Hardness. You and the shield each take any remaining damage, possibly breaking or destroying the shield.',	'General',	NULL,	1,	'You snap your shield in place to ward off a blow. ',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actShieldBlock", "name": "Shield Block", "traits": "General", "trigger": "While you have your shield raised, you would take physical damage (bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing) from an attack.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You snap your shield in place to ward off a blow. Your shield prevents you from taking an amount of damage up to the shield’s Hardness. You and the shield each take any remaining damage, possibly breaking or destroying the shield."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaSteadyBalance',	'Steady Balance',	'You can keep your balance easily, even in adverse conditions. Whenever you roll a success using the Balance action, you get a critical success instead. You''re not off-guard while attempting to Balance on narrow surfaces and uneven ground.',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can keep your balance easily, even in adverse conditions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaHeftyHauler',	'Hefty Hauler',	'You can carry more than your frame implies. Increase your maximum and encumbered Bulk limits by 2.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can carry more than your frame implies. ',	'0',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_bonus": 2, "overburdened_bonus": 2}}',	NULL),
('feaPhreaker',	'Phreaker',	'You''ve learned how to hack using alternative methods. You can use Computers to Disable a Device or Slice a system using any computer, comm unit, or terminal instead of a slicer''s toolkit. If you''re an expert in Computers and the equipment you use is at least 3rd level, you gain a +1 item bonus to Disable a Device or Slice.

<b>Special</b> If you have the Combat Hack or Digital Diversion skill feat, you can use this feat to Combat Hack or Create a Diversion without a hacking toolkit.',	'General, Skill, Computers',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You''ve learned how to hack using alternative methods.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaElectricalEngineer',	'Electrical Engineer',	'You can fuel battery-powered devices by drawing electricity from different sources. Doing so takes 1 minute of work and an adjacent source of power appropriate to the device. If the source of power is a technological creature or hazard, it must have been destroyed within the last 10 minutes and provides charges equal to twice its level. If the source is a facility capable of charging a battery, the battery-powered device operates as if the battery were always fully charged. If you’re a master in Crafting, you can connect a device to a power source as a 3-action activity. If you’re legendary, it takes 1 action.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can fuel battery-powered devices by drawing electricity from different sources.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaSenseLife',	'Sense Life',	'You can reach out to sense the presence of living beings. You can use The Force for Perception checks to Seek living creatures. Even if you cannot see a creature (due to darkness or invisibility), you can sense their life force, though they are still Hidden (not Observed) unless you succeed at a precise location check. Constructs and Droids cannot be sensed this way.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You can reach out to sense the presence of living beings.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickSqueeze',	'Quick Squeeze',	'You Squeeze 5 feet per round (10 feet on a critical success). If you''re legendary in Acrobatics, you Squeeze at full Speed.',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You Squeeze 5 feet per round (10 feet on a critical success).',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaHolisticCare',	'Holistic Care',	'You provide emotional and spiritual care. Add frightened, stupefied, and stunned to the list of conditions you can reduce with Treat Condition. If the stunned condition has a duration instead of a value, you can’t use Treat Condition to reduce it.',	'Archetype, Skill',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMedicDedication", "type": "class"}, {"id": "feaTreatCondition", "type": "skill"}]}]',	6,	'You provide emotional and spiritual care. Add frightened, stupefied, and stunned to the list of conditions you can reduce with Treat Condition.',	'0',	NULL,	'arcMedic'),
('feaTelekineticReach',	'Telekinetic Reach',	'You can use the Force to manipulate small objects from a distance. You can perform a simple Interact action (such as opening an unlocked door, pulling a lever, or picking up an unattended object of Light Bulk or less) at a range of 30 feet. You cannot use this to Activate an item, Strike, or perform complex manipulations (like thievery) unless you have other abilities that allow it.',	'General, Skill',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You can use the Force to manipulate small objects from a distance.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLengthyDiversion',	'Lengthy Diversion',	'When you critically succeed to Create a Diversion, you continue to remain hidden after the end of your turn. This effect lasts for an amount of time that depends on the diversion and situation, as determined by the GM (minimum 1 additional round).',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'When you critically succeed to Create a Diversion, you continue to remain hidden after the end of your turn.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFavoredDisguise',	'Favored Disguise',	'You create a favored disguise that you can call upon at a moment''s notice. When you Impersonate, you can decide that the disguise becomes your favored disguise. If you have a holoskin or can Change Shape, you can always adopt your favored disguise when Impersonating. You still roll Deception for the Impersonate check but count any critical failure results as failures instead. You can have one favored disguise and gain an additional favored disguise you can employ at expert, master, and legendary proficiency in Deception.­',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You create a favored disguise that you can call upon at a moment''s notice.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaHobnobber',	'Hobnobber',	'You are skilled at learning information through conversation. The Gather Information exploration activity takes you half as long as normal (typically reducing the time to 1 hour). If you''re a master in Diplomacy and roll a critical failure to Gather Information, you get a failure instead. There is still no guarantee that a rumor you learn with Gather Information is accurate.',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You are skilled at learning information through conversation.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickCoercion',	'Quick Coercion',	'You can Coerce a creature after 1 round of conversation instead of 1 minute. You still can''t Coerce a creature in the midst of combat, or without engaging in a conversation.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can Coerce a creature after 1 round of conversation instead of 1 minute.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaIntimidatingShot',	'Intimidating Shot',	'You attempt to Demoralize a foe with your ranged weapon by firing it into the air, using ammo equal to the weapon’s expend and the weapon’s maximum range rather than the usual range of 30 feet. This check doesn’t take a –4 circumstance penalty if the target doesn’t share a language with you.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You attempt to Demoralize a foe with your ranged weapon by firing it into the air.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actIntimidatingShot", "name": "Intimidating Shot", "traits": "General, Intimidation, Skill", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You attempt to Demoralize a foe with your ranged weapon by firing it into the air, using ammo equal to the weapon’s expend and the weapon’s maximum range rather than the usual range of 30 feet. This check doesn’t take a –4 circumstance penalty if the target doesn’t share a language with you."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaBreathMastery',	'Breath Mastery',	'You can suspend your biological functions through meditation. You can hold your breath for 1 hour. You are immune to inhaled poisons and diseases while holding your breath. You can survive in a vacuum for a number of rounds equal to your Level without taking damage.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can suspend your biological functions through meditation.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaForcePersuasion',	'Force Persuasion',	'You weave a subtle suggestion into your words. You can use The Force skill instead of Diplomacy to Make an Impression or Request. If you critically succeed, the target doesn''t realize they were influenced by the Force; they believe the idea was their own.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaEmpathicSense", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You weave a subtle suggestion into your words. You can use The Force skill instead of Diplomacy to Make an Impression or Request.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaForceStabilization',	'Force Stabilization',	'You can use the Force to sustain a dying life. You can use The Force skill instead of Medicine to Administer First Aid (Stabilize). If you succeed, the target loses the Dying condition and remains unconscious at 0 HP. You do not need a medkit to perform this action.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You can use the Force to sustain a dying life.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickJump',	'Quick Jump',	'You can use High Jump and Long Jump as a single action instead of 2 actions. If you do, you don''t perform the initial Stride (nor do you fail if you don''t Stride 10 feet).',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can use High Jump and Long Jump as a single action instead of 2 actions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaEmpathicSense',	'Empathic Sense',	'You can read the emotional currents of those around you. You can use The Force skill instead of Perception to Sense Motive. Additionally, if you converse with a target for at least 1 minute, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your next Diplomacy or Deception check against them.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}]}]',	1,	'You can read the emotional currents of those around you.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Empathic Sense", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus if you converse for at least 1 minute.", "target": "sklDeception"}, {"name": "Empathic Sense", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus if you converse for at least 1 minute.", "target": "sklDiplomacy"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaAssurance',	'Assurance',	'Even in the worst circumstances, you can perform basic tasks. Choose a skill you’re trained in. You can forgo rolling a skill check for that skill to instead receive a result of 10 + your proficiency bonus (do not apply any other bonuses, penalties, or modifiers).
Special You can select this feat multiple times. Each time, choose a different skill and gain the benefits for that skill.',	'Fortune, General, Skill',	NULL,	1,	'Even in the worst circumstances, you can perform basic tasks.',	'1',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Assurance", "value": "Take {10 + level + rank(choice(''assurance_skill''))} instead of rolling.", "target": "choice(''assurance_skill'')"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "assurance_skill", "type": "skill", "label": "Assurance Skill", "filter": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}',	NULL),
('feaTerrainExpertise',	'Terrain Expertise',	'Your experience in navigating a certain type of terrain makes you supremely confident while doing so. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Survival checks in one of the following types of terrain, chosen when you select this feat: aquatic, arctic, desert, forest, mountain, plains, sky, space, swamp, or underground.

<b>Special</b> You can select this feat more than once, choosing a different type of terrain each time.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your experience in navigating a certain type of terrain makes you supremely confident while doing so.',	'1',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Terrain Expertise", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus in choice(''terrain'') terrain.", "target": "sklSurvival"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "Terrain", "options": ["Aquatic", "Arctic", "Desert", "Forest", "Mountain", "Plains", "Sky", "Space", "Swamp", "Underground"]}]}',	NULL),
('feaTelekineticHaul',	'Telekinetic Haul',	'Your mental grip is as strong as your physical one. When you use Telekinetic Reach, you can lift objects of up to 2 Bulk. You can also Sustain a levitated object for up to 1 minute by concentrating.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"feat": [{"feat": "feaTelekineticReach", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'Your mental grip is as strong as your physical one. ',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCloudMemory',	'Cloud Memory',	'You can wipe a small segment of recent memory. If a target is willing or Stunned/Unconscious, you can attempt a The Force check against their Will DC to erase the last 5 minutes of their memory. On a success, they forget the events (or recall a vague blur). This cannot be used in combat.',	'General, Skill, The Force',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaForcePersuasion", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can wipe a small segment of recent memory.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaRapidMantel',	'Rapid Mantel',	'You easily pull yourself onto ledges. When you Grab an Edge, you can pull yourself onto that surface and stand. You can use Athletics instead of a Reflex save to Grab an Edge. If you Climb or Leap to within 5 feet beneath the top of an edge, you can pull yourself onto the surface and stand as part of that action.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You easily pull yourself onto ledges.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaAutomaticKnowledge',	'Automatic Knowledge',	'<b>Prerequisites</b> expert in a skill with the Recall Knowledge action, Assurance in that skill

You know basic facts off the top of your head. Choose a skill you''re an expert in that has the Recall Knowledge action and for which you have the Assurance feat. You can use the Recall Knowledge action with that skill as a free action once per round. If you do, you must use Assurance on the skill check.

<b>Special</b> You can select this feat multiple times, choosing a different skill each time. You can use Automatic Knowledge with any skills you have chosen, but you can still use Automatic Knowledge only once per round.',	'General, Skill',	NULL,	2,	'You know basic facts off the top of your head. ',	'1',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickDisguise',	'Quick Disguise',	'You can set up a disguise in one-tenth the usual time (generally 1 minute). If you''re a master in Deception, you can create a full disguise and Impersonate as a 3-action activity. If you''re legendary, it takes a single action.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You can set up a disguise in one-tenth the usual time (generally 1 minute).',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaConfabulator',	'Confabulator',	'You pile lie upon lie. Reduce the circumstance bonus a target gains for your previous attempts to Create a Diversion or Lie to it from +4 to +2. If you''re a master in Deception, reduce the bonus to +1, and if you''re legendary, your targets don''t get these bonuses at all.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You pile lie upon lie.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaRobustRecovery',	'Robust Recovery',	'You learned folk medicine to help recover from diseases and poisons, and using it diligently has made you especially resilient. When you Treat a Disease or a Poison, or someone else uses one of these actions on you, increase the circumstance bonus granted on a success to +4, and if the result of the patient''s saving throw is a success, the patient gets a critical success.',	'General, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You learned folk medicine to help recover from diseases and poisons, and using it diligently has made you especially resilient.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuietAllies',	'Quiet Allies',	'You''re skilled at moving with a group. When you are Avoiding Notice and your allies Follow the Expert, you and those allies can roll a single Stealth check, using the lowest modifier, instead of rolling separately. This doesn''t apply for initiative rolls.',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You''re skilled at moving with a group.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaNoCauseForAlarm',	'No Cause for Alarm',	'You attempt to reduce panic. Attempt a Diplomacy check, comparing it to the Will DC of creatures in a 10-foot emanation around you who are frightened. Each of them is temporarily immune for 1 hour.',	'Auditory, Concentrate, Emotion, General, Linguistic, Mental, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You attempt to reduce panic.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actNoCauseForAlarm", "name": "No Cause for Alarm", "traits": "General, Auditory, Concentrate, Deception, Emotion, Linguistic, Mental, Skill,", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You attempt to reduce panic. Attempt a Diplomacy check, comparing it to the Will DC of creatures in a 10-foot emanation around you who are frightened. Each of them is temporarily immune for 1 hour.\n\n**Critical Success** Reduce the creature''s frightened value by 2.\n**Success**Reduce the creature''s frightened value by 1."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaLastingCoercion',	'Lasting Coercion',	'When you successfully Coerce someone, the maximum time they comply increases to a week, still determined by the GM. If you’re legendary, the maximum increases to a month.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'When you successfully Coerce someone, the maximum time they comply increases to a week, still determined by the GM.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaGlad-Hand',	'Glad-Hand',	'First impressions are your strong suit. When you meet someone in a casual or social situation, you can immediately attempt a Diplomacy check to Make an Impression on that creature rather than needing to converse for 1 minute. If you fail, you can engage in 1 minute of conversation and attempt a new check at the end of that time rather than accepting the failure or critical failure result.',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'First impressions are your strong suit.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCrowdControl',	'Crowd Control',	'Your voice can be heard over the noise in a crowd. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Diplomacy checks against crowds. The first time each round you Stride into a square containing a crowd, you can attempt a DC 20 Diplomacy check to move the crowd out of your way. A GM might use a different DC under certain circumstances, such as when the crowd has a level or set DC to disperse.

<b>Critical Success</b> As success, and the crowd departs from all adjacent squares as you move.
<b>Success</b> The crowd disperses from squares you move into.
<b>Failure</b> The crowd doesn''t move, but you can continue moving.
<b>Critical Failure</b> The crowd forcefully resists you and disrupts your Stride.',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'Your voice can be heard over the noise in a crowd.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Crowd Control", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus against crowds.", "target": "sklDiplomacy"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaContinualRecovery',	'Continual Recovery',	'You zealously monitor a patient''s progress to administer treatment faster. When you Treat Wounds, your patient becomes immune for only 10 minutes instead of 1 hour. This applies only to your Treat Wounds activities, not any other the patient receives.',	'General, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You zealously monitor a patient''s progress to administer treatment faster.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaNimbleCrawl',	'Nimble Crawl',	'You can Crawl incredibly swiftly—up to half your Speed, rather than 5 feet. If you''re a master in Acrobatics, you can Crawl at full Speed, and if you''re legendary, you aren''t off-guard while prone.',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You can Crawl incredibly swiftly—up to half your Speed, rather than 5 feet.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaDiveForCover',	'Dive for Cover',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Dive for Cover</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 2</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Acrobatics</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    When threatened, you can quickly take a dive and find somewhere to hunker down. You Leap, land prone, and immediately Take Cover, which allows you to hunker down and gain greater cover against ranged attacks.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'When threatened, you can quickly take a dive and find somewhere to hunker down.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDiveForCover", "name": "Dive for Cover", "traits": "General, Skill, Acrobatics", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "When threatened, you can quickly take a dive and find somewhere to hunker down. You Leap, land prone, and immediately Take Cover, which allows you to hunker down and gain greater cover against ranged attacks."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaBattleMedicine',	'Battle Medicine',	'You can patch up wounds, even in combat. Attempt a Medicine check with the same DC as for Treat Wounds and restore the corresponding amount of HP; this doesn''t remove the wounded condition. As with Treat Wounds, you can attempt checks against higher DCs if you have the minimum proficiency rank. The target is then immune to your Battle Medicine for 1 day. This does not make them immune to, or otherwise count as, Treat Wounds.',	'General, Healing, Manipulate, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You can patch up wounds, even in combat.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBattleMedicine", "name": "Battle Medicine", "traits": "General, Healing, Manipulate, Medicine, Skill", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You can patch up wounds, even in combat. Attempt a Medicine check with the same DC as for Treat Wounds and restore the corresponding amount of HP; this doesn''t remove the wounded condition. As with Treat Wounds, you can attempt checks against higher DCs if you have the minimum proficiency rank. The target is then immune to your Battle Medicine for 1 day. This does not make them immune to, or otherwise count as, Treat Wounds.", "requirements": "You’re holding or wearing a medkit."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaAncestralParagon',	'Ancestral Paragon',	'Whether through instinct, study, or magic, you feel a deeper connection to your ancestry. You gain a 1st-level ancestry feat.',	'General',	NULL,	3,	'Whether through instinct, study, or magic, you feel a deeper connection to your ancestry.',	'0',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''ancestral_paragon_feat'')", "type": "ancestry"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "ancestral_paragon_feat", "type": "ancestry_feat", "label": "Ancestral Paragon Feat", "filter": {"level": 1}}]}',	NULL),
('feaBattleCry',	'Battle Cry',	'When you roll initiative, you can yell a mighty battle cry and Demoralize an observed foe as a free action. If you''re legendary in Intimidation, you can use a reaction to Demoralize your foe when you critically succeed at an attack roll.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'When you roll initiative, you can yell a mighty battle cry and Demoralize an observed foe as a free action.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaAdvancedFirstAid',	'Advanced First Aid',	'You use your medical training to ameliorate sickness or assuage fears. When you use Medicine to Administer First Aid, instead of Stabilizing a character or Stopping Bleeding, you can reduce an ally''s frightened or sickened condition by 2, or remove either of those conditions entirely on a critical success. You can remove only one condition at a time. The DC for the Medicine check is usually the DC of the effect that caused the condition.',	'General, Skill, Medicine, Healing, Manipulate',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You use your medical training to ameliorate sickness or assuage fears.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaStuntManeuver',	'Stunt Maneuver',	'Whether you''re a natural ace or a veteran pilot, you can push a vehicle to perform incredible stunts. Remove the reckless trait when you attempt a Stunt with a –1 penalty. If you''re a master in Piloting, remove the reckless trait when you attempt a Stunt with a –2 penalty or lower. If you''re legendary in Piloting, remove the reckless trait from any Stunt you attempt.',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'Whether you''re a natural ace or a veteran pilot, you can push a vehicle to perform incredible stunts.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPrescientPlanner',	'Prescient Planner',	'<strong>Cost</strong> the Price of the chosen item
<strong>Requirements</strong> You haven’t used this ability since the last time you were able to purchase goods.

You regularly create convoluted plans and contingencies, using your resources to enact them. You take 1 minute to remove your backpack, then carefully remove an item you hadn''t previously declared that you purchased—you intuited that you would come to need the item and purchased it at the latest opportunity. The item must be a piece of adventuring gear (from the table on page 240 or other sources of adventuring gear), and can''t be a weapon, armor, serum, magic item, or other treasure. It must be common with a level no higher than half your level, and its Bulk must be low enough that carrying it wouldn''t have made you encumbered.',	'General',	NULL,	3,	'You regularly create convoluted plans and contingencies, using your resources to enact them. ',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaWardMedic',	'Ward Medic',	'You''ve studied in large medical wards, treating several patients at once and tending to all their needs. When you use Treat Disease or Treat Wounds, you can treat up to two targets. If you''re a master in Medicine, you can treat up to four targets, and if you''re legendary, you can treat up to eight targets.',	'General, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You''ve studied in large medical wards, treating several patients at once and tending to all their needs.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaWaryDisarmament',	'Wary Disarmament',	'If you trigger a device or set off a trap while disarming it, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your AC or saving throw against the device or trap. This applies only to attacks or effects triggered by your failed attempt, not to any later ones, such as additional attacks from a complex trap.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'If you trigger a device or set off a trap while disarming it, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your AC or saving throw against the device or trap.',	'0',	'{"ac": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Wary Disarmament", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus against a device or trap you trigger.", "target": "ac"}]}, "saving_throw": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Wary Disarmament", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus against a device or trap you trigger.", "target": "all"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaUnmistakableLore',	'Unmistakable Lore',	'You never get information about your areas of expertise wrong. When you Recall Knowledge using any Lore subcategory in which you''re trained, if you roll a critical failure, you get a failure instead. If you''re a master in a Lore subcategory, on a critical success, you gain even more information or context than usual.',	'General, Skill, Lore',	'[{"skill": [{"rank": "Expert", "trait": "Lore"}]}]',	2,	'You never get information about your areas of expertise wrong.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaStreetwise',	'Streetwise',	'You know about life on the streets and feel the pulse of your local settlement. You can use your Society modifier instead of your Diplomacy modifier to Gather Information. In any settlement you frequent regularly, you can use the Recall Knowledge action with Society to know the same sorts of information that you could discover with Diplomacy to Gather Information. The DC is usually significantly higher, but you know the information without spending time gathering it. If you fail to recall the information, you can still subsequently attempt to Gather Information normally.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You know about life on the streets and feel the pulse of your local settlement.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickSwim',	'Quick Swim',	'You Swim 5 feet farther on a success and 10 feet farther on a critical success, to a maximum of your Speed. If you''re legendary in Athletics, you gain a swim Speed equal to your Speed.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You Swim 5 feet farther on a success and 10 feet farther on a critical success, to a maximum of your Speed.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaSlipperySecrets',	'Slippery Secrets',	'You elude and evade attempts to uncover your true nature or intentions. When an effect tries to read your mind, detect whether you are lying, or reveal your identity, you can attempt a Deception check against the effect''s DC. If you succeed, the effect reveals nothing.',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You elude and evade attempts to uncover your true nature or intentions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaIntimidatingProwess',	'Intimidating Prowess',	'In situations where you can physically menace the target when you Coerce or Demoralize, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your Intimidation check and you ignore the penalty for not sharing a language. If your Strength modifier is +5 or higher and you are a master in Intimidation, this bonus increases to +2.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert"}], "attribute": [{"STR": 3}]}]',	2,	'In situations where you can physically menace the target when you Coerce or Demoralize, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your Intimidation check and you ignore the penalty for not sharing a language.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Intimidating Prowess", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Coerce or Demoralize; +2 if Master and STR +5; no penalty for not sharing a language.", "target": "sklIntimidation"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaPrescientConsumable',	'Prescient Consumable',	'You can predict which consumables you might need in advance. When using Prescient Planner, you can procure a consumable item from your backpack, instead of a piece of adventuring gear. The consumable item must still be common with a level no higher than half your level, and its Bulk must be low enough that carrying it wouldn''t have made you encumbered.',	'General',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaPrescientPlanner", "type": "general"}]}]',	7,	'You can predict which consumables you might need in advance.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTerrifiedRetreat',	'Terrified Retreat',	'When you critically succeed at the Demoralize action, if the target''s level is lower than yours, the target is fleeing for 1 round.',	'General, Skill, Intimidation',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'When you critically succeed at the Demoralize action, if the target''s level is lower than yours, the target is fleeing for 1 round.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPushIt',	'Push It',	'Whenever you succeed at a Piloting check, the vehicle you''re piloting gains a +10-foot circumstance bonus to all its Speeds until the end of your turn. If you critically succeed, this bonus increases to +15 feet.',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'Whenever you succeed at a Piloting check, the vehicle you''re piloting gains a +10-foot circumstance bonus to all its Speeds until the end of your turn.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaSwiftSneak',	'Swift Sneak',	'You can move your full Speed when you Sneak. You can use Swift Sneak while Burrowing, Climbing, Flying, or Swimming instead of Striding if you have the corresponding movement type.',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You can move your full Speed when you Sneak.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaMonsterCrafting',	'Monster Crafting',	'You can use the parts of monsters to aid in crafting. You can use the body of a monster to help Craft items, using Survival instead of Crafting for the Craft activity when you do so. If parts of the monster''s body are valuable, you can expend them toward the item''s raw material cost as well. (The GM makes the determination if the monster''s entry doesn''t list any valuable materials from its body.)

If you spend additional days working on the item, reduce the Price using the monster''s level instead of your own. Certain items may require specific creatures in their Craft requirement.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You can use the parts of monsters to aid in crafting.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFoilSenses',	'Foil Senses',	'You are adept at foiling creatures'' special senses and cautious enough to safeguard against them at all times. Whenever you use the Avoid Notice, Hide, or Sneak actions, you are always considered to be taking precautions against special senses (see Detecting with Other Senses sidebar under Detecting Creatures).',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You are adept at foiling creatures'' special senses and cautious enough to safeguard against them at all times.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickUnlock',	'Quick Unlock',	'You can Pick a Lock using 1 action instead of 2.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You can Pick a Lock using 1 action instead of 2.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaImpeccableCrafting',	'Impeccable Crafting',	'You craft flawless creations with great efficiency. Whenever you roll a success at a Crafting check to make an item of the type you chose with Specialty Crafting, you get a critical success instead.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaSpecialtyCrafting", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'ou craft flawless creations with great efficiency.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaExpeditiousSearch',	'Expeditious Search',	'You have a system that lets you search at great speed, finding details and secrets twice as quickly as others can. When Searching, you take half as long as usual to Search a given area. This means that while exploring, you double the Speed you can move while ensuring you’ve Searched an area before walking into it (up to half your Speed). If you’re legendary in Perception, you instead Search areas four times as quickly.',	'General',	'[{"perception": {"rank": "Master"}}]',	7,	'You have a system that lets you search at great speed, finding details and secrets twice as quickly as others can.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaQuickClimb',	'Quick Climb',	'When Climbing, you move 5 more feet on a success and 10 more feet on a critical success, up to your Speed. If you''re legendary in Athletics, you gain a climb Speed equal to your Speed.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'When Climbing, you move 5 more feet on a success and 10 more feet on a critical success, up to your Speed.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaShamelessRequest',	'Shameless Request',	'Shameless requests are your specialty. When you Request something, you reduce any DC increases for making an outrageous request by 2, and if you roll a critical failure for your Request, you get a failure instead. While this means you can never cause your target to reduce their attitude toward you by making a Request, they eventually tire of requests, even though they still have a positive attitude toward you.',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'Shameless requests are your specialty.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCraftAnything',	'Craft Anything',	'You can find ways to craft just about anything, despite restrictions. As long as you have the appropriate Crafting skill feat (such as Magical Crafting for magic items) and meet the item''s level and proficiency requirements, you ignore just about any other requirement, such as being of a specific ancestry or providing spells. If a requirement adds to the item''s cost, you must still pay it (including castings of spells that themselves have a cost). You can''t ignore requirements of special items that have exclusive means of access and Crafting, such as artifacts. The GM decides whether you can ignore a requirement.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can find ways to craft just about anything, despite restrictions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFlyAnything',	'Fly Anything',	'You can intuit how even the most interesting vehicles function. You can pilot a ship even if it would be physiologically impossible for you, including those that require telepathy or other supernatural abilities. You can use Piloting instead of Crafting to Repair a part of a vehicle, starship, or mech with a –2 circumstance penalty as long as you have the appropriate parts available to you. You can use Piloting instead of Computers to Hack a vehicle, starship, or mech with a –2 circumstance penalty.',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	' You can intuit how even the most interesting vehicles function.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendaryCodebreaker',	'Legendary Codebreaker',	'Your skill with languages and codes is so great you can decipher information with little more than a quick read through a text. You can Decipher Writing using Society while reading at normal speed. If you slow down and spend the full amount of time that''s ordinarily required and roll a success, you get a critical success; if you critically succeed while spending the normal amount of time, you gain a nearly wordfor-word understanding of the document.',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'Your skill with languages and codes is so great you can decipher information with little more than a quick read through a text.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendaryProfessional',	'Legendary Professional',	'Your fame has spread throughout the galaxy (for instance, if you have Warfare Lore, you might be a legendary general or tactician). This works as Legendary Performer, except you gain higher-level jobs when you Earn Income with Lore.',	'General, Skill, Lore',	'[{"skill": [{"rank": "Legendary", "trait": "Lore"}]}]',	15,	'Your fame has spread throughout the galaxy (for instance, if you have Warfare Lore, you might be a legendary general or tactician).',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaCloudJump',	'Cloud Jump',	'Your unparalleled athletic skill allows you to jump impossible distances. Triple the distance you jump on a successful Long Jump (so you could jump 90 feet with an Athletics result of 30). When you successfully High Jump, use the distance jumped and distance limit for a Long Jump but don''t triple the distance.

You can jump a distance greater than your Speed by spending additional actions when you Long Jump or High Jump. For each additional action spent, add your Speed to the distance limit.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'Your unparalleled athletic skill allows you to jump impossible distances.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendaryMedic',	'Legendary Medic',	'You''ve discovered medical breakthroughs or techniques that achieve miraculous results. Once per day for each target, you can spend 1 hour treating that target and attempt a Medicine check to remove a disease or the blinded, deafened, doomed, or drained condition. Use the DC of the disease or of the spell or effect that created the condition. If the effect''s source is an artifact, above 20th level, or similarly powerful, increase the DC by 10.',	'General, Skill, Medicine',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You''ve discovered medical breakthroughs or techniques that achieve miraculous results.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendaryLinguist',	'Legendary Linguist',	'You’re so skilled with languages you can create a pidgin instantly. You can always talk to any creature that has a language—even a language you don’t know—by creating a new pidgin language that uses simplified terms and conveys basic concepts. To do so, you must first understand at least what medium of communication the creature uses (speech, sign language, and so on).',	'General, Skill, Society',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaMultilingual", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklSociety", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You’re so skilled with languages you can create a pidgin instantly.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendaryPerformer',	'Legendary Performer',	'Your fame has spread throughout the galaxy. Creatures who have any listed skill in Society have heard of you and usually have an attitude toward you one step better than normal, depending on your reputation and the creature''s disposition. For instance, if you''re well-known for cruel and demanding behavior, creatures might be intimidated by you, rather than be friendly toward you. When you Earn Income with Performance, you attract higher-level audiences than your location would allow, as audiences flock to see you. For instance, famous socialites and spectra might travel to a dive bar in a backwater port to hear you perform. Typically, this increases the audiences available to your level or by two levels, whichever is higher.',	'General, Skill, Performance',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaVirtuosicPerformer", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'Your fame has spread throughout the galaxy.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPredatorsEye',	'Predator''s Eye',	'Your eye magnifies distant targets as well as a scope. You can adjust your sight in that eye as a single action to Seek a specific creature with a +2 circumstance bonus to your Perception check, or Seek to search a 10-foot square up to 100 feet away for any undetected or hidden creatures or objects. You don''t take penalties for an object or creature being too far away unless you''re more than 2 miles away.',	'General, Skill, Nature',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	7,	'Your eye magnifies distant targets as well as a scope.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTechCrafting',	'Tech Crafting',	'You can Craft level 1 or higher tech items, though some have other requirements. When you select this feat, you gain formulas for four common tech items of 2nd level or lower.',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You can Craft level 1 or higher tech items, though some have other requirements, as listed in Chapter 6: Equipment.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPowerfulLeap',	'Powerful Leap',	'You can jump 5 feet up with a vertical Leap without making a High Jump. You also increase the horizontal distance when you Leap, including as part of a High Jump or Long Jump, by 5 feet.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You can jump 5 feet up with a vertical Leap without making a High Jump.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendarySneak',	'Legendary Sneak',	'You''re always sneaking unless you choose to be seen, even when there''s nowhere to hide. You can Hide and Sneak even without cover or being concealed. When you employ an exploration tactic other than Avoiding Notice, you also gain the benefits of Avoiding Notice unless you choose not to.',	'General, Skill, Stealth',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaSwiftSneak", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You''re always sneaking unless you choose to be seen, even when there''s nowhere to hide.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaInventor',	'Inventor',	'You are a genius at Crafting, easily able to determine how things are made and create new inventions. You can spend downtime to invent a common formula that you don''t know. This works just like the Craft activity: you spend half the Price of the formula up front, attempt a Crafting check, and on a success either finish the formula by paying the difference or work for longer to decrease the Price. The difference is that you spend the additional time in research, design, and development, rather than in creating an item. Once it''s complete, you add the new formula you invented to your formula book.

The GM might allow you to invent uncommon or rare formulas, typically with an increased DC. You need the Magical Crafting feat to invent hybrid and magical formulas.',	'General, Skill, Crafting, Downtime',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You are a genius at Crafting, easily able to determine how things are made and create new inventions.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaLegendarySurvivalist',	'Legendary Survivalist',	'You can survive indefinitely without food or water and can endure severe, extreme, and incredible cold and heat without taking damage from doing so.',	'General, Skill, Survival',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can survive indefinitely without food or water and can endure severe, extreme, and incredible cold and heat without taking damage from doing so.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaFoolTheCamera',	'Fool the Camera',	'You know how to fool security cameras and tech items that confer special senses, such as scopes. Whenever you use the Avoid Notice, Hide, or Sneak actions, you''re always considered to be taking precautions against special senses from tech items. In addition, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your Stealth DC to Avoid Notice by cameras and technological hazards.',	'General, Skill, Computers',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You know how to fool security cameras and tech items that confer special senses, such as scopes.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Fool the Camera", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Avoid Notice DC against cameras and technological hazards.", "target": "sklStealth"}]}}',	NULL),
('feaVirtuosicPerformer',	'Virtuosic Performer',	'You have exceptional talent with one type of performance. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus when making a certain type of performance. If you are a master in Performance, this bonus increases to +2. Select one of the following specialties and apply the bonus when attempting Performance checks of that type. If it''s unclear whether the specialty applies, the GM decides.

Specialty	Examples
Acting	Drama, live streams, reality shows
Comedy	Buffoonery, joke telling, stand-up routines
Dance	Ballet, ballroom, interpretive, pop, traditional
Keyboards	Keytar, organ, piano
Oratory	Epic, ode, poetry, storytelling
Percussion	Bells, chimes, drum kit, xylophone
Singing	Ballad, chant, pop, rock, shanty
Strings	Guitar, singing coil, theremin
Synths	Synth deck, turn table
Winds	Horn, flute, pipes
',	'General, Skill, Performance',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You have exceptional talent with one type of performance.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Virtuosic Performer", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to performing choice(''Performance''); +2 if Master.", "target": "sklPerformance"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "Performance", "options": ["Acting", "Comedy", "Dance", "Keyboards", "Oratory", "Percussion", "Singing", "Strings", "Synths", "Winds"]}]}',	NULL),
('feaLegendaryThief',	'Legendary Thief',	'Your ability to Steal defies belief. You can attempt to Steal something that is actively wielded or that would be extremely noticeable or time consuming to remove (like worn shoes or armor). You must do so slowly and carefully, spending at least 1 minute (and significantly longer for items that are normally time consuming to remove, like armor). Throughout this duration you must have some means of staying hidden, such as the cover of darkness or a bustling crowd. Even if you succeed, if the item is extremely prominent—like a suit of full plate armor—onlookers will quickly notice it''s gone after you steal it.',	'General, Skill, Thievery',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "feaPickpocket", "type": "skill"}], "skill": [{"id": "sklThievery", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'Your ability to Steal defies belief.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaWallJump',	'Wall Jump',	'You can use your momentum from a jump to propel yourself off a wall. If you''re adjacent to a wall at the end of a jump (whether performing a High Jump, Long Jump, or Leap), you don''t fall as long as your next action is another jump. Your previous jump gives you momentum, letting you use High Jump or Long Jump as a single action, but you don''t get to Stride as part of the activity.

You can use Wall Jump only once in a turn, unless you''re legendary in Athletics, in which case you can use it as many times as you can use consecutive jump actions in that turn.',	'General, Skill, Athletics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You can use your momentum from a jump to propel yourself off a wall.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaPowerSlide',	'Power Slide',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Power Slide</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] to [three-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 3</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Piloting</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You throw the vehicle into a barely controlled skid, turning sharply to evade pursuit. You Drive with a –2 penalty to your Piloting check, gaining the effects of the Drive action for the same number of actions you spent to Power Slide. At the end of the movement, if you succeed, you can turn the vehicle up to 90 degrees. If you critically succeed at your Piloting check, you can instead turn the vehicle up to 180 degrees.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Piloting',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklPiloting", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	3,	'You throw the vehicle into a barely controlled skid, turning sharply to evade pursuit.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPowerSlide", "name": "Power Slide", "traits": "General, Skill, Piloting", "action_cost": "[one-action] to [three-actions]", "description": "You throw the vehicle into a barely controlled skid, turning sharply to evade pursuit. You Drive with a –2 penalty to your Piloting check, gaining the effects of the Drive action for the same number of actions you spent to Power Slide. At the end of the movement, if you succeed, you can turn the vehicle up to 90 degrees. If you critically succeed at your Piloting check, you can instead turn the vehicle up to 180 degrees."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaTrainAnimal',	'Train Animal',	'You spend time teaching an animal to do a certain action. You can either select a basic action the animal already knows how to do (typically those listed in the Command an Animal action) or attempt to teach the animal a new basic action. The GM determines the DC of any check required and the amount of time the training takes (usually at least a week). It''s usually impossible to teach an animal a trick that uses critical thinking. If you''re expert, master, or legendary in Nature, you might be able to train more unusual creatures, at the GM''s discretion.<br><br><strong>Success</strong> The animal learns the action. If it was an action the animal already knew, you can Command the Animal to take that action without attempting a Nature check. If it was a new basic action, add that action to the actions the animal can take when Commanded, but you must still roll.<br><strong>Failure</strong> The animal doesn''t learn the trick.',	'General, Skill, Nature',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklNature", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'You spend time teaching an animal to do a certain action.',	'0',	NULL,	NULL),
('feaTestPowerSlots',	'Test Power Grant Feat',	'Test feat that grants power slots',	'',	NULL,	1,	'Test',	'0',	'{"power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 2, "level": 1}]}}',	NULL),
('feaPowerTraining',	'Power Training',	'Grants a power slot at your current level',	'',	NULL,	1,	'Test',	'0',	'{"power": {"power_slot": [{"count": 1}]}}',	NULL),
('feaKipUp',	'Kip Up',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Kip Up</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 7</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Acrobatics</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You stand up. This movement doesn’t trigger reactions.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Acrobatics',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Master"}]}]',	7,	'You stand up.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKipUp", "name": "Kip Up", "traits": "General, Skill, Acrobatics", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You stand up. This movement doesn’t trigger reactions."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaTreatCondition',	'Treat Condition',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Treat Condition</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[two-actions]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Archetype</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Healing</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Manipulate</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Reuqirements</strong>
      <span>You are holding a medkit, or you are wearing one and have a hand free.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You treat an adjacent creature in an attempt to reduce the clumsy, enfeebled, or sickened condition. If a creature has multiple conditions from this list, choose one. Attempt a counteract check against the condition using your Medicine modifier as your counteract modifier and the condition’s source to determine the DC. You can’t treat a condition that came from an artifact or effect above 20th level unless you have Legendary Medic; even if you do, the counteract DC increases by 10. Treating a Condition that is continually applied under certain circumstances (for instance, the enfeebled condition a holy character gains from carrying a weapon with the unholy rune) has no effect as long as the circumstances continue.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> Reduce the condition value by 2.<br><strong>Success</strong> Reduce the condition value by 1.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Increase the condition value by 1.
  </div>
</div>',	'Archetype, Healing, Manipulate, Skill',	'[{"feat": [{"id": "cftMedicDedication", "type": "class"}]}]',	4,	'You treat an adjacent creature in an attempt to reduce the clumsy, enfeebled, or sickened condition.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTreatCondition", "name": "Treat Condition", "traits": "Archetype, Healing, Manipulate, Skill", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You treat an adjacent creature in an attempt to reduce the clumsy, enfeebled, or sickened condition. If a creature has multiple conditions from this list, choose one. Attempt a counteract check against the condition using your Medicine modifier as your counteract modifier and the condition’s source to determine the DC. You can’t treat a condition that came from an artifact or effect above 20th level unless you have Legendary Medic; even if you do, the counteract DC increases by 10. Treating a Condition that is continually applied under certain circumstances (for instance, the enfeebled condition a holy character gains from carrying a weapon with the unholy rune) has no effect as long as the circumstances continue.<br><br><strong>Critical Success</strong> Reduce the condition value by 2.<br><strong>Success</strong> Reduce the condition value by 1.<br><strong>Critical Failure</strong> Increase the condition value by 1.", "requirements": "You are holding a medkit, or you are wearing them and have a hand free."}]}}',	'arcMedic'),
('feaKissItBetter',	'Kiss It Better',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Kiss It Better</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 2</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Deception</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You have a hand free and are adjacent to an ally who isn’t at full Hit Points.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You perform a token medical effort to convince an ally they''ve recovered from an injury. Attempt a Deception check with the same DC as for Treat Wounds. On a success, the target gains temporary Hit Points equal to half the corresponding amount of Hit Points from Treat Wounds. These temporary Hit Points last 1 round. Kiss It Better doesn''t remove the wounded condition. The target is temporarily immune to Kiss It Better for 24 hours.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You perform a token medical effort to convince an ally they''ve recovered from an injury.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKissItBetter", "name": "Kiss It Better", "traits": "General, Skill, Deception", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You perform a token medical effort to convince an ally they''ve recovered from an injury. Attempt a Deception check with the same DC as for Treat Wounds. On a success, the target gains temporary Hit Points equal to half the corresponding amount of Hit Points from Treat Wounds. These temporary Hit Points last 1 round. Kiss It Better doesn''t remove the wounded condition. The target is temporarily immune to Kiss It Better for 24 hours.", "requirements": "You have a hand free and are adjacent to an ally who isn’t at full Hit Points."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaLegendaryTroll',	'Legendary Troll',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Legendary Troll</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 15</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Deception</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements</strong>
      <span>You or your target are using a comm unit, datapad, or other computer.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Attempt a Deception check against the Will DC of a target within 60 feet. On a success, the target is off-guard for 1 round, and on a critical success, it''s confused for 1 round. The target''s reaction gives you information about it as though you''d attempted to Recall Knowledge using an appropriate skill and received the same result on your roll. The target is then temporarily immune to your Legendary Troll attempts for 24 hours.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'Attempt a Deception check against the Will DC of a target within 60 feet.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLegendaryTroll", "name": "Legendary Troll", "traits": "General, Skill, Deception", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Attempt a Deception check against the Will DC of a target within 60 feet. On a success, the target is off-guard for 1 round, and on a critical success, it''s confused for 1 round. The target''s reaction gives you information about it as though you''d attempted to Recall Knowledge using an appropriate skill and received the same result on your roll. The target is then temporarily immune to your Legendary Troll attempts for 24 hours.", "requirements": "You or your target are using a comm unit, datapad, or other computer."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaFeignDeath',	'Feign Death',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Feign Death</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 2</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Deception</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger</strong>
      <span>You take damage.</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You lie prone and Impersonate a corpse. As long as you don''t take any actions requiring anything other than your mind, you appear dead. To see through your ruse, a creature must succeed at a check against your Deception DC, either by Seeking or Recalling Knowledge. You can Ready an Action without ending this effect if you''re a master in Deception.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Deception',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Expert"}]}]',	2,	'You lie prone and Impersonate a corpse.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFeignDeath", "name": "Feign Death", "traits": "General, Skill, Deception", "trigger": "You take damage.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You lie prone and Impersonate a corpse. As long as you don''t take any actions requiring anything other than your mind, you appear dead. To see through your ruse, a creature must succeed at a check against your Deception DC, either by Seeking or Recalling Knowledge. You can Ready an Action without ending this effect if you''re a master in Deception."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaLegendaryNegotiation',	'Legendary Negotiation',	'<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Legendary Negotiation</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[three-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 15</span>
    </div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">General</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Skill</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Diplomacy</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You can negotiate incredibly quickly in adverse situations. You attempt to Make an Impression and then Request your opponent cease their current activity and engage in negotiations. You take a –5 penalty to your Diplomacy check. Generally, the DC of this check is the creature''s Will DC, although your GM may modify it based on the situation. Some creatures may be unable to stop regardless of their personal desires, and even those who agree to parley might ultimately find your arguments lacking and return to violence.
  </div>
</div>',	'General, Skill, Diplomacy',	'[{"skill": [{"id": "sklDiplomacy", "rank": "Legendary"}]}]',	15,	'You can negotiate incredibly quickly in adverse situations.',	'0',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actLegendaryNegotiation", "name": "Legendary Negotiation", "traits": "General, Skill, Diplomacy", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "You can negotiate incredibly quickly in adverse situations. You attempt to Make an Impression and then Request your opponent cease their current activity and engage in negotiations. You take a –5 penalty to your Diplomacy check. Generally, the DC of this check is the creature''s Will DC, although your GM may modify it based on the situation. Some creatures may be unable to stop regardless of their personal desires, and even those who agree to parley might ultimately find your arguments lacking and return to violence."}]}}',	NULL),
('feaSpecialtyCrafting',	'Specialty Crafting',	'Your training focused on Crafting one particular kind of item. Select one of the specialties listed below; you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Crafting checks to Craft items of that type. If you are a master in Crafting, this bonus increases to +2. If it''s unclear whether the specialty applies, the GM decides. Some specialties might apply only partially. For example, if you were making an Abadarcorp travel suit and had specialty in textiles, the GM might give you half your bonus because the item requires both armorsmithing and textiles to craft.

Specialty	Applicable Items
Armorsmithing	Armor, shields and upgrades
Artistry	Fine art, including jewelry
Automotives	Vehicles, including spaceships
Chemicals	Alcohol, ammunition, explosives, and fuel
Computer	Comm units, datapads, and virtual items
Engineering	Tech gadgets and accessories
Gunsmithing	Firearms and firearm upgrades
Life Science	Biotechnology and some pharmaceuticals
Robotics	Drones, mechs, and robots
Textiles	Clothing, leather, and polymer armor
',	'General, Skill, Crafting',	'[{"skill": {"id": "sklCrafting", "rank": "Trained"}}]',	1,	'Your training focused on Crafting one particular kind of item.',	'0',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Specialty Crafting", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to crafting choice(''Craft''); +2 if Master.", "target": "sklCrafting"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "Craft", "options": ["Armorsmithing", "Artistry", "Automotives", "Chemicals", "Computer", "Engineering", "Gunsmithing", "Life Science", "Robotics", "Textiles"]}]}',	NULL);

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Feature";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Feature" (
    "FeatureID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Description" text NOT NULL,
    "Features" jsonb,
    CONSTRAINT "Feature_FeatureID" PRIMARY KEY ("FeatureID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

INSERT INTO "Feature" ("FeatureID", "Name", "Description", "Features") VALUES
('clfLowlightVision',	'Low-Light Vision',	'Your specialized goggles grant you the ability to see in dim light as if it were bright light.',	'{"sense": {"lowlight_vision": true}}'),
('clfFearsomeBulwark',	'Fearsome Bulwark',	'Your sheer bulk terrifies foes, clearing a path for you on the battlefield. You can use your Constitution modifier instead of your Charisma modifier on Intimidation checks to Coerce or Demoralize and instead of your Strength modifier on Athletics checks to Reposition or Shove.',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Fearsome Bulwark", "value": "CON instead of CHA (+{con - cha}) to Coerce or Demoralize.", "target": "sklIntimidation"}, {"name": "Fearsome Bulwark", "value": "CON instead of STR (+{con - str}) to Reposition or Shove.", "target": "sklAthletics"}]}}'),
('clfWeaponSpecialization',	'Weapon Specialization',	'You''ve learned how to inflict greater injuries with the weapons you know best. You deal 2 additional damage with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you''re an expert. This damage increases to 3 if you''re a master, and 4 if you''re legendary.',	'{"attack": {"specialization_damage": {"Expert": 2, "Master": 3, "Legendary": 4}}}'),
('clfSkillIncreaseMaster',	'Skill Increase (Master)',	'At 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill increase. You can use this increase either to increase your proficiency rank to trained in one skill you''re untrained in, or to increase your proficiency rank in one skill in which you''re already trained to expert.

At 7th level, you can use skill increases to increase your proficiency rank to master in a skill in which you''re already an expert, and at 15th level, you can use them to increase your proficiency rank to legendary in a skill in which you''re already a master.',	'{"skill": {"skill_increase": [{"max": "Master", "count": 1}]}}'),
('clfMasterGunner',	'Master Gunner',	'You are a highly skilled sharpshooter and never go anywhere without your gun. Your proficiency rank increases to master with simple and martial guns, and increases to expert with advanced guns. You gain access to the critical specialization effects for all guns for which you have expert proficiency.',	'{"attack": [{"simple": [{"ranged": {"rank": "Master"}}]}, {"martial": [{"ranged": {"rank": "Master"}}]}, {"advanced": [{"ranged": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}]}'),
('clfWiseToTheGame',	'Wise to the Game',	'Using your words to influence others is what you do, and you easily recognize when others attempt to use the same tactics against you. You gain a +1 status bonus to your Perception DC against attempts to Feint or Lie to you and attempts to divert your attention with Create a Diversion, and a +1 status bonus to your Will DC against emotion effects.',	'{"perception": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Wise to the Game", "value": "+1 status bonus to DC against Feint, Lie, and Create a Diversion.", "target": "all"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Wise to the Game", "value": "+1 status bonus to DC against emotion effects.", "target": "will"}]}]}'),
('clfTactician',	'Tactician',	'When you aren''t directing allies, you focus on a situation''s shifting circumstances, readying to react. At the end of each of your turns, you gain one additional reaction, which you can use before the beginning of your next turn for any envoy reaction.',	NULL),
('clfInscrutable',	'Inscrutable',	'It''s nigh impossible for your enemies to unravel your schemes or your long-term plans. When a creature rolls a critical success or success on a Perception check to Sense Motive against you, or on a skill check to Gather Information or Recall Knowledge about your secrets, they get a failure instead. When you roll a critical failure or failure on a saving throw against an effect or ability that would read or reveal your thoughts, emotions, or intentions, you get a success instead.',	NULL),
('clfLightArmorExpertise',	'Light Armor Expertise',	'You''ve learned how to dodge while wearing light or no armor. Your proficiency ranks for light armor and unarmored defense increase to expert.',	'{"defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfLegendaryGunner',	'Legendary Gunner',	'You''re a local legend who''s known for your prowess with weaponry. Your proficiency rank increases to legendary with simple and martial guns, and to master with advanced guns. Your proficiency rank increases to expert with simple weapons, martial weapons, and unarmed attacks.',	'{"attack": [{"simple": [{"melee": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"ranged": {"rank": "Legendary"}}]}, {"martial": [{"melee": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"ranged": {"rank": "Legendary"}}]}, {"advanced": [{"ranged": {"rank": "Master"}}]}, {"unarmed": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfOperativesEdge',	'Operative''s Edge',	'You''ve developed keen awareness and attention to detail. Your proficiency rank for Perception increases to master. In addition, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to initiative rolls, making you faster to react during combat. If you take the Incredible Initiative feat, your circumstance bonus to initiative rolls becomes +3 instead.',	'{"perception": {"rank": "Master"}}'),
('clfOnTheMove',	'On the Move',	'You gain a +5-foot status bonus to your Speed. This increases to a +10-foot status bonus to your Speed at 16th level.',	'{"speed": {"bonus": [{"type": "status", "value": "5", "target": "base"}]}, "level_unlock": {"16": {"speed": {"bonus": [{"type": "status", "value": "10", "target": "base"}]}}}}'),
('clfReflexMastery',	'Reflex Mastery',	'You''ve learned to move quickly to avoid explosions, sentry turrets, and worse. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Reflex save, you get a critical success instead.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"reflex": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfResolve',	'Resolve',	'You''ve steeled your mind with resolve. Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Will save, you get a critical success instead.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"will": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfFlawlessOverclock',	'Flawless Overclock',	'You have perfectly calibrated your Custom Rig. The flat check DC for your Overclock actions is reduced from 13 to 10.',	NULL),
('clfAnalyticalHeuristics',	'Analytical Heuristics',	'You become trained in Medicine or in any Science lore, and your chassis is equipped with an integrated medikit (commercial-grade).',	'{"skill": {"grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Medicine or any Science Lore", "filter": [{"id": ["sklMedicine"]}, {"trait": ["Science"]}]}}}'),
('clfFocused',	'Focused',	'You''re highly focused on your target and able to discern their moves. When you roll a success on a Reflex save against your mark, you get a critical success instead.',	NULL),
('clfIntercede',	'Intercede',	'While you are Focused, you can use the Force to dampen impacts and intercept attacks meant for your allies.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Intercede</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Guardian</span><span class="trait-tag">Focused</span><span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger</strong><span>An enemy damages an ally within 15 feet of you.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You project a telekinetic cushion or physically intercept the blow. The damage the ally takes is reduced by  2 + your Level. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your next Attack roll against the triggering enemy before the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "actIntercede", "name": "Intercede", "level": 1, "traits": "Guardian, Focused, Force Power", "trigger": "An enemy damages an ally within 15 feet of you.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You project a telekinetic cushion or physically intercept the blow. The damage the ally takes is reduced by  2 + your Level. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your next Attack roll against the triggering enemy before the end of your next turn."}]}}'),
('clfUrbanOperator',	'Urban Operator',	'You are accustomed to urban environments and can move swiftly through a crowded cityscape. You ignore difficult terrain in urban environments, and greater difficult terrain from urban environments is only difficult terrain for you.',	NULL),
('clfCriticalAim',	'Critical Aim',	'The first time in each round when you Aim and successfully make a ranged Strike against your mark, add your weapon''s critical specialization effect to the attack even if you didn''t score a critical hit.',	NULL),
('clfReflexExpertise',	'Reflex Expertise',	'You''ve developed a knack for dodging danger. Your proficiency rank for Reflex saves increases to expert.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfCybotGalacticaInteractionMatrix',	'Cybot-Galactica Interaction Matrix',	'You become trained in Diplomacy or Society. You learn two additional languages at 1st level. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to checks to Make an Impression when following proper etiquette.',	'{"skill": {"grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Diplomacy or Society", "filter": [{"id": ["sklDiplomacy", "sklSociety"]}]}}, "extra_languages": 2}'),
('clfLegendaryImprovisation',	'Legendary Improvisation',	'Your improvisation skills have dramatically improved. Improvised Mastery triggers on skill checks using a skill that you don''t have legendary proficiency in, rather than master proficiency, and it grants you legendary proficiency for the triggering check, rather than master proficiency.',	NULL),
('clfVersatile',	'Versatile Human',	'Select a general feat of your choice for which you meet the prerequisites (as with your ancestry feat, you can select this general feat at any point during character creation).',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "general"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "feat", "label": "Versatile Human Feat", "filter": {"trait": ["General"]}}]}'),
('clfImprovisedMastery',	'Improvised Mastery',	'Whether by luck or instinct, you display impressive talent on the fly. You gain the Improvised Mastery action.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Improvised Mastery</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger</strong><span>You’re about to attempt a skill check using a skill that you don’t have master proficiency in, and you haven’t rolled yet.</span></div>
    <div><strong>Frequency</strong><span>Once per day.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You trust your instincts to see you through. You gain master proficiency with the triggering skill for the skill check.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actImprovisedMastery", "name": "Improvised Mastery", "traits": "Envoy", "trigger": "You’re about to attempt a skill check using a skill that you don’t have master proficiency in, and you haven’t rolled yet.", "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You trust your instincts to see you through. You gain master proficiency with the triggering skill for the skill check."}]}}'),
('clfWalkingArmory',	'Walking Armory',	'Your endurance training empowers you to carry a load of heavy equipment. When determining your Strength for using armor, you can instead choose to use your Constitution modifier. If you already meet the Strength requirement for the armor you''re wearing, reduce that armor''s Bulk by 1 (to a minimum of 1).

In addition, increase the amount of Bulk you can carry before becoming encumbered by half your Constitution modifier rounded up. Increase your maximum carried Bulk by your Constitution modifier.',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_bonus": "{-(-con // 2)}", "overburdened_bonus": "{con}", "armor_use_con_for_str": true, "armor_bulk_reduction_if_str_met": 1}}'),
('clfGalaxyRenowned',	'Galaxy Renowned',	'Your reputation as a shooter precedes you wherever you go in the galaxy. Your proficiency rank increases to legendary with advanced guns. Your proficiency rank for your operative class DC increases to master.',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Operative Class DC", "rank": "Master"}], "attack": [{"advanced": [{"ranged": {"rank": "Legendary"}}]}]}'),
('clfOperativeResilience',	'Operative Resilience',	'You have a hardy physique. Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to expert.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfSuppressingFire',	'Suppressing Fire',	'You have a knack for using powerful weapons to harry your foes and hinder their movement, preventing them from operating at their peak. If you make an attack with a weapon that has the area trait (such as from the Area Fire or Auto-Fire actions), you use it in a manner that suppresses your targets. Enemies in the affected area who fail their save against your attack become suppressed until the start of your next turn. A suppressed target takes a –1 circumstance penalty on attack rolls and takes a –10-foot status penalty to its Speeds. Some soldier abilities and class feats interact further with the suppressed condition.',	NULL),
('clfPrimaryTarget',	'Primary Target',	'You can focus fire on a single target when unleashing the full devastation of your powerful area weaponry. Before you make an area attack with a weapon (such as from the Area Fire or Auto-Fire actions), you can make a ranged Strike as a free action with the same weapon against a single creature in the area, who''s selected as your primary target. If your attack is a burst, you must select the creature closest to the center of the attack. If your attack is a cone or line, you must select the creature closest to you. If two or more creatures are equidistant, you can choose which one is your primary target. On a hit, if your primary target rolls a success against your Area Fire or Auto-Fire action, they get a failure instead. This Strike doesn''t count toward your multiple attack penalty.',	NULL),
('clfCorellianRiskTaker',	'Corellian Risk-Taker',	'You become Trained in Piloting or Deception (your choice). At 5th level, your rank in your chosen skill automatically increases to Expert.<br><br>You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to checks made to Feint in combat or to perform a Stunt while piloting a vehicle. Additionally, once per day, if you roll a Critical Failure on a Piloting or Deception check, you can treat it as a standard Failure instead.',	'{"5": {"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''corellian_skill'')", "rank": "Expert"}]}}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''corellian_skill'')", "rank": "Trained"}], "conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Corellian Risk-Taker", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Feint", "target": "sklDeception"}, {"name": "+1 circumstance bonus to Stunt", "value": "Corellian Risk-Taker", "target": "sklPiloting"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "corellian_skill", "type": "skill", "label": "Deception or Piloting", "filter": [{"id": ["sklDeception", "sklPiloting"]}]}]}'),
('clfForcePremonition',	'Force Premonition',	'',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powForcePremonition", "name": "Force Premonition", "level": 1, "traits": "Concentrate, Force Power, Fortune", "frequency": "Once per round", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You focus on a creature you can see. Roll a d20. This is your Premonition Roll. If you make a Strike against the chosen creature later this round, you must use the result of your Premonition Roll for your attack roll (instead of rolling a new d20). If you Strike the chosen creature using your Premonition Roll, you can use your Wisdom modifier for the attack roll instead of Strength or Dexterity.<br><br>If your Premonition Roll is low (a likely miss), you are not forced to attack. You can choose to use your remaining actions to move, use a Force Power, or perform a Skill action, knowing that an attack would have failed."}]}}'),
('clfConsularInitialProficiencies',	'Consular Initial Proficiencies',	'At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.<br><br><strong>Perception</strong><br><br>Master in Perception<br><br><strong>Saving Throws</strong><br><br>Expert in Fortitude<br>Trained in Reflex<br>Master in Will<br><br><strong>Skills</strong><br><br>Trained in The Force<br>
Trained in Diplomacy or Intimidation<br>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 3 plus your Intelligence modifier<br><br><strong>Attacks</strong><br><br>Trained in simple weapons<br>Trained in lightsabers<br>Trained in unarmed attacks<br><br><strong>Defenses</strong><br><br>Trained in light armor<br>Trained in unarmored defense<br><br><strong>Class DC</strong><br><br>Trained in consular class DC',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Consular Class DC", "rank": "Trained", "attribute": "WIS"}], "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}], "grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Diplomacy or Intimidation", "filter": [{"id": ["sklDiplomacy", "sklIntimidation"]}]}, "skill_increase": [{"max": "Trained", "count": 3}]}, "attack": [{"unarmed": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"simple": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}], "defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Trained"}}], "perception": {"rank": "Master"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfToughAsNails',	'Tough As Nails',	'Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Fortitude save, you get a critical success instead.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfAdaptiveWill',	'Adaptive Will',	'You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Will saves against effects that would control your actions, reflecting the stubborn independence of the human spirit.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Adaptive Will", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against effects that would control your actions.", "target": "will"}]}]}'),
('clfOuterRimResistance',	'Outer Rim Resistance',	'Choose Fire or Cold. You gain Resistance to that energy type equal to half your level (minimum 1). Additionally, you treat environmental conditions matching your chosen energy type (extreme heat or extreme cold) as one step less severe.',	NULL),
('clfSentinelsStrike',	'Sentinel''s Strike',	'When you act on your visions, you strike vital points. When you make a Strike against a creature that you used Force Premonition on this round, and you use the substitution to use Wisdom for the attack, you deal an extra 1d6 precision damage.<br><br>This damage increases by 1d6 at 5th, 9th, 13th, and 17th levels.',	NULL),
('clfLeadersConfidence',	'Leader''s Confidence',	'Whether you''re calm and collected or projecting confidence through gritted teeth, you don''t let your team see you lose your cool. You gain the Steel Yourselves! envoy directive.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Steel Yourselves!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span><span class="trait-tag">Healing</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Frequency</strong><span>Once per hour.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You encourage your allies to brace for impact or otherwise prepare for incoming damage. Allies within 60 feet who can sense you can spend 1 action on their turn to Brace For Impact. This action has the concentrate trait. Creatures that Brace for Impact gain temporary Hit Points equal to your Charisma modifier + your half your level for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Lead by Example</strong> If you spends two actions, you Brace For Impact. You and any ally who Braces for Impact before the start of your next turn also gain a +1 status bonus to saving throws against effects that deal damage for 1 minute.
  </div>
</div>',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSteelYourselves!", "name": "Steel Yourselves!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive, Healing", "frequency": "Once per hour.", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You encourage your allies to brace for impact or otherwise prepare for incoming damage. Allies within 60 feet who can sense you can spend 1 action on their turn to Brace For Impact. This action has the concentrate trait. Creatures that Brace for Impact gain temporary Hit Points equal to your Charisma modifier + your half your level for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Lead by Example</strong> If you spends two actions, you Brace For Impact. You and any ally who Braces for Impact before the start of your next turn also gain a +1 status bonus to saving throws against effects that deal damage for 1 minute."}]}}'),
('clfSentinelInitialProficiencies',	'Sentinel Initial Proficiencies',	'<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>
<div style="column-count: 2;">
<div><p><strong>Perception</strong></p>
<p>Expert in Perception</p></div>
<div><p><strong>Saving Throws</strong></p>
<p>Trained in Fortitude<br>Expert in Reflex<br>
Expert in Will</p></div>
<div><p><strong>Skills</strong></p>
<p>Trained in The Force<br>Trained in one skill determined by your Sentinel Path<br>Trained in a number of additional skills equal to 6  plus your Intelligence modifier</p></div>
<div><p><strong>Attacks</strong></p>
<p>Trained in simple weapons<br>Trained in martial weapons<br>Trained in lightsabers<br>Trained in unarmed attacks</p></div>
<div><p><strong>Defenses</strong></p>
<p>Trained in light armor<br>Trained in unarmored defense</p></div>
<div><p><strong>Class DC</strong></p>
<p>Trained in sentinel class DC</p></div></div>',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Sentinel Class DC", "rank": "Trained", "attribute": "WIS"}], "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklTheForce", "rank": "Trained"}], "skill_increase": [{"max": "Trained", "count": 6}]}, "attack": [{"unarmed": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"simple": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"martial": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"group": [{"lightsaber": {"rank": "Trained"}}]}], "defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Trained"}}], "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Trained"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfSoldierWeaponExpertise',	'Soldier Weapon Expertise',	'Through practical experience, you''ve learned how to use your weapons in a way that both pulverizes your foes and best takes advantage of your area attacks. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons, martial weapons, and unarmed attacks increases to expert. You gain access to the critical specialization effects of weapons with the area or automatic traits.',	'{"attack": [{"simple": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"martial": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"unarmed": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfSoldiersResolution',	'Soldier''s Resolution',	'Your proficiency rank for Will saves increases to master. When you roll a success on a Will save, you get a critical success instead.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"will": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfUnshakableJuggernaut',	'Unshakable Juggernaut',	'Your proficiency rank for Fortitude saves increases to legendary. When you roll a critical failure on a Fortitude save, you get a failure instead. When you fail a Fortitude save against an effect that deals damage, you halve the damage you take.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Legendary"}}]}'),
('clfSkillIncreaseExpert',	'Skill Increase (Expert)',	'At 3rd level and every 2 levels thereafter, you gain a skill increase. You can use this increase either to increase your proficiency rank to trained in one skill you''re untrained in, or to increase your proficiency rank in one skill in which you''re already trained to expert.

At 7th level, you can use skill increases to increase your proficiency rank to master in a skill in which you''re already an expert, and at 15th level, you can use them to increase your proficiency rank to legendary in a skill in which you''re already a master.',	'{"skill": {"skill_increase": [{"max": "Expert", "count": 1}]}}'),
('clfTacticalBarrage',	'TacticalBarrage',	'You unleash a devastating barrage of attacks upon your mark. Your multiple attack penalty for attacks against your mark is –3 (–2 with an agile weapon) on your second attack of the turn instead of –5, and –6 (–4 with an agile weapon) on your third or subsequent attack of the turn, instead of –10.',	'{"hook": {"multiattack_penalty_override": {"base": 3, "agile": 2}}}'),
('clfAdaptiveTalent',	'Adaptive Talent',	'You''re quick thinking and adaptable, capable of picking up new skills and talents with little practice or training. During your daily preparations, select one skill feat that you meet the prerequisites for. You gain this skill feat until you prepare again. Since you have this feat temporarily, you can''t use it as a prerequisite for a permanent character option. You can use this for effects that temporarily give you access to other abilities, such as taking Multilingual to temporarily learn a new language.

As your envoy level increases, so does your ability to adapt to new situations. At 9th level and 15th level, increase the number of skill feats you gain this way by 1. You can use feats that you temporarily gain through adaptive talent as a prerequisite for other feats that you temporarily gain through adaptive talent, but you still can''t use them as prerequisites for permanent character options.',	NULL),
('clfSavvyImproviser',	'Savvy Improviser',	'You can use Improvised Mastery twice per day. Additionally, the first time per day when you roll a natural 1 on a Deception, Diplomacy, or Intimidation check, you don''t automatically reduce your degree of success (you get a critical failure only if your result is 10 lower than the DC).',	NULL),
('clfIntegratedUtilitySockets',	'Integrated Utility Sockets',	'You become trained in Computers or Crafting. You gain a built-in datajack or arc welder (choose one). You can use your internal comms to interface with local networks without a handheld device.',	'{"skill": {"grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Computers or Crafting", "filter": [{"id": ["sklComputers", "sklCrafting"]}]}}}'),
('clfOperativeExpertise',	'Operative Expertise',	'Your techniques are now harder to resist. Your proficiency rank for your operative class DC increases to expert.',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Operative Class DC", "rank": "Expert"}]}'),
('clfHeavyGradeHydraulicFrame',	'Heavy-Grade Hydraulic Frame',	'You were built with a low center of gravity and high-torque servos. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to your Fortitude or Reflex DC against attempts to Shove or Trip you. Additionally, you ignore the Speed penalty caused by the Encumbered condition (you still take the maximum Dex, check, and Speed penalties for being Overburdened).',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Heavy-Grade Hydraulic Frame", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to DC against Shove or Trip.", "target": "all"}]}]}'),
('clfSpecializedSkillSet',	'Specialized Skill Set',	'At 1st level, 3rd level, 7th level, and 15th level, you gain a skill feat. This feat must be for the trained skill from your operative''s specialization.',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "choice(''target_feat'')", "type": "skill"}]}, "inputs": [{"name": "target_feat", "type": "feat", "label": "Specialist Feat", "filter": {"traits": ["flag:operative_spec_skill"]}}]}'),
('clfGreaterWeaponSpecialization',	'Greater Weapon Specialization',	'Your damage from weapon specialization increases to 4 with weapons and unarmed attacks in which you''re an expert, 6 if you''re a master, and 8 if you''re legendary.',	'{"attack": {"specialization_damage": {"Expert": 4, "Master": 6, "Legendary": 8}}}'),
('clfSimpleWeaponExpertise',	'Simple Weapon Expertise',	'You''ve learned a few tricks with your weapons. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons and unarmed attacks increase to expert.',	'{"attack": [{"unarmed": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"simple": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfSoldierWeaponMastery',	'Soldier Weapon Mastery',	'Through skill and dedication, you''ve mastered devastating weapons. Your proficiency rank for your soldier class DC increases to master. Your proficiency ranks for unarmed attacks, simple weapons, and martial weapons increase to master.',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Soldier Class DC", "rank": "Master"}], "attack": [{"simple": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"martial": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"unarmed": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfSoldierExpertise',	'Soldier Expertise',	'Your ability to unleash area attacks and utilize your equipment improves. Your proficiency rank for your soldier class DC increases to expert.',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Soldier Class DC", "rank": "Expert"}]}'),
('clfLegendarySoldier',	'Legendary Soldier',	'You''re a legendary hero (or outlaw) of the galaxy renowned for the rain of destruction you unleash on a battlefield. Your proficiency rank for your soldier class DC increases to legendary.',	'{"dc": [{"name": "Soldier Class DC", "rank": "Legendary"}]}'),
('clfArmorExpertise',	'Armor Expertise',	'You have grown accustomed to wearing armor and can make the most of its protection. Your proficiency ranks for light armor, medium armor, heavy armor, and unarmored defense increase to expert. You gain the armor specialization effects of medium and heavy armor.',	'{"defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"medium": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"heavy": {"rank": "Expert"}}]}'),
('clfArmorMastery',	'Armor Mastery',	'Your skill with armor further improves. Your proficiency ranks for light armor, medium armor, heavy armor, and unarmored defense increase to master.',	'{"defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"medium": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"heavy": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfLegendaryArmor',	'Legendary Armor',	'Your skill with armor is unparalleled. Your proficiency ranks for light armor, medium armor, heavy armor, and unarmored defense increase to legendary.',	'{"defense": [{"unarmored": {"rank": "Legendary"}}, {"light": {"rank": "Legendary"}}, {"medium": {"rank": "Legendary"}}, {"heavy": {"rank": "Legendary"}}]}'),
('clfSimpleWeaponMastery',	'Simple Weapon Mastery',	'You know your weapons like you know yourself. Your proficiency ranks for simple weapons and unarmed attacks increase to master.',	'{"attack": [{"unarmed": {"rank": "Master"}}, {"simple": {"rank": "Master"}}]}'),
('clfTechSpecialistInitialProficiencies',	'Tech Specialist Initial Proficiencies',	'<p>At 1st level, you gain the listed proficiency ranks in the following statistics. You are untrained in anything not listed unless you gain a better proficiency rank in some other way.</p>
