('idRepairToolkitT',	'Repair Toolkit (Tactical)',	3,	'250',	'1',	'Toolkit',	'A repair toolkit contains a variety of delicate tools and supplies that allows you to perform simple repairs while traveling. You can use a repair toolkit to Repair items using the Crafting skill. You can draw and replace a worn repair toolkit as part of the action that uses it. A tactical repair toolkit gives you a +1 item bonus to the check.',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Repair Toolkit", "value": "+1 item bonus to Repair.", "target": "sklCrafting"}]}}',	'1',	NULL,	NULL),
('idSlicersToolkitA',	'Slicer''s Toolkit (Advanced)',	5,	'700',	'1',	'Toolkit',	'A slicer''s toolkit is required for Computers checks to Hack computers. You can use a slicer''s toolkit to access a computer without using a user interface, but this requires physical contact with the computer or contact via a network. An advanced slicer''s toolkit adds a +1 item bonus and allows you to access computers at a range of 30 feet, unless you''re in a radioactive environment.',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Slicer''s Toolkit", "value": "+1 item bonus to Hack.", "target": "sklComputers"}]}}',	'1',	NULL,	NULL),
