('minMedicalDroid',	'Medical Droid',	'A multi-armed, hovering droid equipped with advanced diagnostic sensors, surgical tools, and a comforting, bedside-manner heuristic.

<strong>Support Benefit</strong> The GH-7 monitors your vitals and dispenses micro-stimulants. Until the start of your next turn, you and allies adjacent to the droid gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against poisons, diseases, and bleed effects.',	'Construct, Minion, Tech',	'Small',	NULL,	'{"Fly": 25}',	'{"Low-light Vision": null}',	'{"name": "Basic Medical Droid", "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSupport", "name": "Support", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The GH-7 monitors your vitals and dispenses micro-stimulants. Until the start of your next turn, you and allies adjacent to the droid gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against poisons, diseases, and bleed effects."}]}, "weapon": {"grant": [{"id": "wepScalpel", "bulk": null, "name": "Scalpel", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Agile, Finesse", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d4", "damagetype": "S"}]}, "template": [{"infiltrator": {"name": "Infiltrator-Spec Medical Droid", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}], "speed": [{"amount": 10, "target": "all"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBattlefieldTriage", "name": "Battlefield Triage", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The droid administers a fast-acting bacta spray. It attempts a Medicine check to Administer First Aid or Treat Wounds using your Medicine modifier. If it uses Treat Wounds in combat, it only restores 1d8 Hit Points but takes 1 action instead of 10 minutes.", "requirements": "The GH-7 is adjacent to a living ally."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 1, "con": 1, "dex": 5, "int": 3, "str": 0, "wis": 5}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"escort": {"name": "Escort-Spec Medical Droid", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBattlefieldTriage", "name": "Battlefield Triage", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The droid administers a fast-acting bacta spray. It attempts a Medicine check to Administer First Aid or Treat Wounds using your Medicine modifier. If it uses Treat Wounds in combat, it only restores 1d8 Hit Points but takes 1 action instead of 10 minutes.", "requirements": "The GH-7 is adjacent to a living ally."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "damage_bonus": 3, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 1, "con": 1, "dex": 5, "int": 3, "str": 0, "wis": 5}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"upgraded": {"name": "Upgraded Medical Droid", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}], "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 1, "con": 1, "dex": 3, "int": 3, "str": -1, "wis": 4}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}]}',	1,	6,	'{"cha": 1, "con": 0, "dex": 2, "int": 3, "str": -2, "wis": 3}',	'A multi-armed, hovering droid equipped with advanced diagnostic sensors and surgical tools.',	'sklMedicine'),
('minMassiff',	'Massiff',	'A rugged, armored canine native to desert worlds like Tatooine and Geonosis, favored by Tusken Raiders as guard animals.

<strong>Support Benefit</strong> The massiff snaps at your enemy''s heels, ruining their footwork. Until the start of your next turn, if you hit and damage a creature the massiff threatens, that creature takes a –10-foot status penalty to its Speeds for 1 round.',	'Animal, Minion',	'Small',	NULL,	'{"base": 30}',	'{"Scent": "Precise", "Darkvision": null}',	'{"weapon": {"grant": [{"id": "wepJaws", "bulk": null, "name": "Jaws", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Grapple", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d6", "damagetype": "P"}]}, "template": [{"nimble": {"name": "Nimble Massiff", "size": "Medium", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDragDown", "name": "Drag Down", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The massiff uses its locked jaws to pull the target to the ground. It automatically knocks the target prone.", "requirements": "The massiff''s last action was a successful jaws Strike."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 4, "dex": 5, "int": -4, "str": 4, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"savage": {"name": "Savage Massiff", "size": "Large", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDragDown", "name": "Drag Down", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The massiff uses its locked jaws to pull the target to the ground. It automatically knocks the target prone.", "requirements": "The massiff''s last action was a successful jaws Strike."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "damage_bonus": 3, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 4, "dex": 4, "int": -4, "str": 5, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"mature": {"name": "Mature Massiff", "size": "Medium", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}], "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 3, "dex": 3, "int": -4, "str": 3, "wis": 2}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}]}',	1,	8,	'{"cha": -1, "con": 2, "dex": 2, "int": -4, "str": 2, "wis": 1}',	'A rugged, armored canine native to desert worlds like Tatooine and Geonosis, favored by Tusken Raiders as guard animals.',	'sklSurvival'),
('minVaractyl',	'Varactyl',	'A large, avian-reptilian hybrid with strong gripping claws, capable of scaling sheer cliff faces at high speeds.

<strong>Support Benefit</strong> The varactyl weaves erratically, protecting its rider. Until the start of your next turn, if you are mounted on the varactyl, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against reactions triggered by your movement.',	'Animal, Minion',	'Medium',	'1',	'{"base": 40}',	'{"Low-light Vision": null}',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSupport", "name": "Support", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The varactyl weaves erratically, protecting its rider. Until the start of your next turn, if you are mounted on the varactyl, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against reactions triggered by your movement.<br><br>If the animal uses the Support action, the only other actions it can use on this turn are basic move actions to get into position to take advantage of the Support benefits; if it has already used any other action this turn, it can’t Support you."}]}, "weapon": {"grant": [{"id": "wepBeak", "bulk": null, "name": "Beak", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Finesse", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d6", "damagetype": "P"}, {"id": "wepTail", "bulk": null, "name": "Tail", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Reach 10 feet, Sweep", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d4", "damagetype": "B"}]}, "template": [{"nimble": {"name": "Nimble Varactyl", "size": "Large", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actWallRun", "name": "Wall Run", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The varactyl Strides. During this movement, it can run up vertical surfaces and across liquids without falling, though it must end its movement on a surface that can support it or it falls."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 0, "con": 4, "dex": 3, "int": -4, "str": 5, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"savage": {"name": "Savage Varactyl", "size": "Large", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actWallRun", "name": "Wall Run", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The varactyl Strides. During this movement, it can run up vertical surfaces and across liquids without falling, though it must end its movement on a surface that can support it or it falls."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "damage_bonus": 3, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 0, "con": 4, "dex": 3, "int": -4, "str": 5, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"mature": {"name": "Mature Varactyl", "size": "Large", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}], "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": 0, "con": 3, "dex": 2, "int": -4, "str": 3, "wis": 2}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}]}',	1,	8,	'{"cha": 0, "con": 2, "dex": 2, "int": -4, "str": 2, "wis": 1}',	'A large, avian-reptilian hybrid with strong gripping claws, capable of scaling sheer cliff faces at high speeds.',	'sklSurvival'),
('minAkkDog',	'Akk Dog',	'A heavily armored, reptilian canine from Haruun Kal, fiercely loyal and naturally resistant to both physical trauma and Force abilities.

<strong>Support Benefit</strong> The akk dog positions its heavily plated body between you and danger. Until the start of your next turn, you and any ally adjacent to the akk dog gain lesser cover against physical attacks.',	'Animal, Minion',	'Small',	NULL,	'{"base": 30}',	'{"Scent": "Imprecise", "Darkvision": null}',	'{"name": "Young Akk Dog", "weapon": {"grant": [{"id": "wepJaws", "bulk": null, "name": "Jaws", "type": "Melee", "group": "Brawling", "hands": "1", "traits": "Grapple", "category": "Unarmed", "damagedie": "d8", "damagetype": "P"}]}, "template": [{"nimble": {"name": "Nimble Akk Dog", "size": "Medium", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForcefulSlam", "name": "Forceful Slam", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "The Akk Dog throws its armored bulk into an enemy. It makes a Jaws Strike. If the attack hits, the target is pushed 5 feet away from the Akk Dog."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 5, "dex": 4, "int": -4, "str": 5, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"savage": {"name": "Savage Akk Dog", "size": "Large", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert"}, {"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actForcefulSlam", "name": "Forceful Slam", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "The Akk Dog throws its armored bulk into an enemy. It makes a Jaws Strike. If the attack hits, the target is pushed 5 feet away from the Akk Dog."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "damage_bonus": 3, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 5, "dex": 3, "int": -4, "str": 6, "wis": 3}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}, {"mature": {"name": "Mature Akk Dog", "size": "Medium", "skill": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklSurvival", "rank": "Trained"}, {"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Expert"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSupport", "name": "Support", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "The akk dog positions its heavily plated body between you and danger. Until the start of your next turn, you and any ally adjacent to the akk dog gain lesser cover against physical attacks.<br><br>If the animal uses the Support action, the only other actions it can use on this turn are basic move actions to get into position to take advantage of the Support benefits; if it has already used any other action this turn, it can’t Support you."}]}, "perception": {"rank": "Expert"}, "saving_throw": [{"fortitude": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"reflex": {"rank": "Expert"}}, {"will": {"rank": "Expert"}}], "attribute_set": {"cha": -1, "con": 4, "dex": 2, "int": -4, "str": 4, "wis": 2}, "damage_dice_count": 2}}]}',	1,	8,	'{"cha": -1, "con": 3, "dex": 1, "int": -4, "str": 3, "wis": 1}',	'A heavily armored, reptilian canine from Haruun Kal, fiercely loyal and highly durable.',	'sklIntimidation');

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Modification";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Modification" (
    "ModID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Level" smallint DEFAULT '1' NOT NULL,
    "Description" text,
    "Prerequisites" jsonb,
    "Traits" character varying,
    "Features" jsonb,
    "Price" smallint,
    CONSTRAINT "Modification_ModID" PRIMARY KEY ("ModID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

INSERT INTO "Modification" ("ModID", "Name", "Level", "Description", "Prerequisites", "Traits", "Features", "Price") VALUES
('modCorrosiveSolvent',	'Corrosive Solvent',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> You can secrete small, controlled amounts of solvent to silently melt weak mechanisms. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Thievery checks to Pick a Lock or Acrobatics checks to Escape, provided the lock or binding is susceptible to acid.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Area: 20-foot cone; Saving Throw: Reflex</em>. You spray a highly caustic chemical foam designed to rapidly melt through armor plating and bulkheads. Creatures in the area take <strong>2d6</strong> acid damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You highly pressurize the chemical mixture, causing it to aggressively cling to targets and eat through their defenses. The acid damage is rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d6s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save takes persistent acid damage equal to your Intelligence modifier and becomes clumsy 1 as long as they are taking the persistent damage.</p>',	NULL,	'Acid, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Corrosive Solvent", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Escape.", "target": "sklAcrobatics"}, {"name": "Corrosive Solvent", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Pick a Lock.", "target": "sklThievery"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCorrosiveSolvent", "name": "Corrosive Solvent", "traits": "Acid, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Area: 20-foot cone; Saving Throw: Reflex.</em> You spray a highly caustic chemical foam designed to rapidly melt through armor plating and bulkheads. Creatures in the area take 2d6 acid damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You highly pressurize the chemical mixture, causing it to aggressively cling to targets and eat through their defenses. The acid damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save takes persistent acid damage equal to your Intelligence modifier and becomes clumsy 1 as long as they are taking the persistent damage."}]}}',	360),
('modHoloProjector',	'Holo-Projector',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> Your rig constantly projects minor visual aids and dynamic camouflage patterns. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Deception checks to Create a Diversion or Impersonate.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet</em>. You deploy a stationary, medium or smaller hologram of an object or creature. The hologram is opaque but obviously composed of hard-light. A creature that uses a Seek action against the hologram''s space can attempt a Perception check against your class DC to disbelieve the illusion. The projection lasts for 1 minute. The maximum size of the hologram increases to Large at 4th level, Huge at 12th level, and Gargantuan at 19th level.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You overload the projector''s lumen-output, turning it into a blinding, hyper-realistic active decoy. Enemies within 10 feet of the hologram take a –1 circumstance penalty to ranged attack rolls and Perception checks as the erratic light and movement distract them.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Holo-Projector", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Create a Diversion or Impersonate.", "target": "sklDeception"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHoloProjector", "name": "Holo-Projector", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet.</em> You deploy a stationary, medium or smaller hologram of an object or creature. The hologram is opaque but obviously composed of hard-light. A creature that uses a Seek action against the hologram''s space can attempt a Perception check against your class DC to disbelieve the illusion. The projection lasts for 1 minute. The maximum size of the hologram increases to Large at 4th level, Huge at 12th level, and Gargantuan at 19th level.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You overload the projector''s lumen-output, turning it into a blinding, hyper-realistic active decoy. Enemies within 10 feet of the hologram take a –1 circumstance penalty to ranged attack rolls and Perception checks as the erratic light and movement distract them."}]}}',	20),
('modAeroBooster',	'Aero-Booster',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The thrusters passively detect rapid descent and fire automatically to arrest your fall. You treat all falls as if they were 20 feet shorter.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> You activate a compact jump-pack or repulsor boots. You fly up to your Speed. If you don''t end this movement on solid ground, you fall, but you take no falling damage and land on your feet.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You disable the fuel regulators for sustained propulsion. You gain a fly Speed equal to your land Speed for 5 minutes.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actAeroBooster", "name": "Aero-Booster", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You activate a compact jump-pack or repulsor boots. You fly up to your Speed. If you don''t end this movement on solid ground, you fall, but you take no falling damage and land on your feet.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You disable the fuel regulators for sustained propulsion. You gain a fly Speed equal to your land Speed for 5 minutes."}]}}',	360),
('modSensoryBaffle',	'Sensory Baffle',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig runs a background acoustic filter. You can perfectly hear and understand the whispered speech of any ally within 15 feet of you, even in environments with overwhelming ambient noise (like a nightclub, a factory floor, or a windstorm).</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Area: 15-foot emanation</em>. You generate a localized dampening field that suppresses ambient sound. You and allies within the emanation gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks. The field lasts for 1 minute or until you move.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> The frequency actively cancels out incoming and outgoing acoustic waves. The bonus to Stealth checks increases to +2, and creatures entirely within the emanation gain resistance to sonic damage equal to your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong>.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Auditory, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSensoryBaffle", "name": "Sensory Baffle", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Auditory, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Area: 15-foot emanation.</em> You generate a localized dampening field that suppresses ambient sound. You and allies within the emanation gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks. The field lasts for 1 minute or until you move.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> The frequency actively cancels out incoming and outgoing acoustic waves. The bonus to Stealth checks increases to +2, and creatures entirely within the emanation gain resistance to sonic damage equal to your Intelligence modifier."}]}}',	20),
('modQuantumDisplacementField',	'Quantum Displacement Field',	15,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> You project minor spatial distortions to manipulate your immediate surroundings. You can Interact with objects or open unlocked doors up to 15 feet away from you as if you were physically adjacent to them.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 60 feet (which increases to 120 feet at 19th level); Targets: You and up to 4 willing allies</em>. You manipulate a highly unstable gravity lens, bending space. You and the chosen allies instantly teleport to unoccupied spaces you can see within range.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You leave the spatial tears open, weaponizing the vacuum collapse. The empty spaces you and your allies vacated immediately implode. Any enemy adjacent to one of those starting spaces takes <strong>3d8</strong> bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional bludgeoning damage equal to your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong>, with a basic Fortitude save. If an enemy is adjacent to multiple vacated spaces, they only take the damage once.</p>',	NULL,	'Teleportation, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actQuantumDisplacementField", "name": "Quantum Displacement Field", "traits": "Teleportation, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 60 feet (which increases to 120 feet at 19th level); Targets: You and up to 4 willing allies.</em> You manipulate a highly unstable gravity lens, bending space. You and the chosen allies instantly teleport to unoccupied spaces you can see within range.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You leave the spatial tears open, weaponizing the vacuum collapse. The empty spaces you and your allies vacated immediately implode. Any enemy adjacent to one of those starting spaces takes 3d8 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional bludgeoning damage equal to your Intelligence modifier, with a basic Fortitude save. If an enemy is adjacent to multiple vacated spaces, they only take the damage once."}]}}',	6500),
('modNeuralOverride',	'Neural Override',	15,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> You operate with passive machine empathy. You can communicate basic concepts with any creature with the construct trait or technological vehicle as if you shared a common language, even if they lack a vocal synthesizer or visual interface.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 60 feet; Targets: 1 creature with the construct trait, a hazard with the tech trait, or a technological vehicle; Saving Throw: Will</em>. You broadcast a localized, overwhelming slice directly into the target''s motor cortex or central processor. The target must attempt a Will save.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The target is unaffected and temporarily immune for 24 hours.</li>
<li><strong>Success:</strong> The target is stunned 1 as it fights off the intrusive code.</li>
<li><strong>Failure:</strong> You take control of the target. It is controlled by you for 1 round. It can fight off the code, attempting a new Will save at the end of each of its turns to end the effect.</li>
<li><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> As failure, but the target is controlled for up to 1 minute.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You embed a malicious logic bomb that triggers when the connection is severed. If the target fails or critically fails its save, when the controlled condition ends, the target immediately takes <strong>3d8</strong> sonic damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional sonic damage equal to your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong>, as its internal components violently feedback.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Mental, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actNeuralOverride", "name": "Neural Override", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Mental, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 60 feet; Targets: 1 creature with the construct trait, a hazard with the tech trait, or a technological vehicle; Saving Throw: Will.</em> You broadcast a localized, overwhelming slice directly into the target''s motor cortex or central processor. The target must attempt a Will save.<br><ul><li><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The target is unaffected and temporarily immune for 24 hours.</li><li><strong>Success:</strong> The target is stunned 1 as it fights off the intrusive code.</li><li><strong>Failure:</strong> You take control of the target. It is controlled by you for 1 round. It can fight off the code, attempting a new Will save at the end of each of its turns to end the effect.</li><li><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> As failure, but the target is controlled for up to 1 minute.</li></ul><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You embed a malicious logic bomb that triggers when the connection is severed. If the target fails or critically fails its save, when the controlled condition ends, the target immediately takes 3d8 sonic damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional sonic damage equal to your Intelligence modifier, as its internal components violently feedback."}]}}',	6500),
('modNaniteReconstructionSwarm',	'Nanite Reconstruction Swarm',	15,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The nanites passively patrol your bloodstream, aggressively purging impurities. You gain immunity to mundane diseases and a +4 circumstance bonus to saving throws against poisons.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Area: 30-foot emanation</em>. You release a cloud of programmable medical micro-droids. You and all willing allies within the area regain <strong>3d6</strong> Hit Points (which increases by 1d6 at 19th level), and you can attempt to counteract one poison or disease effect on each target using your Tech Specialist class DC. A creature cannot benefit from your Nanite Reconstruction Swarm again for 10 minutes.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You override the nanites'' safety protocols, forcing them to aggressively knit tissue and fuse bone. The healing is rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d6s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total Hit Points regained. Any ally healed by the swarm also gains Fast Healing 10 for 1 minute (which increases to Fast Healing 15 at 19th level).</p>',	NULL,	'Healing, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actNaniteReconstructionSwarm", "name": "Nanite Reconstruction Swarm", "traits": "Healing, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Area: 30-foot emanation.</em> You release a cloud of programmable medical micro-droids. You and all willing allies within the area regain 3d6 Hit Points (which increases by 1d6 at 19th level), and you can attempt to counteract one poison or disease effect on each target using your Tech Specialist class DC. A creature cannot benefit from your Nanite Reconstruction Swarm again for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You override the nanites'' safety protocols, forcing them to aggressively knit tissue and fuse bone. The healing is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total Hit Points regained. Any ally healed by the swarm also gains Fast Healing 10 for 1 minute (which increases to Fast Healing 15 at 19th level)."}]}, "defense": {"immunity": [{"type": "Disease (Mundane)", "source": "Nanite Reconstruction Swarm (Active Modification)"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Nanite Reconstruction Swarm", "value": "+4 circumstance bonus against poisons.", "target": "all"}]}]}',	6500),
('modDeflectorScreen',	'Deflector Screen',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The emitter projects a low-power kinetic umbrella. You are completely protected from non-damaging environmental precipitation (like rain or snow), and you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against severe environmental weather hazards.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [one-action]</strong> You activate a momentary magnetic or energy shield from your Custom Rig. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC until the start of your next turn.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You overdrive the emitter. The circumstance bonus to AC increases to +2. If an enemy hits you with a melee unarmed attack or a melee weapon without the reach trait while the screen is active, they take 2d4 electricity damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level), plus additional electricity damage equal to your Intelligence modifier, as the shield arcs back at them.</p>
',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDeflectorScreen", "name": "Deflector Screen", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You activate a momentary magnetic or energy shield from your Custom Rig. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC until the start of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You overdrive the emitter. The circumstance bonus to AC increases to +2. If an enemy hits you with a melee unarmed attack or a melee weapon without the reach trait while the screen is active, they take 2d4 electricity damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level), plus additional electricity damage equal to your Intelligence modifier, as the shield arcs back at them."}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Deflector Screen", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against severe environmental weather hazards.", "target": "all"}]}]}',	20),
('modMagneticGrapple',	'Magnetic Grapple',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> Your rig magnetizes your grip and extremities. You gain a climb Speed of 10 feet, but only when climbing metallic surfaces or structures.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [one-action]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 unattended object of 1 Bulk or less, or a sturdy structure</em>. You fire a magnetized tether. If you target an unattended object, you immediately pull it into your free hand. If you target a sturdy environmental structure (like a ceiling beam or balcony edge), you immediately pull yourself in a straight line to an empty space adjacent to the structure. This movement does not trigger reactions.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You increase the tether''s kinetic winch capacity. You can target a creature within range. Attempt an Athletics check against the target''s Fortitude DC (using your Intelligence modifier instead of Strength). On a success, you can either pull the target 10 feet toward you, or pull yourself 10 feet toward the target. On a critical success, you can pull the target 20 feet, or pull yourself to an empty space adjacent to the target.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"speed": [{"amount": 10, "target": "Climb (metallic)"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actMagneticGrapple", "name": "Magnetic Grapple", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 unattended object of 1 Bulk or less, or a sturdy structure.</em> You fire a magnetized tether. If you target an unattended object, you immediately pull it into your free hand. If you target a sturdy environmental structure (like a ceiling beam or balcony edge), you immediately pull yourself in a straight line to an empty space adjacent to the structure. This movement does not trigger reactions.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You increase the tether''s kinetic winch capacity. You can target a creature within range. Attempt an Athletics check against the target''s Fortitude DC (using your Intelligence modifier instead of Strength). On a success, you can either pull the target 10 feet toward you, or pull yourself 10 feet toward the target. On a critical success, you can pull the target 20 feet, or pull yourself to an empty space adjacent to the target."}]}}',	20),
('modStimInjector',	'Stim-Injector',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig constantly monitors your vitals and flushes fatigue toxins. You need half the normal amount of sleep to be fully rested, and you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to saving throws against effects that would make you fatigued.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [one-action]</strong> <em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature</em>. You administer a rapid-injection cocktail of synthetic adrenaline and pain-dampeners. The target gains <strong>1d4</strong> temporary Hit Points (which increase by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) that last for 1 minute. While the target has these temporary Hit Points, they gain a +5-foot status bonus to their Speeds. A creature cannot benefit from your Stim-Injector again for 10 minutes.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You inject a highly volatile, hyper-oxygenated stimulant. The temporary Hit Points are rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d4s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total temporary Hit Points granted. The status bonus to Speeds increases to +10 feet, and the target can immediately Step as a free action when you apply the stim.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actStimInjector", "name": "Stim-Injector", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "<em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature.</em> You administer a rapid-injection cocktail of synthetic adrenaline and pain-dampeners. The target gains 1d4 temporary Hit Points (which increase by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) that last for 1 minute. While the target has these temporary Hit Points, they gain a +5-foot status bonus to their Speeds. A creature cannot benefit from your Stim-Injector again for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You inject a highly volatile, hyper-oxygenated stimulant. The temporary Hit Points are rolled with d8s instead of d4s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total temporary Hit Points granted. The status bonus to Speeds increases to +10 feet, and the target can immediately Step as a free action when you apply the stim."}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Stim-Injector", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus against fatigue.", "target": "all"}]}]}',	20),
('modKoltoBurst',	'Kolto Burst',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig continuously monitors nearby biometric data and regulates your stabilizing injections. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Medicine checks to Administer First Aid. Additionally, if you critically fail a check to Administer First Aid, the target does not take damage or increase their dying value, as the rig''s fail-safes instantly halt the injection.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature</em>. You inject a concentrated dose of kolto and synthetic coagulants. The target regains <strong>1d8</strong> Hit Points (which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). A creature cannot benefit from your Kolto Burst again for 10 minutes.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the injector''s safe-dosage limiters. The healing is rolled with <strong>d12s instead of d8s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total Hit Points regained. You also automatically end one source of persistent bleed damage affecting the target.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Kolto Burst", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Administer First Aid. ", "target": "sklMedicine"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actKoltoBurst", "name": "Kolto Burst", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature.</em> You inject a concentrated dose of kolto and synthetic coagulants. The target regains 1d8 Hit Points (which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). A creature cannot benefit from your Kolto Burst again for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the injector''s safe-dosage limiters. The healing is rolled with d12s instead of d8s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total Hit Points regained. You also automatically end one source of persistent bleed damage affecting the target."}]}}',	20),
('modDefibrillationMatrix',	'Defibrillation Matrix',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> Your rig runs advanced biometric tracking. You automatically know the exact Hit Point value and any active conditions of willing allies within 30 feet of you. You also gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Medicine checks to Treat Disease or Treat Poison.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature</em>. You deliver a massive, stabilizing bio-electric shock. The target regains <strong>2d8</strong> Hit Points (which increases by 1d8 at 12th and 19th level). If the target has the dying condition, their dying value is reduced by 1. A creature cannot benefit from your Defibrillation Matrix again for 10 minutes.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You push the generator to maximum voltage, attempting to jump-start a failing heart. The healing is rolled with <strong>d12s instead of d8s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total Hit Points regained. If the target died within the last round, they are returned to life with the Hit Points granted by this Modification, and their wounded condition increases by 1.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Defibrillation Matrix", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Treat Disease or Treat Poison.", "target": "sklMedicine"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDefibrillationMatrix", "name": "Defibrillation Matrix", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Healing, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 willing living creature.</em> You deliver a massive, stabilizing bio-electric shock. The target regains 2d8 Hit Points (which increases by 1d8 at 12th and 19th level). If the target has the dying condition, their dying value is reduced by 1. A creature cannot benefit from your Defibrillation Matrix again for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You push the generator to maximum voltage, attempting to jump-start a failing heart. The healing is rolled with d12s instead of d8s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total Hit Points regained. If the target died within the last round, they are returned to life with the Hit Points granted by this Modification, and their wounded condition increases by 1."}]}}',	360),
('modPlasmaIncinerator',	'Plasma Incinerator',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig safely vents excess thermal energy. You are permanently protected from the effects of severe environmental cold, and you can instantly ignite exposed combustible materials (like paper or dry wood) with a touch using an Interact action.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Area: 30-foot line; Saving Throw: Reflex</em>. You unleash a highly pressurized stream of ignited plasma. Creatures in the area take <strong>2d6</strong> fire damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You widen the aperture and flood the ignition chamber. The area becomes a 60-foot line, the fire damage is rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d6s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save also takes persistent fire damage equal to your Intelligence modifier.</p>',	NULL,	'Fire, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actPlasmaIncinerator", "name": "Plasma Incinerator", "traits": "Fire, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Area: 30-foot line; Saving Throw: Reflex.</em> You unleash a highly pressurized stream of ignited plasma. Creatures in the area take 2d6 fire damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You widen the aperture and flood the ignition chamber. The area becomes a 60-foot line, the fire damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save also takes persistent fire damage equal to your Intelligence modifier."}]}}',	360),
('modOverloadLogic',	'Overload Logic',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig continuously broadcasts background handshake protocols and localized spoofing telemetry. You can attempt Computers checks to Hack a System or Thievery checks to Disable a Device on technological targets wirelessly from up to 15 feet away, provided you have a clear line of sight to the access panel or mechanism.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 creature or a hazard with the tech trait; Saving Throw: Reflex</em>. You broadcast a localized, aggressive frequency spike. The target takes 2d6 electricity damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You compile a malicious code-bomb that physically overheats the target''s gear or cybernetics. The damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. If the target fails their Reflex save, they become clumsy 1 until the start of your next turn. If they critically fail, they become clumsy 2.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Electricity, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOverloadLogic", "name": "Overload Logic", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Electricity, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 creature or a hazard with the tech trait; Saving Throw: Reflex.</em> You broadcast a localized, aggressive frequency spike. The target takes 1d6 electricity damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You compile a malicious code-bomb that physically overheats the target''s gear or cybernetics. The damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. If the target fails their Reflex save, they become clumsy 1 until the start of your next turn. If they critically fail, they become clumsy 2."}]}}',	20),
('modSonicResonator',	'Sonic Resonator',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The emitter constantly bounces sub-audible telemetry off your surroundings. You gain imprecise echolocation out to 30 feet, allowing you to detect unseen creatures or objects.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 creature or object; Saving Throw: Fortitude</em>. You direct a concentrated beam of high-frequency sound to rupture organs or shatter materials. The target takes <strong>2d8</strong> sonic damage (which increases by 1d8 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save is deafened for 1 minute.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You induce a catastrophic sympathetic vibration. The sonic damage is rolled with <strong>d10s instead of d8s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is deafened for 1 minute and stunned 1. A creature that critically fails is deafened for 1 minute and stunned 2.</p>',	NULL,	'Sonic, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"sense": [{"Echolocation (30ft)": "Imprecise"}], "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSonicResonator", "name": "Sonic Resonator", "traits": "Sonic, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 creature or object; Saving Throw: Fortitude.</em> You direct a concentrated beam of high-frequency sound to rupture organs or shatter materials. The target takes 2d8 sonic damage (which increases by 1d8 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save is deafened for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You induce a catastrophic sympathetic vibration. The sonic damage is rolled with d10s instead of d8s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is deafened for 1 minute and stunned 1. A creature that critically fails is deafened for 1 minute and stunned 2."}]}}',	360),
('modFusionTorch',	'Fusion Torch',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The emitter maintains a tightly focused pilot light that passively analyzes structural integrity. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Athletics checks to Force Open metallic doors, gratings, or containers, as you rapidly superheat and weaken the hinges or locking mechanisms before applying force.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [one-action]</strong> <em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 creature or object</em>. You ignite a short, intensely hot plasma blade from your rig to cut through bulkheads or armor. Make a melee Strike against the target''s AC. This counts as a simple weapon with the finesse trait. On a success, you deal 1d4 fire damage and 1d4 slashing damage. Each damage type increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level. This attack ignores the first 2 points of an object''s Hardness.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You hyper-focus the plasma stream. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to the attack roll, the damage is rolled with d6s instead of d4s, and you add half of your Intelligence modifier to the each damage type. On a hit, the attack ignores the first 5 points of an object''s Hardness.</p>',	NULL,	'Fire, Slashing, Tech Specialist, Attack, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Fusion Torch", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Force Open metallic objects.", "target": "sklAthletics"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFusionTorch", "name": "Fusion Torch", "traits": "Fire, Slashing, Tech Specialist, Attack, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "<em>Range: Touch; Targets: 1 creature or object.</em> You ignite a short, intensely hot plasma blade from your rig to cut through bulkheads or armor. Make a melee Strike against the target''s AC. This counts as a simple weapon with the finesse trait. On a success, you deal 1d8 damage (half fire, half slashing, which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). This attack ignores the first 2 points of an object''s Hardness.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You hyper-focus the plasma stream. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to the attack roll, the damage is rolled with d10s instead of d8s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. On a hit, the attack ignores the first 5 points of an object''s Hardness."}]}}',	20),
('modRepulsorEmitter',	'Repulsor Emitter',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig passively lightens your physical load using micro-repulsors. Your maximum Bulk limit and your encumbered Bulk limit both increase by 2.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Saving Throw: Fortitude</em>. You trigger a localized anti-gravity blast from your rig in a 15-foot cone. Creatures in the area take 2d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save is also pushed 5 feet away from you.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the directional limiters, venting the blast indiscriminately in a 10-foot emanation around you, and this action loses the Manipulate trait. The bludgeoning damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is pushed 5 feet away from you, and a creature that critically fails is pushed 10 feet and knocked prone.</p>',	NULL,	'Bludgeoning, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_bonus": 2, "overburdened_bonus": 2}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRepulsorEmitter", "name": "Repulsor Emitter", "traits": "Bludgeoning, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Saving Throw: Fortitude.</em> You trigger a localized anti-gravity blast from your rig in a 15-foot cone. Creatures in the area take 2d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save is also pushed 5 feet away from you.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the directional limiters, venting the blast indiscriminately in a 10-foot emanation around you, and this action loses the Manipulate trait. The bludgeoning damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is pushed 5 feet away from you, and a creature that critically fails is pushed 10 feet and knocked prone."}]}}',	20),
('modGraviticSnare',	'Gravitic Snare',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> You project a micro-gravity field around your boots. You ignore difficult terrain caused by rubble, uneven ground, or shifting surfaces (like deep snow or sand).</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 60 feet; Area: 10-foot burst; Saving Throw: Reflex</em>. You launch a module that creates a crushing localized gravity well. Creatures in the area take <strong>2d6</strong> bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. The area becomes difficult terrain for 1 minute.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You magnify the singularity''s pull. The bludgeoning damage is rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d6s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is immobilized for 1 round, and a creature that critically fails is restrained for 1 round or until they Escape against your Tech Specialist class DC.</p>',	NULL,	'Bludgeoning, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actGraviticSnare", "name": "Gravitic Snare", "traits": "Bludgeoning, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 60 feet; Area: 10-foot burst; Saving Throw: Reflex.</em> You launch a module that creates a crushing localized gravity well. Creatures in the area take 2d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. The area becomes difficult terrain for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You magnify the singularity''s pull. The bludgeoning damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. A creature that fails its save is immobilized for 1 round, and a creature that critically fails is restrained for 1 round or until they Escape against your Tech Specialist class DC."}]}}',	360),
('modOpticalCloak',	'Optical Cloak',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The cloak passively bends ambient light to obscure your exact outline. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Stealth checks to Hide or Sneak in areas of dim light or darkness.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> You bend light and thermal emissions around your body, becoming undetected to visual sensors and sight. This lasts for 5 minutes. If you use a hostile action, the cloak immediately shatters and the effect ends.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You push the projector to maintain the illusion through kinetic disruption. The duration is reduced to 1 minute, but the cloak does not end if you use a hostile action. You remain undetected (though enemies can still use the Seek action to locate your square, making you hidden instead).</p>',	NULL,	'Illusion, Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Optical Cloak", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus to Hide or Sneak in areas of dim light or darkness.", "target": "sklStealth"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actOpticalCloak", "name": "Optical Cloak", "traits": "Illusion, Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You bend light and thermal emissions around your body, becoming undetected to visual sensors and sight. This lasts for 5 minutes. If you use a hostile action, the cloak immediately shatters and the effect ends.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You push the projector to maintain the illusion through kinetic disruption. The duration is reduced to 1 minute, but the cloak does not end if you use a hostile action. You remain undetected (though enemies can still use the Seek action to locate your square, making you hidden instead)."}]}}',	360),
('modHardLightBastion',	'Hard-Light Bastion',	15,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig projects a persistent micro-barrier while you rest. When you use the Subsist action or Make Camp, you and your allies are completely protected from the elements, as if resting in a secure, climate-controlled shelter.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [three-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 60 feet</em>. You deploy a massive, complex schematic that instantly projects a 20-foot-by-20-foot enclosed bunker made of solid, opaque hard-light. The bunker provides standard cover to those inside firing out, and greater cover against attacks originating from the outside. The walls have Hardness 20 and 80 Hit Points (which increase to Hardness 25 and 100 Hit Points at 19th level). The bunker lasts for 1 minute or until you Dismiss it.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You weaponize the exterior projector grid. The bunker''s baseline Hardness increases to 30. Any enemy that ends its turn adjacent to the exterior of the bastion takes <strong>3d8</strong> electricity damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional electricity damage equal to your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong>, with a basic Reflex save.</p>',	NULL,	'Light, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actHardLightBastion", "name": "Hard-Light Bastion", "traits": "Light, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[three-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 60 feet.</em> You deploy a massive, complex schematic that instantly projects a 20-foot-by-20-foot enclosed bunker made of solid, opaque hard-light. The bunker provides standard cover to those inside firing out, and greater cover against attacks originating from the outside. The walls have Hardness 20 and 80 Hit Points (which increase to Hardness 25 and 100 Hit Points at 19th level). The bunker lasts for 1 minute or until you Dismiss it.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You weaponize the exterior projector grid. The bunker''s baseline Hardness increases to 30. Any enemy that ends its turn adjacent to the exterior of the bastion takes 3d8 electricity damage (which increases by 1d8 at 19th level) plus additional electricity damage equal to your Intelligence modifier, with a basic Reflex save."}]}}',	6500),
('modFlashBangMatrix',	'Flash-Bang Matrix',	7,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig deploys localized ocular and auditory dampeners. You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to saving throws against visual and auditory effects.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 60 feet; Area: 20-foot burst; Saving Throw: Fortitude</em>. You launch a non-lethal sensory overload charge that detonates with blinding light and deafening sound. Creatures in the area must attempt a Fortitude save.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The creature is unaffected.</li>
<li><strong>Success:</strong> The creature is dazzled until the start of its next turn.</li>
<li><strong>Failure:</strong> The creature is blinded and deafened until the start of its next turn.</li>
<li><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The creature is blinded and deafened for 1 minute.</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You pack the matrix with experimental hyper-resonators, creating a physical shock to the nervous system. Creatures that fail their save are also stunned 1, and creatures that critically fail are stunned 2.</p>',	NULL,	'Auditory, Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFlashBangMatrix", "name": "Flash-Bang Matrix", "traits": "Auditory, Tech Specialist, Visual, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 60 feet; Area: 20-foot burst; Saving Throw: Fortitude.</em> You launch a non-lethal sensory overload charge that detonates with blinding light and deafening sound. Creatures in the area must attempt a Fortitude save.<br><ul><li><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The creature is unaffected.</li><li><strong>Success:</strong> The creature is dazzled until the start of its next turn.</li><li><strong>Failure:</strong> The creature is blinded and deafened until the start of its next turn.</li><li><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The creature is blinded and deafened for 1 minute.</li></ul><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You pack the matrix with experimental hyper-resonators, creating a physical shock to the nervous system. Creatures that fail their save are also stunned 1, and creatures that critically fail are stunned 2."}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Flash-Bang Matrix", "value": "+2 circumstance bonus against visual and auditory effects.", "target": "all"}]}]}',	360),
('modEndothermicVent',	'Endothermic Vent',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> The rig''s coolant lines constantly cycle ambient air around your body. You are permanently protected from the effects of severe environmental heat.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Saving Throw: Fortitude</em>. You vent a rapid blast of super-chilled coolant gas from your rig in a 15-foot cone. Creatures in the area take 2d6 cold damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save also takes a –5-foot status penalty to its Speeds until the end of its next turn.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You disable the thermal regulators entirely. The cold damage is rolled with <strong>d8s instead of d6s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. A creature that fails its save takes the –5-foot status penalty to its Speeds, and a creature that critically fails is instead immobilized until the end of its next turn or until it uses an Interact action to break the ice.</p>',	NULL,	'Cold, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actEndothermicVent", "name": "Endothermic Vent", "traits": "Cold, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "You vent a rapid blast of super-chilled coolant gas from your rig in a 15-foot cone. Creatures in the area take 2d6 cold damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails its save also takes a –5-foot status penalty to its Speeds until the end of its next turn.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You disable the thermal regulators entirely. The cold damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. A creature that fails its save takes the –5-foot status penalty to its Speeds, and a creature that critically fails is instead immobilized until the end of its next turn or until it uses an Interact action to break the ice."}]}}',	20),
('modTelemetryUplink',	'Telemetry Uplink',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> Your rig establishes a flawless, localized tactical network. You can communicate silently and instantly with your droid companion or any willing ally wearing a commlink within 100 feet. Additionally, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Crafting checks to Repair creatures with the construct trait.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [one-action]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 willing ally</em>. You broadcast a tightly beamed packet of predictive combat algorithms. The target''s next Strike before the end of their next turn deals an additional <strong>1d4</strong> precision damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) as their targeting is perfectly synchronized with enemy vulnerabilities.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the receiver''s bandwidth limiters, forcing a hyper-efficient autonomic combat routine. The precision damage is rolled with <strong>d6s instead of d4s</strong>, and you add your <strong>Intelligence modifier</strong> to the total damage. The target can also immediately Step as a free action when they receive the uplink.</p>',	NULL,	'Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Telemetry Uplink", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Repair construct creatures.", "target": "sklCrafting"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actTelemetryUplink", "name": "Telemetry Uplink", "traits": "Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet; Targets: 1 willing ally.</em> You broadcast a tightly beamed packet of predictive combat algorithms. The target''s next Strike before the end of their next turn deals an additional 1d4 precision damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) as their targeting is perfectly synchronized with enemy vulnerabilities.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You bypass the receiver''s bandwidth limiters, forcing a hyper-efficient autonomic combat routine. The precision damage is rolled with d6s instead of d4s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. The target can also immediately Step as a free action when they receive the uplink."}]}}',	NULL),
('modFragmentationCharge',	'Fragmentation Charge',	1,	'<p><strong>Standby</strong> Your rig constantly scans for structural weaknesses and blast vectors. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to Engineering or Crafting checks to Disable a Device or demolish structures.</p>
<p><strong>Activate [two-actions]</strong> <em>Range: 30 feet; Area: 5-foot burst. You construct and lob a volatile explosive that detonates on impact. Creatures in the area take 2d6 piercing damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.</p>
<p><strong>Overclock</strong> You pack the explosive with secondary micro-shrapnel. The burst radius increases to 10 feet, the piercing damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save also takes persistent bleed damage equal to your Intelligence modifier.</p>',	NULL,	'Piercing, Tech Specialist, Manipulate',	'{"skill": {"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Fragmentation Charge", "value": "+1 circumstance bonus to Disable a Device or demolish structures.", "target": "sklThievery"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFragmentationCharge", "name": "Fragmentation Charge", "traits": "Piercing, Tech Specialist, Manipulate", "action_cost": "[two-actions]", "description": "<em>Range: 30 feet; Area: 5-foot burst.</em> You construct and lob a volatile explosive that detonates on impact. Creatures in the area take 2d6 piercing damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save.<br><br><strong>Overclock</strong> You pack the explosive with secondary micro-shrapnel. The burst radius increases to 10 feet, the piercing damage is rolled with d8s instead of d6s, and you add your Intelligence modifier to the total damage. Any creature that fails its Reflex save also takes persistent bleed damage equal to your Intelligence modifier."}]}}',	20);

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Power";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Power" (
    "PowerID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Level" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "Description" text,
    "ActionCost" character varying,
    "Prerequisites" jsonb,
    "Traits" character varying,
    "Range" character varying,
    "Target" character varying,
    "Duration" character varying,
    "Trigger" character varying,
    "Frequency" character varying,
    "Requirements" character varying,
    CONSTRAINT "Power_PowerID" PRIMARY KEY ("PowerID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

INSERT INTO "Power" ("PowerID", "Name", "Level", "Description", "ActionCost", "Prerequisites", "Traits", "Range", "Target", "Duration", "Trigger", "Frequency", "Requirements") VALUES
('powPrecognitiveParry',	'Precognitive Parry',	1,	'You foresaw the blow a split second before it landed. You gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against the triggering attack. If this bonus causes the attack to miss, you successfully parried it. The bonus increases to +2 at 12th level.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If the attack misses, you can immediately Step as part of the reaction.',	'[reaction]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'You are hit by an attack from an enemy you can see.',	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceBarrier',	'Force Barrier',	1,	'You dampen kinetic energy and disperse heat with a field of compressed energy. You gain resistance to physical and energy damage equal to 2 plus half your level.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can Sustain this power for up to 1 minute. While Sustained, the resistance applies to all damage types except mental and poison.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Concentrate',	NULL,	NULL,	'until the start of your next turn',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceSurge',	'Force Surge',	1,	'You channel energy into your muscles to perform impossible feats of athleticism. You Stride. During this movement, you ignore difficult terrain and increase your Speed by 10 feet. At 4th level, you gain a climb Speed equal to your Speed during this movement. At 12th level, you can move along vertical surfaces and across liquids without falling.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You do not trigger reactions with movement during this Stride.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Move',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powBreathControl',	'Breath Control',	1,	'You slow your metabolic rate and oxygen consumption. You gain a +2 status bonus to Fortitude saves against inhaled toxins, gases, and suffocation. You can hold your breath for the duration without risk of drowning or suffocating. At 12th level, you become completely immune to inhaled toxins and gases.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The duration increases to 1 hour.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control, Concentrate',	NULL,	NULL,	'10 minutes',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powTelekineticGrasp',	'Telekinetic Grasp',	1,	'You lift and manipulate an object with your mind. You can move the object up to 20 feet through the air. You can bring it to your hand, move it to another location, or perform a simple interaction (like pulling a lever or opening an unlocked door). You can target an unattended object of 1 Bulk or less (which increases to 3 Bulk at 4th level, 6 Bulk at 12th level, and 9 Bulk at 19th level).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The range increases to 60 feet, and you can Sustain the action to maintain your hold on the object.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Concentrate, Manipulate',	'30 feet',	'1 unattended object of Bulk 1 or less',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powBattleFocus',	'Battle Focus',	1,	'You center your mind, purging doubt and fear. You immediately attempt a new Will save against one fear effect currently affecting you. If you succeed, the effect ends. At 12th level, you can attempt to purge the confused or controlled conditions.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If you succeed on the save, you gain temporary Hit Points equal to your Wisdom modifier.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control, Concentrate, Mental',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceFear',	'Force Fear',	1,	'You project a nightmarish vision into the target''s mind. The target makes a Will save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target is frightened 1.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target is frightened 2.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target is frightened 3 and fleeing for 1 round.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If the target is already frightened, they take 1d4 mental damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level).',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Emotion, Fear, Mental',	NULL,	'1 living creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForcePush',	'Force Push',	1,	'You slam the target with a blast of compressed energy. The target makes a Fortitude save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target is pushed 5 feet.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target is pushed 10 feet and takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level).<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target is pushed 20 feet, takes double damage, and falls prone.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You change the area from a single target to a 15-foot cone, forcing all creatures in the area to save.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Alter',	'30 feet',	'1 creature or object',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powSenseLife',	'Sense Life',	1,	'You expand your awareness to detect the presence of living beings. You sense the presence of any living creature within range, even if they are hidden or undetected. This counts as an imprecise sense. The range increases to 60 feet at 12th level.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can Sustain the effect for up to 1 minute. While Sustained, you cannot be flanked.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense, Detection',	'30-foot emanation',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceHold',	'Force Hold',	5,	'You encase a target in a field of solid energy, freezing them in place. The target makes a Fortitude save. The maximum size of the creature you can target increases to Large at 12th level and Huge at 19th level.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target is slowed 1 for 1 round.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target is restrained for 1 round.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target is paralyzed for 1 round.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can Sustain the effect on a failure or critical failure. If you do, the target can attempt a new save at the end of their turn to end the effect, but the DC increases by 1 for each round you have Sustained it.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Incapacitation',	'30 feet',	'1 creature of Medium size or smaller',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceShock',	'Force Shock',	1,	'You fire a quick arc of lightning from your fingertips. Make a ranged Strike using The Force. On a hit, you deal 1d8 electricity damage (which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). If the target is wearing metal armor or has the construct trait, they take a –1 circumstance penalty to AC against this attack.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If you critically hit, the lightning arcs to a second creature within 10 feet of the target, dealing half damage to them (no attack roll required).',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Electricity',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powKineticSlam',	'Kinetic Slam',	5,	'You lift a target into the air and violently slam them into the ground. The target makes a Reflex save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Target takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) and lands prone.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes double damage, falls prone, and is stunned 1.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> Target takes double damage, falls prone, and is stunned 2.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can target two creatures if they are within 10 feet of each other.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Offense',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceCelerity',	'Force Celerity',	5,	'You accelerate your perception and muscle response. You gain the quickened condition. You can use the extra action only to Stride or Step. When this effect ends, you become fatigued for 10 minutes.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> While Connected, you can also use the extra action to Strike or Take Cover.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body',	NULL,	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceValor',	'Force Valor',	5,	'You project a wave of courage and vitality. You and all allies in the area gain 10 temporary Hit Points (which increases to 15 at 12th level and 20 at 19th level) and a +1 status bonus to Will saves against fear effects.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If an ally in the area is currently frightened, their frightened value is reduced by 1 immediately.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Emotion',	'30-foot emanation',	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powEnergyAbsorption',	'Energy Absorption (Tutaminis)',	5,	'You raise a hand to catch and dissipate energy. You gain resistance 10 against the triggering damage type for this instance of damage (which increases to resistance 15 at 12th level and 20 at 19th level).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If you reduce the damage to 0, you regain Hit Points equal to half the damage prevented (up to a maximum of your level).',	'[reaction]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'You are targeted by an attack dealing Energy damage (including Fire, Cold, or Electricity) or fall into an environmental hazard dealing such damage.',	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceCloak',	'Force Cloak',	5,	'You bend light and sound waves around your form to vanish from sight. You become invisible. If you use a hostile action, the invisibility ends immediately.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The first hostile action you take does not end the invisibility (though the invisibility ends at the end of that turn).',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control, Illusion',	NULL,	NULL,	'1 minute (Sustained)',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceDisruption',	'Force Disruption',	5,	'You disrupt the target’s focus, cutting them off from their support or abilities. The target makes a Will save.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> If the target is a Force User, they lose their Connected state (or similar stance). If they are not a Force User, they cannot use actions with the concentrate trait for 1 round.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> On a failure, the target is also off-guard until the start of your next turn.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceLightning',	'Force Lightning',	5,	'You unleash a storm of violet lightning from your fingertips. All creatures in the cone take 2d6 electricity damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. Creatures that critically fail are also slowed 1 for 1 round as their muscles spasm.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The area increases to a 40-foot cone.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Electricity',	'30-foot cone',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powIonize',	'Ionize',	5,	'You overload the circuits of a technological target. Make a tech attack roll.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Deal 2d6 ion damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level). If the target is a construct or wearing powered armor, they are stunned 1.<br><strong>Critical Success:</strong> Deal double damage. If the target is a construct, they are stunned 2 and take 1d6 persistent ion damage.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> On a success, the surge arcs to one adjacent enemy, dealing half damage.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense',	'60 feet',	'1 creature or object',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powGuidanceOfTheForce',	'Guidance of the Force',	5,	'You surrender your conscious control, letting it guide your hand for a perfect strike. Roll a d20. On your next Strike this turn, you use this result instead of rolling. You cannot use this ability if you have already rolled an attack this turn and cannot use it again for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If the d20 result is an 18, 19, or 20, the Strike improves its degree of success by one step.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense, Fortune',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powTelekineticFlight',	'Telekinetic Flight',	9,	'You lift yourself and move freely through the air. You gain a fly Speed equal to your Speed. The duration increases to 1 hour at 12th level.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> Your fly Speed increases by 10 feet.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter',	NULL,	NULL,	'5 minutes',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceWave',	'Force Wave',	9,	'You unleash a devastating cascade of kinetic energy, ripping up the floor and hurling debris. Creatures in the cone take 2d8 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d8 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. A creature that critically fails is pushed 20 feet and knocked prone.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The area increases to a 50-foot cone.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Offense',	'30-foot cone',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceRevivify',	'Force Revivify',	9,	'You pour your own life force into the target to prevent their death. The target returns to life with Hit Points equal to 4d8 plus your Wisdom modifier (which increases by 2d8 at 12th and 19th level). They gain the wounded 1 condition (or increase their wounded value by 1 if they already had it). You immediately gain the drained 2 condition. This condition cannot be removed by any means until you complete a full night''s rest.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The target returns to life with temporary Hit Points equal to double your level.',	'[reaction]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Healing',	'30 feet',	'',	NULL,	'A living creature within 30 feet of you dies.',	NULL,	NULL),
('powDominateMind',	'Dominate Mind',	9,	'You crush the target''s will and replace it with your own. The target makes a Will save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Target is stunned 1.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> Target is controlled for 1 minute. However, the target can attempt a new Will save at the end of each of its turns to end the effect.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> Target is controlled for 1 minute. They only get a new save if you force them to take a clearly self-destructive action.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The range increases to 60 feet.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental, Incapacitation',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powPhaseShift',	'Phase Shift',	13,	'You vibrate your molecules to match the frequency of the matter around you. You become incorporeal. You gain resistance to all damage equal to your level (except force damage and ghost touch weapons), and you can move through solid objects. If you end your turn inside an object, you are shunted to the nearest open space and take 3d6 force damage (which increases by 1d6 at 19th level). When the effect ends, you are stunned 1 and fatigued.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The duration increases to 10 minutes (Sustained).',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Force',	NULL,	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powTelekineticCataclysm',	'Telekinetic Cataclysm',	13,	'You seize a massive section of the environment and implode it upon a central point. Creatures in the area take 6d10 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 2d10 at 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. The area becomes difficult terrain.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can choose to exclude the difficult terrain effect, or instead create a wall of debris around the perimeter (providing standard cover).',	'[three-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Offense',	'30-foot burst within 120 feet',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'Once per 10 minutes.',	NULL),
('powForceStatis',	'Force Stasis',	9,	'You attempt to halt the biological functions of a target, freezing them in time. The target makes a Fortitude save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Target is slowed 1 for 1 round.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> Target is paralyzed for 1 round.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> Target is paralyzed for 4 rounds. At the end of each of its turns, it can attempt a new Fortitude save to reduce the remaining duration by 1 round.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can Sustain this power. If you do, a paralyzed target takes a –2 circumstance penalty to their checks to end the effect.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Incapacitation',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceReflection',	'Force Reflection',	9,	'You gain a +2 circumstance bonus to AC against the triggering attack. If the attack misses, you redirect the bolt at another creature within 30 feet. Make a tech attack roll against the new target. On a hit, you deal the damage of the original attack to the new target.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can use this reaction even if you don''t have a weapon drawn (catching the bolt with your bare hand).',	'[reaction]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'You are targeted by a ranged energy attack (blaster bolt, lightning, etc.) and you have a Lightsaber drawn.',	NULL,	NULL),
('powMasterValor',	'Master Valor',	9,	'You become a beacon of hope. You and all allies in the area are quickened, gaining an extra action that can only be used to Stride or Strike. When the effect ends, you are slowed 1 for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The range increases to a 60-foot emanation.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control, Mental',	'30-foot emanation',	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMassMindTrick',	'Mass Mind Trick',	9,	'You weave a complex illusion or suggestion into the minds of a group. All living creatures in the area make a Will save.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The creatures become confused for 1 round (attacking the nearest creature).<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The creatures become controlled by you for 1 round.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can exclude a number of creatures equal to your Wisdom modifier from the effect.',	'[three-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental, Incapacitation',	'30-foot burst within 60 feet',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powChainLightning',	'Chain Lightning',	9,	'You unleash an arc of lightning that leaps from foe to foe. The primary target takes 2d12 electricity damage (which increases by 1d12 at 12th and 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. If the primary target takes damage, the lightning arcs to a secondary target within 30 feet of the first. The secondary target takes the same damage. It continues to arc to new valid targets within 30 feet, reducing the number of damage dice rolled by 1 for each jump until the target critically succeeds at its Reflex save, the number of damage dice reduces to zero, or there are no more valid targets. No single creature can be targeted more than once.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The number of damage dice does not start to decrease until the fourth target.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Electricity',	'60 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powSaberThrow',	'Saber Throw',	9,	'You hurl your ignited lightsaber in a spinning arc. You make a Strike against a target within range using your melee weapon. If the attack hits, you can immediately make a second Strike against a different target within 20 feet of the first. At 13th level, you can ricochet to a third target. All attacks made using this power count toward and are subject to multiple attack penalties. Regardless of hits or misses, the weapon flies back to your hand at the end of the action.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You treat all Strikes made during this action as having the agile trait.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense',	'60 feet',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powFarseeing',	'Farseeing',	9,	'You enter a deep trance to view a remote location. You can see and hear a location you are familiar with (or a person you are familiar with) as if you were standing there. The sensor is invisible.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can cast this ability as a 3-action activity instead of 10 minutes, but the duration becomes "Sustained (up to 1 minute)."',	'10 minutes',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense',	'Planetary',	NULL,	'Sustained (up to 10 minutes)',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powSuspendedAnimation',	'Suspended Animation (Morichro)',	13,	'You place the target into a trance so deep it mimics death. The target ceases to age, breathe, or require food/water. They appear dead to all scanners and mundane checks. The trance can last indefinitely. You can set a "wake up" condition (a specific time, a touch, or a noise).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can use this on an unwilling creature (Incapacitation, Fortitude save). On a failure, they are trapped in the trance for 1 week.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body',	'touch',	'1 willing creature (or yourself)',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceImmunity',	'Force Immunity',	13,	'You create a perfect shield against a specific threat. Choose one energy type (fire, cold, electricity, sonic, acid) or one physical trait (slashing, piercing, bludgeoning). You are immune to damage of that type until the start of your next turn.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can target an adjacent ally to give them the immunity instead of yourself.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control',	NULL,	NULL,	'1 round',	NULL,	'Once per hour.',	NULL),
('powSeverForce',	'Sever Force',	13,	'You attempt to permanently blind the target to the Force. The target must make a Will save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Target is stupefied 2 for 1 round.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> Target loses the ability to Cast Spells, use Force Powers, or use abilities with the Force trait for 1 minute.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> As failure, but the duration is permanent. This is a curse effect.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> On a failure or critical failure, the target also takes 3d6 mental damage (which increases by 1d6 at 19th level) as their connection is ripped away.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Curse, Incapacitation',	'30 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMindWipe',	'Mind Wipe',	13,	'You systematically rewrite or erase the target''s memories. You can erase up to 1 week of memories, or modify a specific event in their past. This is a permanent alteration.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can perform this action in 3 rounds instead of 1 minute.',	'1 minute',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental',	'touch',	'1 incapacitated or willing creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceStorm',	'Force Storm',	13,	'You tear the sky open, raining down violet lightning and chaotic energy. All creatures in the cylinder take 3d12 electricity damage (which increases by 1d12 at 19th level) with a basic Reflex save. You can Sustain this power for up to 1 minute. Each round you Sustain it, creatures in the area take the damage again. Sustaining this power is taxing; you are immobilized while Sustaining it.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You are not immobilized while Sustaining, but you cannot move more than 10 feet from your original spot or the storm ends.',	'[three-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Electricity',	'120-foot high, 60-foot radius cylinder',	NULL,	'Sustained (up to 1 minute)',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMasterPrecognition',	'Master Precognition',	13,	'You see the entire battle before it begins. You roll Initiative twice and keep the higher result. Additionally, for the first round of combat, you and all allies within 30 feet gain the concealed condition against all attacks (representing your pre-emptive warnings preventing hits).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can also Stride as a free action immediately after rolling Initiative.',	'[free-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense, Fortune',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'You roll Initiative.',	NULL,	NULL),
('powTrueSight',	'True Sight',	13,	'You see things as they truly are. You gain the effects of the True Seeing spell. You automatically succeed at disbelieving illusions and can see through invisibility, darkness, and magical disguises.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can spend two actions casting the power to share this vision with one ally by touching them.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Sense',	NULL,	NULL,	'10 minutes',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powTelekineticSingularity',	'Telekinetic Singularity',	17,	'You collapse a point in space, creating a momentary gravity well that crushes everything. Creatures and unattended objects in the area take 4d10 bludgeoning damage with a basic Fortitude save. All creatures in the area are pulled 20 feet toward the center of the burst. A creature that critically fails takes double damage, is stunned 1, and takes an additional 4d10 force damage.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can Sustain the singularity for 1 round. If you do, creatures remaining in the area at the start of your next turn take half the original damage again (no save).',	'[three-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Alter, Force',	'50-foot burst at up to 120 feet',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceEnlightenment',	'Force Enlightenment',	17,	'You become a conduit for energy, transcending physical limits. You gain the following benefits: Regenerate 20 Hit Points at the start of your turn; immunity to the drained, enfeebled, fatigued, and slowed conditions; and a +4 status bonus to all saving throws.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> When you activate this power, you also cast Force Valor as a free action.',	'[one-action]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body',	NULL,	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	'Once per day',	NULL),
('powTransferEssence',	'Transfer Essence',	17,	'You refuse to fade away. You immediately transfer your consciousness into another vessel. If you have a prepared clone or vessel within planetary range, you wake up in that body with 1 HP. Otherwise, you attempt to possess a creature within 30 feet. The target makes a Will save. On a failure, you possess them (as the Possession spell) and stabilize. On a success, you die normally.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The target of your possession takes a –2 circumstance penalty to the Will save.',	'[reaction]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'You would die.',	'Once per week',	NULL),
('powWallOfLight',	'Wall of Light',	17,	'You purge the area of darkness. The area becomes hallowed. Dark Side powers used within the area (or targeting into it) must succeed at a DC 11 flat check or fail. Undead and Dark Side users who start their turn in the area take 4d8 vitality damage and 4d8 fire damage.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> Allies in the area gain resistance 10 to all damage from Dark Side sources.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control, Light',	'60-foot burst',	NULL,	'1 minute',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceChoke',	'Force Choke',	5,	'You crush the target''s windpipe. The target must make a Fortitude save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level).<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target takes double damage and is grabbed.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target takes double damage and is restrained in the air (off-guard).<br><br><strong>Sustain:</strong> You can Sustain this power. When you do, the target takes the damage again (basic Fortitude save) and remains grabbed/restrained. While Sustaining this power, you are slowed 1.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You are not slowed while Sustaining this power.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense',	'60 feet',	'1 living creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMindTrick',	'Mind Trick',	1,	'You suggest a reasonable course of action to the target. The target makes a Will save against your class DC. Regardless of the result, the target is temporarily immune to your Mind Trick for 1 hour.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The creature is unaffected and knows you tried to influence it.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The creature is fascinated by you and follows the suggestion for 1 round (which increases to 1 minute at 12th level).<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The creature follows the suggestion for 1 minute.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> On a failure or critical failure, the target does not remember that you used this power on them after the effect ends.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental, Incapacitation',	'30 feet',	'1 living creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powVitalTransfer',	'Vital Transfer',	1,	'You transfer your own vitality or ambient life energy into another. The target regains 1d8 Hit Points (which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). You take damage equal to your level (which cannot be prevented) to fuel the power.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can target a creature within 30 feet instead of touch.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Healing',	'touch',	'1 willing living creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceVoid',	'Force Void',	17,	'You create a bubble where supernatural energy cannot exist. No Force Powers or other supernatural abilities can be cast within the area. Active Force effects entering the area are suppressed. Energy weapons function as normal metal clubs.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You are the exception. You can continue to use Force Powers within your own void, though you must make a DC 5 flat check to do so.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Control',	'20-foot emanation',	NULL,	'Sustained (up to 1 minute)',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMindFracture',	'Mind Fracture',	17,	'You subject a target to the total weight of the galaxy''s suffering, attempting to shatter their psyche. The target makes a Will save.<br><strong>Success:</strong> Target takes 2d10 mental damage and is stunned 1.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> Target takes 4d10 mental damage and is confused for 1 minute.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> Target dies instantly (from brain death). If the target is immune to death effects, they instead take 8d10 mental damage and are stunned 3.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> If the target survives (success or failure), they are permanently stupefied 2.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental, Incapacitation',	'60 feet',	'1 creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceDestruction',	'Force Destruction',	17,	'You concentrate pure energy into a sphere of annihilation and hurl it. Creatures in the area take 4d6 force damage and 4d6 fire damage with a basic Reflex save. If this damage reduces a creature to 0 HP, it is disintegrated (turned to dust).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can shape the blast into a 100-foot line instead of a burst.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Force',	'20-foot burst at up to 500 feet',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForesight',	'Foresight',	17,	'You grant the target a sixth sense that constantly warns of danger. The target gains the following benefits: They cannot be surprised or off-guard; they gain a +2 status bonus to AC and Reflex saves; whenever they roll a d20 for an attack, save, or skill check, they roll twice and take the higher result; and whenever an enemy attacks them, the enemy rolls twice and takes the lower result.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can cast this on yourself as a 1-action activity.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force  Power, Sense, Fortune, Misfortune',	'touch',	'1 creature',	'1 hour',	NULL,	'Once per day.',	NULL),
('powDeathField',	'Death Field',	13,	'You drain the life essence of all enemies around you. All enemies in the area take 5d8 void damage (which increases by 2d8 at 19th level) with a basic Fortitude save. You regain Hit Points equal to half the total damage dealt (max 100 HP).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> Enemies who fail the save are also enfeebled 2 for 1 minute.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Dark Side, Offense, Healing, Void',	'30-foot emanation',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'Once per 10 minutes.',	NULL),
('powKineticBombardment',	'Kinetic Bombardment',	17,	'You reach into the sky and pull down a massive object (a starship, a meteor, a building) to crush a target point. This acts as a localized artillery strike. Creatures within the burst take 8d12 bludgeoning damage with a basic Reflex save. Structures and vehicles take double damage.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> You can center the burst on a target you can see via Farseeing, even if you don''t have physical line of sight.',	'[three-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Offense, Alter',	'60-foot burst at up to 1 mile',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	'Once per 10 minutes.',	NULL),
('powDrainLife',	'Drain Life',	1,	'You violently siphon the life force of a victim to fuel your own. The target makes a Fortitude save. Regardless of the result, the target is temporarily immune to your Drain Life for 24 hours.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target takes 1d4 void damage (which increases by 1d4 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). You regain Hit Points equal to the damage dealt.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target takes 1d8 void damage (which increases by 1d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level). You regain Hit Points equal to the damage dealt.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target takes 2d8 void damage (which increases by 2d8 at 4th level and again at 12th and 19th level) and is enfeebled 1 for 1 minute. You regain Hit Points equal to the damage dealt.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The range increases to 30 feet.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Dark Side, Body, Void',	'Touch',	'1 living creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powMindProbe',	'Mind Probe',	5,	'You forcefully delve into a target''s mind to extract information. You ask a specific question. The target makes a Will save.<br><strong>Critical Success:</strong> The target resists and knows you tried to probe them. You take 2d6 mental damage (which increases by 1d6 at 12th and 19th level) from the feedback.<br><strong>Success:</strong> The target resists, but does not know the source of the intrusion.<br><strong>Failure:</strong> The target must give a truthful, brief answer to your question.<br><strong>Critical Failure:</strong> The target answers truthfully and you can ask a second question immediately (which they must also answer).<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> On a failure, the target is also stupefied 1 for 1 minute due to the mental trauma.',	'[two-actions]',	NULL,	'Force Power, Mind, Mental',	'30 feet',	'1 intelligent creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL),
('powForceResurrection',	'Force Resurrection',	13,	'You perform a deep meditation to coax a spirit back to its body, repairing fatal wounds. You restore life to a creature that has been dead for no longer than 3 days. The target returns with 1 Hit Point and the drained 4 condition. You gain the drained 4 condition. This value decreases by 1 for every 24 hours of rest you take. You cannot use this power again until your drained condition reaches 0.<br><br><strong>Connected:</strong> The target returns with drained 2 instead of drained 4.',	'10 minutes',	NULL,	'Force Power, Body, Healing',	'touch',	'1 dead creature',	NULL,	NULL,	NULL,	NULL);

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Shield";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Shield" (
    "ShieldID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Level" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "ACBonus" smallint DEFAULT '1',
    "SpeedPenalty" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "Bulk" character varying DEFAULT 'L',
    "Hardness" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "HP" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "BrokenThreshold" smallint DEFAULT '0',
    "Traits" character varying,
    "Description" text,
    "Features" jsonb,
    "Price" smallint,
    CONSTRAINT "Shield_ShieldID" PRIMARY KEY ("ShieldID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Shield"."ACBonus" IS 'Bonus to AC when Raised';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Shield"."Hardness" IS 'Damage reduction for Shield Block';

INSERT INTO "Shield" ("ShieldID", "Name", "Level", "ACBonus", "SpeedPenalty", "Bulk", "Hardness", "HP", "BrokenThreshold", "Traits", "Description", "Features", "Price") VALUES
('shdGunganEnergyShield',	'Gungan Energy Shield',	0,	2,	0,	'L',	5,	20,	10,	'Gungan, Tech',	'Carried into battle by the Gungan Grand Army, this shield is generated by a heavy, metallic handle. When activated, it projects a shimmering, purple plasma barrier that is highly effective at deflecting both kinetic impacts and blaster bolts.

<strong>Plasma Deflection</strong> Because the shield is made of cohesive plasma rather than physical matter, it is incredibly resilient against standard blaster fire. If you use the Shield Block reaction against an attack dealing energy damage (such as a laser or plasma weapon), you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the shield''s Hardness for that specific attack.',	NULL,	25);

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Skill";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Skill" (
    "SkillID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "KeyAttribute" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Description" text,
    "Lore" character varying,
    "Features" jsonb,
    CONSTRAINT "Skill_SkillID" PRIMARY KEY ("SkillID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Skill"."SkillID" IS 'Unique Skill ID';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Skill"."Name" IS 'Skill Name';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Skill"."KeyAttribute" IS 'Key Attribute';

COMMENT ON COLUMN "public"."Skill"."Description" IS 'Description';

INSERT INTO "Skill" ("SkillID", "Name", "KeyAttribute", "Description", "Lore", "Features") VALUES
('sklCrafting',	'Crafting',	'INT',	'You can use this skill to create and repair items. Even if you''re untrained, you can Recall Knowledge.
Recall Knowledge about the value of items, tech gear, engineering, unusual materials, and tech creatures.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklThievery',	'Thievery',	'DEX',	'You are trained in a particular set of skills favored by thieves and scoundrels.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklAcrobatics',	'Acrobatics',	'DEX',	'Acrobatics measures your ability to perform tasks requiring coordination and grace. When you use the Escape basic action, you can use your Acrobatics modifier instead of your unarmed attack modifier. You can also use it for the basic actions Arrest a Fall and Grab an Edge instead of Reflex.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklAthletics',	'Athletics',	'STR',	'Athletics allows you to perform deeds of physical prowess. Most Athletics actions let you move about the environment (Climb, High Jump, Long Jump, Swim) or control your opponent''s movement in combat (Grapple, Reposition, Shove, Trip, and Disarm).
Escape: When you use the Escape basic action, you can use your Athletics modifier instead of your unarmed attack modifier.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklIntimidation',	'Intimidation',	'CHA',	'You bend others to your will using threats. Unlike Deception or Diplomacy, Intimidation is typically a blunt instrument with little room for nuance or care.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklMedicine',	'Medicine',	'WIS',	'You can patch up wounds and help people recover from diseases and poisons. Treat Wounds is especially useful, allowing your adventuring party to heal up between fights. It can be made more efficient with skill feats like Continual Recovery and Ward Medic.
Even if you''re untrained in Medicine, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.
Recall Knowledge about diseases, poisons, wounds, and forensics. You can use this to perform forensic examinations if you spend 10 minutes (or more, as determined by the GM) checking for evidence such as wound patterns. This is most useful when determining how a body was injured or killed.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklNature',	'Nature',	'WIS',	'You know about the natural world, and you command and train animals and magical beasts. Even if you''re untrained in Nature, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.
Recall Knowledge about fauna, flora, geography, weather, the environment, natural creatures (like animals, beasts, and plants), and the galaxy.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklPerformance',	'Performance',	'CHA',	'You are skilled at a form of performance, using your talents to impress a crowd or make a living.
Even if you''re untrained in Performance, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.
Recall Knowledge about impressive performances, specific songs or media pieces, music groups, media personalities, and creatures who use song or dance abilities (such as magic songs or dances).',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklSociety',	'Society',	'INT',	'You understand the people and systems that make organized society run, and you know the historical events that make societies what they are today. Further, you can use that knowledge to navigate the complex physical, societal, and economic workings of planets and settlements. Even if you''re untrained in Society, you can use it for the following general skill actions.
Recall Knowledge about celebrities, history, laws, social structures, and cultural nuances of an organized society.
Subsist in a settlement by finding shelter, scrounging, or begging for food.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklDeception',	'Deception',	'CHA',	'You can use this skill to create and repair items. Even if you''re untrained, you can Recall Knowledge.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklDiplomacy',	'Diplomacy',	'CHA',	'You influence others through negotiation and flattery, or find out information through friendly chats.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklComputers',	'Computers',	'INT',	'Computers is your ability to work with computer systems and some technological equipment. Even if you''re untrained in Computers, you can use it for the following general skill actions.
Recall Knowledge about digital and virtual equipment, digital hazards, computer programs, and vidgames.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklStealth',	'Stealth',	'DEX',	'You are skilled at avoiding detection, allowing you to slip past foes, hide, or conceal an item.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklSurvival',	'Survival',	'WIS',	'You are adept at living in the wilderness, foraging for food and building shelter, and with training you discover the secrets of tracking and hiding your trail. Even if you''re untrained, you can still use Survival to Subsist.
Subsist in the wild by foraging for food and building shelter.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklTheForce',	'The Force',	'WIS',	'You are knowledgable in the ways of The Force and have studied to unravel its mysteries.

If you are sensitive in The Force, this skill also represents your skill at reaching out through The Force to interact with the world around you.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklPiloting',	'Piloting',	'DEX',	'Piloting represents your ability to command mechs, drive vehicles, pilot starships, and navigate. This also represents your basic knowledge related to identifying notable models or parts belonging to most piloted (and some semi-autonomous) vehicles. Even if you''re untrained, you can Recall Knowledge.
Recall Knowledge about models of mechs, vehicles or starships; areas of piloting significance (like notable black holes or interstellar phenomena); and specific equipment or parts that might be installed on a mech, vehicle, or starship.',	NULL,	NULL),
('sklLoreTailoring',	'Tailoring Lore',	'INT',	'You have specialized information on a narrow topic. Lore features many subcategories. You might have Corporate Lore, Piracy Lore, Mandalorian Lore, or any similar subcategory of the skill. Each subcategory counts as its own skill, so applying a skill increase to Coruscant Lore wouldn''t increase your proficiency with Corporate Lore, for example.

Most backgrounds make you trained in a specific subcategory of the Lore skill. The GM determines what other subcategories they''ll allow as Lore skills, though these categories are always less broad than any of the other skills that allow you to Recall Knowledge, and they should never be able to take the place of another skill''s Recall Knowledge action. For instance, you couldn''t choose Force Lore to recall the breadth of knowledge about Force powers covered by Arcana, Nature, Occultism, and Religion, or choose Adventuring Lore to give you all the information an adventurer needs, or choose Galaxy Lore to gain all the information spread across various skills and subcategories such as Outer Rim Lore.

If you''re making a check and multiple subcategories of Lore could apply, or a non-Lore skill could apply, you can use whichever skill you prefer. If there''s any doubt whether a Lore skill applies to a specific topic or action, the GM decides whether it can be used or not.

Even if you''re untrained in Lore, you can use it to Recall Knowledge.

* **Recall Knowledge** about the subject of the Lore skill''s subcategory.

## Lore Trained Actions

* **Earn Income** by using your knowledge to practice a trade.

## Common Lore Subcategories

You can learn any Lore skill your GM gives you permission to take. The following list covers a wide variety of common Lore topics appropriate for most campaigns. Backgrounds often grant you a Lore skill from this list.

* Art Lore
* Astrogation Lore
* Cantina Lore
* Chemistry Lore
* Cooking Lore
* Corporate Lore
* Cybernetics Lore
* Fashion Lore
* Galactic History Lore
* Gambling Lore
* Genetic Engineering Lore
* HoloNet Lore
* Labor Lore
* Legal Lore
* Life Science Lore
* Market Lore
* Media Lore
* Mining Lore
* Music Lore
* Paranormal Lore
* Physical Science Lore
* Piracy Lore
* Psychology Lore
* Scrapper Lore
* Sports Lore
* Technology Lore
* Underworld Lore
* Warfare Lore
* Lore about a specific Force tradition or philosophy (Jedi Lore, Sith Lore, Nightsister Lore, etc.)
* Lore about a specific creature, species, or narrow category (Droid Lore, Hutt Lore, Wookiee Lore, etc.)
* Lore about a specific planet (Coruscant Lore, Mandalore Lore, Tatooine Lore, etc.)
* Lore about a specific galactic region or sector (Core Worlds Lore, Outer Rim Lore, Unknown Regions Lore, etc.)
* Lore about a specific organization or faction (Bounty Hunters'' Guild Lore, Imperial Security Bureau Lore, Rebel Alliance Lore, etc.)
* Lore about a specific settlement or station (Black Spire Outpost Lore, Cloud City Lore, Mos Eisley Lore, etc.)',	'Lore, Craft',	NULL),
('sklLoreDemolitions',	'Demolitions Lore',	'INT',	'You have specialized information on a narrow topic. Lore features many subcategories. You might have Corporate Lore, Piracy Lore, Mandalorian Lore, or any similar subcategory of the skill. Each subcategory counts as its own skill, so applying a skill increase to Coruscant Lore wouldn''t increase your proficiency with Corporate Lore, for example.

