  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger</strong><span>A creature within your reach leaves a square during a move action it’s using.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You’re able to move deftly around your foes, getting out of tricky situations or managing to put yourself into a place where you hold the advantage. You Step up to twice directly toward the triggering creature.
  </div>
</div>
<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Overwhelming Strike</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Trigger</strong><span>Your Strike hits a creature you’ve designated as your mark and deals damage.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    The target becomes your choice of enfeebled 1, off-guard, or suppressed until the end of your next turn. That creature becomes immune to Overwhelming Strike until the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	'Operative',	'clsOperative',	'{"flag": {"operative_spec_skill": "Athletics"}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actReactiveStep", "name": "Reactive Step", "traits": "Operative", "trigger": "A creature within your reach leaves a square during a move action it’s using.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You’re able to move deftly around your foes, getting out of tricky situations or managing to put yourself into a place where you hold the advantage. You Step up to twice directly toward the triggering creature."}, {"id": "actOverwhelmingStrike", "name": "Overwhelming Strike", "traits": "Operative", "trigger": "Your Strike hits a creature you’ve designated as your mark and deals damage.", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "The target becomes your choice of enfeebled 1, off-guard, or suppressed until the end of your next turn. That creature becomes immune to Overwhelming Strike until the end of your next turn."}]}, "feature": ["clfSpecializedSkillSet"]}'),
('subMandateOfDominance',	'Mandate of Dominance',	'You believe the Force is a tool to be commanded to bring order to chaos. Whether through telekinetic might or crushing will, you control the physical position of your enemies.

You gain the Battle Focus power.

<strong>Connected Benefit</strong> Your telekinetic powers carry physical weight. Whenever you successfully hit a creature with a Force Power that deals damage, you can push that creature 5 feet in any direction.',	'Consular',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"fixed": ["powBattleFocus"]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheSwift',	'Cause of the Swift',	'You are a blur of motion. You believe that standing still is a death sentence. You use the Force to enhance your speed, striking where the enemy least expects.

You gain the Form IV: Ataru form feat.

<strong>Swift Focus</strong> Momentum is your ally. While Focused, you ignore Difficult Terrain.

<strong>Swift Intercede</strong> You intercept attacks from impossible distances. The range of your Intercede reaction increases from 15 feet to 30 feet.  If you are more than 15 feet from the targeted ally, you automatically Step or Stride to within 15 feet of them.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftAtaruStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheStalwart',	'Cause of the Stalwart',	'You are the ultimate shield. You believe that if you cannot be moved and cannot be broken, victory is inevitable. You protect others at all costs.

You gain the Form III: Soresu form feat.

<strong>Stalwart''s Focus</strong> You are a bastion of vitality. When you enter the Focused state, you gain Temporary Hit Points equal to your Level. These last until you stop being Focused.

<strong>Stalwart''s Intercede</strong> Your protection is absolute. When you use Intercede, the damage reduction increases by an amount equal to your Constitution modifier.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftSoresuStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheDuelist',	'Cause of the Duelist',	'You view combat as a contest of individual skill. You ignore the rabble to hunt down the enemy commander or Sith Lord and engage them in single combat.

You gain the Form II: Makashi form feat.

<strong>Duelist''s Focus</strong> Your focus is razor-sharp. While Focused, you gain a +1 status bonus to Will saves against Mental effects. If the effect originates from your Dueling Target, the bonus increases to +2.

<strong>Duelist''s Intercede</strong>* When you use Intercede, you can immediately Step to place yourself between the attacker and your ally. This movement must be in the direction of either the attacker that triggered Intercede or the ally being attacked.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftMakashiStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheVanguard',	'Cause of the Vanguard',	'You are trained to fight on the front lines of large-scale conflicts, managing multiple enemies at once. You are the breaker of armies.

You gain the Form I: Shii-Cho Form feat.

<strong>Vanguard''s Focus</strong> You are impossible to surround. While Focused, you cannot be Flanked by creatures of your level or lower.

<strong>Vanguard''s Intercede</strong> When you use Intercede, you can push the attacking enemy 5 feet away from your ally after the attack resolves.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftShiiChoStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subMandateOfVisions',	'Mandate of Visions',	'The Force flows through time as well as space. You focus on the Cosmic Force, peering into the immediate future to guide your allies and avoid danger.

You gain the Precognitive Parry power.

<strong>Connected Benefit</strong> You see attacks moments before they happen. While Connected, you cannot be Off-Guard to creatures of your level or lower. Additionally, you gain a +1 status bonus to Perception checks and Initiative rolls.',	'Consular',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"fixed": ["powPrecognitiveParry"]}}'),
('subMandateOfConflict',	'Mandate of Conflict',	'You accept that conflict is an unavoidable constant of the galaxy. Whether you serve the Light as a crusader or the Dark as a destroyer, you focus your study on the raw destructive potential of the Force. You master the art of turning cosmic energy into physical violence.

You gain the Force Push power.

<strong>Connected Benefit</strong> Your attacks carry a lingering resonance. Whenever you deal damage with Telekinetic Impact or a Force Power with the Offense trait, the target takes a –1 circumstance penalty to AC until the start of your next turn.',	'Consular',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"fixed": ["powForcePush"]}}'),
('subMandateOfTheAscendant',	'Mandate of the Ascendant',	'You view your own body as the ultimate vessel for the Force. Through rigorous physical and mental conditioning, you channel the Force to perform impossible feats of athleticism, turning yourself into a living projectile or an immovable object.

You gain the Force Surge power.

<strong>Connected Benefit</strong> Your movements are enhanced by the Force. You gain a +10-foot status bonus to your Speed. Additionally, whenever you use a Body Force Power, you ignore Difficult Terrain until the start of your next turn.',	'Consular',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"fixed": ["powForceSurge"]}}'),
('subFromTheShadows',	'From the Shadows',	'You prefer to direct your allies in subtle ways, without drawing much attention from foes. You might sneak in behind your bodyguards or support your team from a safe distance.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Stealth

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You gain Assurance (Stealth) as a bonus feat.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Coordinate Ambush

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Coordinate Ambush</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    With perfect timing, you call on hidden allies to take down an unsuspecting target. Designate an enemy creature within 60 feet and an ally within 60 feet. If the ally is hidden, undetected, or unnoticed to the target at the start of their turn, they treat the target as off-guard until the end of their turn instead of when they become visible to the target.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, Hide or Sneak. Until the start of your next turn, you can Strike the enemy target as a reaction the first time the ally you targeted attacks your designated enemy.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaAssurance", "type": "skill", "context_override": {"target_skill": "sklStealth"}}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actCoordinateAmbush", "name": "Coordinate Ambush", "traits": "Envoy, Directive", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "With perfect timing, you call on hidden allies to take down an unsuspecting target. Designate an enemy creature within 60 feet and an ally within 60 feet. If the ally is hidden, undetected, or unnoticed to the target at the start of their turn, they treat the target as off-guard until the end of their turn instead of when they become visible to the target.\n\n<b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, Hide or Sneak. Until the start of your next turn, you can Strike the enemy target as a reaction the first time the ally you targeted attacks your designated enemy."}]}}'),
('subMandateOfTheSage',	'Mandate of the Sage',	'You study the minds of sentient beings. You understand that the greatest conflicts are fought not with lightsabers, but with words and thoughts.

You gain the Mind Trick power.

<strong>Connected Benefit</strong> Your presence is soothing—or terrifying. While Connected, you can use your Wisdom modifier in place of your Charisma modifier for Diplomacy and Intimidation checks.',	'Consular',	'clsConsular',	'{"power": {"fixed": ["powMindTrick"]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheWarden',	'Cause of the Warden',	'You are a scholar-warrior. You believe that the lightsaber is just one tool among many, and that true mastery comes from balancing martial skill with Force abilities.

You gain the Form VI: Niman form feat.

<strong>Warden''s Focus</strong> Your mind is expanded. While Focused, you can use Recall Knowledge as a Free Action once per round.

<strong>Warden''s Intercede</strong> You soothe the pain as you block it. When you use Intercede, the ally also gains Temporary Hit Points equal to your Wisdom modifier.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftNimanStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subBombard',	'Bombard',	'There’s nothing like a big gun (or maybe several) to get you through tough times. You’ve come to terms with the fact that a stray bullet from one of your barrages might sometimes hit an ally, but you try to minimize such instances of “friendly fire.” You’ve trained to avoid harming allies with your barrages and learned to expertly position your attacks around them.

When you attack with an area weapon, you can select a number of allies within the area equal to half your Constitution modifier. The selected allies are unaffected by the attack. In addition, enemies who succeed (but not critically succeed) on their save against an area attack you make are still suppressed until the start of your next turn.',	'Soldier',	'clsSoldier',	NULL),
('subPathOfTheArtisan',	'Path of the Artisan',	'You understand that the Force exists in metal and circuitry just as it does in flesh. You are a builder, a slicer, and a saboteur. You analyze structures to find their breaking points.

You are trained in either Computers or Crafting and gain the Combat Hack skill feat. You also gain the following benefit:

<strong>Deconstruct</strong> You see the flaw in the machine. When you use Force Premonition against a Construct, Droid, or Vehicle (or an unattended object), your attack ignores an amount of Hardness or resistance equal to your Level. Additionally, you can trigger your Sentinel''s Strike damage on ranged attacks against these targets within 60 feet.',	'Sentinel',	'clsSentinel',	'{"skill": {"grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Computers or Crafting", "filter": [{"id": ["sklComputers", "sklCrafting"]}]}}}'),
('subPathOfTheShadow',	'Path of the Shadow',	'You serve the Order by doing what the Guardians cannot. You are a Jedi Shadow, tasked with eliminating threats before they can endanger the Republic. You strike from the darkness, silence the alarm, and vanish.

You are trained in Stealth and gain the Cloud Minds power.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Cloud Minds</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top">
      <span class="power-level">Level 1</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Force Power</span>
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Range</strong>
      <span>30 feet</span>
    </div>
    <div>
      <strong>Target</strong>
      <span>1 creature</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You reach into the target''s mind and erase your presence from their immediate perception. The target must attempt a Will save against your Class DC.<br><br><b>Success</b> The target is unaffected.<br><b>Failure</b> You become Hidden to the target until the start of your next turn or until you use a hostile action against them. (While Hidden, they know you are there but cannot see you clearly; you are not Off-Guard to them, and they must succeed at a DC 11 flat check to target you).<br><b>Critical Failure</b> You become Undetected by the target until the start of your next turn or until you use a hostile action.
  </div>
</div>

You also gain the follwing benefit:

<b>Deadly Visions</b> You foresee exactly where to strike to cause massive trauma. If you hit a creature with an attack using Force Premonition and that creature is Off-Guard (Flat-Footed), you deal additional Persistent Bleed Damage equal to your Sentinel''s Strike dice (e.g., 1d6 at level 1).',	'Sentinel',	'clsSentinel',	'{"power": {"grant": [{"id": "powCloudMinds", "name": "Cloud Minds", "level": "1", "range": "30 feet", "target": "1 creature", "traits": "Sentinel, Force Power, Mental", "action_cost": ["one-action"], "description": "You reach into the target''s mind and erase your presence from their immediate perception. The target must attempt a Will save against your Class DC.\n\n**Success:** The target is unaffected.\n\n**Failure:** You become Hidden to the target until the start of your next turn or until you use a hostile action against them. (While Hidden, they know you are there but cannot see you clearly; you are not Off-Guard to them, and they must succeed at a DC 11 flat check to target you).\n\n**Critical Failure:** You become Undetected by the target until the start of your next turn or until you use a hostile action."}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklStealth", "rank": "Trained"}]}}'),
('subCloseQuarters',	'Close Quarters',	'While you have the necessary training to employ heavy weapons, you believe it''s important to keep a backup for when foes get too close. You might be a veteran Veskarium trooper who knows their way around a doshko or a devotee of Zon-Shelyn dealing holy wrath with a painglaive. Blows with heavy close combat weapons hinder your foes just as effectively as when you fire a rotolaser or a missile launcher.

As long as you''re wielding a two-handed melee weapon, you meet the requirements for soldier feats that require an area weapon. When you''re using a soldier feat, any two-handed melee weapon you''re wielding gains area (burst 5 feet), and you''re unaffected by your attacks with that weapon. You can make a melee Strike with a two-handed melee weapon instead of a ranged Strike with primary target or any soldier feat. In addition, you gain the Whirling Swipe feat.',	'Soldier',	'clsSoldier',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftWhirlingSwipe", "type": "class"}]}}'),
('subArmorStorm',	'Armor Storm',	'Your armor feels like a part of you and stands up to heavy fire in the thick of battle. Your armor absorbs greater damage from attacks made by enemies you''ve suppressed. In a fight, you likely body block or stand in front and try to keep the enemy''s ire, trusting your armor to keep you alive.

You never count as being in the area of a ranged weapon you''ve made an attack with. You gain resistance equal to half your level (minimum 1) to all damage against attacks made by suppressed targets.

You don''t need a free hand to Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, or Trip. You gain a +1 status bonus on Athletics checks to Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, and Trip suppressed foes. When you successfully Disarm, Grapple, Reposition, Shove, or Trip a creature, it becomes suppressed until the start of your next turn.',	'Soldier',	'clsSoldier',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Suppressed Enemies", "amount": "{max(1, level // 2)}", "source": "Armor Storm Subclass"}]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheDestroyer',	'Cause of the Destroyer',	'You walk the line. Whether you are a Sith Lord or a Jedi attempting to master Vaapad, you channel your inner darkness into a weapon. You enjoy the fight.

You gain the Form VII: Juyo/Vaapad form feat.

<strong>Destroyer''s Focus</strong> You feed on fear. While Focused, you gain a +1 status bonus to Attack Rolls against creatures that are Frightened.

<strong>Destroyer''s Intercede</strong> Your defense is terrifying. When you use Intercede, you can attempt to Demoralize the attacker as part of the reaction (using Intimidation).',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftJuyoVaapadStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subPathOfTheCorsair',	'Path of the Corsair',	'You are a fringe-dweller, perhaps a Gray Jedi or a Sentinel assigned to the Outer Rim. You fight dirty, utilizing blasters, shoto-sabers, and tricks alongside the Force. You are unpredictable and dangerous.

You are trained in Deception and gain the Underhanded Trick action.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Underhanded Trick</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Mental</span>
  </div>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Requirements </strong>
      <span>You are wielding a one-handed melee weapon, a blaster, or are unarmed.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You use a dirty trick—kicking sand, flashing a lightsaber, or feigning surrender—to lower their guard. Attempt a Deception check to Feint against a target within melee reach (or within 30 feet if wielding a blaster).<br><br><b>Success</b> The target is Off-Guard against your attacks until the end of your next turn.<br><b>Critical Success</b> The target is Off-Guard against all attacks until the end of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>

You also gain the following benefit:

<strong>Ricochet Shot</strong> You see the angles. You can use Force Premonition with Ranged Weapons (Blasters) within 30 feet. When you do so, your Ranged Strikes do not provoke Reactive Strikes, and you ignore the penalty for shooting into melee cover.

',	'Sentinel',	'clsSentinel',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actUnderhandedTrick", "name": "Underhanded Trick", "traits": "Mental", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You use a dirty trick—kicking sand, flashing a lightsaber, or feigning surrender—to lower their guard. Attempt a Deception check to Feint against a target within melee reach (or within 30 feet if wielding a blaster).<br><br><b>Success</b> The target is Off-Guard against your attacks until the end of your next turn.<br><b>Critical Success</b> The target is Off-Guard against all attacks until the end of your next turn.", "requirements": "You are wielding a one-handed melee weapon, a blaster, or are unarmed."}]}}'),
('subCauseOfTheCrusader',	'Cause of the Crusader',	'You are the hammer of justice. You believe that defense is only useful if it leads to a decisive counter-attack. You meet force with overwhelming force.

You gain the Form V: Shien / Djem So form feat.

<strong>Crusader''s Focus</strong> You channel impact into power. While Focused, if you have taken damage since the end of your last turn, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to damage rolls with Lightsabers.

<strong>Crusader''s Intercede</strong> You punish the attacker. When you use Intercede, the attacker takes Force damage equal to your Strength modifier.',	'Guardian',	'clsGuardian',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "cftShienDjemSoStance", "type": "form"}]}}'),
('subPathOfTheWatchman',	'Path of the Watchman',	'You are the investigator and the beat cop of the galaxy. You walk the streets of Coruscant or the bazaars of Tatooine, sensing trouble before it starts. You prefer to subdue enemies rather than kill them.

You are trained in either Diplomacy or Society and gain the following benefits:

<strong>Deductive Angle</strong> Your mind processes information faster than a droid. When you use the Force Premonition action, you can immediately attempt to Recall Knowledge about the target as part of that action. If you succeed on the Recall Knowledge check, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus to the attack roll generated by your Premonition Roll.

<strong>Precognitive Maneuvers</strong> You can use your vision to predict an enemy''s movement. You can use your Premonition Roll to attempt an Athletics check to Grapple, Trip, or Disarm a target. You use your Wisdom modifier for this check instead of Strength. If you succeed, you deal your Sentinel''s Strike damage to the target (even though the maneuver deals no weapon damage).',	'Sentinel',	'clsSentinel',	'{"skill": {"grant": {"count": 1, "label": "requires Diplomacy or Society", "filter": [{"id": ["sklDeception", "sklSociety"]}]}}}'),
('subFromTheFront',	'From the Front',	'You’re most comfortable leading your allies from the front lines of battle while you fight alongside them. You might raise a shield to help weather the storm of incoming gunfire or simply lead with a pointed finger and a shout of encouragement as you run into the center of the enemy formation.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Athletics

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You’re trained in medium armor. When you gain light armor expertise, you also gain expert proficiency in medium armor, and when you gain light armor mastery, you also gain master proficiency in medium armor.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Into Position!

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Into Position!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span><span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You call on allies to get out of a threat''s area or close on a threat. Select an enemy within 60 feet. Allies within the target''s reach can Step as a reaction. Allies within 30 feet of you and not adjacent to the target can Stride as a reaction but must end closer to the target.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, Strike the target to focus their attention on you. The target takes a –1 circumstance penalty on attacks made against other creatures until the start of your next turn.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklAthletics", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actIntoPosition", "name": "Into Position!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive, Traversal", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You call on allies to get out of a threat''s area or close on a threat. Select an enemy within 60 feet. Allies within the target''s reach can Step as a reaction. Allies within 30 feet of you and not adjacent to the target can Stride as a reaction but must end closer to the target.\\n\\n<b>Lead by Example<b> If you used two actions, Strike the target to focus their attention on you. The target takes a –1 circumstance penalty on attacks made against other creatures until the start of your next turn.\""}]}, "armor_progression": {"sequence": ["medium"], "base_rank": "Trained", "level_upgrades": [{"rank": "Expert", "min_level": 13}, {"rank": "Master", "min_level": 19}]}}'),
('subInfosphereDirector',	'Infosphere Director',	'You control the flow of information, playing a critical role during a battle or while planning your next mission. You might give commands through a comm unit or datapad or using telepathic communication.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Computers

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You gain Digital Diversion as a bonus feat.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Digital Assessment!

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Digital Assessment!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    A quick check of your records and local infospheres lets you quickly disseminate information to your allies. Choose a creature within 100 feet and Recall Knowledge about the target. When you succeed at identifying your target with Recall Knowledge, you note a resistance or immunity in the creature''s defenses in addition to any other benefits.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you Strike the target. You and your allies gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against attacks made by the target until the start of your next turn. If the target has the tech trait, it must attempt a Fortitude save against your class DC. On a failure, the target becomes glitching 1. The target is then immune to Digital Assessment for 1 hour.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaDigitalDiversion", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDigitalAssessment", "name": "Digital Assessment!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "A quick check of your records and local infospheres lets you quickly disseminate information to your allies. Choose a creature within 100 feet and Recall Knowledge about the target. When you succeed at identifying your target with Recall Knowledge, you note a resistance or immunity in the creature''s defenses in addition to any other benefits.\n\n<b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you Strike the target. You and your allies gain a +1 circumstance bonus to AC against attacks made by the target until the start of your next turn. If the target has the tech trait, it must attempt a Fortitude save against your class DC. On a failure, the target becomes glitching 1. The target is then immune to Digital Assessment for 1 hour."}]}}'),
('subInTheSpotlight',	'In the Spotlight',	'Whether through conversation, clever lies, dazzling performances, or threats, you rely on charm and cunning to influence others. You crave being in the spotlight.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Performance

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You gain Impressive Performance as a bonus feat.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Dance Partner!

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Dance Partner!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span><span class="trait-tag">Traversal</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    Every good performer needs an accompanying act. Nominate yourself and an ally within 10 feet. Stride or Step, then your ally can Stride or Step as a reaction as long as they end the same distance or closer to you than they started.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, enemies are off-guard to your Strikes if within reach of your selected ally, and vice-versa, until the start of your next turn. Your ally becomes concealed against ranged Strikes made by creatures within 10 feet until the start of your next turn or the ally moves, whichever comes first.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaImpressivePerformance", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklPerformance", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actDancePartner", "name": "Dance Partner!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive, Traversal", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "Every good performer needs an accompanying act. Nominate yourself and an ally within 10 feet. Stride or Step, then your ally can Stride or Step as a reaction as long as they end the same distance or closer to you than they started.\n\n<b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, enemies are off-guard to your Strikes if within reach of your selected ally, and vice-versa, until the start of your next turn. Your ally becomes concealed against ranged Strikes made by creatures within 10 feet until the start of your next turn or the ally moves, whichever comes first."}]}}'),
('subGunsBlazing',	'Guns Blazing',	'You lead your team by making an impression with firepower. Your bombastic personality has a barrage of gunfire to back it up, and you always shoot first.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Acrobatics

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You gain Incredible Initiative as a bonus feat.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Ready Arms!

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Ready Arms!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    With quick commands, you get your allies to ready their equipment. You and all allies within 30 feet can Interact to draw, Switch Hands, or swap weapons as a reaction.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you can Strike, Area Fire, or Auto-Fire with a weapon you drew or swapped to (including by changing active set of hands). If your Strike hits or if a target failed its save against your Area Fire or Auto-Fire, one ally can make a Strike against the same target as a free action.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaIncredibleInitiative", "type": "general"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actReadyArms", "name": "Ready Arms!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "With quick commands, you get your allies to ready their equipment. You and all allies within 30 feet can Interact to draw, Switch Hands, or swap weapons as a reaction.\n\n<b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you can Strike, Area Fire, or Auto-Fire with a weapon you drew or swapped to (including by changing active set of hands). If your Strike hits or if a target failed its save against your Area Fire or Auto-Fire, one ally can make a Strike against the same target as a free action."}]}}'),
('subGhost',	'Ghost',	'You specialize in slipping into a location, completing an objective, and extricating yourself without being discovered. You might use stealth tactics, cover identities, disguises, or spy tech. Whether you''re an assassin getting close to your target, a spy gathering sensitive intelligence, a grifter out to dupe your mark, or a thief casing the joint for your next job, you''re good at blending in and avoiding notice. You''re trained in Deception. You gain a skill feat for Deception.

<h3>Exploit</h3>

You''re adept at taking your foe by surprise. You can Aim at targets you''re undetected by as a free action.

<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span><h3>Enhanced Exploit</h3></span><span><h3>Level 9</h3></span></div>

You avoid detection even after engaging your enemy. You gain the Ghost Tap action.

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Ghost Tap</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[free-action]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Operative</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div><strong>Requirements</strong><span>Your last action this round was a successful Strike against a target you were hidden from or undetected by.</span></div>
  </div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You throw an object, activate a hidden flare, or take some other action while your target is still disoriented from your attack. Attempt a Deception check against the Will DC of the target of your last Strike; on a success, you''re hidden from the target or undetected on a critical success.
  </div>
</div>',	'Operative',	'clsOperative',	'{"9": {"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actGhostTap", "name": "Ghost Tap", "traits": "Operative", "action_cost": "[free-action]", "description": "You throw an object, activate a hidden flare, or take some other action while your target is still disoriented from your attack. Attempt a Deception check against the Will DC of the target of your last Strike; on a success, you''re hidden from the target or undetected on a critical success.", "requirements": "Your last action this round was a successful Strike against a target you were hidden from or undetected by."}]}}, "flag": {"operative_spec_skill": "Deception"}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklDeception", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "feature": ["clfSpecializedSkillSet"]}'),
('subSkirmisher',	'Skirmisher',	'You specialize in close-quarters missions that require you to operate in crowded or tight spaces, such as inside buildings or vehicles, down narrow alleys, or in busy downtown streets. Whether you''re a mugger, bodyguard, assassin, or urban mercenary, you favor pistols and can use them efficiently in tight spaces. You''re trained in Acrobatics. You gain a skill feat for Acrobatics.

<h3>Exploit</h3>

You''re trained to fight in close combat using pistols. Your ranged Strikes with one-handed ranged weapons don''t trigger reactions that are triggered by a ranged attack.

<div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between;"><span><h3>Enhanced Exploit</h3></span><span><h3>Level 9</h3></span></div>

Your point-blank shots are particularly deadly. When you make a successful Strike against an adjacent enemy with a one-handed ranged weapon, you calculate the damage as if the lowest-rolled weapon damage die for the attack had the maximum result instead. At 17th level, the two lowest-rolled damage dice increase to the maximum result.',	'Operative',	'clsOperative',	'{"flag": {"operative_spec_skill": "Acrobatics"}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklAcrobatics", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "feature": ["clfSpecializedSkillSet"]}'),
('subThroughDesperateTimes',	'Through Desperate Times',	'You step up to lead during difficult times. You might have experienced a traumatic event, perhaps escaping a pirate ship during a mutiny, or you fought in some notorious battle. Your allies trust your instincts, knowing you’ll keep them safe.

<h3>Leadership Skill</h3>

Medicine

<h3>Leadership Perk</h3>

You gain Battle Medicine as a bonus feat.

<h3>Leadership Directive</h3>

Keep on Keeping On!

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Keep on Keeping On!</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[one-action] or [two-actions]</span>
    </div>
    <div class="power-meta-top"><span class="power-level">Subclass Feature</span></div>
  </header>
  <div class="power-card-traits">
    <span class="trait-tag">Envoy</span><span class="trait-tag">Directive</span>
  </div>
  <div class="power-card-meta-grid"></div>
  <hr class="power-card-divider" />
  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You push your allies to continue fighting despite their injuries. Select an ally within 30 feet. Until the start of your next turn, that ally increases the next healing they receive by an amount equal to your Charisma modifier plus half your level.<br><br><b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you Battle Medicine the target, and the target only becomes immune to Battle Medicine for the next 10 minutes instead of 1 day.
  </div>
</div>',	'Envoy',	'clsEnvoy',	'{"feat": {"fixed": [{"id": "feaBattleMedicine", "type": "skill"}]}, "skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklMedicine", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "ctKeepOnKeepingOn", "name": "Keep on Keeping On!", "traits": "Envoy, Directive", "action_cost": "[one-action] or [two-actions]", "description": "You push your allies to continue fighting despite their injuries. Select an ally within 30 feet. Until the start of your next turn, that ally increases the next healing they receive by an amount equal to your Charisma modifier plus half your level.\n\n<b>Lead by Example</b> If you used two actions, you Battle Medicine the target, and the target only becomes immune to Battle Medicine for the next 10 minutes instead of 1 day."}]}}'),
('subPathOfTheJusticar',	'Path of the Justicar',	'You are the shield against the darkness within. You specialize in hunting rogue Force users, Sith, and magical threats. Your fighting style disrupts concentration and severs connections to the Force.

You are trained in Intimidation and gain the Slay the Witch reaction.  

<div class="power-card-display">
  <header class="power-card-header">
    <div class="power-title-line">
      <h3 class="power-name">Slay the Witch</h3>
      <span class="power-action-cost">[reaction]</span>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="power-card-meta-grid">
    <div>
      <strong>Trigger </strong>
      <span>A creature within your reach uses a Force Power.</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <hr class="power-card-divider" />

  <div class="power-card-description markdown-body">
    You strike to disrupt their focus. Make a melee Strike against the triggering creature. If the attack is a Critical Hit, the spell or power is disrupted.
  </div>
</div>

You also gain the following benefit:

<strong>Disruptive Strike</strong> You strike the mind as well as the body. If you hit a target with your Force Premonition attack, the target becomes Stupefied 1 until the start of your next turn. If the target attempts to use a Force Power while Stupefied, they must succeed at a Flat Check (DC 5 + Stupefied value) or lose the action.',	'Sentinel',	'clsSentinel',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklIntimidation", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "action": {"grant": [{"id": "actSlayTheWitch", "name": "Slay the Witch", "trigger": "A creature within your reach uses a Force Power.", "action_cost": "[reaction]", "description": "You strike to disrupt their focus. Make a melee Strike against the triggering creature. If the attack is a Critical Hit, the spell or power is disrupted."}]}}'),
('subDroidwright',	'Droidwright',	'<p>You specialize in robotics and artificial intelligence, treating your droid not just as a tool, but as a partner, a protector, and a remote extension of your own capabilities.</p>
<p><h3>Droid Companion</h3> You gain a droid companion. It functions similarly to an animal companion, having the construct trait instead of the animal trait. It shares your proficiency in attacks and AC.<br><br>
You become trained in Droid Engineering Lore.</p>
<p><h3>Remote Uplink</h3>Your custom rig is wirelessly tethered to your droid companion. Whenever you activate a Modification from your rig, you can calculate line of effect and range from your droid companion''s space instead of your own. You automatically add the Telemetry Uplink modification to your modification library, and you can keep it loaded in your Rig without it counting against your prepared modifications.</p>
<p><h3>Feedback Loop</h3> If you Overclock a Modification through your droid companion''s Remote Uplink and fail the flat check, your droid absorbs the brunt of the ambient energy surge. You still lose the ability to Overclock for 10 minutes, but your droid gains a +1 status bonus to its attack rolls and AC until the end of its next turn.</p>',	NULL,	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklLoreDroidEngineering", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "minion": {"companion_slot": [{"count": 1, "label": "Droid Companion", "trait_filter": "Construct"}]}, "modification": {"mod_slot": {"fixed": ["modTelemetryUplink"]}, "library_slot": {"fixed": ["modTelemetryUplink"]}}}'),
('subSlicer',	'Slicer',	'<p>You specialize in code, decryption, and electronic warfare. To you, a locked blast door, an enemy''s targeting computer, and a high-security camera feed are all just puzzles waiting to be solved.</p>
<p></p>
<p><h3>Wireless Breach</h3> You become trained in Computers. You can attempt Computers checks to Disable a Device, bypass security, or manipulate technology at a range of 30 feet, rather than needing physical access. You must be holding your custom rig to do this.</p>
<p><h3>Intrusive Code</h3> Your rig is pre-loaded with aggressive malware. You automatically add the Overload Logic modification to your modification library, and you can keep it prepared in your custom rig without it counting against your daily limit of prepared Modifications.</p>
<p><h3>Security Compromise</h3> When you successfully Overclock a Modification that requires a saving throw or an attack roll against an enemy, the target''s armor or personal shielding is briefly compromised by your code. The target is off-guard until the start of your next turn.</p>',	NULL,	'clsTechSpecialist',	'{"skill": {"fixed": [{"id": "sklComputers", "rank": "Trained"}]}, "modification": {"mod_slot": {"fixed": ["modOverloadLogic"]}, "library_slot": {"fixed": ["modOverloadLogic"]}}}');

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "Upgrade";
CREATE TABLE "public"."Upgrade" (
    "UpgradeID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Name" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Level" smallint NOT NULL,
    "Price" integer NOT NULL,
    "Bulk" character varying,
    "Type" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Traits" character varying,
    "Description" text NOT NULL,
    "Features" jsonb
)
WITH (oids = false);

INSERT INTO "Upgrade" ("UpgradeID", "Name", "Level", "Price", "Bulk", "Type", "Traits", "Description", "Features") VALUES
('upgPersonalEnergyShieldT',	'Personal Energy Shield (Tactical)',	4,	1000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Force fields absorb damage. A force field''s Hit Points are based on its version. While your force field is active, any physical or energy damage you would take is applied to the force field''s Hit Points first before being applied to your Hit Points (including temporary Hit Points). If you have a shield raised, your force field and shield both take damage. If damage from an attack or effect reduces the force field to 0 Hit Points, you take any excess damage, the force field deactivates, and it can''t be activated again for 10 minutes. Force fields replenish the indicated number of Hit Points each round at the beginning of your turn while they''re active.

If your force field is tactical or better, it also protects you from deadly blows. Each time you''re critically hit while your force field is active, attempt a flat check against the listed DC. On a success, it becomes a normal hit.

The force field has 14 Hit Points and replenishes 3 Hit Points on your turn, and the flat check DC is 20.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRaiseForceField", "name": "Raise Force Field", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your force field becomes active. It remains active for 1 minute or until it''s reduced to 0 Hit Points."}]}}'),
('upgPersonalEnergyShieldA',	'Personal Energy Shield (Advanced)',	7,	3600,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Force fields absorb damage. A force field''s Hit Points are based on its version. While your force field is active, any physical or energy damage you would take is applied to the force field''s Hit Points first before being applied to your Hit Points (including temporary Hit Points). If you have a shield raised, your force field and shield both take damage. If damage from an attack or effect reduces the force field to 0 Hit Points, you take any excess damage, the force field deactivates, and it can''t be activated again for 10 minutes. Force fields replenish the indicated number of Hit Points each round at the beginning of your turn while they''re active.

If your force field is tactical or better, it also protects you from deadly blows. Each time you''re critically hit while your force field is active, attempt a flat check against the listed DC. On a success, it becomes a normal hit.

