The force field has 32 Hit Points and replenishes 6 Hit Points on your turn, and the flat check DC is 17.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRaiseForceField", "name": "Raise Force Field", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your force field becomes active. It remains active for 1 minute or until it''s reduced to 0 Hit Points."}]}}'),
('upgJetpackC',	'Jetpack (Commercial)',	5,	1600,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Boosters attached to your armor allow you to fly.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFly", "name": "Fly", "traits": "Manipulate, Move", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You activate a jetpack to gain a fly Speed of 20 feet. This effect lasts for 1 minute or until you Dismiss it. You can use an action to Fly 0 feet to hover in place, but you''re off-guard while doing so. A jetpack can''t lift you if you''re encumbered."}]}}'),
('upgIRVisor',	'IR Visor',	1,	150,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This visor wraps around your visual organs, enhancing your natural senses. You gain darkvision.',	'{"sense": [{"darkvision": 60}]}'),
('upgManeuveringUnitA',	'Maneuvering Unit (Advanced)',	11,	13400,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Internal stabilizers and jets synchronize your movements in zero gravity. You aren''t off-guard or clumsy while untethered.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actThrust", "name": "Thrust", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You move 15 feet in any direction you choose. You begin to float in that direction.", "requirements": "You are in a zero-G environment."}]}}'),
('upgActiveCamouflageT',	'Active Camouflage (Tactical)',	9,	6500,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Hardlight projectors shift the appearance of your armor using shifting colors and patterns that respond to your environment. You gain a +2 item bonus to Stealth checks while wearing the armor.',	'{"skill": {"bonus": [{"id": "sklStealth", "type": "item", "amount": 2, "source": "Active Camouflage (Tactical)"}]}}'),
('upgMobilityEnhancerT',	'Mobility Enhancer (Tactical)',	10,	11000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Automated braces help you to move faster in bulky armor. Reduce your armor''s penalty to Speeds by 10 feet.',	'{"defense": [{"light": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 10}}, {"medium": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 10}}, {"heavy": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 10}}, {"unarmored": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 10}}]}'),
('upgPersonalEnergyShieldUP',	'Personal Energy Shield (Paragon)',	19,	400000,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Force fields absorb damage. A force field''s Hit Points are based on its version. While your force field is active, any physical or energy damage you would take is applied to the force field''s Hit Points first before being applied to your Hit Points (including temporary Hit Points). If you have a shield raised, your force field and shield both take damage. If damage from an attack or effect reduces the force field to 0 Hit Points, you take any excess damage, the force field deactivates, and it can''t be activated again for 10 minutes. Force fields replenish the indicated number of Hit Points each round at the beginning of your turn while they''re active.

If your force field is tactical or better, it also protects you from deadly blows. Each time you''re critically hit while your force field is active, attempt a flat check against the listed DC. On a success, it becomes a normal hit.

The force field has 42 Hit Points and replenishes 8 Hit Points on your turn, and the flat check DC is 15.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRaiseForceField", "name": "Raise Force Field", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your force field becomes active. It remains active for 1 minute or until it''s reduced to 0 Hit Points."}]}}'),
('upgAutoCPRUnit',	'Auto-CPR Unit',	2,	200,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This device monitors your vital signs and automatically administers aid. When you have the dying condition while wearing this armor, the DC of your recovery checks is equal to 8 + your dying value (instead of 10 + your dying value).',	NULL),
('upgJumpJets',	'Jump Jets',	3,	550,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Boosters attached to your armor supercharge your leap.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actJump", "name": "Jump", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Once per round.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You activate the jump jets to get a quick boost. You Fly up to 20 feet with a maximum height of 10 feet, or you Fly up to 20 feet straight up. You must land at the end of this movement or fall. Jump jets can''t lift you if you''re encumbered."}]}}'),
('upgManeuveringUnitT',	'Maneuvering Unit (Tactical)',	7,	3200,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Internal stabilizers and jets synchronize your movements in zero gravity. You aren''t off-guard or clumsy while untethered.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actThrust", "name": "Thrust", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You move 10 feet in any direction you choose. You begin to float in that direction.", "requirements": "You are in a zero-G environment."}]}}'),
('upgManeuveringUnitC',	'Maneuvering Unit (Commercial)',	4,	800,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Internal stabilizers and jets synchronize your movements in zero gravity. You aren''t off-guard or clumsy while untethered.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actThrust", "name": "Thrust", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You move 5 feet in any direction you choose. You begin to float in that direction.", "requirements": "You are in a zero-G environment."}]}}'),
('upgManeuveringUnitS',	'Maneuvering Unit (Superior)',	15,	64400,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Internal stabilizers and jets synchronize your movements in zero gravity. You aren''t off-guard or clumsy while untethered.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actThrust", "name": "Thrust", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You move 30 feet in any direction you choose. You begin to float in that direction.", "requirements": "You are in a zero-G environment."}]}}'),
('upgLoadLifterT',	'Load Lifter (Tactical)',	4,	750,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This series of support braces allow you to carry and lift beyond your normal capacity. You can carry an amount of Bulk equal to 7 plus your Strength modifier without becoming encumbered, and you can hold and carry a total Bulk up to 12 plus your Strength modifier.',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_base": 7, "overburdened_base": 12}}'),
('upgActiveCamouflageC',	'Active Camouflage (Commercial)',	5,	500,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Hardlight projectors shift the appearance of your armor using shifting colors and patterns that respond to your environment. You gain a +1 item bonus to Stealth checks while wearing the armor.',	'{"skill": {"bonus": [{"id": "sklStealth", "type": "item", "amount": 1, "source": "Active Camouflage (Commercial)"}]}}'),
('upgMobilityEnhancerC',	'Mobility Enhancer (Commercial)',	3,	1000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Automated braces help you to move faster in bulky armor. Reduce your armor''s penalty to Speeds by 5 feet.',	'{"defense": [{"light": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 5}}, {"medium": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 5}}, {"heavy": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 5}}, {"unarmored": {"reduce_speed_penalty": 5}}]}'),
('upgThermalCapacitorA',	'ThermalCapacitor (Advanced)',	10,	21300,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade regulates heat, protecting you from extreme temperatures. You''re protected from extreme cold and extreme heat.',	NULL),
('upgBasicEnvironmentalProtection',	'Basic Environmental Protection',	1,	10,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This upgrade protects the user against the effects of space as well as thick and thin atmospheres. This armor loses the exposed trait for as long as the upgrade is installed.',	NULL),
('upgRadiationBufferC',	'Radiation Buffer (Commercial)',	1,	130,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'A layer of treated lead lines your armor with integrated radiation sensors networked into your comm unit. While you''re wearing armor with this upgrade, you gain resistance 2 to poison damage from radiation effects and a +1 status bonus to Fortitude saves against radiation.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Poison (Radiation)", "amount": 2, "source": "Radiation Buffer (Commercial)"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Radiation Buffer (Commercial)", "value": "+1 status bonus against radiation", "target": "fortitude"}]}]}'),
('upgRadiationBufferT',	'Radiation Buffer (Tactical)',	6,	2150,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'A layer of treated lead lines your armor with integrated radiation sensors networked into your comm unit. While you''re wearing armor with this upgrade, you gain resistance 4 to poison damage from radiation effects and a +2 status bonus to Fortitude saves against radiation.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Poison (Radiation)", "amount": 4, "source": "Radiation Buffer (Tactical)"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Radiation Buffer (Tactical)", "value": "+2 status bonus against radiation", "target": "fortitude"}]}]}'),
('upgJetpackT',	'Jetpack (Tactical)',	19,	350000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Boosters attached to your armor allow you to fly.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actFly", "name": "Fly", "traits": "Manipulate, Move", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You activate a jetpack to gain a fly Speed of 40 feet. This effect lasts for 1 minute or until you Dismiss it. You can use an action to Fly 0 feet to hover in place. A jetpack can''t lift you if you''re encumbered."}]}}'),
('upgCloakingDeviceC',	'Cloaking Device (Commercial)',	8,	5000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This projector bends light around your body.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBendLight", "name": "Bend Light", "traits": null, "frequency": "Once per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You become invisible for 1 minute, becoming undetected to all creatures lacking precise senses other than vision.  Creatures can attempt to Seek you, making you hidden to them instead.  Using any hostile action ends the invisibility after the action resolves."}]}}'),
('upgCloakingDeviceT',	'Cloaking Device (Tactical)',	10,	10000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This projector bends light around your body.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actBendLight", "name": "Bend Light", "traits": null, "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "You become invisible for 1 minute, becoming undetected to all creatures lacking precise senses other than vision.  Creatures can attempt to Seek you, making you hidden to them instead.  Using any hostile action ends the invisibility after the action resolves."}]}}'),
('upgFilteredRebreatherC',	'Filtered Rebreather (Commercial)',	1,	5,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade supplements your armor''s environmental protections and filters out common contaminants, including protection from most toxic atmospheres.',	NULL),
('upgThermalCapacitorC',	'ThermalCapacitor (Commercial)',	1,	120,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade regulates heat, protecting you from extreme temperatures. You''re protected from mild cold and mild heat.',	NULL),
('upgThermalCapacitorT',	'ThermalCapacitor (Tactical)',	6,	1800,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade regulates heat, protecting you from extreme temperatures. You''re protected from severe cold and severe heat.',	NULL),
('upgThermalCapacitorS',	'ThermalCapacitor (Superior)',	14,	37800,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade regulates heat, protecting you from extreme temperatures. You’re protected from incredible cold and incredible heat.',	NULL),
('upgBipodT',	'Bipod (Tactical)',	1,	100,	'1',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A bipod can be attached to powerful weapons—those with the kickback trait—to allow wielders with lower Strength to use them at the cost of mobility. You can set up the bipod with a single Interact action using one appendage, setting the bipod in your square. When using a bipod, you don''t take the –2 penalty for firing a kickback weapon, even if your Strength isn''t high enough to avoid the penalty.

You must spend a free action to retrieve the bipod before you can move the weapon to a different position. Deploying or retrieving a bipod with an Interact action doesn''t automatically make you observed like an Interact action normally would, so long as you don''t set up or remove the bipod when it''s in a spot where creatures can see it.',	NULL),
('upgFilteredRebreatherE',	'Filtered Rebreather (Elite)',	14,	40000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade supplements your armor''s environmental protections and filters out common contaminants, including protection from most toxic atmospheres. You gain a +4 status bonus to saves against inhaled effects.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Filtered Rebreather (Elite)", "value": "+4 status bonus against inhaled effects", "target": "all"}]}]}'),
('upgFilteredRebreatherT',	'Filtered Rebreather (Tactical)',	1,	150,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade supplements your armor''s environmental protections and filters out common contaminants, including protection from most toxic atmospheres. You gain a +1 status bonus to saves against inhaled effects.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Filtered Rebreather (Tactical)", "value": "+1 status bonus against inhaled effects", "target": "all"}]}]}'),
('upgBipodA',	'Bipod (Advanced)',	2,	450,	'1',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A bipod can be attached to powerful weapons—those with the kickback trait—to allow wielders with lower Strength to use them at the cost of mobility. You can set up the bipod with a single free action using one appendage, setting the bipod in your square. When using a bipod, you don''t take the –2 penalty for firing a kickback weapon, even if your Strength isn''t high enough to avoid the penalty.

You must spend a free action to retrieve the bipod before you can move the weapon to a different position.',	NULL),
('upgSilencerC',	'Silencer (Commercial)',	1,	10,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A cylinder is filled with internal sound baffles to reduce noise. The weapon doesn''t make a loud noise when fired. However, creatures hit by the ammunition might still cry out in pain.',	NULL),
('upgSnipersScopeT',	'Sniper''s Scope (Tactical)',	3,	700,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A telescopic sighting attachment helps view distant targets. The scope grants you a +1 item bonus to visual Perception checks to Seek creatures through the scope.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actAdjustSight", "name": "Adjust Sight", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Increase the range increment of the weapon the scope is attached to by 10 feet. If the weapon has a base range increment of 50 feet or more, increase the range of the weapon by 20 feet instead. This lasts until the beginning of your next turn or until you''re no longer wielding the weapon this scope is attached to, whichever comes first. This does not increase the size of area attacks."}]}}'),
('upgSnipersScopeA',	'Sniper''s Scope (Advanced)',	9,	8000,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A telescopic sighting attachment helps view distant targets. The scope grants you a +2 item bonus to visual Perception checks to Seek creatures through the scope.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actAdjustSight", "name": "Adjust Sight", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Increase the range increment of the weapon the scope is attached to by 20 feet. If the weapon has a base range increment of 50 feet or more, increase the range of the weapon by 40 feet instead. This lasts until the beginning of your next turn or until you''re no longer wielding the weapon this scope is attached to, whichever comes first. This does not increase the size of area attacks."}]}}'),
('upgSnipersScopeS',	'Sniper''s Scope (Superior)',	17,	160000,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A telescopic sighting attachment helps view distant targets. The scope grants you a +3 item bonus to visual Perception checks to Seek creatures through the scope.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actAdjustSight", "name": "Adjust Sight", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Increase the range increment of the weapon the scope is attached to by 40 feet. If the weapon has a base range increment of 50 feet or more, increase the range of the weapon by 80 feet instead. This lasts until the beginning of your next turn or until you''re no longer wielding the weapon this scope is attached to, whichever comes first. This does not increase the size of area attacks."}]}}'),
('upgUniclamp',	'Uniclamp',	1,	100,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'This is the ultimate all-purpose accessory item for holding everything from a fire extinguisher or flashlight to a musical instrument or comm unit. You can securely attach a single piece of tech gear of up to 1 Bulk to a uniclamp when you install the upgrade. You can activate the attached item using the same number of hands you use to wield your weapon while still wielding your weapon. The uniclamp can be properly configured to handle only non-magical tech gear and doesn''t function with weapons or shields. The GM might determine that some items don''t fit on certain weapons.',	NULL),
('upgSmugglersGripC',	'Smuggler''s Grip (Commercial)',	2,	400,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'These grips are designed to make it easy to conceal your weapon and are frequently used by detectives, diplomats, and smugglers. The weapon gains the concealable trait.',	NULL),
('upgLoadLifterC',	'Load Lifter (Commercial)',	2,	550,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This series of support braces allow you to carry and lift beyond your normal capacity. You can carry an amount of Bulk equal to 6 plus your Strength modifier without becoming encumbered, and you can hold and carry a total Bulk up to 11 plus your Strength modifier.',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_base": 6, "overburdened_base": 11}}'),
('upgLoadLifterA',	'Load Lifter (Advanced)',	6,	2100,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This series of support braces allow you to carry and lift beyond your normal capacity. You can carry an amount of Bulk equal to 8 plus your Strength modifier without becoming encumbered, and you can hold and carry a total Bulk up to 13 plus your Strength modifier.',	'{"flags": {"encumbered_base": 8, "overburdened_base": 13}}'),
('upgActiveCamouflageA',	'Active Camouflage (Advanced)',	17,	140000,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Hardlight projectors shift the appearance of your armor using shifting colors and patterns that respond to your environment. You gain a +3 item bonus to Stealth checks while wearing the armor.',	'{"skill": {"bonus": [{"id": "sklStealth", "type": "item", "amount": 3, "source": "Active Camouflage (Advanced)"}]}}'),
('upgFilteredRebreatherA',	'Filtered Rebreather (Advanced)',	6,	2550,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade supplements your armor''s environmental protections and filters out common contaminants, including protection from most toxic atmospheres. You gain a +2 status bonus to saves against inhaled effects.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Filtered Rebreather (Advanced)", "value": "+2 status bonus against inhaled effects", "target": "all"}]}]}'),
('upgFilteredRebreatherS',	'Filtered Rebreather (Superior)',	10,	24100,	'L',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'This armor upgrade supplements your armor''s environmental protections and filters out common contaminants, including protection from most toxic atmospheres. You gain a +3 status bonus to saves against inhaled effects.',	'{"saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Filtered Rebreather (Superior)", "value": "+3 status bonus against inhaled effects", "target": "all"}]}]}'),
('upgPersonalEnergyShieldC',	'Personal Energy Shield (Commercial)',	1,	200,	NULL,	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Force fields absorb damage. A force field''s Hit Points are based on its version. While your force field is active, any physical or energy damage you would take is applied to the force field''s Hit Points first before being applied to your Hit Points (including temporary Hit Points). If you have a shield raised, your force field and shield both take damage. If damage from an attack or effect reduces the force field to 0 Hit Points, you take any excess damage, the force field deactivates, and it can''t be activated again for 10 minutes. Force fields replenish the indicated number of Hit Points each round at the beginning of your turn while they''re active.

The force field has 6 Hit Points and replenishes 2 Hit Points on your turn.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRaiseForceField", "name": "Raise Force Field", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your force field becomes active. It remains active for 1 minute or until it''s reduced to 0 Hit Points."}]}}'),
('upgPersonalEnergyShieldU',	'Personal Energy Shield (Ultimate)',	16,	100000,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'Force fields absorb damage. A force field''s Hit Points are based on its version. While your force field is active, any physical or energy damage you would take is applied to the force field''s Hit Points first before being applied to your Hit Points (including temporary Hit Points). If you have a shield raised, your force field and shield both take damage. If damage from an attack or effect reduces the force field to 0 Hit Points, you take any excess damage, the force field deactivates, and it can''t be activated again for 10 minutes. Force fields replenish the indicated number of Hit Points each round at the beginning of your turn while they''re active.

If your force field is tactical or better, it also protects you from deadly blows. Each time you''re critically hit while your force field is active, attempt a flat check against the listed DC. On a success, it becomes a normal hit.

The force field has 37 Hit Points and replenishes 7 Hit Points on your turn, and the flat check DC is 16.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actRaiseForceField", "name": "Raise Force Field", "traits": "Manipulate", "frequency": "Three times per day.", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Your force field becomes active. It remains active for 1 minute or until it''s reduced to 0 Hit Points."}]}}'),
('upgBipodC',	'Bipod (Commercial)',	1,	2,	'1',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A bipod can be attached to powerful weapons—those with the kickback trait—to allow wielders with lower Strength to use them at the cost of mobility. You can set up the bipod with a single Interact action using one appendage, setting the bipod in your square. When using a bipod, you don''t take the –2 penalty for firing a kickback weapon, even if your Strength isn''t high enough to avoid the penalty.

However, you must spend a single Interact action to retrieve the bipod before you can move the weapon to a different position. Deploying or retrieving a bipod with an Interact action doesn''t automatically make you observed like an Interact action normally would, so long as you don''t set up or remove the bipod when it''s in a spot where creatures can see it.',	NULL),
('upgSnipersScopeC',	'Sniper''s Scope (Commercial)',	1,	150,	'L',	'Weapon',	'Tech',	'A telescopic sighting attachment helps view distant targets.',	'{"action": {"grant": [{"id": "actAdjustSight", "name": "Adjust Sight", "traits": "Manipulate", "action_cost": "[one-action]", "description": "Increase the range increment of the weapon the scope is attached to by 10 feet. If the weapon has a base range increment of 50 feet or more, increase the range of the weapon by 20 feet instead. This lasts until the beginning of your next turn or until you''re no longer wielding the weapon this scope is attached to, whichever comes first. This does not increase the size of area attacks."}]}}'),
('upgRadiationBufferA',	'Radiation Buffer (Advanced)',	10,	22100,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'A layer of treated lead lines your armor with integrated radiation sensors networked into your comm unit. While you''re wearing armor with this upgrade, you gain resistance 8 to poison damage from radiation effects and a +3 status bonus to Fortitude saves against radiation.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Poison (Radiation)", "amount": 8, "source": "Radiation Buffer (Advanced)"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Radiation Buffer (Advanced)", "value": "+3 status bonus against radiation", "target": "fortitude"}]}]}'),
('upgRadiationBufferS',	'Radiation Buffer (Superior)',	14,	35000,	'1',	'Armor',	'Tech',	'A layer of treated lead lines your armor with integrated radiation sensors networked into your comm unit. While you''re wearing armor with this upgrade, you gain resistance 12 to poison damage from radiation effects and a +4 status bonus to Fortitude saves against radiation.',	'{"defense": {"resistance": [{"type": "Poison (Radiation)", "amount": 12, "source": "Radiation Buffer (Superior)"}]}, "saving_throw": [{"conditional_bonus": [{"name": "Radiation Buffer (Superior)", "value": "+4 status bonus against radiation", "target": "fortitude"}]}]}');

DROP TABLE IF EXISTS "User";
DROP SEQUENCE IF EXISTS "public"."User_UserID_seq";
CREATE SEQUENCE "public"."User_UserID_seq" INCREMENT 1 MINVALUE 1 MAXVALUE 2147483647 CACHE 1;

CREATE TABLE "public"."User" (
    "UserID" integer DEFAULT nextval('"User_UserID_seq"') NOT NULL,
    "DiscordID" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Username" character varying NOT NULL,
    "Email" character varying,
    "AvatarURL" character varying,
    "CreatedAt" timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
    "IsAdmin" boolean,
    "Preferences" jsonb,
    CONSTRAINT "User_pkey" PRIMARY KEY ("UserID")
)
WITH (oids = false);

CREATE UNIQUE INDEX "User_DiscordID_key" ON public."User" USING btree ("DiscordID");

